insert into GREWordBook values ('0', 'abandon', '[əbændən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abandon', '{vt.}++放弃；弃绝；绝望；断念：**++(因形势紧迫、危险等)离弃(家园、飞机、船只等)；【航空学】(机上人员)弃机(跳伞)：**++丢弃(信仰等)；(不顾信义、义务、责任等而)遗弃，抛弃(妻儿等)：**++使屈服：**++[abandon oneself] 放纵;纵情;无拘无束;使沉溺于：**++【保险业】委付**++[废语]开除，逐出**{n.}++放纵；纵情；无拘无束，放任**++狂热，狂放，狂放不羁**', '++Only they will not abandon me, only they will not betray.**++只有它们不会遗弃我，只有它们不会背叛。**++Finding himself under fire from all quarters, he had no alternative but to abandon his scheme for the time being.**++在这四面楚歌的情况下， 他没有别的办法， 只好暂时放弃他的计划。**++But why should they? Why should China abandon a trade policy that is working marvelously well for them, and adopt a trade policy that is failing dismally for us?**++但是他们为什么要这么做呢，为什么中国应该放弃对他们特别适用的贸易政策而采取一种惨败的贸易政策，那说得过去吗？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1', 'abase', '[əbes]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abase', '{vt.}++[abase oneself] 降低…的威信(或地位、身份、职务等)；羞辱，使丢脸，使出丑；使谦卑，使卑微；贬抑：**++[古语]降下，降低，放下，放低，使下降，使向下，垂下：**++[废语]使(货币)贬值；降低…的价格(或价值)**', '++We should abase ourselves before God.**++我们应该在上帝面前表示谦卑。**++E. g. refused to abase herself by asking for an invitation.**++因请求得到他人的邀请被拒绝而使自己的威望降低。**++Now I Nebuchadnezzar praise and extol and honour the King of heaven, all whose works are truth, and his ways judgment: and those that walk in pride he is able to abase.**++现在我尼布甲尼撒赞美，尊崇，恭敬天上的王。 因为他所作的全都诚实，他所行的也都公平。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2', 'abash', '[əbæʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abash', '{vt.}', '++When the child see all the room fille with stranger he is much abash.**++那小孩一看到满屋子都是陌生人，感到非常局促不安。**++When the child see all the room fille with stranger, he is much abash .**++中文翻译：那小孩一看到满屋子都是陌生人， 感到非常局促不安。**++The entire metropolitan centre possessed a high and mighty air calculated to overawe and abash the common applicant, and to make the gulf between poverty and success seem both wide and deep.**++整个都市中心显出一种财大气粗，高不可攀的气势，为的是让那些普通的求职者望而生畏，不敢问津，也为的是让贫富之间的鸿沟显得又宽又深。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3', 'abate', '[əbet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abate', '{vt.}++使(数量、程度等)减少，减轻，减退，缩减；缓和:**++降(价)，对(价格)打折扣：**++削减(成本或费用等)： **++减(税)：**{vi.}++(数量、程度、价值等)减少；减轻，减退：**++(洪水、风暴等)平息；(病痛等)减少：**++【法律】(法令等)被废除(或取消)，失效，作废；(诉讼等)中止：**', '++In this phase, the shouts and histrionics will abate somewhat.**++在这个阶段，大呼小叫和装腔作势都将减少。**++Some see commodities in general, and gold in particular, as a hedge against inflation, and so may sell if their fears about rising prices abate.**++有些人把一般商品看作常规的，而把黄金看作特殊的，作为对冲通胀（的商品），当他们对于物价上升的顾虑减轻后，就会出售。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('4', 'abbreviate', '[əbrivɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abbreviate', '{vt.}++使简短；缩短；缩简；节略(演讲等)：**++缩写(词或短语)：**{vi.}++使用缩写词：**++使用缩写词：**', '++And, furthermore, he started to abbreviate.**++此外，他开始使用缩写词。**++Do not abbreviate, and do spell all words correctly.**++不要使用缩写形式，并要保证拼写正确。**++N You can even abbreviate and put Y or N.**++甚至可以缩写Y或。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('5', 'abdicate', '[æbdɪket]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abdicate', '{vt.}++(国王)退(位)；辞(职)：**++正式(或公开、自愿)放弃(权力、权利、要求、职责、责任等)：**{vi.}++退位，逊位；辞职；正式(或公开、自愿)放弃权力(或权利、要求、职责、责任等)：**++退出(from):**', '++To accomplish  first-class businesses, he can not but abdicate happiness, travels, entertainments,love and hatred, quarrels, arguments and clarifications.**++为了完成第一流的事，他必须放弃或减少凡夫俗子的快乐、交游、娱乐、爱恨、争执、答辩与澄清。**++When Paula Dobriansky told the gathering that the Bush Administration "will not abdicate our responsibility" to address global warming, the hall filled with boos.**++当 保拉·多布里扬斯基向大会宣布布什政府“不会放弃自己的责任”去处理全球变暖这一问题时，全场报以唏嘘声。**++Amid the excitement surrounding the birthday celebrations, the queen@s cousin, Margaret Rhodes, said that she is "perfectly sure" the monarch will never abdicate the throne.**++生日庆祝宴会的气氛十分欢愉，女王的堂妹玛格丽特·罗德斯说，她“非常肯定”女王不会退位。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('6', 'aberrant', '[æbɛrənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aberrant', '{adj.}++与正确(或真实情况)相背的**++离开正路的，偏离常规的；反常的**++【生物学】异常的；畸变的，变态的**{n.}++离开正路的人，偏离常规的物，反常的人(或事)**++【生物学】畸变生物(群)；畸变器官**', '++Sure, we may get a few aberrant album names if the MP3 files are not named right, but is it worth the effort to perfect that regular expression?**++当然，如果 MP3 文件未正确命名，那么我们可能会获得一些异常的专辑名，但是这值得去尽力完善正则表达式吗？**++I should start off by saying that a technology conference like part of SXSW is probably not the most ideal situation to be noticing aberrant human behavior.**++我想说，其实以一次技术性会议（比如在SXSW盛典上部分呈现的）来关察异常的人类行为也许并非最佳选择。**++Traditional custom, taken the world over, is a mass of detailed behaviour more astonishing than what any one person can ever evolve in individual actions, no matter how aberrant.**++从世界范围来看，传统风俗是由许多细节性的习惯行为组成，它比任何一个养成的行为都更加引人注目，不管个人行为多么异常。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('7', 'abet', '[əbɛt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abet', '{vt.}++对…进行教唆，唆使，煽动；怂恿(尤指干坏事、犯罪)；助长：**++支持；帮助；鼓励：**', '++That@s meant lower costs and faster trading, but it has also helped aid and abet the current crisis.**++这意味着低花费和更快的交易，但它同时也怂恿并教唆了当前的危机。**++And what of Iran, which apparently continues to aid and abet both Shi@ite and Sunni insurgent groups with IEDS and other weapons?**++显然继续以简易爆炸装置和其他武器援助和教唆什叶派和逊尼派叛军组织的伊朗是什么？**++Under current legislation, those who "aid, abet, counsel or procure" someone to end their own life can be prosecuted and jailed for up to 14 years.**++根据现行的英国法律，“帮助，教唆，建议或者鼓励”他人自杀的，将被起诉，并判14年监禁。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('8', 'abeyance', '[əbeəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abeyance', '{n.}++暂停，暂缓，暂搁，中止**++【法律】(土地)所有权等的未决，未定，待定，归属待定**', '++The sanctions againt the country fell into abeyance yesterday.**++对那个国家的制裁昨天中止。**++This is a good plan but not at this time. Let@s just hold it in abeyance until things get better.**++这个计划很好，但是眼下不适合执行这个计划，我们先把它搁置一下，等待形势好转吧！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('9', 'abhor', '[əbhɔr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abhor', '{vt.}++憎恶，厌恶；痛恨，痛绝；深恶：**++(厌恶地)回避；拒绝；淘汰：**++[废语]使产生反感；使恐惧；使震惊**', '++I have learned to see the relativity of things, to abhor war, and dogmatism in any form.**++我学会了以辩证的角度看待事物，学会了憎恶战争和任何形式的独断专行。**++Do not abhor an Edomite, for he is your brother.**++不可憎恶以东人，因为他是你的弟兄。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('10', 'abiding', '[əbaɪdɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abiding', '{adj.}', '++It is a deeper, more abiding emotion.**++幸福是更深刻、更持久的情感。**++Once we have, through analytic meditation, come to an insight or deeper understanding, then we should cease our analysis and begin the practice of "calm abiding.**++一旦我们通过分析冥想获得了洞察力和更深的理解，那么我们应该停止分析，转而开始练习“平静持久”。**++People should be on no doubt that we are on the side of the law abiding.**++人民应该相信，我们是站在维护法律和遵纪守法的人民这一边的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('11', 'abject', '[æbdʒɛkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abject', '{adj.}++绝望的；凄惨的，悲惨的；无助的，可怜的；糟透的，蹩脚的**++卑劣的，可鄙的，卑鄙的，卑怯的**++卑躬屈节的；奴性的，奴隶般的；怯懦的；自卑的**++[废语]遭拒绝的；被抛弃的**{n.}++[古语]弃儿**{vt.}++[废语]拒绝；抛弃**', '++"In contrast to the dominant idea of Moore, we propose that he presented the body as abject, erotic, vulnerable, violated and visceral, " Stephens writes.**++“与人们长期对摩尔的印象不同，我们认为他呈现出一种不幸的、情欲的、脆弱的、侵犯的和发自肺腑的本体，”斯蒂文写道。**++But I have since come to realize that my abject ignorance was really a gift: to be a literarily inclined illiterate at age 26 is one of the most glorious fates that can befall mortal girl.**++但是现在，我意识到我可怜的无知却是一件礼物：对于一个凡间女子来说，26岁时能在文学上倾向于无知，是最荣耀的事情之一。**++She whimpers; she is permanently in discomfort if not abject pain, not only from her arthritis but from leg ulcers and bedsores.**++她低声呻吟；她永远感到不舒服，要么就是无助的疼痛，不仅因为关节炎，还因为小腿溃疡和褥疮。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('12', 'abjure', '[əbdʒʊr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abjure', '{vt.}++发誓弃绝(国籍等)，发誓放弃(权利等)；郑重拒绝：**++郑重放弃(意见)，正式放弃(信仰、主张等)；宣布撤回(声明等)：**++避免；节制；戒除，戒去：**', '++They were compelled to abjure their faith.**++他们被迫发誓放弃自己的信仰。**++Adrienne Lecouvreur on her deathbed was willing to confess and receive communion, but refused to abjure her profession.**++阿德莉娜勒库弗勒临终之时希望忏悔、聆听圣言，但她拒绝发誓放弃她的职业。**++But consumer-oriented companies that abjure the blogosphere are missing out on opportunities to generate buzz, monitor customer concerns, and -- perhaps most importantly -- show their human side.**++但是，对于消费者导向的公司而言，放弃博客等于错过了口碑营销、监听客户关怀和最重要的——表现他们人性化的机会。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('13', 'abnegate', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abnegate', '{vt.}++克制(私心、欲望等)；不容自己享受(特权、优待、玩乐等)：**++交出(权力等)；抛弃，放弃(信仰、思想、权利、要求等)；拒绝(承认)：**', '++Although the general design method of the position loop composed of the position sensor is abnegate, but the information radar servo system has high orientation precision in this way.**++采用该方法，虽然舍弃了由位置传感器构成位置回路的常规设计方法，但情报雷达伺服系统仍然有较高的定位精度。**++I know that my ideal is now very far away from me, and there will be a lot of difficulties to face, but I will never give up, I must complete own ideal, never abnegate.**++我知道现在离自己的理想还是很远很远的，而且还会遇到很多困难阻碍，但我是不会放弃的，我一定要完成自己的理想，永不气馁。**++What emergency things that let persons abnegate their lifes.**++是什么事情如此紧急让人们可以舍弃生命呢？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('14', 'abominate', '[əbɑmɪnet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abominate', '{vt.}++憎恨，憎恶，厌恶：**++[口语]极不喜欢，不喜爱：**', '++I abominate dancing.**++我痛恨跳舞。**++To regard with horror or loathing; abominate .**++憎恶，厌恶恐惧或憎恨；痛恨。**++Much as I abominate writing, I would not give up Mr. Collins@s correspondence for any consideration.**++我平常虽然最讨厌写信，可是我无论如何也不愿和柯林斯断绝书信往来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('15', 'aboveboard', '[əbʌvbord]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aboveboard', '{adv.,adj.}', '++His part in the affair was quite aboveboard.**++在这事情上，他的行为是非常光明磊落的。**++It guarantees a fair and aboveboard election by letting every voter express his or her will freely without subject to coercion, surveillance or threat by anyone.**++它通过让每位选民自由表达自己的选举意志，并且没有任何人可以对选民进行胁迫、监视以及威胁，来保证选举是公平、光明正大的。**++Knowing a few etiquette guidelines can help you keep your conduct aboveboard, and perhaps ease a few fears about putting yourself in front of the well-connected.**++了解一些礼仪规范能够让你的举止上得了台面，也许还能帮助你缓解面对人脉很广的人时的恐惧。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('16', 'abrade', '[əbred]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abrade', '{vt.}++擦掉；摩擦，磨蚀，磨损；擦伤(皮肤等)；擦毛…的表面：**++[比喻](在精神方面)折磨(人)；消磨(意志、精神等)；使精疲力尽；使厌烦；激怒：**{vi.}++经受磨损；受擦伤**{vt.,vi.}', '++If produce exterior accident abrade, want to use polishing agent only, can rapid conveniently nap purify .**++假如发生表面意外擦伤，只要使用抛光剂，即可迅速方便地修整去除。**++Inside of pockets is to have a surface which will not abrade other printed materials inserted within by end users.**++口袋的内部将有将不擦伤在里面被使用者所插入的其他的印刷材料的一个表面。**++We can experience what it feels like to be another person – perhaps with a personality that would normally abrade us.**++我们可以经历另外一个人的经历——也许这个人的个性和我们大相径庭。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('17', 'abreast', '[əbrɛst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abreast', '{adv.,adj.}++[一般作表语]**++朝同方向并列(的)，并排(的)，并肩(的)，肩并肩地(的)**++(使)与…齐头并列(常与 of 或with连用)**++了解最新发展的(of)；通晓新近发展的(with)，与…新近发展并进的；赶得上，使不落后于(with)**', '++This passage admits two abreast.**++这过道可容纳两人并排进出。**++Don@t all cycle abreast.**++不要并排骑车。**++The bridge can take four lorries abreast.**++这座大桥可容4辆卡车并列通行。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('18', 'abridge', '[əbrɪdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abridge', '{vt.}++缩短：**++减少，消减；限制：**++(在保留主要内容之时)精减(或减少)…的篇幅，节略，删去，简写，精简(文章等)：**++[古语]剥夺(某人)的权利(或特权等)，褫夺(of):**', '++He decides to abridge his stay here after he received a letter from home.**++他接到家信后决定缩短在这里的逗留时间。**++Article 33 A book publisher may alter or abridge a work with the permission of the copyright owner.**++第三十三条 图书出版者经作者许可，可以对作品修改、删节。**++The generation which is passing in its turn over the earth, is not forced to abridge it for the sake of the generations, its equal, after all, who will have their turn later on.--"I**++目前的一代人有权在地球上过路，不能强迫他们为了后代而缩短自己的路程，后代和他们是平等的，将来才轮到后代过路。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('19', 'abrogate', '[æbrəɡet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=abrogate', '{vt.}++(通过行政命令)废除(法令、条约、习俗等)：**++取消，撤销；去掉；抛开；终止：**', '++In Nebraska they swing by the hospital and abrogate all responsibility.**++在内布拉斯加是和医院一起摇摆，取消了所有的责任。**++However, abandoning the Cold War mindset is not to abrogate arms control treaties concluded in that era.**++但是，摆脱冷战思维不应被简单地理解为废除冷战时达成的军控条约。**++While nominally handing massive new budget powers to the DNI the law also makes clear that he will not“abrogate the statutory responsibilities” of any existing intelligence related agency.**++虽然这项法律名义上授予国家情报局长在预算问题上新的巨大权力，但同时也明确规定，他将不得“废除”现有任何与情报相关机构的“法律规定的职责”。**');
