insert into GREWordBook values ('85', 'aggregate', '[æɡrɪɡət; (for v.) æɡrɪˌɡet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aggregate', '{adj.}++聚合的，集合的，聚集的；总和的，合计的**++【地质学】聚合的；聚成岩的**++【植物学】**++(花等)聚生的**++(木莓等)攒集的**{n.}++总计，合计**++聚集，集合；聚集体，集合体，集成体，组合体**++【数学】集，集合**++【建筑业】(混凝土或灰泥的)骨料，集料，粒料**++【地质学】集合体，聚合体**++【土壤学】团聚体**{vt., vi.}++(使)聚集，(使)积聚，(使)集合，(使)凝结；结合，团聚：**++[口语]共计，合计(为)，总共达…，总数达…，总计达…：**', '++...**++...**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('86', 'aggressive', '[əɡrɛsɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aggressive', '{adj.}++侵略的；侵犯的；挑衅的**++过分自信的，(行为等)过分的，放肆的；好寻衅的，咄咄逼人的**++积极进取的，有进取心的，竞争心强的，活跃有为的，敢作敢为的，勇往的**++【精神病学】攻击(性)的，侵犯性的**++[美国俚语]顶呱呱的**++[学生俚语]妙极的，非常好的**++采用强制手段的**', '++The female of the  species is very  aggressive.**++这个物种中雌性是非常好斗的。**++Take, for example, the case of rutting stags or fighting chimps and you get the generally aggressive idea.**++例如，以发情的雄鹿或好战的黑猩猩为例，你就会得到通常所说的好斗概念。**++Should I be aggressive or conservative with my money before 30?**++在30岁之前我应该风险投资还是保守存钱？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('87', 'aggrieve', '[əgriv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aggrieve', '{vt.}++[常用被动语态或用非人称动词或代词]使悲痛，使悲伤；使苦恼，使烦恼；使委屈；使受伤害，伤害…的感情；冒犯：**++(尤指在某人的合法权利方面)侵害，伤害；侵犯…的合法权利；冤枉**', '++With the development of the tobacco study, a series of research reports point out that tobacco harms human health, at the same time, also aggrieve human life;**++随着烟草研究的不断深入，一系列的研究报告指出，烟草在损害人类健康的同时，也在侵蚀人类的生命；**++As the development of market economy, we realize that, non-standard competitive behaviors of the Natural Monopoly make serious damage to competition order and aggrieve the interests of whole society.**++但是随着市场经济的逐渐发展，我们发现，自然垄断行业的一些不规范竞争行为严重破坏了竞争秩序，侵害了社会整体利益。**++I hope I didn@t aggrieve her feeling.**++我希望我并没有伤害到她的感情。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('88', 'agility', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=agility', '{n.}++灵活，敏捷；轻快**++(反应、思维等的)机敏**', '++I am not against Agility.**++我并不反对敏捷。**++This is the third reason for the confusion when we talk about Agility.**++这就是我们在谈论敏捷时容易产生混乱的第三个原因。**++If for some reason you don@t have or cannot adopt these values, then you should not worry about agility.**++如果因为某些原因您没有或者不能采用这些价值，那么您就不需要为敏捷而操心了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('89', 'agitate', '[ædʒɪˌteɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=agitate', '{vt.}++(尤指剧烈地)摇动，拨动；搅动，搅拌(液体等)：**++使激动；使焦虑；使狂躁不安：**++鼓动，煽动，扰乱(人心)：**++为(引起对某事的注意或争取对某事的支持而)公开激烈争论(计划、问题等)：**++[古语]沉思，反复斟酌，仔细掂量**{vi.}++煽动,鼓动(for 或 against):**++煽动,鼓动(for 或 against):**', '++In the meantime, people like Allen Frances will agitate for the number of diagnoses and their scope to be reduced.**++届时，像艾伦·福朗瑟斯一样的人们将会因书中诊断词条的数量和缩减余地而忧虑。**++The cat will self agitate and make ample suds. (Never mind the noises that come from the toilet, the cat is actually enjoying this.)**++用同样连贯迅速的动作把猫咪放进去，盖上马桶盖．（之后，你需要站在马桶盖上面）猫儿会变激动，并搅动出充足泡沫．（这些惨叫不要紧的，其实猫儿正享受着呢）**++I wish I could be acquainted with the feelings and thoughts which must agitate the heart and present themselves to the mind of an enlightened Englishman, when he first lands on this continent.**++赫克托．圣约翰．克雷夫科尔 但愿我能熟悉那种必将鼓动人心的感情和思想，并且在一个开明的英国人首次踏上这片大陆时，将这种思想和感情原原本本地展现在他眼前。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('90', 'agog', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=agog', '{adj. [一般作表语],adv.}', '++The children were all agog to hear the story.**++孩子们都渴望着要听这个故事。**++While the trials in general have grabbed attention, residents have been agog at details of 46-year-old Xie@s case, with several expressing amazement that a woman could head a "black society".**++而审判本身也引起了广泛关注。 当地居民惊讶于女人可以领导“黑社会”的事实，急切想得知更多关于这位46岁“女老大”的信息。**++Europe was then agog at the apparent success of John Law’s schemes in France, where the sale of shares in a project to develop the Mississippi delta had relieved the monarchy of much of its debt.**++当时的欧陆正为约翰•劳法国方案的表层成功而兴奋不已。 该方案出售项目股权用以开发密西西比三角洲，缓解了君主国法兰西的许多债务。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('91', 'agonize', '[æɡənaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=agonize', '{vi.}++力争，苦斗，痛苦(或拼命)挣扎：**++感到极度痛苦；苦闷，苦恼，烦恼：**{vt.}++使(极度)痛苦，折磨：**++使(极度)痛苦，折磨：**', '++I agonize for a while before buying a new toothbrush.**++而我，在买一支牙刷之前还要挣扎一番。**++As a mother, I agonize over what my children will inherit.**++作为一个母亲，我对我的孩子们将要继承的东西感到极度痛苦。**++I’m sorry but those decisions you agonize over just don’t make any difference. The color you paint your house, whether you should let your child do x, where you go on vacation, etc.**++原谅我这么说，但是那些令你苦恼的决定真的改变不了什么，比如你把房间刷成什么颜色，你是否应该让孩子做某事，你在哪里度假等等。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('92', 'agreeable', '[əɡriəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=agreeable', '{adj.}++[口语]欣然同意的；愿意的**++令人愉快的；惬意的；合某人胃口的；舒适的；讨人喜欢的**++一致的，符合的，适合的**', '++@I\@ll come along with you, then, \@ Ellen, always agreeable.**++“那我和你一起去吧，”埃伦总是那么讨人喜欢。**++It is not agreeable to bring this home to one’s self, but the fact is not without its significance in another direction.**++但是让某人明白这个道理是不太合适的，但事实上，这个在另外的一个方向是具有重大意义的。**++He described it as @a very agreeable situation located within two small hills in the midst of which flowed a great river@.**++他把这个地方描绘成“一个非常令人愉快的地方，地处两个小山之间，中间流过一条大河”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('93', 'airtight', '[ɛrtaɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=airtight', '{adj.}++不漏气的，不透气的，气密的，密封的**++[主美国口语](防守等)严密的；(论点等)无懈可击的，(论点、契约等)无漏洞的，天衣无缝的**', '++All powders should be kept in airtight jars or tins as they quickly deteriorate if allowed to become damp.**++各种发粉如果让其吸潮就会迅速变坏，所以都应保存在密封的瓶子或铁罐中。**++Make sure you buy fresh eggs as you need them, keep them in an airtight container on a shelf in the fridge and eat within a week.**++如果你需要的话，买一些新鲜的鸡蛋，然后把它放到一个密封的容器里面，再放到冰箱的架子上面，但务必在一周内吃完。**++If you go through your white flour in less than a year, however, you can safely keep it on the counter in an airtight jar or canister.**++不过，如果您可以在不到一年的时间里用完您的白面粉，那您就可以放心的把它放在柜台上的一密闭瓶或罐中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('94', 'alacrity', '[əlækrəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=alacrity', '{n.}++乐意，欣然；欣然同意的表示**++敏捷，活泼，轻快**', '++First, move with alacrity.**++首先，动作敏捷。**++He turns you adrift on the world with surprising alacrity.**++他以令人惊奇的喜爱任你在世上漂泊。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('95', 'alibi', '[æləbaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=alibi', '{n.}++【法律】(被告)不在犯罪现场(的申辩、事实或证据)**++[美国口语]借口，口实，托辞**{vi.}++[美国口语]辩解，找借口，找托辞开脱，托辞闪避：**++[美国口语]辩解，找借口，找托辞开脱，托辞闪避：**{vt.}++为…辩解，为…找托辞开脱，为…找借口；为…作不在犯罪现场的证词：**++为…辩解，为…找托辞开脱，为…找借口；为…作不在犯罪现场的证词：**{adv.}++不在犯罪现场**', '++The police broke her alibi by proving she knew how to shoot a pistol.**++警方通过她知道如何使用手枪射击来证明案发时她不在现场的辩解不实。**++Lawyers for the accused may call witnesses to testify to an alibi for the defendant.**++被告律师传唤证人的目的可能是要证明被告不在犯罪现场。**++Citing the war on terrorism as an all-purpose alibi, he denies breaking the letter or spirit of any law.**++反恐成为所有决策的托辞，无视任何法律条文和法律精神。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('96', 'alienate', '[elɪənˌet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=alienate', '{vt.}++使疏远；离间；使不友好，使憎恨：**++使深居简出，使隐居；使转移，使转向：**++使移情；使(感情)变冷漠；转移(感情)：**++【法律】(使)转让，让渡(财产等)，把(财产)所有权让渡(给别人)：**', '++His attempts to alienate the two friends failed because they had complete faith.**++他离间那两个朋友的企图失败了,因为他们彼此完全信任。**++Some men keep their emotions so pent up that they eventually burst in an unhealthy fit of anger or alienate their partners or friends.**++一些男性把情绪闷在心里，以致于最后会一股脑儿爆发出来（这很不健康），或是疏远自己的伴侣或朋友。**++If you can, turn that kind of sponsor away - it@s not worth the money to alienate your audience.**++要是你有能力，尽量拒绝这样的赞助商，不值得为了钱而疏远你的宾客们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('97', 'align', '[əlaɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=align', '{vt.}++使成一直线，使成一行，把…排列成行，使排齐，对准，校直：**++调整；校正，校直，调准(将机构的各部调整至正确的相互关系)：**++[常作 align oneself] 使密切合作;使结盟;使一致(with):**{vi.}++排队，列队，排成一行；成一直线：**++被调准，被校正；被调整**++结盟(with):**', '++How should we highlight the labels and how should we align them?**++我们应该怎么样高亮标签，应该怎么样排列他们？**++You should be excited about your goals and the best way to do that is to align your goals with your life and passions.**++你应该对自己的目标感到兴奋，做到这一点的最好的办法是把你的目标和你的生活以及热情相匹配。**++Though initiated from the system tests, in both cases the plan has the potential to include test levels other than system testing in order to align these test levels.**++尽管是从系统测试开始的，但为了排列这些测试级别，在这两种情况中，计划都有可能包括系统测试之外的其它测试级别。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('98', 'allay', '[əle]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=allay', '{vt.}++平息；使平静，使镇静；消除(恐惧、怀疑等)：**++减轻，缓解，解除(忧虑、苦痛、疼痛等)；制止：**{vi.}++[废语]减弱**', '++The "DNA Dozen" want to allay fears amongst the public that information about their genes should not be widely shared on the grounds that it is private and sensitive.**++“DNA十二人组”想减轻公众关于他们基因信息不应该被广泛共享的恐惧，因为这个信息是私人的也是敏感的。**++If they really do that, will this allay China@s concerns?**++如果他们确实这样做了，这是否能减轻中国的关切呢？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('99', 'allegiance', '[əlidʒəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=allegiance', '{n.}++(诸侯对其封建君主的)忠顺；(臣民对君主的)臣服义务，臣从**++(对统治者、政府、国家等的)效忠，忠诚**++(对事业、团体、个人等的)忠诚，忠贞；献身；热爱；拥戴，爱戴**++(侨民对所在国政府的)效忠义务**++效忠对象**', '++His attendance at the rally declared his political allegiance.**++他们出席大会显示了他政治上的忠诚。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('100', 'alleviate', '[əlivɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=alleviate', '{vt.}++减轻(苦痛、疾苦等)，使(痛苦等)易于忍受；使缓和：**++减小，减少；减轻：**', '++In this article, you have learned how to alleviate some of the restrictions and problems that developers unknowingly create for their consumers during development time.**++在本文中，您了解了如何减轻开发人员在进行开发时不知不觉为用户制造的一些限制和问题。**++He not only feels a sorrow of the same kind with that which they feel, but as if he had derived a part of it to himself, what he feels seems to alleviate the weight of what they feel.**++说倾听者和他们一起分担忧愁似乎不大合适，他不仅和他们一样感觉到了悲伤，而且似乎在他们的心理负担减轻了之后，自己又得到了一些悲伤。**++An organic weariness drives the nerves and the flesh to a despair that only an exploration of all forms of pleasure can alleviate.**++有机的疲倦驾驭着神经与肉体驶向绝望——一种只有通过对各种形式愉快的探索才能减轻的绝望。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('101', 'alloy', '[ælɔɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=alloy', '{n.}++(金属的)成色，纯度，品位**++【冶金学、化学】合金；合金状态**++(和金或银等贵金属熔合的)贱金属，低级金属**++(有害的或降低质量的)增加物，增添物，掺杂物，混合物，杂质**++混合，融合**{vt.}++使(贵金属)不纯，用贱金属熔合(贵金属)，(通过掺加贱金属)使(贵金属)降低成色；使变硬(或变轻)：**++合铸(金属)使成合金，将…铸(或熔)成合金：**++(混有杂质)使低劣，使低贱，(通过掺杂作用)减少，减损(或减低影响)(幸福、乐趣、兴趣等)；使缓和：**{vi.}++合铸；易于和其他金属铸成合金：**++合铸；易于和其他金属铸成合金：**', '++Last October the first batch of low-alloy channel steel was successfully rolled.**++去年10月， 成功地轧出了第一批低合金槽钢。**++Until 2001, alloy plants in northern areas of the province spewed a number of metals into the air.**++2001年以前，布雷西亚北部地区的合金厂向空气中排放出大量的金属粒子。**++A paper on the alloy was published in the journal Advanced Energy Materials.**++先进能源材料杂志上发表过一篇关于此合金的论文。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('102', 'allude', '[əlʊd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=allude', '{vi.}++随时(或间接)提到；略为一提；暗指，暗讽，影射(to):**++(泛泛)提到，提及，说起，谈到(to)：**', '++But sometimes it allude to what they seems to be regard as the British Government distinguished censorship of the press during the Second World War.**++但有时他们会顺便提到二战中，他们所谓的英国政府著名新闻审查制度。**++Alexander, 14, weighs 555 pounds, and though authorities have cited his weight as a main concern, they also allude to more pressing medical problems that prompted social services to take action.**++亚历山大14岁，体重555磅。 虽然当局称主要担心其体重，但暗示促使社会服务部门采取行动的还有更急迫的医学问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('103', 'allure', '[əlʊr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=allure', '{vt.}++(强烈地)吸引；诱惑；引诱；诱使：**++(强烈地)吸引；诱惑；引诱；诱使：**{vi.}++吸引人；迷人**{n.}++诱惑力，迷惑力，吸引力，魅力**{n.}{n.}', '++The allure and charm of Paris captivate all who visit there.**++巴黎的诱惑与魅力吸引了所有到此游玩的人。**++Perhaps Paris’ allure lies in the zest and style of the Parisians.**++或许巴黎的诱惑力在于巴黎人的特殊品味和风格。**++Milton surveys the wealth of literary tradition before him, and he resists its allure without the help of any human guide.**++弥尔顿在他之前就调查过文学传统的宝藏，他在没有人帮助的情况下抗拒了这一诱惑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('104', 'ally', '[ælaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ally', '{vt.}++[ally oneself]使联姻；使(国家)结盟；使联合；使结合(to，with) [一般用于被动语态]：**++与…(在起源或性质上)关联，(在血统、组织等方面)使发生关联；使同源(to，with) [通常用于被动语态]：**++使发生联系(to， with) [常用被动语态]：**{vi.}++结盟；联合；成为同盟(或联姻)：**++结盟；联合；成为同盟(或联姻)：**{n.}++同盟国；同盟者，盟友，同盟组织 [亦见Allies]**++助手，帮手；伙伴；合伙人；支持者，拥护者，辅助者，协助者；辅助物**++【生物学】亲缘动物(或植物)，同源(或同类)动物(或植物)；同类物**', '++And America is proud to have him as an ally in the cause of peace and freedom.**++美国为有他作为和平与自由事业中的同盟者而感到骄傲。**++Treat the larger body of humanity as your friend and ally, and it will respond in kind.**++把人类的那个上层“躯体”视为你的朋友和同盟者，它将以同样的方法来回报你。**++However, sometimes an ally that has influence can really give your idea legs. They can also be a source of encouragement.**++不过有时候，有影响力的同盟者的确会使你的想法更有力，他们还可以起到激励的作用。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('105', 'aloft', '[əlɔft]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aloft', '{adv.}++[一般作表语]**{adj.}++高高地(的)；在上面(的)，在高处(的)；在天上(的)，在空中(的)**++向上(的)，向高处(的)；向空中(的)**++【航海学】在船上高处(的)；在(或向)帆索高处(或桅顶)(的)，在帆索上(甲板以上的高处)(的)**{prep.}++在…之上；在…顶上：**++在…之上；在…顶上：**', '++But in the stratosphere they can stay aloft for years, spread by fast winds known as jets, meaning the threat is global.**++但在平流层，它们可以在高处停留数年，高速的风对其进行传播，这意味着全球都受到了威胁。**++Maples make those little whirlybird seeds you see spiraling down in droves each spring. Their papery little wings keep them aloft so they can find a good place to germinate and make a new maple.**++正如你所看到的，每个春天枫树的翅果都会大批地盘旋而下，它们纸一样的薄翅能够使自己停留在高处，这样它们就能找到一个适合生根发芽的好地方了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('106', 'aloof', '[əluf]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aloof', '{adv.}++在(视力能及的)距离上；远离，离开；避开；游离在外**++冷漠超然地，冷漠地，超然离群地**{adj.}++远隔的，远离的，孤零的**++疏远的，冷漠的，冷淡的，无情的；超然离群的**', '++Her hospitality thawed out his aloof manner.**++她的盛情缓和了他的冷淡态度。**++An awkward, aloof figure, he has been out kissing babies and even allowing himself to be interviewed on television.**++一直是尴尬的冷漠的形象的他已经开始外出亲吻婴儿，甚至允许电视采访。**++It is this sense of dignity that seems crucial. We expect courts to have an aloof and slightly intimidating atmosphere. Moreover, we expect them to take time.**++这种庄重感是非常重要的。我们希望法庭的气氛是冷淡和稍显威严的。更重要的是，我们希望审判能从容进行。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('107', 'altruism', '[æltruɪzəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=altruism', '{n.}++无私，忘我，利他**++【伦理学】利他主义(egoism之对)**++(动物的)自我牺牲行为，利他行为，利他主义[参较sociobiology]**', '++One biologist developed a formula for how much genetic material would have to be to saved in the act of altruism for it to be worthwhile.**++一位生物学家发展了一套公式，用来计算到底有多少遗传物质可以被保留下来的时候，利他的行为才是值得的。**++There are several other theories about altruism, but one of the more intriguing ones is that it@s all relative.**++关于利他主义还有别的一些理论，但最有意思的一种认为这一切都是有亲缘关系的。**++They raise basic philosophical issues dealing with the nature of ownership, the validation of knowledge, and concepts such as altruism and collective goods.**++他们提出基本的哲学问题涉及所有权性质、知识验证、以及如利他主义和集体财产这样的概念。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('108', 'amalgamate', '[əmælɡəmet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amalgamate', '{vt.}++使(思想、阶级等)混合；使(公司、社团等)合并，使联合；使合成一体：**++【冶金学】使(金属)汞齐化；调制…成为汞合金**{vi.}++合并；混合：**++(金属)汞齐化，混汞**{adj.}++混合的**', '++The company has decided to amalgamate with the parent firm.**++这家子公司已决定和母公司合并。**++If we amalgamate our two businesses, we can creat a more powerful one.**++如果将我们两家小企业合并起来，就能创造出一个实力更为雄厚的大企业。**++We inform you that we have agreed to amalgamate the two houses doing business in this town under the style respectively of F. and C.**++本地先前以F.及C.商号营业的两店, 经协商同意合并, 特此告知。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('109', 'ambiguous', '[æmbɪɡjuəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ambiguous', '{adj.}++可能有两种(或多种)解释的；引起歧义的；双关的，双重意义的；模棱两可的**++不明确的；模糊的，含糊不清的，含糊其辞的；难以理解(或区分)的**', '++Perhaps, but the contrast is ambiguous and unclear.**++也许可以，但对比却是模糊不清的。**++All of that said, ambiguous data structures can be valuable.**++大家都说，含糊不清的数据也可能有价值。**++If they investigated more from reliable sources, they would find that claims of danger are more ambiguous than they’ve heard.**++如果他们从可靠的来源详细调查，他们可能会发现，危险的断言比他们听到的更加模糊不清。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('110', 'ambivalent', '[æmbɪvələnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ambivalent', '{adj.}++(心理、态度)矛盾的；有矛盾情绪的**++[非规范用语]含糊不清的，模棱两可的，不明确的**{n.}++【病理学】两性人**', '++Just state your wish and resolve, even if you feel ambivalent about it.**++即使你感到很矛盾，你也只需表明你的愿望和决心。**++On his way out the rabbi told me my mother was ambivalent about dying, after all those years of nagging us all to help her on her way.**++在出来时，牧师告诉我说，虽然这些年来母亲一直唠叨让我们帮助她归西，但是对于死亡，她的内心还是矛盾。**++As a group, they are ambivalent about whether the quality of online content would suffer if companies could not charge for it—34% think so while 30% do not; and the remaining 36% have no firm opinion.**++对于如果网站对内容不收费这些内容的质量是否会变差的调查有矛盾：34%的人认为会变差，同时30%的认为不会，而36%的人没有固定的意见。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('111', 'amble', '[æmbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amble', '{vi.}++(马)缓行，侧对步，溜(花)蹄**++骑马缓行；骑缓行的马**++从容不迫(或悠然自在、轻松)地行走，从容漫步；缓行，缓步，慢步：**{n.}++(马的)缓行步态，溜花蹄，侧对步；小步跑，轻跑**++(从容)轻松的步伐，缓行，漫步**', '++3 p.m. - While in downtown Cairo, amble through its 19th and early 20th century boulevards and buildings.**++下午3点--在开罗市中心19世纪及20初期的林荫大道和建筑群中漫步。**++These traditions continue at the company where workers amble about the offices in jeans and casual shirts.**++这些传统在公司得以延续，工作人员穿着牛仔裤和非正式的衬衣在公司漫步。**++At Nanjing University, for example, students amble past, their noses buried in books as they walk.**++比如，南京大学的学生基础雄厚，在他们走路时也在埋头苦读。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('112', 'ambrosial', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ambrosial', '{adj.}++神的，适用于神的，敬神的；神圣的**++似神仙食物的；特别美味的，可口的，芳香的，芬芳的**', '++The ambrosial aroma of the roast whetted our appetites.**++烤肉的香味刺激了我们的食欲。**++The ambrosial and essential part of the fruit is lost with the bloom which is rubbed off in the market cart , and they become mere provender .**++水果的美味和它那本质的部分，在装上了车子运往市场去的时候，跟它的鲜丽一起给磨损了，它变成了仅仅是食品。**++Next, you can delicately dip your content into a warm bath of ambrosial CSS—but before you jump to the hard candy shell, there are some additional considerations.**++接下来，你可以将内容小心地浸入芳香美味的CSS暖浴中了。不过在你跳进糖果硬壳之前，还有些额外的考虑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('113', 'ameliorate', '[əmilɪəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ameliorate', '{vt.}++使变好，改善，改进；改良；减轻：**++使变好，改善，改进；改良；减轻：**{vi.}++变好，改善：**++变好，改善：**', '++Should his condition ameliorate the sentence?**++他的病情应该减轻刑罚吗？**++In every human being there is a wish to ameliorate his own condition.**++改善自己境况的愿望人皆有之。**++In an attempt to ameliorate the loss of investments due to international sanctions over its weapons program, North Korean officials have initiated a tourism push, focused on Chinese visitors.**++试图以此来改善由于国际制约其核武器计划而导致的外来经济损失，朝鲜官方已经针对中国游客开始了一个旅游推动项目。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('114', 'amenable', '[əminəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amenable', '{adj.}++对…负有责任(或义务)的，(应)负责的，有服从的义务的，应服从的**++易受控制(或影响)的；易做出响应的；肯接受劝告的，服从启导的；(愿)服从的，服理的**++经得起检验(或考验、考查)的 (to)**', '++America cut “amenable” deaths by only 4% during that period; it fell to bottom of the table.**++在那段时间里，美国的“可预防”死亡只减少了4%，落到了表格的最底部。**++"Just about any natural science has the type of structure that would be amenable, " she said.**++“几乎任何自然科学都有能够经受这个程序检验的那种结构。” 她说。**++Some systems, especially those that involve the integration of custom hardware with software, may not be amenable to using Small Releases.**++一些系统，特别是那些涉及到集成通用硬件和软件的系统，对与使用小型版本可能不太友好。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('115', 'amenity', '[əmɛnəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amenity', '{n.}++(性情等的)愉快，快乐**++(地方、气候等的)舒适，宜人，温和，温柔 **++舒服；方便，便利**', '++Development and natural resource amenity areas are often controversial.**++自然资源开发与绿化，经常引起争议。**++And why has theM.T.A. decided to use the new Vignelli map solely as a weekend amenity?**++可为什么纽约市大都会运输署（M.T.A）决定把这个地图仅仅用于周末的便利设施？**++Since then, however, land has become more valuable, not just for timber but for providing "environmental services" such as flood control, climate change measures and amenity.**++但是从那时起，林地变得越来越有价值，不仅是因为伐木业，而且因为它所提供的环境服务，例如控制洪水，调节气候等。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('116', 'amiable', '[emɪəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amiable', '{adj.}++令人愉悦的，悦人的，友善的；亲切的；和蔼可亲的**++[古语、废语]可爱的；讨人喜欢的；出色的**', '++The leader did the amiable.**++那名领导人装出和蔼可亲的样子。**++I couldn@t have guessed then, drifting to sleep to the sound of their amiable chatter, that every last one of them was a terrorist.**++在他们和蔼可亲的唠叨声中，我终于进入了梦乡。 当时的我怎么也不会想到——其实这些人都是恐怖分子。**++Edward is very amiable, and I love him tenderly.**++爱德华非常和蔼可亲，我也很喜爱他。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('117', 'amicable', '[æmɪkəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amicable', '{adj.}', '++"I hope that we can find an amicable solution to this issue through the consultation process," she said in a statement.**++她在一份声明中指出：“我希望我们能通过磋商来寻求这一问题的友好的解决办法。”**++Arbitration：All disputes arising in connection with this Sales Contract or the execution thereof shall be settled by way of amicable negotiation.**++仲裁：凡因执行本合约或有关本合约所发生的一切争执，双方应以友好方式协商解决；**++They have remained amicable over the years, and she has been a supporter of his political career.**++多年来，他们保持友善关系，前妻一直是他政治事业的支持者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('118', 'amity', '[æməti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amity', '{n.}', '++Walter had strong feelings about courtesy and fairness and amity, and he was borderline uxorious as a husband, but he was apparently willing neither to support his wife nor to curb her.**++沃尔特看重客气、公正、友好关系，作为丈夫，他不无妻管严的嫌疑，但显然他即不愿意支持自己的妻子，也不愿意去限制她。**++Two nations that appreciate and learn from each other should be able to live in amity and progress together.**++两个相互欣赏、相互学习的民族，也应该是友好相处、共同进步的民族。**++Europe is particularly intoxicated by the possibility of restoring amity with America in an Obama presidency.**++欧洲尤其对修复与奥巴马任总统的美国的友好关系的可能性感到特别兴奋。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('119', 'amorphous', '[əmɔrfəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=amorphous', '{adj.}++无定形的，无固定形状的；难以名状的；无固定界线的**++不规则的，无组织的；难以归类的，无法分类的**++含糊的，模糊的；不明确的**++无明确目标(或方向)的**++【生物学】(如培养基上的低等植物)无定形的**++【化学】非晶形的，非结晶的**++【地质学】非结晶质的**', '++This releases a mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide, known as syngas, and leaves a residue of amorphous elemental carbon called carbon black.**++这一过程产生氢气和一氧化碳的混合物，也叫做合成气，剩余的是无定形的基本碳，也叫做炭黑。**++Glass, by definition, is amorphous; its atoms lack order and are arranged every which way.**++玻璃，根据定义，是无定形、非晶态的；它的原子排布缺乏规律性，排列在各个方向上。**++The device uses an amorphous rubber bag filled with small particles that can mold and tighten around objects with the help of vacuum pressure.**++这个设备使用填满小颗粒的不定形橡胶袋，里面的小颗粒可以在真空压力的帮助下塑形和夹紧物体。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('120', 'anachronistic', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anachronistic', '{adj.}', '++Don@t be anachronistic; don@t think back into the ancient text something that actually arose later.**++不要犯时代错误，不要把之后发生的事情,想回到古代经文里去。**++One of their cabinet posts, secretary of state for Scotland, has been anachronistic since powers were devolved to Edinburgh in 1998.**++一个内阁发布了苏格兰的国务大臣在1998年将权利转移到爱丁堡是一个时代错误。**++He only owns one shirt -- the one he wore for the first time on the day of his marriage -- and it has an anachronistic plastic collar.**++他只有一件西装——是在他结婚那天第一次穿的那件——它有一颗有时代印记的塑料纽扣。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('121', 'analgesic', '[ænldʒizɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=analgesic', '{adj.}++【病理学】痛觉缺失(或消失)的；止痛的**{n.}++【药物】镇痛药(或剂)，止痛剂[亦作analgetic]**', '++Ginger Tea - Ginger, being a natural analgesic and antipyretic, can help reduce your fever and its effects.**++姜茶 ——姜，作为一种天然的止痛剂和退热剂，可以帮助退热和减轻由此引起的其他症状。**++Even more intriguing, he says was that love activated different parts of the brain than the normal analgesic pathways.**++更令人觉得有趣的是，他说比起普通的用止痛的方法爱情更能使大脑的不同部位活跃起来。**++A lot more research is needed before anyone can say that any analgesic is an effective means of treating social pain.**++我们还需要更多的研究才能证明镇痛剂对社会疼痛有疗效。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('122', 'analogous', '[ənæləɡəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=analogous', '{adj.}++类似的，相似的；可比拟的(to，with)**++【计算机】模拟的**++【生物学】同功的**++【自动化】模拟的**', '++The gills of fishes are analogous to the lungs in terrestrial animals.**++鱼类的鳃与陆上动物的肺类似。**++There are no naming restrictions for the deployment manager profile, since there is no analogous object in V4.**++对于部署管理器配置文件没有命名约束，这是由于 V4 中没有类似的对象。**++In the Middle East and North Africa, nothing analogous occurred.**++但在中东和北非，并没有发生类似的变化。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('123', 'anarchist', '[ænɚkɪst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anarchist', '{n.}++无政府主义者；无政府主义信徒(或鼓吹者)**++造成无政府状态的人(如藐视或无视法律、义务、纪律的人)；煽动叛乱的人，扰乱分子**{adj.}++无政府主义(者)的**', '++One must choose between God and Man, and all "radicals" and "progressives, " from the mildest Liberal to the most extreme Anarchist, have in effect chosen Man.**++一个人必须在上帝与人之间做出选择，而所有的“激进派”和“进步派”，从最温和的自由主义者到最极端的无政府主义者，实际上都选择了人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('124', 'anathema', '[ənæθəmə]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anathema', '{n.}++被诅咒的物(或人)，受诅咒(或谴责)的对象**++非常令人厌恶的物(或人)**++【宗教】诅咒，咒逐，革(或逐)出教门；(对被革出教门者的)咒词；革除教籍令**++强烈的谴责，诅咒，咒骂**', '++Campbell summed up by saying that nutrition is holistic, a concept which is “anathema” to most scientists’ method.**++坎贝尔总结说，营养是全面的，这个概念是对大多数科学家的方法的“诅咒”。**++But such approaches are anathema to the US Republican Party, and to its Tea Party faction in particular, and they might unnerve the many Asians who are nervous at China’s growing military might.**++但美国共和党会认为这是一个诅咒而选择废止，而这对于茶叶党来说尤为特殊，也许还会扰动许多亚洲人的神经，这部分人多担忧日益增长的中国军力。**++Naturally, these views are anathema to modern Austrians in the tradition of Murray Rothbard, who think the central bank should be abolished.**++事实上，这些观点是对罗斯巴德一派的现代奥地利学派的诅咒，因为奥地利学派认为中央银行必须取消。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('125', 'ancillary', '[ænsəlɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ancillary', '{adj.}++从属的，附属的，附随的，有关的(常与 to连用)**++作为助手的；辅助的；补充的**{n.}++[英国英语]**++助手，助理，随从，辅助者；仆人**++附件，附属部件，附属物(品)**', '++The company also will supply ancillary and support equipment, spare and repair parts, and logistics support.**++该公司还将提供辅助支持设备、备用零部件和维修以及后勤支持。**++I have great respect for our nurses and other ancillary personnel and the work they do, but this doesn@t seem to happen to my male colleagues.**++我很尊重我们的护士和其他的辅助医护人员以及他们所做的工作，但是这些似乎没有发生在我的男同事们身上。**++This information is supplemented by ancillary data.**++此信息通过辅助数据进行补充。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('126', 'anecdote', '[ænɪkdot]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anecdote', '{n.}++轶事，逸事，趣闻**++[常作复数]( 历史或名人生平事迹中未曾公开发表过的 )秘闻，(个人经历或传记中不为世人所知的)趣闻**', '++There she read an anecdote.**++她读到一桩轶事。**++She departed from the text to tell an anecdote.**++她脱离课文扯到一段轶事上去了。**++But I remember an anecdote I once heard from one of my German friends. Shortly after the unification, an Ossie and a Weissie meet in Berlin.**++但我记得从一个德国朋友那里听来的这样一件轶事：统一后不久，一个东德人与一个西德人在柏林相遇。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('127', 'anemic', '[əniːmɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anemic', '{adj.}', '++That is not realistic at all, as a weak, anemic U-shaped recovery is the most likely scenario for advanced economies.**++但这毕竟是不真实的，因为发达经济体最有可能面对的是一次虚弱、贫血的U型复苏。**++Back to the office we went to fill out the paper work and see how anemic my purse was going to be for the next five years or until my daughter finds a job, whichever comes first.**++回到售车处后，我们开始填写文档，眼睁睁看到我的钱包如何瘪了下去。 除非女儿找到份工作，否则在今后五年之内钱包都会患上贫血症了。**++But since the recovery in private demand will be weak, the economy is poised to slip back to anemic growth (well below potential) in 2010, posing the risk of a double-dip recession.**++但由于私人需求的复苏将会乏力，2010年的经济仍将返回到贫血的增长（增长完全低于潜在趋势）之中，并形成双头衰退的风险。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('128', 'anesthetic', '[,ænɪsθɛtɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anesthetic', '{n., adj.}', '++“They say the needle pricks like an ant bite, ”he explained, when the first patient flinched at the local anesthetic.**++当第一位患者在局部麻醉时缩了一下时，他解释说，“他们说，针刺好像蚂蚁咬了一口。**++During a kiss, natural antibiotics are secreted in the saliva.Also, the saliva contains a type of anesthetic that helps relieve pain.**++接吻时，唾液中会分泌一种天然的抗生素，另外，唾液中还含有一种可以减轻疼痛感的麻醉物。**++It@s also used as a local anesthetic for other types of small procedures.**++它还会在一些小的治疗过程中,作为局部麻醉剂使用。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('129', 'animate', '[ænɪmet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=animate', '{vt.}++赋予…以生命，使有生命：**++使活泼，使有生气，使有活力，使生气勃勃；使容光焕发：**++鼓舞，鼓动，激励，激动：**++使行动起来，推动，驱动，促进：**++使栩栩如生地动作；操作，操纵：**++把…摄制(或绘制、制)成动画片**{adj.}++活着的，有生命的(尤指动物生命)**++动物的(与植物相对而言)**++活泼的，有生气的，有活力的；生气勃勃的；愉快的**++【语言学】(名词的性)动物的**++自动的**', '++You can animate position, color, shape, size, rotation and other elements at the property level.**++你可以设置动画的位置，颜色，形状，大小，旋转和其他属性级别的因素。**++The NLP swish pattern would have you do a straight cut from one scene to the next, but I recommend you animate the first scene into the second.**++神经语言程式学的闪变模式会让你直接从第一场景切换到第二场景，但我建议你想办法从第一场景发展到第二场景。**++Thus the drives encounter will in the form of other interpreting drives not only those of our fellow human beings but also the drives than animate animals, plants and all other natural phenomena.**++因此，动力遇到意识是以其他,理解动力的次能够使，不只是那些,我们人类，还有有生命的动物,植物，还有其他的自然现象。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('130', 'animus', '[ænɪməs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=animus', '{n.}++主导精神；基本态度；根本目的；基调**++意图，意向；意旨；动机；倾向**++(尤指因偏见而引起的)仇视，仇恨，憎恶；敌意，恶意**++【心理学】[瑞士心理学家荣格用语](女性人格的)男性意向**', '++But not as striking, perhaps, as his animus for Isabel Lyon.**++但，也许，始终不如他对伊莎贝尔里昂的敌意引人注目。**++The viciousness of the official animus toward the indigent can be breathtaking.**++官方针对穷人的敌意之恶毒可以说是惊人的。**++Pakistan@s animus toward India is the cause of both its unwillingness to fight Islamic extremism and its active complicity in undermining the aims of its ostensible ally, the United States.**++正是由于巴基斯坦对印度的这种敌意，促使其不愿意与伊斯兰极端主义对抗，同时积极地和别的国家一起暗中破坏其表面上的盟友──美国──的战略目标。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('131', 'annex', '[ənɛks; ænɛks; (for n.) ænˌɛks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=annex', '{vt.}++附加；添加；附带：**++附加(条件)，增添：**++并吞，兼并(领土等)，强行占取(领土等)；把…并入辖区；使并入：**++把…强行据为己有，不告自取，挪用，侵占：**++得到，获得:**++把…作为附录：**++[古语]签(名)；盖(印章)：**++[古语]与…连起来；接合；联合；合并**{n.}++[英国英语亦作 annexe]附加物；尤指：**++侧厅，边房**++添加(或附属)的建筑物，增建部分**++附件；附录，补遗，增刊**', '++In some instances, one group will "invade" and annex the territory of another, killing all but the adult females, who are forced to incorporate into the dominant group.**++有时候，一个群落还会“入侵”和吞并另一群落的领地，杀死除了成年母猩猩外的所有猩猩，而将这些母猩猩强行纳入自己的群落。**++For this reason, we have included our track record and the other quantitative data in this submission as an additional annex so that you can assess it on a comparable basis.**++由于这个原因，我们已在这次提交材料的附录中包括了我们的跟踪误差以及其它定量数据，这样，你就能在一个比较的基础上进行评估。**++For a start, the first round agreement of a 5% emissions reduction from Annex I (that is, industrialised) countries was woefully insufficient, given the scale of the challenge posed by climate change.**++从一开始，第一回合附件I协定的有关发达国家减少5%排放量——考虑到气候变化所带来的挑战的规模而言——是非常不足的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('132', 'annotate', '[ænətet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=annotate', '{vt.}++给(文学作品等)评注(或注解)，作注，注释：**++给(文学作品等)评注(或注解)，作注，注释：**{vi.}++评注，作注解，注释:**++评注，作注解，注释:**', '++I only need to create a simple POJO and annotate it.**++我只需要创建一个简单的 POJO 并对它进行注释。**++You can, however, annotate the visual layout, but those comments will not appear in the flow text view.**++但是，您可以注释可视化布局，但那些注释不会出现在流文本视图中。**++Once you have that, you can then annotate the URL with any other useful information that you find out about it (for example, its author).**++一旦有了 URL， 您就可以用找到的有关它的任何其它有用信息（例如，其作者）来注释 URL。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('133', 'annoy', '[ənɔɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=annoy', '{vt.}++使烦恼，使苦恼；使恼怒；使恼火，招惹；使有几分生气，使不高兴：**++打扰，打搅，干扰；折磨；【军事】骚扰，扰乱；使受损失，伤害：**{vi.}++惹人烦恼；招讨厌，令人讨厌；烦恼，烦扰；打扰，骚扰；伤害；令人憎恶：**++惹人烦恼；招讨厌，令人讨厌；烦恼，烦扰；打扰，骚扰；伤害；令人憎恶：**{n.}++[古语、诗歌用语] = annoyance**', '++He is not doing this to annoy you.**++他做这件事并非是要惹你烦恼。**++We can annoy the enemy by air raids.**++我们可以用空袭骚扰敌人。**++I am convinced that some people complain just to annoy me, for something to do, or they simply enjoy complaining.**++我以为身边的人抱怨是为了令我烦恼、是为了解决某些事、又或者他们就是喜欢抱怨。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('134', 'annul', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=annul', '{vt.}++废除，废止，取消(法律、协议、合同、规定、用法等)：**++使…无效，宣告…无效，宣告作废：**++抹去；使消失；冲掉：**++[美国英语]使(火车、航班、社交活动等)暂停一天(或一次)，取消(列车等的)运行**', '++The ICR would have the authority to annul laws or dismiss public officials to uphold the Kosovo settlement.**++这位国际民事代表有权为维护科索沃问题的解决而废除法律或撤销公职官员。**++He says Israel is considering a variety of responses but declined to elaborate.Lieberman has earlier suggested that Israel could annul past peace agreements or annex parts of the West Bank.**++利伯曼此前暗示称，以色列可以取消以前签订的和平协议或是与约旦河西岸相关的协议。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('135', 'anomalous', '[ənɑmələs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anomalous', '{adj.}++反常的，异常的；变态的；不规则的，例外的，破例的，破格的**++(与环境、其他事物等)不调和的，不协调的；不一致的；不合适的，不恰当的**++【语法学】不规则的，变则的**++【天文学】反常的**++【生物学】异常的**', '++I wish I could say that this is a single, anomalous group of students, but the trend is unmistakable.**++我希望我可以说这只是异常的一组学生，然而趋势是显而易见的。**++And even more specifically, we will expect both neighbors of an anomalous point to be either strongly higher or strongly lower than the candidate point.**++更具体地说，我们认为一个异常点的两个相邻点比参考点或者特别高， 或者特别低。**++A first step in exploring anomalous data is just finding it.**++探索异常数据的第一步只是 找到 它。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('136', 'anonymous', '[ənɑnəməs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anonymous', '{adj.}++匿名的；无名的，姓氏不明的，作者不明(或不详)的**++出自无名氏之手的，匿名者送(或写)的；不具名的；来源不明的**++缺乏(或无)个性特征的，无特色的；分不清谁是谁(或什么是什么)的**', '++Why is it anonymous?**++为什么它是匿名的？**++Each chunk is executed as the body of an anonymous function.**++每个块都是作为一个匿名函数体来执行的。**++Try not to use anonymous types in schemas.**++不要尝试在模式中使用匿名类型。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('137', 'antagonize', '[æntæɡənaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antagonize', '{vt.}++与…对立(或对抗、为敌、敌对)，竭力反对：**++引起…的敌意(或反感、反抗、反对)；招…的怨；使与自己为敌；使对抗，使对立；得罪：**++对…起反作用，反作用于，中和，抵消**{vi.}++树敌，招怨，引起反感(或对抗、对立)：**++敌视；反对[英国英语，亦作 antagonise]**', '++No company can afford to antagonize China.**++没有一家公司能与中国抗衡。**++The only thing this guy has planned is to sit back, relax, and antagonize all the “uptight bookworm worriers" by liking their pre-exam panic Facebook statuses.**++这种家伙所想的只是坐回去，放松，与他们的“书虫考前焦虑症”对抗，就像是他们在考前在脸簿上的惊慌的状态。**++Protesters have tried hard not to antagonize the police by sticking to their anti-China message, staying on the sidewalk and remaining far from the Chinese embassy.**++示威者在表达反中国信息时尽量保持不与警察发生冲突，他们聚集在人行道上，并且远离中国大使馆。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('138', 'antedate', '[,æntɪdet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antedate', '{vt.}++在…上写上早于实际的日期；倒填(信件、文件等)的日期；把…的日期提前:**++发生(或存在)于…以前，(时间上)先于，早于，前于：**++使提前(或较早)发生；加速：**++把(事件等)的日期确定得比实际发生为早：**++使回到较早时期，使回到过去：**++[古语]提前得到(或享受、使用等)**++[古语]预期，预料：**{n.}++(信件、文件等上面)倒填(或填早)的日期**++(为事件等确定的)早于实际发生的日期，比实际提前的日期，(为事件等确定的)早于原定的日期**', '++To precede in time; antedate.**++先于时间上先于…；**++The great eternal truths and principles of life antedate all religions.**++生活中伟大的永恒真理和原理比宗教信仰出现得早。**++To place a prior date on a legal document, statement or check. Also called antedate .**++在法定文件、报表或支票上填一个以前的日期，又称提前日期。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('139', 'antediluvian', '[,æntɪdɪluvɪən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antediluvian', '{adj.}++(基督教《圣经》中所说的)大洪水以前的[《创世记》7，8]**++古老的，远古的；过时的，远远落后于时代的；陈旧的；老式的**{n.}++大洪水以前的人；存在于大洪水以前的事物(动物或植物)**++年迈的人；背时的老朽；远远落后于时代的人，不合时宜的人**', '++The libraries of the world are doomed to become museums, storage facilities for a form as antediluvian as cave paintings.**++世上的图书馆注定要成为博物馆，里面陈列的书籍就像洞穴壁画一样被列为古董了。**++The mystery surrounding these antediluvian creatures is one of the many attributes that inspires human interest and compassion for their well-being.**++许多关于这些古老创造物的谜团正是激发人类兴趣和同情的力量之一。**++Its navy was antediluvian: mandarins tried to emulate Western paddle-steamers with junks propelled by coolies turning treadmills.**++它的海军落后西方：洋务官员提出纷纷效仿西方有帆的桨轮船的推动力由苦力变成了踏步机。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('140', 'anterior', '[æntɪrɪɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=anterior', '{adj.}++(空间方面)位于前面的，前部的**++【动物学】头部的，头部附近的；朝前的(posterior之对)**++(时间方面)先前的，较早的，先于…的**++【植物学】(叶、花等)前部的，不靠近主干的**++【语音学】齿音的，齿龈音的，唇音的**++【逻辑学】在前的**', '++These @structural changes@ were greatest in the fibres connecting the anterior cingulate, the part of the brain which helps regulate emotions and behaviour.**++这些结构变化在连结前扣带皮层的纤维中最为剧烈，而前扣带皮层为大脑中控制情绪和行为的一部分。**++Anxious monkeys show elevated activity in the amygdala (left) and anterior hippocampus (right), but the effects of heredity seem to act more on the hippocampus.**++焦虑的猴子的左边扁桃体和前部海马回表现兴奋，但遗传因素在海马回部分表现更为突出。**++Pigmented cells in the anterior vitreous, vitreous hemorrhage, posterior vitreous detachment, and elevation of the retina with or without retinal break are observed.**++另外还可观察到前玻璃体内的色素细胞，玻璃体出血，后玻璃体脱离，视网膜抬高并伴有或不伴有破口。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('141', 'antic', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antic', '{adj.}++[古语]古怪的，怪诞的，乖张荒诞的，哗众取宠的[亦作 antick]**++奇特的，滑稽可笑的；丑角般的**++嬉戏的，爱闹着玩的，诙谐的**{n.}++[常作复数]夸张的噱头；怪诞举动；(旨在哗众取宠的)滑稽可笑的动作(或姿势)，古怪的行为(或姿势)**++[古语](马戏、喜剧等的)小丑，丑角**++[古语]幕间滑稽表演**++[古语](建筑物中的)奇形怪状的雕塑**{vi.}++扮小旦；做滑稽动作，扮古怪姿势，做怪相**', '++Antic and colleagues probed the activity of neurons in lab dishes one at a time.**++在实验室，安迪和同事们在培养皿中逐一探测了单个神经元的电活动。**++"The ref had a black day when it came to Serbia, " said their manager Raddy Antic afterwards.**++赛后，塞尔维亚队主教练安蒂奇表示：“裁判给塞尔维亚队带来了黑暗的一天。**++Perhaps it is a flexing of mental muscles to help keep the cells alive, says neuroscientist Srdjan Antic, who led the new study.**++这项研究的负责人神经科学家安迪（Srdjan Antic） 说，这种神经放电活动也许是有助于神经细胞的存活。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('142', 'antipathy', '[æntɪpəθi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antipathy', '{n.}++(尤指生来并根深蒂固的)厌恶,反感,憎恶(against,for,to,toward(s))**++讨厌的人(或东西)，厌憎对象，令人反感的事物**++[古语](在特性、本性、脾性、感情等方面的)不相容(性)，抵触**', '++The antipathy is mutual.**++这种反感是相互的。**++There was an undercurrent of antipathy between them.**++他们两人之间潜伏着一股反感的暗流。**++As this column has pointed out for years, Asians harbor remarkably intense antipathy for their neighbors.**++正如此专栏多年指出的那样，亚洲人对他们的邻居怀有无比强烈的反感。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('143', 'antiquated', '[æntɪkwetɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antiquated', '{vt.}++antiquate的变形**{adj.}++过时的，老式的，陈旧的；被废弃的**++年老的**++年深日久的**{vt.}++使古旧；因陈旧而废弃，废弃；使变得过时而遭淘汰：**++给以古式的外表，以拟古式样设计(或制作)；使具有古董外形，使显得古色古香：**', '++An antiquated law in place until 1996 protected local Georgia banking monopolies by making it difficult for a lender based in one of the state@s 159 counties to open a branch in another.**++直到1996年，仍有一项过时的法令使一个领导性银行很难在自己的地方之外的全州159个县开始分支机构。 想要以此来保护当地的银行垄断。**++Although politicians may have been more comfortable in a world where what was good for General Motors was good for America, that tended to lead to protectionism and antiquated working practices.**++政客们习惯生活在一个这样的一个世界中：那些对通用汽车和美国有利的东西总会导致贸易保护主义和陈旧的工作习惯。**++Instead of replicating the antiquated phone network inside the web, let’s instead dramatically simplify telephony by adding voice on top of our social networks.**++与其费力地在网络中复制过时的电话系统，还不如直接简化电话技术，在社交网站中添加语音功能。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('144', 'antithetical', '[,æntɪθɛtɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=antithetical', '{adj.}++【修辞学】(含有)对语的，对偶的**++正相反的，对立的，对照的(to)**', '++The second mistaken view that one often hears is that emotion is antithetical to rationality.**++我们经常听到的第二种错误的看法认为：情绪与合理性是对立的。**++Structuralism is an approach that unites people with apparently disparate or wholly antithetical methods of thinking.**++结构主义是人们联合看起来完全不同的或全部对立的方法去思考方法。**++And if the two are antithetical then it makes sense.**++如果这俩对立，那就是有意义的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('145', 'apathy', '[æpəθi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apathy', '{n.}++无情，无感情，缺乏感情；无动于衷**++无兴趣，漠不关心，冷漠，冷淡，漠然**++[亦作 apatheia,apathia]【心理学】情感淡漠**', '++The core principles of personal atrophy, as opposed to personal development, should then be Falsehood, Apathy and Powerlessness.**++作为个人发展的对立面，个人退化的核心原则应该是 谎言、冷漠以及无能为力 。**++The more you direct your life towards Falsehood, Apathy and Powerlessness, the more you’ll regress in your life instead of improve.**++你越是把生活指向谎言、冷漠和无能为力，你的生活就会倒退得越多而不会有所改善。**++However, if I talk to them about it, they’re going to feel worse, not better — at least initially — since the path out of apathy runs straight through the territory of negative emotions.**++然而，如果我跟他们讨论起这个，他们的感觉不会变好，而是更糟——至少在开始时如此——因为摆脱冷漠的方法直刺他们内心充满负面情感的部分。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('146', 'aphorism', '[æfərɪzəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aphorism', '{n.}++(对科学原理的)简练叙述**++(任何学科中蕴含着普遍原理的)箴言，原理，定律**++格言,警句;谚语(例：Art is long,and life is short.艺术长存,生命短暂。)**', '++What’s the science behind this old aphorism?**++这句古老的格言背后有什么样的科学依据呢？**++That@s more than a folksy aphorism when it comes to infectious diseases.**++对于传染疾病而言，这句格言可就不仅仅是一句民间习语了。**++"Half the game is 90 percent mental," Yogi Berra once said, or something like that, and science is now getting around to putting his aphorism to the test.**++约吉·贝拉曾经说：“半场比赛是百分之九十的精神比赛（心理战），”或类似这样的话, 而科学目前正在寻找检验他的格言的时机。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('147', 'apocalyptic', '[əˌpɒkəlɪptɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apocalyptic', '{adj.}++启示文学(作品)的**++[A-]【圣经】《启示录》的**++【宗教】启示论的，天启的**++预示世界末日(恐怖景象)的；预示大动乱的，预示大灾变的，可怕的**++漫无边际地乱作预言的**++决定性的，最终的**{n.}++启示文学(作品)**++＝ apocalyptist**', '++Your characterisation of Confucianism, with its simultaneous apocalyptic and grandiose predictions for China, is barely more than a cartoon.**++你对于儒教的描述以及你同时作出的有如天启一般浮夸的中国预言就像一副卡通画。**++Who else was an apocalyptic prophet? Paul.**++还有谁是启示主义先知？保罗。**++Apocalyptic is a political ideology, but what kind of politics it teaches in the early times of Christianity can vary.**++天启论是一种政治意识形态，但它所教导的政治主张,在基督教早期可能不同。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('148', 'apocryphal', '[əpɒkrəfəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apocryphal', '{adj.}++著作者身份(或真实性、权威性)可疑的，伪(书)的**++伪造的，仿造的；假的，假冒的；杜撰的**++[常作 A-]【宗教】**++次经的**++新约外传的**++旁经的**', '++His hopes rested, in part, on an article he read somewhere, which very well might be apocryphal but nevertheless allowed him to dream.**++他的这种感觉部分来自于一篇他在某个地方看到的一篇文章，也不知道是谁写的，但是尽管如此至少给了他梦想的希望。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('149', 'apoplectic', '[,æpəplɛktɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apoplectic', '{adj.}++【医学】**++引起中风的**++患中风病的；卒中的，中风的**++濒于中风的；有中风迹象的；卒中样的，类中风性的**++易怒的**{n.}++患中风者，中风病人**++易中风的人**', '++More to the point, her father would be apoplectic at the idea.**++还有，孩子他爸可能会被女儿的这个主意引发中风的。**++Democrats, for their part, became apoplectic about a proposal to raise the retirement age for Social Security by one year — in 2050.**++民主党，说到他们，在谈到将享受社保的年龄提高一岁这个问题上变得不可理喻，他们认为2050年才可能实现。**++Is it the sound of apoplectic readers typing irate e-mails about the subject of this column?**++是怒火中烧的读者在敲键盘、写邮件投诉这个专栏话题吗？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('150', 'apostasy', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apostasy', '{n.}', '++At its sternest, Islamic law prescribes the death penalty for anybody who commits “apostasy”—or abandons the faith.**++最残酷的是，伊斯兰教法规定，对任何“变节者”或背弃信仰的人，都判处死刑。**++But many left-wing friends never forgave his apostasy, doubtless reinforcing his inclination to keep the outside world at a safe distance.**++但许多左翼的朋友却永远不原谅他的“变节”，这无疑更坚定了他与外界保持一定距离的决心。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('151', 'appall', '[əpɔl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=appall', '{vt., vi.}', '++Defending murderers and thieves would appall them.**++为杀人犯和小偷辩护会使他们吓得魂不附体。**++Gandhi’s nonconformist ways tend to appall and alienate secular-minded observers.**++甘地不随主流的方法往往会吓跑和疏远那些有着世俗思想的旁观者。**++I used practically a whole bottle of red dye in the frosting, which in earlier days would appall me.**++我在做糖霜时用了整整一瓶红色的染料，这在以前会把我自己吓死。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('152', 'apparition', '[,æpərɪʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apparition', '{n.}++出乎意料(或离奇)地出现的东西；(尤指)幻象，幻影，怪影，妖怪，幽灵，鬼**++特异景象**++(非凡的人或事、特异景象等的)出现，显露，显形**++【天文学】(彗星、行星等隐没后的)初现；出现期**', '++Before this awful apparition I retreat in terror -- a terror that is upon me as I write.**++在此幻影前，我在恐惧中退却--这种恐惧即便现在我写作时依然伴随着我。**++This apparition grew to a fine old age, until he reached a maturity he could not improve on, and now he haunts the church in which his parents had married.**++和拉霍斯.佛斯林汉姆不同，他长得很瘦弱，讲故事的时候手里一直紧握着白兰地酒杯。 “那鬼怪一直长到它成熟为止，现在，它就在它父母当年结婚的那家教堂出没。”**++She laughed and coughed, and the husband ran from the room ashen-faced, as if he’d seen a fulminating witch, a dead woman speaking, some kind of horror-flick apparition.**++她边笑边咳嗽，丈夫脸色苍白从房间里跑出来，好像他见到了一个喜好怒斥人的巫婆，一个死亡女人的讲话，某种恐怖片里的幽灵似的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('153', 'appeal', '[əpil]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=appeal', '{vt.}++【法律】将…上诉；将…移交上级法院审理：**++[废语](在法庭上)控诉，控告，指控**{vi.}++【法律】上诉，申诉；移交上级法院审理：**++(迫切)要求，恳求，求援；呼吁，吁请(某人帮助、同情等)：**++求助(于)；求教于；诉(诸)，诉之于，诉请证实(或裁决等)**++有吸引力；有感染力；引起兴趣；引起注意；投其所好；引人入胜(to):**++提请注意：**++【体育】(尤指板球赛)诉诸裁判(against或to):**{n.}++呼吁，吁请，请求；诉诸**++(迫切的)要求(帮助、同情等)恳求，哀恳**++求助于；诉诸于；诉请；申请**++(人或物的)吸引力，感染力；号召力**++【法律】**++上诉，申诉**++上诉请求，诉请**++上诉权，申诉权**++上诉案件**', '++Both these things appeal to him.**++这两样都对他有吸引力。**++The sentence of the court was quashed on appeal.**++经过上诉，法院的判决被宣布无效。**++An appeal is being made for help for those who lost their homes in the earthquake.**++正在呼吁援助在地震中失去家园的人们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('154', 'appealing', '[əpiːlɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=appealing', '{adj.}++有吸引力的，有感染力的，吸引人的，引人入胜的，动人的**++恳求的；哀诉的，哀恳的**', '++The simplicity of this definition is appealing.**++这个定义的简单性是吸引人的。**++The most appealing approach is to say, "Tell us the things you like to do and do well and we will find a way to use those talents.**++最常见的吸引人的办法是去说“告诉我们你愿意做什么，和擅长做什么，我们会找到一个方式去发挥这些天赋。”**++But otherwise most of the stories he only tells his friends in this appealing and attitude-free autobiography are shot through with pain, anxiety and unhappiness.**++但不同的是，在这本吸引人并且态度随意的自传中，大多数他只告诉朋友的事是伴随着痛苦，紧张和悲伤的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('155', 'applause', '[əplɔz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=applause', '{n.}++鼓掌(以示欢迎或赞许)，(拍手)喝彩，欢呼，叫好**++称赞，赞成，赞扬，嘉许，夸奖**', '++The applause burst from the crowd.**++人群中爆发出掌声。**++I do not personate the stage-play emperor to entrap applause.**++我不扮演戏台上的国王骗取掌声。**++We should all be able to agree -- (applause) -- we should all be able to agree on some clear standards.**++我们大家都应当能够达成──(掌声)──我们大家应当能够就一些明确的标准达成共识。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('156', 'applicable', '[æplɪkəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=applicable', '{adj.}++可应用的，适用的，合用的(to)**++可实施的；(药物)可敷用的**++适当的，合适的，恰当的(to)**', '++Users of this document should verify the applicable data for their specific environment.**++该文件的用户应该为指定的环境确认可应用的数据。**++When running a pattern against a model with this extension, this pattern will show up on a list of applicable patterns for this model.**++当针对一个模型运行具有这种扩展名的模式时，这个模式将显示可适用于这个模型的模式的列表。**++The service payloads could be encoded in SOAP messages; however these ideas are applicable even when the messages employ other encodings.**++服务有效负荷可以被编码进SOAP消息；即使在消息使用其它编码时，这些想法也是可应用的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('157', 'apposite', '[æpəzɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apposite', '{adj.}', '++From voting reform to CCTV, from Trident to the debates, there’s a perfect Orwell quotation, apposite, terse and oracular, just waiting to be plucked out and flourished.**++从选举改革，到闭路监视电视，从战斗机到争论，总有一条完美的奥维尔谏言，适当，简洁，神谕似的，就在那边等着被拔找出来，接着繁华开去。**++Just make sure they’re original, clever and apposite, and don’t involve some infantile banter with your co-commentator about an open goal he missed two decades ago.**++但是得保证这些玩笑是原创的、诙谐的、贴切的。 别和你的搭档去谈及诸如他20年前错过了一个开场球此类的幼稚笑话。**++The phrase comes from a quote in the final paragraph, which is also worth repeating because it contains what may turn out to be the most apposite verdict on the whole affair.**++这短语来自于文章的最后一段引用的话，在标题里也值得被重复一下，因为它包含了可能被证明是对整个事件最恰当的评判。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('158', 'appreciable', '[əpriʃəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=appreciable', '{adj.}', '++Did she have any appreciable influence on him, and thus on history?**++她有没有试图对他施以影响，从而改变历史呢？**++Maffei 1 is a lenticular galaxy,which has a disk-like structure and a central bulge but no spiralstructure or appreciable dust content.**++马费伊1是个透镜状星系，它有一个盘状的结构和中央部分的突起，但没有螺旋机构或者可感知的尘埃量。**++Adults with appreciable amounts of brown fat are usually those who have certain types of cancer or hyperthyroidism, conditions that stimulate the growth of brown fat.**++那些患有某种癌症或甲状腺功能亢进症的成年人通常有数额可观的棕色脂肪，身体的这种状况刺激了棕色脂肪的增长。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('159', 'apprehension', '[,æprɪhɛnʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apprehension', '{n.}++逮捕，拘押；捕获，拿获**++理解，领会，领悟，颖悟；理解力**++看法，意见，主张，见解**++(对行将出现的危险、灾祸等的)忧虑，挂念，担心；畏惧，恐惧，恐怖，疑惧**', '++Victory after apprehension and fear.**++胜利在忧虑和恐惧以后。**++It’s the notion of knowing exactly what needs to be done, but lacking the nerve to do it; the apprehension to your aspirations.**++从概念上讲，我们知道我们必须要做什么，但是却没有勇气去做；这就是对你的志向的忧虑。**++His  comprehensive  apprehension about the  appendix of the  pendulum is  obvious.**++他的广泛的关于这个摆的附录的忧虑明显。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('160', 'apprehensive', '[,æprɪhɛnsɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apprehensive', '{adj.}++[通常作表语]有理解能力的，能理解的，善于领会的**++聪颖的，聪明的，敏捷的，敏悟的**++担心的，忧虑的，忧惧的，疑惧的**++有认识力的，认识的，知晓的(of)**', '++As I give the driver my address, I@m half euphoric, half apprehensive about what comes next.**++当我把住址告诉司机时，我对将要发生的事情，感到半是欣快，半是不安。**++There are historical reasons, too, why markets are highly apprehensive about Greece, and these are linked to concerns about the country@s political stability.**++市场会对希腊问题感到高度不安，也存在历史原因，这些原因与人们对其政治稳定性的担忧有关。**++Climatological Cassandras are becoming increasingly apprehensive, for the weather aberrations they are studying may be the harbinger of another ice age.**++气候预言家们开始不安起来，天气的不寻常可能是另外一个冰川时代到来的前兆。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('161', 'apprise', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apprise', '{vt.}{vt.}', '++He came to apprise us that the work had been successfully completed.**++他来通知我们工作已胜利完成。**++My ex-husband was eager to apprise me of the fact that my thesis was appraised as worthless.**++我的前夫迫不及待地告诉我，我的论文被评价得一无是处。**++I must keep my eye upon the gun; the smoke will apprise me--the report arrives too late; it lags behind the missile.**++我必须睁大眼睛，盯着那尊大炮；炮口冒出的硝烟会通知我——炮弹射出来了，炮声响得太慢；它要远远落在炮弹的后面。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('162', 'approbation', '[æprəbeʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=approbation', '{n.}++批准，核准；认可；称许**++赞成，赞同；满意**++[废语]证明，证据，证词**', '++Until his Medicare plan was rolled out in early April he had spent months bathing in warm approbation from many pundits, who had decided to anoint him as an icon of fiscal responsibility.**++在4月初抛出其“老年医保”计划之前的几个月里，他一直浸沉在许多专家热情的赞扬认可气氛之中，这些专家们还将他尊为负责任财政政策的化身。**++When he heard them for the first time he was as surprised as he was pleased, and with his approbation my road to freedom was widened.**++当他第一次听到我对他读这些诗的时候，他是又惊讶又高兴，有了他的好评，我的自由之路更加宽广了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('163', 'appropriate', '[əproprɪət;(for v.) əproprɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=appropriate', '{vt.}++把…据为己有，私占，占用，侵吞；专用，独用：**++(不适当地)擅用，挪用，盗用：**++拨出(款项等)，拨出(款项等)为专用：**++顺手牵羊，不告而取，偷窃(尤指零钱、小件物品等)**{adj.}++合适的，适合的，适宜的，适当的，恰当的，恰如其分的，相称的(for，to)**++政治上正确的[亦作PC(politically correct)]**++[罕用语]专属的；自己的；特定的**', '++Do work by executing appropriate code at each point in the application.**++在应用的每个点上执行适当的代码来完成工作。**++If so, then use an appropriate editor and change the encoding of the input file.**++如果是这样，可以使用一个适当的编辑器来更改输入文件的编码。**++Give a free hug. OK, only do this when appropriate … but if you have a loved one in your life, give them a hug!**++送出你的拥抱 .哦好吧,只能在适当的时候这样做...但是如果你深爱你生命中的某个人,给他一个拥抱!**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('164', 'apropos', '[,æprəpo]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apropos', '{adv.}++适时地，及时地；恰当地，中肯地，正好，恰好**++附带地，附带说说，顺便(说)( = by the way； 用于一句话的开头)**{adj.}++适时的，及时的；恰当的，中肯的，贴切的**{prep.}++就…而言，关于，至于:**++就…而言，关于，至于:**', '++The apropos command does a keyword search of manual pages and lists ones containing your keyword.**++apropos 命令对手册页执行关键字搜索，并列出包含您的关键字的命令。**++Or, to paraphrase more apropos to the subject at hand, "Transitioning to a new platform is pain, Mr. CTO.**++或者，为了更恰当地解释这个主题，可以这样说：“过渡到一个新的平台是痛苦的，CTO 先生。**++Each UNIX manual page has a short description, and apropos searches the corpus of descriptions for instances of the specified keyword.**++每个 UNIX 手册页都有简短的描述，apropos 在描述中搜索指定的关键字。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('165', 'apt', '[æpt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=apt', '{adj.}++适当的，适宜的，恰当的，恰如其分的；得体的，贴切的**++[后接动词不定式]有…倾向的，趋向的；(习性)易于…的；很可能的**++聪明的，聪颖的，敏悟的，反应敏捷的，伶俐的，善于(学习)的**++[古语]准备就绪的，准备好(了)的；现成的；立即可得到的，用起来便利的**{abbr.}++advanced passenger train (英国)高级特快列车,先进型旅客列车,特高速火车,**++Airman Proficiency Test 【军事】空军士兵技能测验**++automatically programmed tools 【计算机】自动数控程序,刀具程控自动编制系统;APT语言**++automatic picture transmission (人造卫星)自动图像传输**++automative professional training 汽车专业训练**{abbr.}++apartment**++aptitude**', '++It was an apt comment.**++这是一个恰当的评论。**++And soon, if you prove an apt student I will take you to where the birds have been teaching me how to fly.**++不久以后，如果事实证明，你是一个聪明的学生，我可以领你到鸟儿教我飞翔的地方去。**++They know not themselves, nor the aim of their wanderings; and, because they do not, they are ever apt to imitate something else.**++它们对自己认识不清，也不清楚自己徘徊的目的；而且正因为它们不清楚，它们就易于老是模仿别人的东西。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('166', 'arable', '[ærəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arable', '{adj.}++【农业】适于耕种(或耕作)的，适耕的，(土地)可耕的；可垦植的，可开垦的**{n.}++耕地；可耕地**', '++The livestock sector is already eligible for carbon finance, but we have made no such progress for arable agriculture and soils.**++畜牧业已经符合碳金融的条件了，但是，我们还没有为可开垦的农业和土壤方面做出这样的努力。**++Some Chinese commentators say the line has already been crossed: some land registered as arable is in fact being used for non-agricultural purposes.**++中国的一些评论员说，这条线早就被越过了：一些土地虽然登记为耕地，但实际上被用作非农业用途。**++Uganda has half of East Africa’s arable land and could become the granary of the region.**++乌干达可耕地占东非地区的一半，因而可以成为该地区的粮仓。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('167', 'arbitrary', '[ɑːrbətreri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arbitrary', '{adj.}++任意(性)的，随意的**++(个人)主观武断的，随心所欲的**++反复无常的，任性多变的，无定见的，变幻莫测的**++专制的，专断的，专横的**{n.}++(工资之外的)津贴，(特殊或额外服务的)额外报酬**++[英国英语][复数]【印刷】(常用成套铅字之外的)特殊活字**', '++This is an arbitrary block of XML, which means it can be formatted to match any XML schema.**++这是一个任意的 XML 块，这意味着可以对它进行格式化来匹配任何 XML 模式。**++This is unfair, and its arbitrary.**++这是不公平的，也是武断的。**++If you expose remote objects from arbitrary processes, you have to ensure those process are running.**++如果从任意进程中提供远程对象，则需要确保那些进程正在运行。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('168', 'arcane', '[ɑrken]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arcane', '{adj.}++深奥的，晦涩难解的**++神秘的；秘密的**++秘传的；限于小圈子内的**', '++It was an arcane dispute over tariffs.**++这是一场关于关税的神秘争斗。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('169', 'archaic', '[ɑrkeɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=archaic', '{adj.}++古的，古代的，古时的，古老的；原始的**++初始期的，早期的，未成熟期的**++陈旧的，过时的，老式的**++(词等)古体的，(除在诗词、宗教仪式等特殊用途外)已不通用的**++[常作 A-]【考古学】(尤指公元前7世纪至公元前5世纪的古希腊雕塑、绘画等文化、美术等)创始期的，早期的，古(代)风(格)的[参较 classical， Hellenistic]**', '++And I feel like it@s archaic in a way that it@s a long list of stuff sorted by date and time or sender, and we waste so much time sorting.**++我认为在某种程度上来说，电子邮件非常陈旧，因为它按日期和时间或发件人列出一长串资料，我们要浪费很多时间去排序。**++Water supply, sewage disposal, housing, epidemics and the disposal of the dead were high on a long list of problems that swamped the resources of an archaic system of local government.**++一长串问题让当地政府陈旧的资源体系不堪重负，而供水系统、污水处理、住宅、流行病和尸体处置这些都是最亟待解决的问题。**++When you think about the fact that we have a permanently manned space station and the Internet, using plastic cards with pictures on them to officially identify ourselves seems a bit archaic.**++人们思考一下，我们处在建立人居住永久太空站和互联网时代，如果我们仍采用有相片塑料卡确认自己身份，是否似乎有点陈旧。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('170', 'archetype', '[ɑrkətaɪp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=archetype', '{n.}++原型，原始(模)型**++典型，范例，样板**++(文艺作品、绘画等的)主题 **++(已失传的)原始手稿**', '++Additionally, you need to include the actual style code only once for an archetype.**++除此之外，对于原型只需要包含一次实际样式代码。**++An archetype is a group of characteristics and traits that are commonly seen in groups of people of any language, history, and size around the world.**++一个原型是一组特点和特性，这些特性常见于在世界各地说任何一种语言，有着任何一种历史、人口数量的群体。**++The Interaction Design methodology for user modeling captures archetype Users into User Personas, along with their goals and skills.**++用于用户建模的交互设计方法将原型用户捕获到用户角色中，也包括其目标和技能。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('171', 'ardor', '[ɑrdɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ardor', '{n.}', '++I began tracking the columnists’ pronouncements with some ardor.**++我开始带着某种狂热追踪专栏作家的文章。**++"Here@s fresh meat for your axe, Kreis, " he said; "a rose-white youth with the ardor of a lover for Herbert Spencer.**++“克瑞斯，你那板斧有了新对象了，”他说，“一个纯洁得像白玫瑰的青年，对斯宾塞怀着恋人一样的热情。**++As testament to her environmental ardor, a grove of skyscraper-esque trees in Redwood National Park bears the name of Lady Bird Johnson.**++在红杉国家公园，以伯德约翰逊夫人命名的小树林，那里种满的参天大树见证了她环保的热情。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('172', 'arduous', '[ɑrdʒuəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arduous', '{adj.}++困难的，艰难的，艰巨的，费力的**++勤奋的，努力的，辛勤的；使劲的**++险峻的，陡峭的，难攀登的**++难以忍受的；严重的**++[1530 ～ 1540]**', '++This work will be arduous, but we have to overcome the difficulty.**++这将是十分艰苦的工作，但也是我们必须克服的困难。**++Therefore, they need the stopover habitat—the shallows, the sandbars, the security, the corn and invertebrates—to complete their arduous yearly cycle.**++因此，它们需要这个中途停留的栖息地——浅滩、沙洲、安全、玉米和无脊椎动物——来完成年复一年的努力。**++The process of changing from what you are to what you would like to become can be either arduous and frustrating or easy and rewarding.**++从现在的你变成你想成为的自己的过程可能是艰辛和令人沮丧的，也可以是容易且值得的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('173', 'argot', '[ɑrgo]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=argot', '{n.}++[法语]**++(盗贼及黑社会所操的)黑话，切口，隐语，暗语**++(同工作、同行业者的)行话；俚语[见slang<sup style="font-size: 60%">1</sup>]**', '++How! Argot!**++怎么！ 黑话！**++Just as the financial crisis has morphed into a daily grind instead of a daily fire drill, its peculiar argot has found its way into everyday conversations.**++随着金融危机从“狼来了”变成活生生的磨难，金融业的一些特有隐语也进入到了日常对话中。**++Even the prose is weirdly rootless: the multicultural argot of global VIPs who spend their lives at 35,000 feet.**++甚至散文都是离奇得无厘头：那是一生都在35000英尺高空的全球贵宾们的多元文化暗语。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('174', 'argument', '[ɑrɡjumənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=argument', '{n.}++理由；论据；论点**++理由的提出，推论，推理；说理；论证**++辩论；争论，争执，争吵**++(书、剧本等文学作品的)情节，概要，内容提要；内容；主题思想**++【数学】(函数的)自变数；(复数的)辐角，幅度；(矢量的)辐角**++【逻辑学】归纳论证，演绎论证，(三段论中的)中项，中词**++[古语]证明，证据；迹象**++[废语](节、段的)主题；(谈话、讨论、文章等的)题目；导言；自序**', '++His argument appealed to me.**++他的论据引起了我的兴趣。**++She was made to step down by my forceful argument.**++在我的有力论据下，她放弃了争论。**++The lawyer won his case with an impregnable argument.**++律师以无可辩驳的论据打赢了那场官司。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('175', 'arid', '[ærɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arid', '{adj.}++(地区、气候等)干燥的；干旱的**++(由于缺水，土地等)贫瘠的，不毛的**++[比喻]无结果的**++无趣的，无生气的；死板的，沉闷的；枯燥无味的**', '++There are extreme arid regions where only the fittest survive.**++这里是极端干旱地区，只有适者能够生存。**++Ningxia, one of the most arid regions, recently claimed to have reduced its desert land by more than a quarter since 1949.**++宁夏是中国最干旱的地区之一，最近宣称，自1949年以来，其沙漠面积已减少了四分之一强。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('176', 'array', '[əre]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=array', '{vt.}++排列，集结(部队)，使(军队)列成(战斗队形)；配置(兵力)；(军队等)列阵，整(队)，部署，列(队)：**++制定(计划等)**++[array oneself]装饰,装扮,打扮：**++【法律】(为审理某一案件)选任(陪审员)，召集(陪审团)**{n.}++(军队等的)列阵，排列；编队；队形**++(列阵的)军队；部队；民兵；军事力量；(昔日)民兵的武装**++(军事力量的)配置**++(排列整齐的)一批；大量；显眼的一系列**++排列，序列(一个完整单位的组成部分的布置或集合)**++衣饰，服装，盛装**++【法律】陪审员名单**++【电学】(用于雷达等的)天线阵(＝ antenna array)**++【数学、统计学、计算机】阵列，数组[参较package]**', '++We can do that by turning it into an array.**++我们可以通过把它转为一个数组来完成以上操作。**++An array of one or more notification messages.**++包含一条或多条通知消息的数组。**++In this case, it would store its decisions, and then update the array of nodes after its last decision.**++在这种情况下，它将存储它的判定，然后在最后一个判定做出后更新数组的节点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('177', 'arrest', '[ərɛst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arrest', '{vt.}++逮捕，拘捕，拘押，拘押；捕获；(依法)扣留(船只货物等)：**++引起或吸引(注意等)，吸引…的注意，吸住：**++阻止；使停止；妨碍；减(速)；**++【医学】抑制；控制(疾病)：**++心脏病发作**{n.}++逮捕，拘捕，拘押；(依法对船只的)扣留；(尤指)拘留(有时前接under)**++(用武力)夺取，攫取；抓住**++停止；阻止；阻碍；制止，控制，抑制；制动；延滞**++止动器，制动器，制动装置；火花捕捉器**', '++I have to arrest you, of course.**++当然了，我还得要逮捕你。**++Policemen have authority to arrest lawbreakers.**++警察有权逮捕犯法者。**++She swore out a warrant for the arrest of the man who stole her car.**++她宣誓所控属实，因此领到了偷她车那个人的逮捕证。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('178', 'arresting', '[ərɛstɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arresting', '{adj.}++引起注意的，引人注目的，醒目的；给人以深刻印象的；有趣的**++(装置等)制止飞机继续滑行的**++逮捕人的，拘捕人的**', '++"The Cambridge police acted stupidly in arresting somebody when there was already proof that they were in their own home, " he said.**++“当那人已经有证据表明他是在自己家的时候还逮捕他，坎布里奇警察的行为愚蠢透顶，”奥巴马说。**++Because the first thing cops do after arresting you is exchange phone numbers.**++因为警察逮捕你之后第一件做的事情就是和你交换电话号码。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('179', 'arrhythmic', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arrhythmic', '{adj.}++【音乐、韵律学】无节奏的；不规则的**++【病理学】心律不齐的，心律失常的**', '++Medications. Many types of tachycardias respond well to anti-arrhythmic medications.**++药物  很多种心动过速对 抗心律失常药物反应敏感。**++Objective To observe the effects of oxymatrine on action potential in normal rats and arrhythmic rats induced by aconitine .**++目的：观察氧化苦参碱对正常及乌头碱诱发大鼠心律失常模型动作电位的影响。**++Under these more crowded conditions, the restless nighttime movements of the arrhythmic chipmunks in their burrows clued the weasels in to their locations, and predation increased dramatically.**++在这些更加拥挤的环境中，地洞里无节奏的金花鼠不得休息的夜间活动把它们的所在暴露给黄鼠狼，猎食急剧增加。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('180', 'arrogance', '[ærəgəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=arrogance', '{n.}', '++This means God will reject them for God cannot stand those who are full of arrogance and pride.**++这意味着上帝将拒绝他们，因为上帝不能容忍自大和傲慢的人。**++Their arrogance, or anger or aloofness, are the things that reside in you as potentials, which is why you are so fiercely struggling against them.**++他们的自大，愤怒或者冷漠是潜在于你体内的，这就是为什么你如此强烈的抗争他们。**++I own I did not like her, after her infancy was past; and I vexed her frequently by trying to bring down her arrogance: she never took an aversion to me, though.**++自从她的童年时代过去后，我承认我不喜欢她了；我为了要改掉她那妄自尊大的脾气，我常常惹恼她，尽管她从来没有对我采取憎厌的态度。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('181', 'articulate', '[ɑrtɪkjulet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=articulate', '{adj.}++(人讲话)发音清晰的，分节发音的，分明的，可听懂的**++能说话的，有说话能力的**++(人)表达能力强的，善于表达的，口才好的；嘴快的，心直口快的**++表达得清楚有力的；能系统地阐述的，清楚地提出的**++清晰的；有明显特征的**++组织缜密的；精心构思的；结成有机整体的**++连接的**++【生物学】有关节的；分节的；节关相连的[通常作 articulated]**{vt.}++清楚地发出(声音)，清晰地发…音；清晰地吐(字)：**++【语音学】把…发音；发出(语音)，发(音)：**++明确(有力)地表达：**++按照先后次序安排；使前后一致；使互相配合；使相互连贯(或关联)；使成为系统的整体：**++使(艺术品、观察区域与思想体系等)的各个部分形成有意义的、连贯的关系**++[常用被动语态]【动物学】有关节连接；铰接；连接，使接合：**++展现，使凸现，使显露，显露出，使清晰：**{vi.}++清楚地说话；清晰地发音；讲话：**++【语音学】发音：**++连接起来，结合起来，接合**++【解剖学、动物学】 用关节连接起来，形成关节：**++[废语]达成协议**{n.}++【动物学】**++有体节的无脊椎动物**++有关节的腕足动物**', '++Be careful to articulate your words so that everyone in the room can understand you.**++小心使你的话发音清晰，使室内每人都能听懂。**++Hmmmmm. Well, I cant really articulate how I prepare, as I am not sure myself.**++嗯......是这样，我很难说清楚我是怎样准备的，因为我自己也不确定。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('182', 'ascendant', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ascendant', '{adj.}++上升的，向上的**++支配的；优势的；占支配地位的；优势的；有权势的**++【植物学】(茎)上行的；上升的(＝ ascending)**++【天文学】向天顶上升的[亦作 ascendent]**{n.}++支配地位；主要地位；优势**++[有时作 A-]【占星术】星位；(诞生时的)运星；命宫**++[罕用语]祖先,祖宗(descendant 之对)[亦作 ascendent]**', '++Contradiction emerges only when a situation is viewed over time, because at any one moment, one factor or the other is in the ascendant.**++只有随着时间的推移，一种情况的出现，矛盾才会浮现，因为在任何时刻，一方因素或另一个都会占支配地位。**++A NEW Congress and a new president take office next year, and the ascendant Democrats have big plans to rescue the economy.**++明年，新的国会，新的总统将上任，占优势的民主党有一系列的大计划来拯救经济市场。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('183', 'ascetic', '[əsɛtɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ascetic', '{n.}++禁欲(主义)者**++苦行者；苦修者；修道者**++(早期基督教的)遁世修道者**{adj.}++禁欲(主义)的，制欲的，禁止享受的**++苦行(主义)的**++外貌似苦行者的**++(态度、外貌方面)极其严肃的，认真的[亦作 ascetical]**', '++Throughout history power has been the vice of the ascetic.**++从古至今，权力都是苦行者的罪恶嗜好。**++Not deciding to move to an island or Third World country to live as an ascetic priestess – I like urban cities, and I enjoy having stuff.**++没有决定搬到一个岛上或第三世界国家，像一个苦行的祭司一样活着--我喜欢城市，享受物质。**++For instance, Leo Tolstoy, a great and good man, at one time a sensualist, has now turned ascetic; a common evolution in the lives of the saints.**++列夫·托尔斯泰，一个大好人，一度也曾是个声色狗马之徒，现在却转变为一个苦行者；过起了圣徒般的生活，这是一种一般的演变。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('184', 'aseptic', '[,esɛptɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aseptic', '{adj.}++无菌的，不引起腐烂的，防腐的，防感染的**++无生气的，冷漠的，缺乏热情的；含而不露的；超然的，客观的**++使清洁的，起净化作用的**{n.}++【医学】防腐剂**++[复数，用作单数]无菌真空罐装法**', '++Aseptic food processing allows juices and other liquid foodstuffs to be packaged and shipped around the world in mass quantities.**++无菌食品加工使果汁和其他液体食品的大批量包装和全球运输成为可能。**++Information on the epidemiology of mumps disease during the campaign would be important for the understanding of reported rates of aseptic meningitis.**++在开展接种运动时收集到的流行性腮腺炎的流行病学信息非常重要，有助于我们理解报告的无菌性脑膜炎的发生率。**++Recognition of the clustering of cases of aseptic meningitis has potentially been enhanced during mass immunization campaigns due to increased sensitivity of AEFI surveillance.**++随着AEFI监测系统的敏感性提高，对强化免疫期间聚集发生的无菌性脑膜炎的辨识能力也得到了加强。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('185', 'askew', '[əskju]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=askew', '{adv.}++歪斜地，歪地，斜地；侧地；到一边**++不正确地，错，错误地**++不屑地；轻蔑地**{adj.}++[通常作表语]**++歪斜的，歪的，斜的，侧的，在一边的**++不正确的，错误的**', '++He unfurls his previously hidden carrot-orange crest and streaks out at her, wings askew, then darts back to hide again.**++他打开先前收起的橙黄色羽冠，斜张着翅膀，像一道闪电向雌鸟冲去，然后迅速撤回，把自己藏了起来。**++He said that the surgeon who had implanted Mr. Smith’s artificial hip had installed the cup component slightly askew.**++他说，先前给史密斯先生植入人工髋关节的那位外科医生，在安装杯状臼时没有放正，有点歪斜。**++Your heart could be, and often is, askew.**++你的内心可能而且往往是不平静的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('186', 'aspect', '[æspɛkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aspect', '{n.}++外貌，外表，面貌，外观；样子**++观点；(事物等的)方面**++形势**++神态**++(建筑物等的)方向，方位**++(建筑物等)朝某方向的一面**++(从特定处所看到的)景色**++(平面)形状(或情况)**++【语法学】体，貌[动词的一个语法范畴，表示动作的持续和完成情况，例如，he was acting(未完成体)；he ate(完成体)]**++【天文学、占星术】(太阳系的星体相对于太阳的)视位置；恒星(或行星)的相互位置(占星术认为会影响人事祸福)；运气**++【生物学】季相**++【物理学】有关液体或气态物质的平面的位置**++[古语、废语]看；一瞥；凝视**', '++He has made progress in every aspect.**++他在各方面都有起色。**++The article takes in every aspect of the labour problem.**++这篇文章涉及了劳工问题的各个方面。**++The relations between our two countries have improved markedly in every aspect.**++我们两国的关系在各方面都有了显著的发展。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('187', 'asperity', '[æspɛrəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=asperity', '{n.}++(声音、语调的)刺耳**++(性情、态度、脾气、语气等的)粗暴，严厉，粗俗**++(气候等的)严酷，狂暴；艰苦的条件**++(表面的)粗糙，不平**++(表面上的)微小凸出物**', '++" answered her mother, with an asperity that she had never permitted to herself before.**++她母亲回答说，语气之严厉，是她以前从来不准自己有的。**++Recall the attributes of wabi-sabi: asymmetry, asperity, simplicity, modesty, intimacy, and the suggestion of a natural process.**++回顾一下wabi -sabi的特性：不对称，粗糙，简单，朴素，亲切，合乎自然过程的联想。**++But here he was set right by Mrs. Bennet, who assured him with some asperity that they were very well able to keep a good cook, and that her daughters had nothing to do in the kitchen.**++她相当不客气地跟他说，她们家里现在还雇得起一个象样的厨子，根本用不到女儿们过问厨房里的事。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('188', 'aspersion', '[əspɝʒən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aspersion', '{n.}++破坏名誉，造谣，诽谤，中伤，诋毁**++[常作复数]谣言，诽谤的话，中伤的言语**++洒水 **++【宗教】(行洒圣水礼中的)洒圣水**', '++I emptied it at a draught; and feeling broad awake after this internal cold aspersion, sat upright to make a cigarette.**++我一口气喝完了它，冷水进入体内让我彻底醒来，我坐了起来，点燃一根烟。**++We cast no aspersion on the man or his program. Mr. Obama, in his short career, has not strongly associated himself with any policy idea.**++我们无意诽谤这个人或他的计划，然而奥巴马先生在他短暂的职业生涯里，从未对任何政策主张表现过强烈支持的态度。**++Carrie felt this to contain, in some way, an (? aspersion ) upon her ability.**++卡丽感觉有些受牵制，从某种程度上来说，这是对她能力的一种诽谤。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('189', 'aspirant', '[əspaɪərənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aspirant', '{n.}++(名誉、地位等的)追求者，求高位者，渴望获得者；抱负不凡者，有志向的人，有上进心的人**++【教育学】候补生**{adj.}++有抱负的，有上进心的；渴望的；争取中的；努力向上的，向上爬的**++[诗歌用语]冉冉上升的**', '++The Pakistani tribal areas remain the destination of choice for aspirant militants travelling from the West, he added – despite more than 40 missile strikes by CIA-controlled drones this year alone.**++尽管仅今年中央情报局控制的无人机就对巴基斯坦部落地区进行了超过了40次导弹打击，但是该地区仍是来自西方有野心的武装分子选择的目的地，他补充道。**++He is good on ideology, strong on strategy and even organisation but can never be the focal point for active followers, whether aspirant jihadis or veteran militants, that Bin Laden was.**++他善于意识形态宣传，长于战略和组织，但却永远不可能像本拉登一样，成为那些野心勃勃的圣战分子或退役军人等激进的追随者的焦点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('190', 'assail', '[əsel]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assail', '{vt.}++攻击，袭击，冲击：**++(用言词等)攻击，抨击；非难；质问；责骂：**++毅然着手去完成(任务)，着手解决；毅然对付(或应付)：**++使被困扰，困扰；使苦恼：**', '++The enemy may assail our defense positions tomorrow.**++敌人可能明天就攻击我们的防守据点。**++Whether his giddy ascent will last has been hard to say, in part because his opponents had not had a chance to assail him directly until this week’s debate, the first Mr Perry has participated in.**++Perry令人瞠目的上升势头是否会持续依然是给未知数，这部分由于知道这周的辩论，他还没有参加任何一次，以至于他的对手们还没有机会攻击他。**++But now and then, a frustrated worker will assail his assistant by casting aspersions on some aspect of the other’s work.**++不过，时不时会有一名灰心丧气的工人抨击他的助手，就其工作的某方面进行诽谤。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('191', 'assent', '[əsɛnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assent', '{vi.}++同意，对(意见、计划等)表示同意，赞同，赞成(to):**++[古语]妥协；让步；让与：**{n.}++(对建议等表示的)同意，赞成，赞同**++答应，允许，准许，认可；批准**++顺从，依从，屈从(to)**', '++My assent is given with a hook at the end.**++我的同意是有保留的。**++Tsu’tey gestures assent, and they face the clan together.**++苏泰表示同意，然后他们一起面向族人们。**++All military operations will require the assent of Iraqis.**++所有军事行动都将需要伊拉克人的同意。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('192', 'assert', '[əsɝt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assert', '{vt.}++(坚定地)断言，肯定地说(出)，宣称：**++主张，坚持，维护(权利、要求等)，坚决要求自己的权利(被承认)：**++假定(或肯定)…的存在，假设，以…作前提：**', '++“If you fail to avoid high inequality, you will need more prisons and more police,” they assert.**++“如果不能消除这种高度的不平等，你们将需要更多的监狱和警察，”他们断言。**++At the same time, the manager should step in and assert authority only when required, which should be rarely.**++与此同时，经理应该只有在需要时插手并声称权力，这应该很少发生。**++One difference is that you can assert, for instance, that the plan-driven approach will extend our project duration from twelve to fourteen weeks, an increase of two weeks.**++区别之一就是您能够断言，例如计划驱动的方法将把您的项目周期从十二周扩展到十四周，增加了两周的时间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('193', 'assertive', '[əsɝtɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assertive', '{adj.}++肯定的，断定的，断言的，武断的；过分自信的；有冲劲的；固执己见的**++(酒等)有独特(或浓郁)香味的；有特殊风味的[亦作 assertative]**', '++Many companies start in this quadrant, which is why the founding executive team must play such an assertive role in defining what must be done and how.**++从这个模型出发，这就是为什么许多公司中创始人团队在决定必须要做哪些事和怎样来做的时候发挥肯定作用的原因。**++The emphasis of this course was to teach teenagers to be more assertive in insisting how far they want to go sexually, and for them to learn safer alternatives to sex.**++这类课程的重点是教育这些十几岁的少年们，在坚持自己在性方面的需求上更加自信，同时知道在性关系中可供选择的更安全的方法。**++But, instead of being the demure queen expected of her, she was assertive and ambitious.**++但是，她并没有成为大家所期待的端庄的皇后，而是武断的、野心勃勃的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('194', 'assess', '[əsɛs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assess', '{vt.}++对(财产、收入等)进行估价(作为征税根据)，(为征税)估定(财产)的价值，估定(收入)的金额，评估，把…定值：**++确定(损害赔偿金、税款、罚款等)的金额；估定税款，确定(税)率(at):**++对(某人或财产等)征税；命(某人)支付某项费用；处(某人)以罚金：**++向(某人)摊派：**++征(税)，处(罚款)；分摊(费用)：**++对(人、物、工作等)进行估价，评价，评论，判断，评定(…的意义、重要性或价值)：**', '++They assess his house at 15000 yuan.**++他们给他房子的估价为15000元。**++How do you assess that?**++那你该怎么评估收益？**++If so, how do we assess it?**++如果是，我们如何评价它？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('195', 'assiduous', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assiduous', '{adj.}++殷勤的**++刻苦的，勤奋的，孜孜不倦的**++坚持不懈的，经常的；一丝不苟地进行的**', '++To work for work@s sake, to enjoy a fruitless endeavor, to imagine that you can fulfill yourself through assiduous labor—all that is disgusting and incomprehensible.**++为了工作而工作，喜欢毫无结果的努力，想象一下，你可以通过勤勉的工作实现你自己——所有这些都是令人作呕，无法理解的事情。**++The education system in mainland China focuses on assiduous preparation for the national university entrance exam, the gaokao, often at the expense of extracurricular activities.**++中国大陆的教育体制是为了准备高考而刻苦学习，牺牲了学生们的课外活动时间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('196', 'assuage', '[əswedʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=assuage', '{vt.}++缓和，减轻(精神上或肉体的痛苦)：**++使(人)安静下来，使平静，使镇静，镇定，平息(愤怒等强烈情绪)，息(怒等)；抚慰：**++解(渴)；充(饥)；满足(某种欲望)：**', '++But it could not assuage human grief or find ultimate meaning in life@s struggle.**++但它并不能减轻人类的痛苦，或者在人生的斗争中找到终极意义。**++If we can assuage those concerns with the @bad bank-good bank@ plan, that will help.**++如果@坏帐银行/好银行@方案可以平息这些担心,那麽对市场有帮助.**++In all these areas, Mr Draghi will be tempted to follow his predecessor@s playbook or, to assuage German fears about an Italian in charge of the ECB, be yet tougher.**++在这些区域内，德拉吉会尝试继续遵循他的前任的计划，或是去缓和德国对于意大利将会掌控欧洲央行的恐惧，这已经很艰难了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('197', 'astounding', '[əstaʊndɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=astounding', '{adj.}', '++As you can see above, the result is astounding.**++正如您可以在上面看到的，其结果是令人震惊的。**++The Domestic Shop sequence will demonstrate the astounding range of experiments and projects you can do with household appliances.**++家庭店铺序列将示范一系列令人惊奇的用家用电器就能够做的实验和项目。**++How the astounding complexity and diversity of human cultures sprang from the much simpler traditions found in animal communities has remained a puzzle.**++人类文化令人惊叹的复杂性和多样性如何从动物社会简单得多的传统进化而来，依然是个谜。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('198', 'astute', '[əstut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=astute', '{adj.}++精明的，机敏的，敏锐的**++狡猾的，诡计多端的；足智多谋的**', '++The astute or the mathematicians will realize that what will happen here?**++机敏的人或数学家将认识到,这里将发生什么？**++Hammond said that the NAO was wrong to state that the overspend could have paid for an eighth Astute submarine, but admitted the MoD still had much to do to give taxpayers value for money.**++哈蒙德称国家审计办公室报告称超支的经费够买第八艘“机敏”级潜艇的说法是错误的，不过他承认国防部还需要努力工作才能让纳税人觉得钱花得值。**++Yet Summers, one of the world’s most astute economists, later abandoned these positions in favor of Greenspan’s view that markets will take care of themselves.**++然而不久之后，这位世界上最狡猾的经济学家，放弃了自己的立场，转而拥护格林斯潘的自由市场观点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('199', 'asunder', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=asunder', '{adv.}++[通常作表语]**{adj.}++成数部分，成数块，分成碎片；(分)散；(扯)碎；(折)断**++位置上互相隔开，(向不同方向或位置)分开，分离；星散**++在种类(或性质、质量)上明显不同**', '++Divided there is little we can do, for we dare not meet a powerful challenge at odds and split us asunder.**++我们如果分歧对立，就会一事无成--因为我们不敢在争吵不休、四分五裂时迎接强大的挑战。**++Since 1989, when the party split at the top and almost came asunder, the cardinal rule has been no public divisions in the Politburo.**++1989年，当时档的高层分裂，档几乎分崩离析，自那开始，政治局在档的基本原则上从未出现公开的分歧。**++The Princess Bride starts off as a story a grandfather reads to his sick grandson. The story is about the love between a princess and a farm boy, how these two are torn asunder, and then reunited.**++公主新娘以爷爷给生病的孙子讲故事开始，这个故事讲述了公主和农场男孩的爱情，他们是怎样被分离，又是怎么样重聚。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('200', 'asylum', '[əsaɪləm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=asylum', '{n.}++避难所，庇护所，躲避处；保护设施**++避难；庇护；躲避**++【国际法】政治避难权，庇护权；(一国对他国难民提供的)保护**++[旧语](欠债人等躲藏的)圣所；教堂；寺院**++[旧语]精神病院;救济院,养育院;收容所[此义多用 mental (或 psychiatric)hospital, nursing home 等]**', '++"The Africans do not have problems of political asylum, " Qaddafi .**++“非洲人没有政治庇护的问题”卡扎菲谈到。**++If she could lie about her asylum application, for whatever reason, then she might be lying about her attack.**++如果她在申请庇护时说谎了，那么无论出于什么原因，她都可能在性侵害问题上说谎。**++They continue to flee their homes and nations and seek asylum because they are persecuted for being who they are.**++他们因为自己生就的天性而被迫害，继续逃离他们的家园和国家寻求庇护。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('201', 'asymmetrical', '[,esɪmɛtrɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=asymmetrical', '{adj.}++不对称的，不匀称的**++【逻辑学】非对称的(例如说“玛丽是玛丽娜的母亲”，两者的关系便是非对称的，位置不可互换)**', '++Modeling experiments told the researchers that an asymmetrical deflection of light would create a surprisingly stable lift force.**++模型试验告诉研究人员，光线的非对称偏转可以产生稳定的提拉力，这令人惊奇。**++She likes to talk about symmetrical and asymmetrical triangles.**++她喜欢谈论对称和不对称的三角形。**++In conclusion, our dataset is asymmetrical and contains considerable degree of right skew, due to the presence of outliers in the dataset.**++在结论之中，我们的数据集是非对称的，并且包含了相当程度的右偏，因为在数据集中有异常值的存在。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('202', 'asymmetry', '[esɪmɪtri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=asymmetry', '{n.}', '++So how might this asymmetry have come about?**++那么这种不对称到底是如何产生的呢？**++What this case highlights is the asymmetry of information in public life.**++这个案例显示的是在公众生活中的信息不对称。**++There is also an asymmetry here: you know who I am; in fact some people on these threads seem to know more about me than I do. But I have no idea who I am arguing with.**++这里还存在着一种不对称：你们知道我是谁——事实上，这些板块里的一些人似乎比我还要了解我自己——而我却不知道自己在与什么人争论。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('203', 'atone', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=atone', '{vi.}++赎回，赎罪；偿还，(对罪行)抵偿(for):**++(为了错误、自己的轻率等)进行弥补，进行补偿(for):**++[废语]协调，一致；和好，和解**{vt.}++抵偿，补偿；赎(罪)；为(作恶、犯罪等)而受罚：**++[废语]使一致；使和谐，使协调，使和解，使和好，使和睦，使团结**++[古语]使息怒；安抚，安慰，抚慰；劝解**', '++But is it possible for a nation to atone for atrocities it committed?**++但是一个国家可能为它曾经所犯下的暴行而赎罪吗？**++I have a lot to atone for, but there is one issue I really want to discuss.**++我在很多方面需要赎罪，在这里有一个问题我很想说一下。**++Whatever you@ve done couldn@t atone for the misdeeds.**++无论你做什么，都不能弥补过去的罪行。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('204', 'atrocious', '[ətroʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=atrocious', '{adj.}++残忍的，残暴的；凶恶的，邪恶的；粗暴的**++骇人听闻的；令人震惊的**++[口语]糟透的；令人不快的，可恶的，讨厌的，令人作呕的；恶劣的，差的，次的**', '++She speaks French with an atrocious accent.**++她讲的法语带有很难听的口音。**++I was devastated by the atrocious bombings that struck London today. These vicious acts have cut us all to the core, for they are an attack on humanity itself.**++对于今天在伦敦发生的残忍的爆炸事件我感到非常震惊。这些恶毒的行为把我们所有人都放到了核心处，因为那其实是对人权的攻击。**++Workers at the Mitsumi Electric plant in northern Tianjin city have been on strike since Tuesday, fighting low wages and atrocious working conditions.**++天津市北三美电子厂的工人们，自星期二以来一直在举行罢工斗争，抗议低工资和恶劣的劳动条件。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('205', 'atrophy', '[ætrəfi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=atrophy', '{n.}++【病理学】 (全身或某器官等的)萎缩[亦作atrophia]**++【生理学】 (器官等的)衰退，退化，退减，减缩(现象)**++[比喻](不使用而引起的)衰退，减退；退化；萎缩**{vi.}++萎缩；衰退：**++萎缩；衰退：**{vt.}++使萎退；使衰退：**++使萎退；使衰退：**', '++Some areas of the brain, if not stimulated, will atrophy and die.**++大脑的某些区域如果没有受到促进就会萎缩更甚死亡。**++I had surgery to remove it, but the size and location of the tumor caused my optic nerve to atrophy.**++可以通过手术摘掉它，但是肿瘤的大小和位置造成我的视觉神经萎缩。**++The compounds "likely have an effecton motor neurons"—responsible for controlling movements—"but that isa hunch at present, based on the type of atrophy we saw, " Hughes said inan email.**++这些化合物“可能对运动神经元（负责控制运动）产生作用”----“根据我们观察到的萎缩症类型，目前这只是个预测，”休斯在一封电子邮件中说。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('206', 'attenuate', '[ətɛnjuet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=attenuate', '{vt.}++使变细，使细长，使苗条，使纤细，使纤弱；使变小；使薄：**++稀释；使(气体等)变稀薄，使淡薄：**++(在程度、价值、数量、力、强度、效果等方面)使减少，使减弱；减轻；降低…的价值：**++【微生物学、免疫学】减弱(微生物或病毒)的毒性，使…毒性减弱**++【电子学】使衰弱**{vi.}++变纤细；变小**++变弱；减弱；减少**++变薄**++变稀薄**{adj.}++细长的，苗条的，纤细的，纤弱的，细小的**++稀释了的，稀薄的**++减少的；减轻的；减弱的**++【植物学】渐狭的，渐尖削的**', '++“Maybe one day this could be a way to attenuate the monsoon or reduce flooding in certain areas, ” Kasparian said.**++卡斯帕里安说：“也许有一天这种方法将能够减弱季风，或将少某些地方的洪水泛滥。”**++The repetition of symbols was to be enough, without trauma, as well, perhaps, to attenuate it, or even jar it altogether loose from her memory.**++象征的重复快要足够，即便没有可能的从她记忆中流出的创伤，去减弱它去刺激它。**++IMA elevation is non-specific and hence may attenuate any prognostic significance if it is used for prognosis before first establishing the diagnosis.**++IMA水平升高是不确定的，因此如果在第一次确诊诊断之前使用这种预后手段，就可能减弱其预后显著性。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('207', 'attest', '[ətɛst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=attest', '{vt.}++宣称…为真实(或真正)的；(证人)连署(或宣誓)以证明(遗嘱、行为、事件等)是真的；证明；证实；为…作证：**++(事物)作为…的证据(或证明)，(事物等)是…的证据，为…作证；论证；表明：**++使发誓，使宣誓，使立誓**++[英国英语]使(新兵)宣誓入军籍**++证实(词语等)的使用**{vi.}++证明，用书面形式证明；表明；证实；为…作证( to ):**++[英国英语](新兵)宣誓入军籍**{n.}++[古语]**++证明，证实**++证据；证词；宣誓**', '++I can attest to the absolute truth of his statement.**++我可以证实他的话是千真万确的。**++These ruins sufficiently attest the former grandeur of the place.**++这些遗迹充分证明此处昔日的宏伟。**++As the writers interviewed for this article attest, there is more to being an author than simply putting words to paper.**++为了证明本文观点而被采访的人，更多的是作为一个作者而不仅仅是在纸上写字的人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('208', 'attune', '[ətʊn; ətjʊn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=attune', '{vt.}++[attune oneself] 使协调,使合拍,使一致,使适合(to):**++[古语]【音乐】为(乐器)调音：**{vi.}++协调**', '++Or perhaps it is enough if we simply attune ourselves to structure, balance, rhythm, and precision.**++也许我们仅仅让自己与这些结构、平衡、韵律和准确性协调就足够了。**++Collaborating with scientists from similar socio-economic and scientific backgrounds can help attune research to a particular country’s needs.**++与来自类似的经济社会和科学背景的科学家协作可以有助于让科研和特定国家的需求相适合。**++Often those of this nature can attune inward and hear what the other kingdoms have to say and relay this information back to others in the tribe.**++经常地，那些这种性质者，可以向内感应而听到其它王国要说的东西，并将这一信息传达给部落的其他人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('209', 'audacious', '[ɔdeʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=audacious', '{adj.}++勇敢的，无畏的，大胆的，敢于冒险的**++冒失的，放肆的，鲁莽的；厚颜无耻的，胆大妄为的**++大胆创新的；标新立异的**++无拘无束的；欢快的，活泼的**', '++Her story is audacious, but really, is it that far off base from all our primal urges?**++她的故事是大胆而真实的，而这些是否就是源自我们的最原始的欲望呢？**++Chávez’s hemispheric ambitions have made him one of the most compelling, audacious, and polarizing figures in the world—one of a number of post-Cold War leaders trying to form regional power blocs.**++查韦斯雄心勃勃的南半球抱负，使他成为了世界上最为强势、无畏和两极化的人物之一，以及冷战后试图完成区域政治力量整合的众多领袖中的一个。**++It is modest and audacious, all at once.**++这是适度而大胆的行动，一锤定音。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('210', 'augur', '[ɔgɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=augur', '{n.}++(古罗马的)占卜官(用观察飞鸟行动等方法预卜未来)**++占卜者，算命者；预言者；先知**{vt.}++预言，占卜**++预示，是…的预兆：**{vi.}++推测，预言；占卜**++是一种预兆，预示(通常后接well或ill):**{n.}++话匣子；饶舌者，碎嘴子，多嘴的人**{vi.}++交谈；争辩，争论**', '++Mounting sales augur a profitable year.**++不断增加的销售量预示着好年景。**++But an uptick in output does not augur prosperity.**++但是，产量上扬并不预示着经济繁荣。**++Yet while liberals have cheered the result as a mark of social progress, it does not necessarily augur plain sailing for the al-Sabah family that has ruled Kuwait since the 18th century.**++然而，虽然自由派为这个结果欢呼并以此作为社会进步的标志，但是它不一定预示萨巴赫家族18世纪以来对科威特统治就这么简单。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('211', 'august', '[ɔgʌst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=august', '{adj.}++尊敬的，尊严的；威严的，威风凛凛的；令人敬畏的**++(因高龄、德行等)令人崇敬的，值得敬重的，可敬的，可尊敬的；德高望重的，年高得劭的**++(建筑物等)庄严的，雄伟的**{n.}', '++He moved to another city last August.**++去年八月，他搬到另一座城市。**++That night in August, waiting for the Rolling Stones to come on stage, we felt like rebels.**++在那个八月的夜晚，在等待滚石乐队登台演出时，我们有种造反的感觉。**++They make a huge migration from the north to the south of the US, mostly starting in August and the other way around in the spring.**++大部分是从八月开始，它们开始进行巨大的迁徙，从美国的北部到南部，而到了春天又沿相反方向回来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('212', 'auspicious', '[ɔspɪʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=auspicious', '{adj.}++吉兆的，吉利的，吉祥的；顺利的**++幸运的；繁荣的，昌盛的，兴盛的，兴隆的[亦作auspicial]**', '++Lian: The Hale and Hearty colours are not auspicious in our culture.**++丽安： “哈尔及哈迪”公司使用的颜色在我们的文化中不太吉利。**++It is very auspicious.**++这是非常吉祥的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('213', 'austere', '[ɔstɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=austere', '{n.}++(神色、态度等)严肃的，严厉的，严峻的；严酷的；苛刻的**++严格律己的，自我约束的；操行上一丝不苟的；紧缩的，节制的；禁欲的**++苦行的，清苦的，十分简朴的**++朴素的，无装饰的，不奢华的**++酸涩的，酸苦的，涩的**++阴暗的，暗色的**++坚硬的，不柔软的**++[罕用语]严正的；庄严的，庄重的，稳重的**', '++After an austere year the government may yet be tempted to blow its early oil revenues on restoring popularity.**++在经历了严峻的一年，政府面对着利用鼓吹他前石油收入来保留声望的诱惑。**++Yet perhaps no industry has been as slow to meet the international and technological challenges of this new austere era.**++但是，在这个严峻的新时代，也许没有哪一个行业像法律界那样迟缓地受到国际性的技术挑战。**++THE Bank of England’s austere home in Threadneedle Street may not look like a hospital but for the past few months it has been acting like one.**++针线街（英国伦敦金融街）上英格兰银行简朴的总部看上去不像医院，但是过去的几个月里它却一直在扮演一家医院的角色。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('214', 'authentic', '[ɔθɛntɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=authentic', '{adj.}++可信(赖)的，可靠的；有根据的，来源可靠的**++[口语]真诚的**++真的，真实的，真正的，名副其实的；逼真的**++(契约、宣誓书等)正式的，确证了的；手续完备的；依法有效的**++【音乐】正格终止的**++[废语] = authoritative [亦作 authentical]**', '++I see them longing and reaching out for authentic community.**++我看到他们渴望并向可信的集体张开双臂。**++People who participate feel like they know me, because my heart, my authentic self, my gratitude, is all up in this thing.**++那些参与活动的人们感到他们认识我，因为我的心，真实的自我，我的感恩，全都投入在这件事情上。**++God created you and so He wants you to be the real you. By being authentic when you speak to God, you worship Him as your Creator.**++是神创造了你，他想要你活出真正的你。你与神交谈时要作真实的你，你要敬拜神，真的把他看为你的创造者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('215', 'authority', '[əθɔrəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=authority', '{n.}++权力，权；管辖权 **++(有这种权力者的) 职位，当权地位**', '++He disrespected all authority figures.**++他蔑视所有权威人物。**++They disclaimed the authority of the president.**++他们不承认总统的权威。**++Little by little he usurped his boss@s authority.**++他逐渐地篡夺老板的权力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('216', 'autocracy', '[ɔtɑkrəsi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=autocracy', '{n.}++专制，独裁**++专制制度；独裁政体；独裁统治**++独裁政府，独裁统治的国家(或团体)**++[废语]自主，自立，自力**', '++As an autocracy, moreover, Beijing can act with unparalleled efficiency for good, as shown in the massive rescue operation after the recent earthquake.**++此外，作为一个专制政府，北京拥有无与伦比的行动效率，最近地震后的大规模救援就展示了这一点。**++China@s autocratic government, though a frequent and severe human rights abuser, is still relatively open and stable for an autocracy.**++中国政府对人权的长期忽视与践踏，并不能掩饰它是一个较为开放和稳定的专制政府。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('217', 'automatic', '[ɔtəmætɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=automatic', '{adj.}++无意识的，不假思索的，习惯性的，机械的**++【生理学】(某些肌肉动作等)自动的，不随意的，不受意志支配的**++【心理学】无意识的**++自动的 **++(动作、过程等)以自动装置完成的**{n.}++自动手枪(或步枪等) **++半自动手枪(或步枪等)**', '++There was no available automatic in that factory.**++那家工厂没有可用的自动机械。**++This is an automatic press that performs shaping operations, such as bumping, heading and pocketing.**++这是一台进行造型操作，如碰撞、装头和压袋的自动压力机。**++One caveat to node removal: the node must be running in order for this automatic removal process to proceed.**++关于删除节点的一个警告就是要进行此自动删除过程必须按顺序运行节点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('218', 'autonomy', '[ɔtɑnəmi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=autonomy', '{n.}++自治(的状况)，自治权**++独立；自主，自主权，自由；人身自由；意志自由**++[复数]-mies**++自治国家；自治州，自治区**++自治团体，自治共同体**', '++One way or another, the days of Fed autonomy are coming to an end, as well they should.**++无论哪个法案被通过，美联储自治的日子都将走到尽头，这也是他们应得的。**++However, this decoupling and autonomy conflicts with the use of shared databases.**++但是，这种解耦和自治与共享数据库的使用格格不入。**++Five years ago, all of our units were much freer to do what they wanted for local autonomy; now we see the value of being global as well as local.**++年前，我们的单位都是能可以自由地做任何他们想要为地方自治权而做的事；现在我们看到的是全球和当地的价值。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('219', 'avarice', '[ævərɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=avarice', '{n.}', '++Avarice harshened his features.**++贪婪使他变得冷酷无情。**++Avarice is the bane to happiness.**++贪婪是损毁幸福的祸根。**++George Washington called gambling “the child of avarice, the brother of iniquity and the father of mischief”, but Benjamin Franklin organised a lottery in Philadelphia in 1746.**++乔治华盛顿称博彩业为“贪婪的孩子，邪恶的兄弟，伤痛的父亲”，而本杰明富兰克林1746年在费城组织了彩票业。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('220', 'aver', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aver', '{vt.}++宣告为确实；断言；坚称；自信地说：**++【法律】(在陈述诉讼理由时)证明…属实；作为事实提出；确证；辨明；主张：**{n.}', '++"I don@t know much about art, " you aver, "but I know what I like."**++你如此声称。 「但我知道我喜欢什么东西。」**++I can aver that he is telling the truth.**++我可以断言他说的是实话。**++I aver it will not rain tomorrow.**++我断言明天不会下雨。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('221', 'aversion', '[əvɝʒn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=aversion', '{n.}++反感，厌恶，嫌恶(to)；【心理学】厌恶，反感**++不情愿，不愿意(to)**++被人厌恶的人(或事物)，讨厌的人(或东西)**++[废语]避开，背离；转移；转变方向**', '++Loss aversion, or the reluctance to accept a loss, can be deadly.**++厌恶损失或者是不愿意接受损失都是致命的缺点。**++Risk aversion is one of the biggest factors driving allocation.**++风险厌恶是推动资产配置的最大因素之一。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('222', 'avid', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=avid', '{adj.}++[通常作表语]贪婪的；急切的；渴望的，热望的(for，of)**++热切的，热衷的，热心的；劲头十足的**', '++He had become an avid and accomplished gardener in France.**++他在法国成为了一个热心的精湛的园丁。**++Maybe it was only the beginning of something better in life, better than you could ever have thought possible before clamping your avid jaws down over the vital bait.**++也许这只是更美好生活的开始， 要比你闭上贪婪的嘴咬住那极为重要的鱼饵之前所能够想到的要好。**++Meanwhile, time after time on other issues -- such as the economic stimulus package, health care and Iraq -- he has tacked to the center, much to the frustration of his most avid supporters.**++与此同时，在其他问题上，比如经济刺激计划、医保改革以及伊拉克问题，他不止一次改弦易辙、转向中庸，这让他最热心的支持者感到失望。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('223', 'avowal', '[əvaʊəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=avowal', '{n.}', '++Once the first avowal has been made, “I love you” has no meaning whatever.**++一旦有了第一次的告白，“我爱你”就再没有任何意义。**++Set in small-town Iowa in 1956, Gilead is a quiet, slow-moving but ultimately majestic avowal of the redemptive power of love. LA**++《吉利德》以1956年爱荷华州的小镇为背景，故事恬静而舒缓，但最终成为爱的救赎力的宏大声明。**++Abetting a fugitive slave in antebellum America was widely considered a sin against God, but Huck destroys the letter with the defiant avowal: “All right, then, I’ll go to hell.”**++在内战前的美国，帮助在逃的奴隶被普遍视为对上帝犯下的罪行，但哈克在撕毁这封信的时候大义凛然地宣称：“好吧，我去下地狱。”**');
