insert into GREWordBook values ('523', 'conflate', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conflate', '{vt.}++使结合，合并**++将(两种文本)合并成一个文本**', '++So I think choreography is alive and well. But I wouldn@t conflate that with BPM.**++所以，我认为服务编排是生机勃勃的，但我不想把它和BPM混在一起。**++If you want to defend liberalism, then defend it, but why conflate your love for certain values with love for a certain country?**++如果你想捍卫自由主义，那你就捍卫吧，你为什么要把对某种价值观的热爱和对某个国家的热爱混为一谈？**++It’s easy to conflate mobile e-mail with business users, after all, this was the demographic that first fully embraced the ability to send and receive messages from their mobile devices.**++我们很容易将移动网络电子邮件和商业用户联想到一起，毕竟商业用户是首先完全体验通过他们的移动设备收发信息的人群。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('524', 'confluence', '[kɑnfluəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=confluence', '{n.}++汇流，汇合**++(河流的)汇流点，合流点，汇合处**++合流河，汇流而成的河**++会合；(人群的)汇集，聚集，集合**++人群；集会**++【生物学】细胞覆盖(培养细胞时，培养器的整个底面被一层细胞覆盖)[亦作 conflux]**', '++So today is not only a pivot, but a confluence of pivots.**++所以今天不仅是一个支点，还是一个支点的汇合。**++It emerges from a confluence of factors, some very subtle.**++它浮现于多因子的合流，非常微妙的。**++This confluence of concerns was a natural product of the fact that the speakers were drawn from those working at the vanguard of XML tools and techniques.**++这些问题汇合在一起，自然而然地把发言者和那些从事前卫的 XML 工具和技术研究的人分离了出来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('525', 'conform', '[kənfɔrm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conform', '{vi.}++遵照；适应；顺从，一致(常与to 连用)：**++符合；相似(常与with连用)：**++【历史】遵奉国教会(指英国国教会)惯例**{vt.}++使符合，使一致；使相似：**++使顺应；使协调；使遵照：**{adj.}++[古语]一致的，相似的**', '++It@s not just humans, there@s evidence that chimps conform as well.**++不仅限于人类，也有证据表明黑猩猩也符合这项理论。**++If you disagree and don’t conform to their expectations, some of them get confused or irritated.**++如果你不同意或者和他们期望的不一致，他们中的一些人就会困惑生气。**++These must be in the best interest of the enterprise and also conform to applicable laws and regulations.**++这些计划必须是为了企业利益最大化，并且符合需要遵从的法律及规章制度。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('526', 'confound', '[kənfaʊnd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=confound', '{vt.}++使困惑，弄糊涂，使惊慌失措；搞乱：**++混淆，混同，混在一起：**++／kɔnfaund／ (表示轻微诅咒)罚…入地狱；讨厌，该死：**', '++Now, with climate change, another potential disaster looms: shifts in ocean currents that may confound eels during their migrations.**++如今，随着气候变化，又隐现出另一种潜在的危险：洋流移位有可能迷惑迁移中鳗鱼。**++How will we engage the differences that confound us and bring us to the brink of warfare in our neighborhoods, schools, communities, political parties and nations?**++我们将如何容忍差异？ 它曾令人困惑，曾在邻里、学校、社区、政治派系和国家间，将我们逼向战争的边缘？**++Individuals can (and regularly do) have conversations that confound institutions, because these conversations lie beyond any institutional zone of control.**++个人可以进行对话，并且打败机构，因为这些对话超越了任何机构可以掌控的范围。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('527', 'confront', '[kənfrʌnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=confront', '{vt.}++使面对，使面临；出现在…面前：**++对峙，对抗；面对；遭遇：**++使当面对证，使对质：**++对照，对比：**', '++We must confront future with optimism.**++我们必须乐观地面对未来。**++And how will I confront each whom I meet?**++我该怎样面对遇到的每一个人呢？**++I live in accordance to certain priorities as I have to confront them.**++我以一些优先考虑的事为标准生活,因为我必须面对它们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('528', 'congeal', '[kəndʒil]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=congeal', '{vt.}++使冻结；使凝结；使冻僵：**++使固定，使一成不变；使瘫痪：**{vi.}++冻结；凝结；冻僵：**++变冷：**', '++Gear lubricants may congeal and channel in cold weather.**++天冷时齿轮润滑油可能凝结并形成凹槽。**++A large cloud of gas and dust begins to congeal gravitationally, starts rotating, and eventually flattens into an object called a protostellar disk.**++由气体和尘埃构成的巨大云团在引力的作用下开始凝缩，并且开始旋转，最终变平成为平面状物体，这种物体被称为原恒星盘。**++When the cheese started to cool and congeal, which took a good 30 minutes, all I did was stick it back on the stove, stirring until runny.**++奶酪开始冷却、 凝结，用了整整30分钟，在这期间，我所做的就是把它再放回炉子上，搅拌直至奶酪开始流淌。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('529', 'congenial', '[kəndʒinɪəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=congenial', '{adj.}++性格相同的；意气相投的，情投意合的**++适合的，适意的，相宜的**', '++I found in him a congenial temper.**++他是一个和我意气相投的人。**++It was not a congenial experience and in 1961 he retired to Switzerland with his wife to devote himself to his books.**++但这种感觉与其性格不合，于是1961年他就退休，和妻子去了瑞士，全心全意地写起书来。**++But after this string of errors, wouldn’t you at least begin to suspect that the people you find congenial have a fundamentally wrong-headed view of how the world works?**++但是在这一系列的错误之后，你是否应该至少开始怀疑这些专家有一个根本性的错误，那就是这个世界到底是如何运作的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('530', 'congruent', '[kɑŋɡruənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=congruent', '{adj.}++适合的，相合的，一致的，和谐的**++【数学】同余的；叠合的；全等的**', '++It’s possible if all of those different areas of your life are congruent, if they all follow the same rules.**++如果生活中所有不同方面是一致的，如果它们都遵循同样的原则，那就是可能的。**++That is the first critical step to building out your actions and behaviors so they are congruent with whom you say you want to be.**++这是你建立你行动和行为的第一个步骤，这些行动和行为与你表述的你所要建立的形象是一致的。**++To stack the odds in our favor we therefore need to take into account each one of the three methodologies and hopefully find them to be congruent, meaning that they all point in the same direction.**++为了积累有利的可能性，我们需要把三种方法中的每一种方法都考虑在内，并期望发现它们是一致的，或者说它们都指向同一个方向。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('531', 'conjecture', '[kəndʒɛktʃɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conjecture', '{n.}++推测，猜测，猜想，臆想**++推测的意见；臆说**++[废语](对征兆、梦的)解说；玄妙的预言**{vt.}++推测出，猜想出：**++推测出，猜想出：**{vi.}++推测，猜想：**++推测，猜想：**', '++We could not conjecture the fact from what he said.**++我们从他的话中还推测不出真实情况。**++It is worth mentioning, because while it appears to be a trivial thing, I have seen much conjecture and debate over the topic.**++它值得一提是因为虽然它看起来似乎是一件微不足道的小事，但是我见过很多对这个话题的猜想和争论。**++Intelligence officials acknowledge that much of what they have gleaned is little more than conjecture, based on secondhand information from sources inside North Korea but not independently verified.**++情报官员承认他们收集到的信息很大一部分只不过是推测，是根据来源于朝鲜国内未经独立地证实的二手消息。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('532', 'conjure', '[kʌndʒɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conjure', '{vt.}++念咒召唤或驱赶(鬼、神)：**++用魔法驱除(疾病等)：**++用魔法变出：**++提出；想起；想像；回忆起(常与up连用)：**++／kəndʒuə／ 祈求，恳求；恳切呼吁：**++[废语]承担(责任)**{vi.}++念咒召唤(鬼神)：**++施魔法；变魔术，变戏法：**++／kəndʒuə／ [废语]耍阴谋，密谋策划**{adj.}++[美国英语]行巫的，念咒的，施魔法的**', '++I conjure you to hear my plea.**++我恳求你听取我的请求。**++What different sensations those words conjure up to each of us.**++我们各人对于这四个字都有不同的感觉。**++This enables the researchers to conjure from their database the person you may not realize you have in mind.**++这能让研究者们从他们的数据库中发现一些人，这些人你甚至并未意识到在你脑海中。**');
