insert into GREWordBook values ('534', 'connoisseur', '[,kɑnəsɝ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=connoisseur', '{n.}', '++Become a connoisseur of the best things other people have done.**++让自己成为一个鉴赏家，鉴赏那些由他人完成的佳作。**++No, it’s not just an injustice to your connoisseur taste buds; conventional coffee farming exploits workers and destroys communities in third world countries.**++廉价咖啡不仅仅是对你鉴赏家的味蕾不公平，对在第三世界国家咖啡种植园的工人来说更是不公平。**++Even imagine yourself a connoisseur of that focus point.**++甚至想象你自己是一个鉴赏家。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('535', 'conscientious', '[kɑnʃɪɛnʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conscientious', '{adj.}++有良心的，凭良心的，按良心办事的；认真的；正直的**++小心谨慎的，细致的**', '++She is very conscientious and never skimps her work.**++她办事认真， 从不敷衍了事。**++Be conscientious and make a good job of publication.**++认真做好出版工作。**++To give the devil his due, he is quite a conscientious worker.**++平心而论， 他工作还是认真的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('536', 'consensus', '[kənsɛnsəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consensus', '{n.}++大多数人的意见；舆论**++一致同意，合意**', '++But there was no consensus as to what shape reforms should take.**++但对应当采取何种形式的改革，并没有一致意见。**++There is, in fact, a widespread consensus among economists about what should be done.**++事实上，经济学家对于应该如何行动已经达成了广泛的一致。**++I have spoken to some people [in Libya] and the consensus is it was just an accident, even among the families.**++我与[利比亚]的一些人谈到这个案子，一致的意见是这是一起事故，即使受害者家庭也同意。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('537', 'consent', '[kənsɛnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consent', '{vi.}++允许，答应；顺从；许可：**++赞成，赞同；同意：**++[废语]持相同意见；一致；调和**{n.}++准许，许可，答应；同意，赞同**++(意见等的)一致**', '++I ought first to have asked your consent.**++我本应该首先征得你的同意。**++He threw me a smile that telegraphed consent.**++他朝我微笑，流露出同意的神情。**++He misinterpreted her silence as giving consent.**++他把她的沉默误认为是同意。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('538', 'consequence', '[kɑnsəkwɛns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consequence', '{n.}++结果，后果；影响**++【逻辑学】(逻辑上的)结论，推论，推理**++因果关系**++重要性；重大意义**++重要地位；显要，卓越；举足轻重**++趾高气扬，自命不凡**', '++That is the consequence of its evolution.**++这是其不断进化的结果。**++So, what@s the consequence of forming these gas ions?**++所以，形成这些气态离子的结果是什么呢？**++This is an inevitable consequence of consciousness.**++这是意识的一个不可避免的结果。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('539', 'conservative', '[kənsɝvətɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conservative', '{adj.}++守旧的，保守的**++稳健的；谨慎的**++不时新的，传统标准的**++[C-] 保守党的**++保守主义的**++保存的，贮藏的；防腐的**++[C-]犹太教的守旧运动的；保守犹太教的；保守犹太教徒的**{n.}++保守(主义)者，因循守旧者；小心谨慎者**++保守党党员**++防腐剂**', '++Should I be aggressive or conservative with my money before 30?**++在30岁之前我应该风险投资还是保守存钱？**++The more conservative politicians were trying to deradicalize the liberation movement.**++较保守的政治家正试图使解放运动放弃偏激的立场。**++The young people are the most eager to learn and the least conservative in their thinking.**++青年人最肯学习，最少保守思想。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('540', 'conservatory', '[kənsɝvətɔri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conservatory', '{n.}++(玻璃)暖房，温室**++音乐学院**{adj.}++有保存力的；有保护作用的**', '++The musically versatile young girl enrolled to study folk music at the Chinese Conservatory of Music in Beijing at 16.**++16岁时，这位在音乐方面多才多艺的年轻女子考上了中国音乐学院，学习民族音乐。**++To counteract the audacity of this proceeding he led her to a bamboo sofa in a less secluded part of the conservatory, and sitting down beside her broke a lily-of-the-valley from her bouquet.**++为了抵消这一出格举动的影响，他把她带到温室不太隐蔽部分的一个长竹椅上。 他在她身边坐下，从她的花束上摘下一朵铃兰。**++The dance over, the two, as became an affianced couple, wandered into the conservatory; and sitting behind a tall screen of tree-ferns and camellias Newland pressed her gloved hand to his lips.**++舞会结束了，他们俩既然已成了未婚夫妻，便漫步走到温室里；坐在一片桫椤与山茶的屏障后面，纽兰将她戴着手套的手紧紧压在唇上。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('541', 'conserve', '[kənsɝv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conserve', '{vt.}++保护；保藏，保存，保全，贮存：**++糖渍，把(水果等)制成蜜饯或果酱：**++(物理、化学变化或进化过程中)使(能量等)守恒：**{n.}++[常用复数]蜜饯；果酱**', '++Foods are dehydrated to conserve them for future use.**++把食物脱水弄干贮藏以备将来食用。**++We need to conserve everything.**++我们需要维护一切。**++What can I do at home to conserve this precious resource, and will my efforts actually have any effect?**++那么在家我应该怎样做来保护这一珍贵的资源，而我的努力事实上真的会起到作用吗？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('542', 'considerable', '[kənsɪdərəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=considerable', '{adj.}++相当大的；相当多的；可观的**++重大的，重要的；值得考虑的，值得注意的；显著的**{n.}++[美国口语]许多，不少，大量**', '++He owns considerable real estate.**++他拥有相当可观的房地产。**++He will stand to get a considerable profit through the speculations in lands.**++他在地产投机生意上必定会赚相当可观的一笔钱。**++Impeding means that the persona could use the product, but only with considerable effort.**++阻碍意味着角色可以使用产品，但只有付出相当大的努力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('543', 'consign', '[kənsaɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consign', '{vt.}++移交，交付；押解：**++把…托付给，把…委托给：**++留出，拨出：**++打发；放逐；忘却：**++运送；托运；寄售；寄存：**{vi.}++[废语]赞成，同意**', '++An attempt to sway him by saying he is a historical figure fails – “Don’t consign me to history” – but it does make him smile.**++试图通过提醒他他自己是个失败的历史角色来激怒他，他却笑着说，不要随便就把我丢到历史中去。**++So I ask this Congress to join me in doing whatever proves necessary. Because we cannot consign our nation to an open-ended recession.**++所以我要求本届国会和我一道实施一切必要的措施，因为我们不能让美国陷入无限的衰退中。**++Under the consignment shop structure, banks would consign only assets with doubtful values.**++根据寄售商店的结构，银行只寄售价值不清的资产。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('544', 'console', '[kɑnsol]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=console', '{vt.}{n.}++(包括键盘、踏板等部分的)风琴的操作部分**++【计算机】(电脑的)控制台，操作台**++收音机、电视机等的落地式座架**++=console table**++【建筑工程】(装饰用的)支柱，托臂**', '++Return to the administration console.**++回到这个管理控制台。**++She felt she could console the child better than anyone else.**++她认为自己比任何人都能更好地安慰这孩子。**++In this case, we have it just print a message to the console and then call the base class version for actual handling.**++在此例中，我们仅让它向控制台打印一条消息，然后调用它的基类版本来执行实际的处理。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('545', 'consolidate', '[kənsɑlɪdet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consolidate', '{vt.}++把…合成一体，合并；使联合起来，使结合；统一：**++巩固，加强，强化；加固：**++统一计算金额；合计金额**{vi.}++统一；联合；合并：**++变坚固；巩固，加强：**{adj.}++联合的；统一的**', '++What do they have to consolidate?**++他们还有什么可巩固的？**++He believed that the European Economic Community should consolidate.**++他认为欧洲经济共同体应该加强。**++If you can teach others knowledge, you could consolidate study.**++如果你能把知识教给别人,你也可以巩固学习。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('546', 'consonant', '[kɑnsənənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consonant', '{n.}++【语音学】辅音**++辅音字母**{adj.}++协调一致的，和谐的，符合的**++谐音的，和音的**++【韵律学】辅音韵的**++【语音学】辅音的**', '++Almost every language has an O vowel, a K consonant, and an A vowel.**++几乎所有语言都有O元音、K辅音和A元音。**++The tactic is a bit complicated for a brief article, but the basic idea is to attach each digit to a specific consonant.**++这个方法对于一篇短文来说有点复杂，但基本的概念是把每个数字跟一个特定的辅音字母关联起来。**++Really foreign sounds: Spanish Silbo, a whistle language, has only four vowel and four consonant sounds. Audible for miles, it resembles bird calls and is indigenous to—where else?—the Canary Islands.**++真正的外语：西班牙加那利群岛上的希尔伯哨语，这种口哨语言只有四个元音和四个辅音，发出的声音就像鸟叫，可以传到几英里之外。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('547', 'conspicuous', '[kənspɪkjʊəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conspicuous', '{adj.}++明显的，显而易见的，显著的**++引人注目的，值得注意的；出色的**', '++But their displays of support for the protesters were conspicuous throughout the capital.**++但是他们支持示威者的却在整个首都表现得很明显。**++What the drawing is trying to express is very conspicuous.**++这幅图试图表达的信息是非常明显的。**++This was the least conspicuous of the many curious aspects of my arrest and trial.**++对我的逮捕和审讯有很多可疑之处，这还是其中最不起眼的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('548', 'conspire', '[kənspaɪɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conspire', '{vi.}++共谋；密谋；阴谋策划：**++协力，合作，一致行动；凑在一起造成；**{vt.}++[罕用语]阴谋策划**', '++And you conspire with him against me, do you, viper?**++你和他串通一起反对我，是吧，毒蛇？**++For I hear the slander of many; there is terror on every side; they conspire against me and plot to take my life.**++我听见了许多人的谗谤，四围都是惊吓。 他们一同商议攻击我的时候，就图谋要害我的性命。**++This is one of the ways that science and the law conspire to make the world a safer and better place to live.**++这就是科学和法律如何协作使得我们生活的世界成为一个更加安全适于我们居住的地方了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('549', 'consternation', '[,kɑnstɚneʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consternation', '{n.}', '++As the ball hurtles through the air, the varying air flow around it can send it on unexpected paths, to the consternation of many soccer players.**++当球在空中疾驰时，球表面变化多样的气流可以将它送往意料之外的路径，让许多足球运动员惊愕不已。**++To the government’s consternation, some Chinese have been wondering aloud whether the country’s repressive politics might be at least partly to blame.**++使政府惊愕的是，一些中国人正大声质疑中国的镇压手段，认为这些手段也至少应当受到指责。**++Another reason for middle class "consternation" is that income tells only part of the story: the cost of maintaining a middle-class lifestyle depends heavily on where you live.**++中产阶级“惊慌失措”的另外一个原因就是收入仅仅是事情的一个方面：维持中产阶级的生活很大程度还取决于你的居住地区。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('550', 'constitute', '[kɑnstətut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=constitute', '{vt.}++构成，组成，形成：**++任命，指定；选派：**++制定(法律)；建立(机构等)：**++赋予(会议、法庭等)以合法形式；使(文件等)通过法律手续：**++造成；实际上等于，相当于：**', '++Four quarts constitute a gallon.**++四夸脱构成一加仑。**++They do not constitute a complete and continuous set of memoranda.**++他们不能构成一个完整的、持续的一整套备忘录。**++They constitute your memories; where you were, what you were doing, what you were interested in, what you were thinking of.**++它们组成了你的回忆；你曾在哪里，你曾做了什么，你曾对什么感兴趣，你曾思考过什么。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('551', 'constrain', '[kənstren]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=constrain', '{vt.}++强迫，迫使，强制；使(关系等)紧张：**++监禁,关押;The criminal was constrained  at once. 罪犯立即被关押起来。**++压制，抑制，遏制；约束：**', '++We should only constrain the liberty of others if what they do causes harm.**++我们只能在别人的所作所为对自己造成伤害时限制其自由。**++Whether one favors or opposes these restrictions on drilling, they do constrain the supply of oil and do, therefore, cause the price of oil to be higher than otherwise.**++不管是支持还是反对限制开采，他们限制了石油的供应，因此将使石油价格比另一种方式要更高。**++If you wish to constrain an application to run only on a particular subset of nodes, define a Node Group that includes just that set of nodes.**++如果希望限制一个应用程序，使其仅运行在一个特定节点子集中，则可以定义一个仅包括该节点集的节点组。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('552', 'constrict', '[kənstrɪkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=constrict', '{vt.}++使收缩，压缩；使缩减：**++使放慢(或停止)，抑制；约束，限制：**', '++They purposely wear devices that constrict blood flow in order to shape their bodies.**++她们特意穿上一些压缩血流量的衣服，从而保持她们的体形。**++The whole idea behind the squeezing material is to constrict the human body into a smaller space than gravity would allow.**++在挤压的材料背后，把人体压缩到重力不允许的更小的空间。**++A network of blood vessels along the surface of the beak helps dissipate extra heat, and the vessels constrict when temperatures drop.**++在这个大鸟嘴的表面有一些血管，可以散发多余的热量，而当体温下降后，血管又会收缩。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('553', 'constringe', '[kənstrɪndʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=constringe', '{vt.}', '++This kind of facial cleanser can constringe and clean the pores of face.**++此款洗面奶能够收敛及清洁毛孔。 。**++It can constringe and clean the pores of face. accelerate the cicatrization of wounds.**++刺激毛发生长，收敛及清洁毛孔，促进伤口愈合。**++Ingredients: natural herbage whiten essence, green tea extracts, wild chrysanthemum, aloe, constringe agency ets.**++成份：天然本草美白精华、绿茶提取液、野菊花、芦荟、收敛剂等。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('554', 'construct', '[kənstrʌkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=construct', '{vt.}++建筑，建造；施工；构造；设计**++【几何学】作(图)**{n.}++建筑物，构成物**++思维的产物，概念，观念；学说；逻辑构思**++【语法学】句法结构**++(构成派画家或雕塑家创作的)构成主义作品，结构派作品**++= cassette**', '++It currently compiles a file with one task construct.**++它当前在编译带有一个任务构造的文件。**++The mapping table is a common construct that allows you to map one hierarchical structure to another.**++映射表是一种常见的构造，允许您将一个分层结构映射到另一个中。**++You might need an activity that does nothing at all, such as when you have a construct that requires an activity, but there is no work to be done.**++您可能需要一个根本不执行任何工作的活动，例如，当您拥有一个需要某个活动的构造，但没有要执行的任何工作时。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('555', 'consummate', '[kɑnsəmət]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=consummate', '{vt.}++使完善，使圆满；完成，实现：**++(通过性行为)使(婚姻)实际完成**{vi.}++完成**{adj.}++完整的，完美无缺的，无比的**++高度熟练的，技艺高超的；精通的**', '++When I am tempted to quit and begin again tomorrow I will say them and immediately act to consummate another sale.**++当我今天想放弃，打算明天重新开始时，我会默念这句话，然后立即行动，完成下一桩生意。**++This intense consumption is particularly true of music, where the Japanese excel as the world@s consummate music collectors.**++这种消费热情在音乐上尤其如此，日本人是世界上最完美的音乐收藏家。**++As the Duke of Gloucester@s Private Secretary said: @ Consummate actress.**++正如格洛斯特公爵的私人秘书所说：“完美的演员。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('556', 'contagious', '[kəntedʒəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contagious', '{adj.}++接触传染性的**++传播传染病的**++有感染力的，易感染的，会蔓延开的**++为照管传染病人的；为对付传染病用的**', '++Love, happiness and tranquility are all contagious.**++爱、幸福与宁静都是有感染力的。**++This is both contagious and deadly and must be avoided at all costs.**++这会传染且是致命的，必须不惜一切代价加以避免。**++Attitude is contagious and it will help to motivate you, and even those around you, to drive you towards your goal.**++态度是具有感染性的，它可以使你获得动力，甚至可以感染你周围的人，推动你向目标努力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('557', 'contaminate', '[kəntæmɪnet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contaminate', '{vt.}++弄脏；污染；污损；使感染；传染：**++使受放射性污染**{adj.}++[古语]受到污染的**', '++Aflatoxins are carcinogenic fungal toxins that can contaminate corn, peanuts and other food crops such as tree nuts under certain conditions.**++黄曲霉毒素是致癌的真菌毒素，可在某些条件下污染玉米、花生及其他粮食作物，如树坚果。**++Phones and computers contain dangerous metals like lead, cadmium and mercury, which can contaminate the air and water when those products are dumped.**++手机和电脑含有像铅、镉和汞这样的有毒金属，这些产品在被抛弃后，会同时污染着水和空气。**++Critics fear that fracking can contaminate ground and surface water or even cause gas to leak into domestic water supplies.**++评论家认为这种致裂法会污染地下水和地表水，甚至导致天然气泄漏到民用给水中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('558', 'contemplate', '[kɑntəmplet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contemplate', '{vt.}++注视，凝视：**++思量，仔细考虑，深思：**++打算；计划；期待：**++估计；预计：**{vi.}++沉思默想，深思熟虑：**++沉思默想，深思熟虑：**', '++He goes to the park every day to sit and contemplate.**++他每天去公园，坐在那里沉思默想。**++Time is only created by the inadequate ability of Nature to contemplate the divine.**++时间是在沉思神圣时被自然的不充分的能力创造出来的。**++If it were essential on the stage to love as people really love, to employ that irreplaceable voice of the heart, to look as people contemplate in life, our speech would be in code.**++如果舞台上必须要有现实中的爱情、要运用心灵的不可替代之声、或看似如同生活中的人们一样沉思，那么我们的语言就是这口令。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('559', 'contempt', '[kəntɛmpt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contempt', '{n.}++轻蔑，鄙视**++耻辱，不名誉，不光彩**++【法律】藐视法庭(或国会等)**', '++The judge ordered him to purge his contempt by apologizing to the court.**++法官命令他做出道歉以赎蔑视法庭之罪。**++Here you can see the contempt that some of the Corinthian "Christians"have for Paul.**++从这里你可以看到哥林多的某些“基督徒”对保罗的轻视。**++True, often there is a kind of innocence in prejudices, but in those days I viewed grade-three thinking with an intolerant contempt and an incautious mockery.**++诚然，偏见里是有无辜的成分，但是在那时我对第三等级的思考的态度是毫不宽容的蔑视和不假思索的嘲笑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('560', 'contend', '[kəntɛnd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contend', '{vi.}++搏斗，争斗；抗争：**++竞争，争夺：**++争论，争辩，辩论，据理力争：**{vt.}++主张；声称；坚决认为，坚信；断言：**++主张；声称；坚决认为，坚信；断言：**', '++Many people contend that we have a right to think what we will, and that wicked thoughts, if not translated into wicked deeds, are not harmful.**++许多人主张我们有权利思考我们会怎样，有权利想出一些邪恶的思想，只要不把它变成邪恶的行为，它们就是无害的。**++One after another, in what felt like a very surreal experience, I had to contend with a series of seriously insightful questions.**++一次又一次，我好像是经历着超现实，我试图和盖茨辩论一系列的很有深度的问题。**++Have no fear, Dear Ones, although you have serious troubles to contend with and they are destroying your environment, we can reverse the damage and clear any pollution that has been caused .**++不用害怕，亲爱的，尽管你们有严重的问题要处理，他们正在摧毁你们的环境，但是我们能转变损害并清除任何已经产生的污染。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('561', 'content', '[kɑntɛnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=content', '{n.}++[通常用复数]容纳的东西，内藏物**++内容；目录，目次**++主要内容，要旨；重大意义**++【哲学、逻辑学】内含，内包，内容**++容量，容积；体积**++量；面积，范围；大小；长度**++含量；成分**++【计算机】存储信息**{adj.}++满意的，满足的**++愿意的，心甘情愿的**++[英国英语]赞成的，同意的；投赞成票的**++[古语]高兴的**{vt.}++[content oneself]使满意;使满足：**++[content oneself]使满意;使满足：**', '++You have to content yourself with what you have.**++你必须满足于现状。**++Never content ourselves with book knowledge only.**++不可满足于仅仅有一点书本知识。**++If you tear off the rhetorical top-dressing from his article, you will find there is very little solid content.**++如果从他的文章中剥去堆砌的华丽词藻，你会发现其中少有实际内容。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('562', 'contentious', '[kəntenʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contentious', '{adj.}++好争论的，好争吵的**++争论的，引起争论的；有争议的；争吵性的**', '++So the politics of who is and who is not allowed to enter this country, and on what terms, has always been contentious.**++因此，允许谁进入或不允许谁进入这个国家，以及入境条件是什么，一直都是有争议的政治问题。**++And yet, as contentious and frustrating and messy as our democracy can sometimes be, I know there isn’t a person here who would trade places with any other nation on Earth.**++可是，尽管我们的民主有时可能引起争议、令人沮丧乃至像一团乱麻，但我知道，在场的各位没有一个人会愿意与地球上任何其他国家的人交换位置。**++After a contentious meeting, make time to walk around the block or around the building.**++在一次吵吵闹闹的会议之后，找时间去大楼或公司四处走走。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('563', 'contiguous', '[kəntɪɡjuəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contiguous', '{adj.}++互相接触的，相接的**++邻近的，毗邻的，附近的**++[1605 ～1615]**', '++Note that identical key values will encode the same and will therefore be contiguous.**++请注意，相等的键值将具有相同编码，因此这些值是连续的。**++The characters in a subsequence, unlike those in a substring, do not need to be contiguous.**++子序列中的字符与子字符串中的字符不同，它们不需要是连续的。**++However, a shared memory segment cannot be "split" across quadrants and be guaranteed a contiguous address space.**++但是，共享内存段不能跨象限“拆分”，而应该保证是一个连续的地址空间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('564', 'contort', '[kəntɔrt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contort', '{vt.}', '++Some peoples mouths open. Others faces contort.**++有些人嘴巴张开，另一些人面部扭曲。**++Considering this far in advance of the deadline will prevent you from contorting yourself (or at least, appearing to contort yourself) to fit the criteria.**++在截止日期前考虑这些将会避免你曲解自己（至少看起来像是曲解）从而去适应评选标准。**++With its roots in strip clubs and bedrooms, pole dancing has been dismissed as a misogynistic playground in which women contort themselves for the viewing pleasure of men.**++源自脱衣舞俱乐部和床笫之间的钢管舞一度受到排斥，它被视为一种带有歧视女性色彩的活动，女性扭曲自己的身体，给男性带来视觉快感。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('565', 'contract', '[kɑntrækt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contract', '{n.}++契约，合同，合约**++婚约**++【法律】契约法，合同法**++定约桥牌[亦称作 contract bridge, 参较 auction bridge]**++[俚语]杀人契约**++(买通刺客的)行刺手令；(为暗杀一特定目标而签订的)雇用职业杀手协议**++[美国英语]拉票协议**++特殊期货交易合同的每一部分**++行贿；受贿**{vt.}++使收缩，使紧缩；使缩短；使皱缩：**++缩约，紧缩(词、短语等)：**++沾染，感染(疾病等)：**++招致；负(债等)：**++／kɔntrækt,kəntrækt／ 订(约),缔结：**++与…结交，与…结识：**++与…订婚，订(婚)；把…许配：**{vi.}++缩小；收缩；缩短；皱缩：**++订契约；承包：**', '++They determined the contract.**++他们终止了合同。**++They lost on the contract.**++他们在合同上赔了钱。**++What clause do you require in the contract?**++你要求在合同中订上什么条款?**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('566', 'contradict', '[kɑntrədɪkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contradict', '{vt.}++否认…的真实性；反驳，驳斥；顶嘴：**++与…发生矛盾；与…抵触：**++(行为和事件)相抵触：**++[废语]驳斥；反对**{vi.}++予以反驳；提出反对意见；否认：**++予以反驳；提出反对意见；否认：**', '++The shy girl was afraid to contradict.**++这个害羞的女孩不敢提出反驳意见。**++She does not like to contradict her husband in public.**++她不喜欢当众与丈夫顶嘴。**++Do not contradict yourself.**++不要自相矛盾。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('567', 'contravene', '[,kɑntrəvin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contravene', '{vt.}++与…相抵触；与…背道而驰；反对：**++违犯；违反，违背：**++反驳，否认：**', '++All poker sites reserve the right to do this if you contravene their terms and conditions.**++所有的网站都说如果你违反了条款他们将保留这个权利。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('568', 'contrite', '[kəntraɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contrite', '{adj.}++深感懊悔的，悔恨的，悔罪的**++由悔悟引起的，表示悔悟的**', '++In fact, he sounded somber and contrite.**++事实上，他的声音听起来又沮丧又后悔。**++I agree with those who have said that in my first statement after I testified, I was not contrite enough.**++我同意一些人的这种看法——在作证后的第一次声明中，我没有表现出足够的悔悟。**++God washes clean those who, no matter their past sins, return to him with a contrite heart.**++无论过去的罪多大，只要带着忧伤痛悔的心回到祂那里，祂就洗净他们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('569', 'contrived', '[kəntraɪvd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contrived', '{vt.}++contrive的变形**{adj.}++明显计划好的；不自然的；人为的，做作的**{vt.}++精巧设计，设计，发明，创造：**++策划，图谋：**++以计谋达到：**{vi.}++设计，计划；设法做到：**++策划，图谋**++料理家务，治家：**', '++While the API example is contrived, it has hopefully demonstrated how simple it can be to apply static crosscutting in an enterprise architecture.**++虽然这里的 API 例子是人为的，但它有望证明在企业体系结构中应用静态横切是多么简单。**++This will help you avoid falling into the trap of contrived language that turns off the readers - sometimes to the point where they shred your MRD and feed the shreds through the shredder again!**++这个将有助于你避开陷入那些令读者人厌烦（有时他们会把MRD撕碎然后再碎片喂给碎纸机）的用做作的语言的陷阱。**++They contrived a mask against poison gas.**++他们设计了一种防毒面具。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('570', 'contumacious', '[,kɑntumeʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=contumacious', '{adj.}', '++The contumacious mob shouted defiantly at the police.**++暴徒的顽皮喊道目空一切的警察。**++There is another efficacious method for subduing the most obstinate, contumacious sinner.**++有另一个有效的方法来镇压那最为顽固，抗命不从的罪人。**++Hard labor for life had been the sentence pronounced against the escaped and contumacious accomplices.**++在逃没有到案的同谋则被判处终身苦役。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('571', 'conundrum', '[kənʌndrəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conundrum', '{n.}++(谜底含双关意的)谜语，双关谜**++费解的难题，猜不透的难题**', '++France has grappled with this conundrum for years.**++法国就已经为了这个难题苦恼多年。**++How life had first made proteins without enzymes, which presumably had to be proteins themselves, had been a chicken-and-egg conundrum.**++生命最初如何在没有酶（可能是蛋白质本身）的情况下合成蛋白质？ 这是个鸡与蛋谁先产生的难题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('572', 'convalesce', '[,kɑnvəlɛs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convalesce', '{vi.}', '++He was calling to ask me where he should convalesce in the event of his being injured, there in Texas or at home in Pennsylvania.**++他在电话中还问我，如果他负了伤，是该在得克萨斯州还是在宾夕法尼亚州的家中养伤。**++Never forget the old enmity the human, his wound forever with difficulty will heal; Although that is originally may convalesce.**++一个念念不忘旧仇的人，他的伤口将永远难以愈合；尽管那本来是可以痊愈的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('573', 'convene', '[kənvin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convene', '{vi.}++聚集，集合；集会，开会：**++聚集，集合；集会，开会：**{vt.}++使聚集；召集，召开：**++(法庭)传唤…出庭**', '++While we in government can lead, and convene, and even cajole, we can’t do it all.**++虽然政府可以发挥倡导、召集甚至引导的作用，但是我们无法克竟全功。**++One big Extra in any endeavor is to identify new opportunities or unsolved problems, and then convene conversations around them.**++任何努力中的一个大的额外因素就是确定新的机遇或没有解决的问题，然后召集他们谈话。**++Instead, you need to convene a meeting involving representatives from each discipline, try to figure out who did what, and then extrapolate the solution to problem from there...**++相反，您需要召集一个有来自每个规程的代表参加的会议，试图弄清谁是做什么的，然后从那里开始推断对问题的解决方案...**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('574', 'convenience', '[kənvinɪəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convenience', '{n.}++便利，方便，合适，适宜**++方便的时候，方便的机会**++便利条件；便利设施，方便的用具**++[主英国英语]=water closet**{adj.}++易得到的，易使用的，易达到的；使便利的；(制作)快而(使用)方便的**', '++A new general store has been built for the convenience of the residents.**++为便利居民， 新建了一个百货商店。**++The shop assistants sell goods from door to door for the convenience of the masses.**++售货员送货上门，便利群众。**++For all the contemporary problems cars bring, no one can deny the convenience cars bring us and ignore the effort We make to solve these problems.**++对于汽车所带来的问题，谁也不能否认汽车给我们带来的便利，忽视我们为解决这些问题而做出的努力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('575', 'convention', '[kənvɛnʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convention', '{n.}++集会；(正式)会议，(定期)大会**++(美国)全国代表大会；政党代表大会**++协议，公约；契约，合同**++习惯，习俗，社会习俗**++【桥牌】叫牌的一套常规**', '++Originality often triumphs over convention.**++创新常常战胜惯例。**++He sets at naught every convention of society.**++他轻视所有的社会习俗。**++The party convention drafted the president for a second term.**++该党大会决定由总统竞选连任。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('576', 'converge', '[kənvɝdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=converge', '{vi.}++(向一点)趋于会合，(在一点上)会合；互相靠拢：**++聚集，(向一点)集中：**++趋于相同的目标：**++【数学】收敛**{vt.}++使会聚；使集中于一点：**++使会聚；使集中于一点：**', '++One Saturday morning each month, the vendors of the Greenpoint Food Market converge on the Church of the Messiah in Brooklyn.**++每个月里，都有一个星期六的早上，绿点食品市场的卖主聚集在布鲁克林的弥赛亚教堂。**++It@s very easy to estimate the scheduling cost of adding systems or replacing them when your machines will converge to a known state shortly.**++当机器将很快收敛到一个已知状态时，就可以很容易地估计添加系统或替换它们的调度成本。**++You will run a command and watch the system converge to a stable state.**++您将运行一个命令并观察系统将收敛到一种稳定状态。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('577', 'conversant', '[kənvɝsnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conversant', '{adj.}++熟悉的，熟练的，精通的**++[古语]交往密切的，熟识的；亲近的**', '++Ordinary people need to know what information is available, and they need the training to be conversant in it.**++普通人需要知道什么信息是可利用的，并且他们需要训练的是精通它。**++Have you ever noticed that when you are in love, you seem instinctively affectionate, conversant, admiring and willing to make love?**++当你坠入爱河的时候，有没有注意到，你会本能地产生爱慕、熟悉、钦佩并想要得到对方的全部？**++Those not conversant in Sign may suppose that it@s an invented form of communication like Esperanto or Morse code.**++那些不熟悉语言符号的人会认为这是被发明成像世界语和莫尔斯电码类似的一种沟通形式。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('578', 'convert', '[kənvɝt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convert', '{vt.}++使改变，使转变，使转化；使转换：**++改变…的信仰(或观点、立场等)：**++改建，改造；改装(常与to 或into连用)：**++兑换；换算：**++侵吞；盗用**++【法律】非法挪用；强占**++【逻辑学】使换位**{vi.}++转变，转化；改用；改变信仰，皈依：**++【橄榄球】触地得分后得附加分**{n.}++皈依宗教者；改变信仰者，改教者**{adj.}++(货币、证券等)可兑换的**{n.}', '++I convert waste into wealth," he says.**++我将废物转变为财富，”他说。**++Why does it convert?**++为什么它要转换？**++In order to convert hearers into listeners, you need to know why they should listen to you –and tell them if necessary.**++为了把听众转换成倾听者，您需要了解他们为什么需要听您的演讲----如果必要您可以告诉他们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('579', 'convex', '[kɑnvɛks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convex', '{adj.}++凸面的，凸形的，凸圆的，凸的[参较 concave]**++【数学】连续凸函数的；凸点集的；(几何图形)凸的，构成凸集的**{n.}++凸面，凸状，凸状物；凸面线；凸圆体；凸缘**', '++Because there is no abrasion between the concave and convex, the nut is reusable.**++因为凹面与凸面没有磨损，螺母可以重复使用。**++They’re lenses because they’re convex vessels, and when they’re full of water they act as a lens and you see the horizon in them, upside down and backwards.**++说它们是镜头，因为它们是凸面的容器。 盛满水后，它们可作为镜头使用，你可以通过它们看到颠倒过来的地平线。**++The product they came up with is a round, brushed metal device with a convex glass circle in the middle that displays the temperature and changes color depending on the color of the wall it is on.**++法德尔发布的这款产品是一个圆形、拉丝的金属装置，中间有凸面玻璃显示屏，可以显示温度，并且可以根据其所在? 面的颜色自动变色。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('580', 'convey', '[kənve]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convey', '{vt.}++运输，运送，运载；搬运：**++传送，传递；传播；传导：**++传达；转达；表达：**++【法律】让与，(将所有权)转让给…：**++通知；通报：**++[废语]偷偷地拿走，窃取**', '++What does your smile convey?**++你的微笑传达的是什么？**++What level of enthusiasm would you convey?**++你想要传达什么程度的热情？**++Nevertheless, whatever its other merits or defects may be, I can assure my readers that it was not my intention to propound a riddle, or insidiously convey any erudite teaching.**++然而，不管它的别的优点或者缺点是什么，我能告诉读者的就是，我在诗里无意提出一个谜，或者狡狯地传达什么教诲。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('581', 'conviction', '[kənvɪkʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conviction', '{n.}++证明有罪；(被)判罪，定罪**++说服，信服**++深信，确信，坚强信念**', '++I say this with conviction.**++这一点我确信不疑。**++If you have a conviction about something, stick with it.**++如果你对某事有自己的信念，那就坚持吧！**++This, the jury said in its explanation of the sentence, tipped the balance in favour of conviction.**++陪审团在解释判决结果时说，这些证言为最终的定罪起了重要作用。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('582', 'convoke', '[kənvok]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convoke', '{vt.}', '++The king convoke parliament to cope with the impending danger.**++国王召开国会以应付迫近眉睫的危险。**++In 1978 the Argentinian trainer Menotti didn@t convoke Maradona, as he considered him too young.**++阿根廷教练麦诺提（Menotti）考虑到他年幼，没有召集马拉多纳。**++It is of course possible that, if he wins, he may be true to his promises and convoke a Parliament for all China; but it is at least equally possible that he may not.**++这当然是可能的，如果他获胜，他可能是正确的，他的承诺，并召集所有中国一个议会，但它至少是同样有可能，他可能不会。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('583', 'convoluted', '[kɑnvəlutɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convoluted', '{vt.,vi.}++convolute的变形**{adj.}++盘绕的，缠绕的；卷曲的；回旋的**++结构复杂的，错综的**{vt.,vi.}++(使)盘绕，(使)缠绕**{adj.}++卷起的，卷曲的，盘绕的**++【植物学】席卷的，旋转的；(纵向)盘绕的**', '++This is a little more convoluted than the previous examples, but is still pretty straightforward.**++这个例子要比前面的例子更复杂一点，但是原理仍然非常简单。**++Few programmers understand what it means, not to mention its risk of introducing mistakes into such convoluted code.**++很少有程序员理解它是什么意思，更不用说这种费解的代码所带来的出错风险了。**++The results could be harmful and damaging if they were to expose people’s information in ways they were not expecting, she said, and these issues are only likely to get more convoluted in the future.**++这个结果将是有害的和具有破坏性的，如果他们在某种方式下揭露人们不期望揭露的信息，她说，同时这些问题在未来仅仅就像得到更多的费解。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('584', 'convulsion', '[kənvʌlʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=convulsion', '{n.}++【医学】痉挛，抽搐；惊厥**++狂笑，大笑**++震动，骚动，动乱**++【地质学】灾变，地震**', '++Then if convulsion, then famine.**++动乱，然后是饥荒。**++Oliver and order, Thomas...and convulsion.**++奥利弗是秩序，汤姆斯是……动乱。**++They start by poking a lens at the family@s faces as they learn the news; they end by getting them to act, or re-enact, every emotional convulsion that needs a second, third or umpteenth take.**++当得知这条新闻后，他们将镜头探到这户人家的面前；他们让这家人表演或再现每一次情感的惊厥，需要一而再、再而三数不清的拍摄。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('585', 'coop', '[kʊp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=coop', '{n.}++(关家禽或其他小动物的)笼子；鸡笼，鸡舍；畜栏**++狭小的地方 **++[俚语]监牢；拘留所**{vt.}++把…关进笼子里；将…限制在狭小空间；阻碍；限制；拘禁(常与up或in连用)：**++把…关进笼子里；将…限制在狭小空间；阻碍；限制；拘禁(常与up或in连用)：**{vi.}++[美国俚语](值勤警察)在警车里打瞌睡(警察值勤时在停放的巡逻车内)打瞌睡**{abbr.}', '++As soon as she was alone within the walled garden she sat herself down on a coop, and seriously screwed up her mouth for the long neglected practice.**++当苔丝回到围墙的院子里只剩下一个人时，她就在一个鸡笼上坐下来，认真地把嘴巴撮起来，开始了她早已生疏了的练习。**++It opens with the father, Chef Chu, plucking a live chicken from his backyard coop and minutes later turning it into a steaming, mouth-watering casserole dish.**++该片一开始，就是父亲朱师傅从他家后院的鸡笼里抓出一只活鸡来拨毛，而在几分钟之后把它变成了一道令人垂涎欲滴的砂锅菜。**++Join a community farm or grocery coop.**++加入社区农场或杂货鸡舍。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('586', 'copious', '[kopɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=copious', '{adj.}++丰富的，丰盛的，富裕的，富饶的；大量的；多产的**++(文章等)冗长的，长篇累牍的**++满腹经纶的，博学多闻的**', '++No attempt is made to subdue reality by extensive analysis and copious documentation. Reality is invited in via experiments.**++不要试图让现实屈从于广泛的分析和丰富的文档，因为现实是通过试验得来的。**++It must then, like all the states that have now made their claims, submit copious scientific evidence to show that the seabed in question is indeed continental shelf.**++到时候，这些国家和那些发出声明的国家一样，必定会提出丰富的科学证据来证明那些有争议的海床实际上是大陆架。**++Even on a single physical server, you can have redundant power supplies, error-correcting RAM, redundant disks, and copious monitoring of pre-fault indicators.**++甚至在单个物理服务器上，您都有冗余电源、错误纠正 RAM、冗余磁盘和丰富的故障前诊断指示器监控。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('587', 'coquette', '[kokɛt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=coquette', '{n.}++(向男人)卖弄风情的女人，风骚的女子，妖艳的女人**{vi.}++卖弄风情，卖俏，调情，玩弄，献媚**', '++" She has no conversation, " he said, "and I am afraid that she is a coquette, for she is always flirting with the wind.**++“她不懂得跟人家说说话，”他说，“我担心她根本就是一个轻佻女子，看她风一来就浑身摇晃的轻浮样儿。”**++Of course she had a perfect right to suit herself about the kind of a man she took for a husband, but he certainly had not thought she was such an utter coquette.**++当然，她完全有权利拒绝自己不喜欢的男人，但他完全没想到她之前居然是在卖弄风情。**++He likes girls that play the coquette.**++他喜欢卖弄风情的女子。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('588', 'cordon', '[kɔrdn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cordon', '{n.}++【军事】警戒线，哨兵线，封锁线，包围圈**++(勋章等的)绶带，饰带**++【建筑工程】束带层，带形线条，带饰**{vt.}++用警戒线封闭；用栏栅围住，用障碍物拦住(常与 off连用)：**++用警戒线封闭；用栏栅围住，用障碍物拦住(常与 off连用)：**', '++Scotland Yard said a cordon was used because missiles were being thrown at officers.**++苏格兰场说使用警戒线是因为一直有投掷物扔向警察。**++It has used the pretext of an alleged terrorist threat to impose a restrictive security cordon on the city and curtail visas even for harmless businessmen.**++它以所谓恐怖分子的威胁为借口设置限制性安全警戒线于城中，并且削减普通商务人士的签证。**++The man had collapsed within a police cordon set up to contain the crowds who had assembled in central London and the City to protest over the G20 summit.**++那个人倒在了警察的警戒线之内，这些警戒线是警察为控制在伦敦市中心和伦敦金融城对G20峰会进行示威的人群设置的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('589', 'cornucopia', '[kɔrnjʊkopɪə]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cornucopia', '{n.}++【希腊神话】哺乳宙斯的羊角**++(象征丰收的)丰饶角，丰收角**++丰富，丰饶**++圆锥形容器**', '++In the foreground is a cornucopia (a symbol of abundance that is a common decorative motif at Thanksgiving) labeled @economy@.**++在靠前的地方有一个羊角状器皿(羊角是丰饶的象征，是感恩节时很普遍的装饰图案)，上写着“经济”二字，美国经济的确在大幅增长，但是谁受益呢？**++From the low-growing Indian rhubarb to the mighty English maples, the plants in this region get ready for the winter with a cornucopia of colors.**++从低速度生长的印度大黄到巨大的英国枫树，这一地区的植物用丰富的色彩为冬天的到来做好准备。**++Over the years, I@ve ripped my music onto various computers and, in the process, muddled my MP3 collection to the point where I have numerous directories representing a cornucopia of music.**++多年以来，我把我的音乐截取到不同的计算机上，在这个过程中，我的 MP3 收藏乱到了这样一种层度：只是表示品种丰富的音乐目录就有一大堆。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('590', 'coronation', '[kɔrəneʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=coronation', '{n.}', '++Logue outrages Bertie, to therapeutic effect, by sitting on the throne in Westminster Abbey prior to the coronation.**++为了达成治疗效果，洛格激怒了伯蒂，他在伯蒂加冕礼前坐在了他威斯敏斯特的王座上。**++When they first saw each other in royal clothing, the fine robes and shining crowns for their coronation, that was when they fell in love.**++当他们第一次看到对方穿着王室的衣服——为他们的加冕礼而穿戴的精美的袍子和华丽的王冠——时，那就是他们坠入爱河的时候。**++But the world began to warm in 1650; when Charles II was crowned king of England in 1660, the coronation sparked the Enlightenment era in Europe.**++但是从1650年开始，全球开始转暖，当查理二世于1660年在英国即位时，他的加冕礼成为启动欧洲启蒙时代的转机。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('591', 'corporeal', '[kɔrpɔrɪəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=corporeal', '{adj.}++肉体的，身体的**++物质的；有形的，具体的**++【法律】有形的(指动产等)**', '++The picture forms a link, primitive but palpable, between corporeal and evanescent, between the body and the spirit.**++这样的照片在有形和虚无之间，在肉体和精神之间形成了关联，这种联系虽原始但却可以感知。**++Descartes insisted – as part of his proof of the ‘cogito’ – that the mind must be utterly distinct from corporeal things.**++笛卡尔认为——在对“我思”的证明中——心灵与有形的物体必然是决然不同的。**++While the Cruze ad was schmaltzy, it got me thinking about how big a role technology now plays even in this, um, corporeal aspect of our lives.**++克鲁兹的这个广告虽然有点让人伤感，不过它让我开始思考，科技在我们生活的有形方面扮演了多大的角色。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('592', 'correlate', '[kɔrəlet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=correlate', '{vt.}++使相互关联，使相互对照：**++使相互关联，使相互对照：**{vi.}++关联，相关：**++关联，相关：**{adj.}++关联的，相关的**{n.}++相互关联的人(或物)**', '++This would cause problems if you tried to correlate sent and received messages.**++这将导致您在关联发送与接收到的消息时产生问题。**++This brings up the question of how you correlate a response to its respective request.**++这就带来了一个问题，您如何将一个响应关联到其请求。**++In our model, the client will create a temporary destination for all its requests, and will correlate the individual requests and responses by copying the message ID to the correlation ID.**++在我们的模型中，客户端将为所有的请求创建一个临时目的地，并通过将消息 ID 复制到相关 ID，建立单个请求和响应之间的关联。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('593', 'corroborate', '[kərɑbəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=corroborate', '{vt.}', '++Authorities have also recovered a satellite phone that appears to corroborate much of his testimony.**++当局还找回了一部看起来能证实其大部分证词的卫星电话。**++Her results indicated that pair programming was beneficial, but more data was needed to corroborate her findings.**++她的结果说明配对编程是有益的，但是需要更多的数据以证实她的决定。**++While one study in the US found a possible association between personal use of hair dyes and the risk of developing bladder cancer, a more recent Spanish study failed to corroborate the result.**++美国的一项研究发现个人使用染发剂与患膀胱癌之间存在着可能的联系，但是更近一些时候的西班牙研究无法证实此发现。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('594', 'corrosive', '[kərosɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=corrosive', '{adj.}++腐蚀性的，引起腐蚀的**++讽刺的，挖苦的；尖刻的，刻薄的**{n.}++腐蚀剂，腐蚀物**', '++The corrosive effects of water in those conditions would outpace Bermudan reefs@ ability to grow.**++在那种条件下海水的腐蚀效果将会超过百慕大珊瑚礁的生长能力。**++But safety rules prohibit the ships from remaining in space for more than 200 days, since their batteries can lose power and corrosive thruster fuel can degrade rubberized seals.**++安全守则规定这些飞船不能暴露在宇宙空间中超过200天，因为电池会流失能量和推进器燃油会腐蚀橡胶密封。**++Any accidental release of fluorine could also be an issue: Fluorine is a toxic and corrosive gas and, at high concentrations, can retard plant growth and damage teeth and bones.**++氟气的任一次意外泄漏也都可能造成问题。 氟气是一种有毒的腐蚀性气体，而且，在高浓度时，能阻碍植物生长并，损伤牙齿和骨骼。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('595', 'corrugated', '[kɔrəgetɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=corrugated', '{vt.}++corrugate的变形**{adj.}++皱纹的；波纹的；有瓦楞的**{vt.}++使起皱；使起波纹：**++使起皱；使起波纹：**{vi.}++起皱；起波纹：**++起皱；起波纹：**{adj.}++=corrugated**', '++Once the retina detaches it assumes a slight opaque color with a convex configuration and a corrugated appearance (arrow).**++一旦视网膜发生脱离，其颜色变得不透明且形状凸起呈波纹状（箭头所指）。**++That@s not to say that Galvin expects us all to live in corrugated steel boxes.**++当然，加尔文并不指望所有人都住进外墙波纹起伏的钢铁箱子。**++Shacks made of wood and corrugated steel line the edges of the khlong. Men and women can be found sitting along the edges, dangling their feet above the water, fishing.**++木料和波纹钢板搭建的窝棚枕水而建，绵延两岸，间或有几个居民闲坐岸边，脚在水面上摇来荡去地垂钓，小孩子在河中游泳，嬉戏。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('596', 'cosmopolitan', '[kɑzməpɑlətn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cosmopolitan', '{adj.}++全世界的，世界性的**++【植物学、动物学】广泛分布的，世界各地都有的**++四海为家的，没有地方或国家偏见的**++世界主义的，代表全世界的**{n.}++世界主义者，世界公民，四海为家的人**', '++"I think you@ll find a much more cosmopolitan Korea, " she says.**++“我认为你会发现一个更具世界性的韩国，”她说。**++It is not just a biography more nomadic, more complicated and cosmopolitan than any one of them.**++这不仅仅是在个人传记方面比其他人都更加流离、更加复杂和更加世界性。**++She is, to borrow a term coined by another cosmopolitan writer, Pico Iyer, just the sort of “global soul” we need to guide us into a China that is transforming and being transformed by the world.**++借用另一位世界主义的作家皮柯·艾耶创造的一个词，她就是那种我们需要的“世界人”，引导我们进入一个正在改变世界，也正在被世界改变的中国。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('597', 'cosset', '[kɑsɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cosset', '{vt.}++宠爱；溺爱；娇生惯养：**++宠爱；溺爱；娇生惯养：**{n.}++亲手饲养的羔羊**++供玩赏的宠物，爱畜**', '++Am I you cosset for ever?**++我会是你永远的宠儿吗？**++Some parents cosset their children, and always give them a large amount of pocket money. Such conditions will make children become more and more prodigal.**++一些父母宠爱他们的孩子，总是给孩子大量的零用钱。这种情况将会使孩子变得越来越挥零浪费。**++In our impression, star is the cosset of the destiny, they can make money easily, scene is an upright person.**++在我们的印象里，明星是命运的宠儿，她们可以轻松赚钱、风光做人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('598', 'countenance', '[kaʊntənəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=countenance', '{n.}++面容，(尤指)面部表情；脸，面孔**++容貌**++表示赞许的神色，赞同，同意，许可；支持，鼓励**++(面部表情的)镇定，沉着**++[废语]举止，行为**{vt.}++允许；容忍：**++赞成，同意；鼓励：**', '++He possesses a mild and benevolent countenance.**++他的面容温和而慈祥。**++When she had finished, she resumed her smiling countenance.**++当她哭完后,她又重新恢复了她微笑的表情。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('599', 'counterfeit', '[kaʊntɚfɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=counterfeit', '{adj.}++伪造的，仿造的，假冒的**++装出的，虚假的；假装的**{n.}++伪造品，仿制品，𪪦品**++[古语]摹本，副本**++[古语]肖像，画像**++[废语]骗子，冒充者**{vt.}++伪造，仿造：**++与…极相像，酷似：**++假装，佯作：**{vi.}++从事伪造(货币等的)活动：**++假装，伪装**', '++It is a crime to counterfeit money.**++伪造钱币是犯罪行为。**++If the wholesaler buys, those counterfeit products are now in the supply chain.**++如果大批发商接收贿赂，那么伪造药品就进入了供应链。**++They told some of the volunteers that the sunglasses were real, and others that they were counterfeit.**++他们告诉一部分志愿者这些眼镜是真品，又告诉剩下的人说眼镜是冒牌货。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('600', 'countermand', '[kaʊntɚmænd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=countermand', '{vt.}++撤回，取消(已发出的命令等)：**++下令撤回，下令取消，下令停止：**{n.}++收回成命的命令，相反的命令**', '++I have now to countermand that order, in consequence of the receipting of the letter this morning.**++你太苛求了，我一刻钟前 才 收到他的来信。**++Intimately familiar with the parameters of the droid signal device, Dellso found a way to countermand the deactivate signal, and soon newly minted battle droids began churning out on the fiery world.**++由于熟知机器人信号设备的参数，德尔索找到了取消关闭信号的方法。 很快，大量新建的战斗机器人出现在这个炽热的星球。**++Please countermand our order for same.**++对上述订单，请取消。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('601', 'counterpart', '[kaʊntɚpɑrt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=counterpart', '{n.}++副本，抄件，复制品**++(正本和副本中的)互相对应部分；互为补充的人(或物)，补足物**++相对应的人，对手方；地位相同的人；极相似的人(或物)**', '++Each of them has a counterpart column in the database tables.**++每个字段在数据库表中有一个对应的列。**++Slow Food is against its counterpart: the spirit of Fast Food and what it stands for as a lifestyle.**++慢食运动反对它的对立面：快餐精神和拥护它作为一种生活方式的任何事物。**++In fact, a true service-oriented architecture should only have services with a direct counterpart in the business; otherwise they cannot possibly be modeling a business process.**++事实上，一个真正的面向服务架构应该只有在业务中有直接对等物的服务；否则，它们就不可能被建模成一个业务过程。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('602', 'counterproductive', '[,kaʊntɚprədʌktɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=counterproductive', '{adj.}', '++But, he added, “I think the strikes over all have been counterproductive.**++但是，他补充说，“我认为总的来看，空袭起到了反作用。”**++There are other good books about how killing programmers is counterproductive for managers, but this is one of the best.**++关于 “累死程序员如何让经理们适得其反” 还有许多其他的好书，但这是最好的一本。**++The above discussion shows that use of the term "service" without context and qualification can be confusing and even counterproductive.**++上面的讨论表明，如果没有上下文和限定，使用术语 “服务” 可能会引起混淆，甚至导致误解。**');
