insert into GREWordBook values ('1096', 'felony', '[fɛləni]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=felony', '{n.}', '++The crime is gender-neutral, and contains no age exemption for putative defendants; whether the perpetrator is male or female, 14 or 40, it is still a felony.**++这条罪不受性别限制，对假定的被告也没有年龄限制，无论违法者是男性或女性，14岁或者40岁，它还是一条重罪。**++Finally, eating meat supports cruelty to animalsso severe that it would warrant felony cruelty charges were dogs orcats so horribly abused -- and that@s true even of so-called "humane"farms (video).**++最后，吃肉对虐待动物的支持到如此严重的地步，如果被恐怖虐待的是猫或狗，那肯定要受到重罪指控，即使是所谓“人道”的农场也是这样（视频）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1097', 'fender', '[fɛndɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fender', '{n.}++挡开物，防御物，防护板，防冲物；尤指**++[美国英语](车辆的)挡泥板**++(电车或机车的)缓冲装置，救护装置**++火炉围栏，(壁炉的)炉围**++(船的)碰垫，护舷材，缓冲材，护板；排障器**', '++The impact  dented our car@s fender.**++碰撞把我们汽车挡泥板给撞凹下去了。**++His car bruised the auto fender of my car.**++他的汽车撞瘪了我的汽车挡泥板。**++When Thomas found the device on her vehicle back in 2005, she ripped it from the underside of her fender, but quickly grew fearful the FBI would raid her house if agents suspected she’d removed it.**++当2005年托马斯在她的汽车上发现这个设备时，她从车子的挡泥板下面将它拆下，可她很快担心如果特工怀疑她把设备取下来了，FBI会搜查她的房子。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1098', 'feral', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=feral', '{adj.}++未驯服的，野的，野生的**++凶猛的，残酷的，粗野的**{adj.}++[诗歌用语]阴郁的，忧闷的；丧葬似的；悲哀的**++[古语]致命的；毁灭性的**', '++Feral American mink on the continent are even more damaging than they are here, as they drive out the endangered European mink.**++野生美国貂对这块大陆造成的破坏甚至比在美国本地更甚，因为它们把濒危的欧洲貂赶走了。**++Pristine areas faced their biggest threat from introduced feral animal and plant species including pigs, rabbits, foxes, buffaloes and noxious weeds, the report said.**++报告称，这些原始地区最大的威胁来自野生动植物，其中包括猪、兔子、狐狸、水牛以及有毒野草。**++The "service-users" - as the volunteers here call them - are a truly disparate group - some look as if they@ve just stepped off the tube after a busy day at work, others are unkempt and smell feral.**++这些“服务使用者”——这儿的志愿者这样叫他们——确实是一群异类——有些人看上去好像刚从忙碌工作了一天的管子上下来，其他人则衣衫蓬乱，带着凶猛的气息。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1099', 'ferocious', '[fəroʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ferocious', '{adj.}++凶猛的，残忍的；凶恶的**++[口语](欲望、精力等)极大的，非常的，十分强烈的**', '++After ferocious rows,he kicked the man to death.**++剧烈的争吵之后，他把那个人踢死了。**++The sun is a ferocious ball of energy that can eject massive amounts of plasma from its surface in our direction, causing our equipment to go screwy.**++太阳是一个能量惊人的大火球，它的表面能够向地球释放大量等离子，从而导致我们的设备工作异常。**++Authorities said Friday this latest in a series of eruptions over the last 11 days was the most ferocious yet.**++当局星期五说，火山在过去11天里连续喷发，星期五的这次喷发是迄今为止最为猛烈的一次。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1100', 'fertilize', '[fɝtəlaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fertilize', '{vt.}++[主美国英语]**++使(土壤)肥沃；使多产，使丰产；使丰富：**++施肥于：**++【生物学】使受精，受胎**', '++It takes only one sperm to fertilize the egg.**++然而只有一个精子会让卵细胞受精。**++Moreover, in animals, large numbers of sperm tend to evolve when competition between different males to fertilize a female’s eggs is fierce.**++此外，动物界里，大量的精子在不同雄性使雌性卵细胞受精的激烈竞争中也都趋向进化。**++The best option to preserve the fertility of a female cancer patient is to collect her eggs, fertilize them with sperm and freeze the resulting embryos.**++女性癌症病人保存生育能力的最佳选择就是先收集她的卵，并将其与精子受精，再将由此产生的胚胎冷冻。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1101', 'fervent', '[fɝvənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fervent', '{adj.}++热的，白热的；灼热的**++热烈的，满怀热情的，热心的，深表热诚的；强烈的**', '++Lots of men and women in the West are fervent supporters of bloodstained setups.**++在西方，大量的男人和女人是大规模杀人装置的强烈支持者。**++And not by his coming only, but by the consolation wherewith he was comforted in you, when he told us your earnest desire, your mourning, your fervent mind toward me; so that I rejoiced the more.**++不但藉着他来，也藉着他从你们所得的安慰，安慰了我们。 因他把你们的想念，哀恸，和向我的热心，都告诉了我，叫我更加欢喜。**++So why is an argument that commanded fervent global agreement just two years ago now being trampled over?**++那么，究竟什么原因导致两年前还达成强烈一致的国际争论，如今却惨遭践踏？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1102', 'fervid', '[fɝvɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fervid', '{adj.}++热的，发白光的；灼热的**++热烈的，热情的，热心的，热诚的**', '++He’d be detached from his most fervid followers and merciful and understanding toward foes.**++他懂得与狂热的追随者保持距离，对敌人则是慈悲为怀、理解万岁。**++And one more: Migrating animals maintain a fervid attentiveness to the greater mission, which keeps them undistracted by temptations and undeterred by challenges that would turn other animals aside.**++还有一点：迁徙动物热切关注更大的使命，因而不为诱惑所动，不受吓退其它动物的挑战所阻。**++It must have felt that fervid call**++它一定感到那炽热的召唤**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1103', 'fervor', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fervor', '{n.}', '++Conservative groups responded with equal fervor to the court@s decision.**++保守派对于法院的判决表现出了同样的热情。**++Now, over the past three decades, China has embraced capitalism with the same level of fervor.**++而在过去的这三十年里，中国以同样的热情拥抱了资本主义。**++Michael’s friends and co-workers didn’t know what to make of his religious fervor or his shifting politics.**++迈克尔的朋友和同事都不知道，是什么造就了他对宗教的热情以及摇摆不定的政治立场。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1104', 'fester', '[fɛstɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fester', '{n.}++【病理学】脓疮，轻微溃疡**{vi.}++形成溃疡，生疮，化脓，溃烂：**++引起怨恨，使人痛恨；变得越来越恼人：**++腐败，腐烂，腐朽：**++(不断地)恶化**{vt.}++使腐败，使溃烂，使化脓**++使怨恨；使痛恨；使越来越恼人：**', '++The wound began to fester.**++伤口开始化脓。**++For the truth is that unless we can forgive, we can never recover. Our wounds will continue to fester and never heal.**++这是因为存在这样的真理：如果我们不原谅别人，就永远无法修复自己的创伤，伤口会继续溃烂，永不愈合。**++By expressing your feelings and talking through (not yelling, mind you) problems, you don’t give them a chance to fester and grow.**++表达你的感受并且讨论问题， 这样你就不会给问题一个溃烂或者增长的机会。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1105', 'fetid', '[fɛtɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fetid', '{adj.}', '++The park, a collection of crumbling buildings around a fetid pond, is now closed to the public and overgrown with weeds.**++今天的公园，恶臭的池塘围绕在残破的建筑物周围，现在向公众（免费）开放，里面杂草丛生。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1106', 'fetter', '[fɛtɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fetter', '{n.}++脚镣**++[通常用复数]桎梏；束缚；约束；羁绊**{vt.}++给…上脚镣**++束缚，管束；羁绊；抑制**', '++You may imprison my body, actually could not fetter my mind.**++你可以禁锢我的身体，却束缚不了我的心灵。**++And when the unclean shall be no more, what were modesty but a fetter and a fouling of the mind?**++若无邪狎，那羞怯除了是精神上的束缚和污垢外还能是什么？**++They trapped into some kind of complex whirlpool that could not get extrication. This fetter makes people forget the final pursuit of humanity that is calm , simple , free.**++人生来是简单的，和文明打交道之后变得复杂了，陷入了某种复杂的旋涡中 无法自拔，这些羁绊使人忘记人性的最终追求是平静、简单、自由。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1107', 'fiasco', '[fɪæsko]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fiasco', '{n.}', '++The currency fiasco will accelerate these trends.**++货币改革的惨败将会加快这些趋势。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1108', 'fickle', '[fɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fickle', '{adj.}++(在感情、兴趣、忠诚等方面)易变的，不定的，不专一的，水性杨花的**++(天气等)反复无常的，变幻莫测的**', '++Some people attribute it to the fickle ambience over the whole city.**++有些人归结于，是因为整个城市充满浮躁的气息；**++Unreal Passion is lust, it’s based on fickle things like beauty or money and it eventually burns out.**++虚假的激情是贪欲，它建立在易变的事物如美貌和钱财的基础上，最终是会消失的。**++In the decades after the Second World War, kabuki slid into decline as other forms of entertainment caught the public’s fickle fancy.**++在第二次世界大战后的几十年里，由于其他娱乐形式吸引了公众浮躁的想象力，歌舞伎滑向衰落。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1109', 'fictitious', '[fɪktɪʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fictitious', '{adj.}++小说(中)的，像小说的；想像的，虚构的，杜撰的**++不真实的；假装的；习惯上假定的，假设的**++虚假的，假的**', '++The characters in this story are all fictitious.**++这个故事里的人物都是假想的。**++The story my mother told me when I was young is fictitious.**++小时候妈妈对我讲的那个故事是虚构的。**++This example is fictitious, but it demonstrates the point.**++这个示例是假想的，但它能说明问题所在。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1110', 'fidelity', '[fɪdɛləti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fidelity', '{n.}++(对职责、义务等的)忠诚，忠实；守信；尽职**++(翻译等的)准确，精确；(描述的)逼真**++(收音、录音设备等的)逼真度，保真度，保真性**++【生态学】确限度**', '++They betokened their fidelity to the leader with a vow.**++他们以宣誓来表示他们对领袖的忠诚。**++With sweat on my brow I ate my bread, yet in all these practices there is evidence only of my fidelity, nothing of enjoyment.**++带着眉头上的汗水，我吃我的面包，在所有这些修行中只见我的忠诚，而无享受。**++We will support those revolutions with fidelity to our ideals, with the power of our example, and with an unwavering belief that all human beings deserve to live with freedom and dignity.**++我们将支持那些革命，同时保持对我们的理念的忠诚，以我们的榜样做为力量，并坚定不移地相信所有人类都理应过上自由和有尊严的生活。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1111', 'figment', '[fɪɡmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=figment', '{n.}++想像的事，空想，幻想，虚构**++虚构的理论、故事等**', '++Part of the answer is that those earlier profits were in part a figment of the accountants’ imaginations.**++部分的原因是，那些早期的利润是会计师们想像力虚构的一部分。**++From a scientific perspective we may even say that the chair that you@re sitting on is just a figment of your imagination, because only the eternal is real.**++从科学的角度，我们甚至可能会说，你正坐着的椅子只是你想象的一个碎片，因为只有永恒是真实的。**++Being one myself, I know that they are not just some figment, but the truth of the matter is, gaming is male dominated, the same way knitting is dominated by females.**++因为我本人就是一个游戏迷，所以知道这样的女孩绝非虚构。 然而事情的真相是，视频游戏是男人的地盘，就好像编织衣物大多由女人从事一样。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1112', 'figurative', '[fɪgərətɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=figurative', '{adj.}++比喻的，借喻的，隐喻的**++用图形表现的，用形象、象征、符号等表现的**++象征性的；表象的**++爱用比喻的；比喻多的；有文采的；用修辞手段的**', '++This topic can be literal, such as price updates on a particular stock, or figurative, such as events from the database.**++这个主题可以是很明确的，比如某只股票的价格更新，也可以是比较宽泛的，比如来自数据库的事件。**++Bulls (of the figurative kind) contend that the economics of farming are enjoying a secular improvement as the climate changes, as people in emerging markets adopt more protein-based diets, and so on.**++看涨者（比喻的说法）称，由于气候变化，新兴市场的人们采用更多以富含蛋白质食品为基础的饮食等原因，务农的经济效益有所改善。**++Rob is talented figurative artist. Paintings below are painted by using oil colors. Rob@s every painting shows different emotions which is the style of his work.**++罗伯是一位才华横溢的人像画家。下面这几幅是油画。罗伯的每一幅作品，都流露出不同的情绪，这已经成为他的一种风格。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1113', 'figurine', '[,fɪɡjərin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=figurine', '{n.}', '++The centerpiece of the project, is a 20 centimeter limited edition figurine picked out in nearly 20,000 crystals -- and carrying a price tag of nearly 15 thousand US Dollars.**++该展览的核心展品是一个从近两万个水晶中挑选出来的20厘米高的限量版小雕像，该雕像还带着一个接近1.5万美元的价格标签。**++This recycled fair trade plastic bag chicken figurine is handcrafted by disadvantaged crafters in the townships near Cape Town, South Africa, and produced exclusively for Wow!**++这组可回收的平价公鸡小塑像是由一群南非开普敦附近乡镇的贫民工匠们手工制作完成，并且专供给WOW进口公司。**++This recycled fair trade plastic bag chicken figurine is handcrafted by disadvantaged crafters in the townships near Cape Town, South Africa, and produced exclusively for Wow! Imports.**++这组可回收的平价公鸡小塑像是由一群南非开普敦附近乡镇的贫民工匠们手工制作完成，并且专供给WOW进口公司。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1114', 'filibuster', '[fɪləbʌstɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=filibuster', '{n.}++【历史】擅自入侵与本国政府和平相处的国家的冒险家；尤指19世纪领导对拉丁美洲国家进行军事远征的美国冒险家；海盗；强盗**++[主英国英语](在议会中)使用阻挠议事的战术，拖延技巧，拖延办法(少数派议员在议会上用不正当或阻挠性战术，如用冗长的演说等阻挠采取普遍拥护的措施，或强行通过几乎一致不赞成的决定)**++[主美国英语] ＝ filibusterer**{vi.}++擅自侵略外国；进行海盗活动**++[主美国英语](以冗长演说或提出不相干的问题等手法)阻挠议事进程：**{vt.}++[主美国英语](以冗长演说或提出不相干的问题等手法)阻碍(议案)通过：**++[主美国英语](以冗长演说或提出不相干的问题等手法)阻碍(议案)通过：**', '++If all of them choose to support a filibuster, then you take it to the American people and show the obstructionists for what they are.**++如果他们人人都选择支持国会拖延方案，那么你可以向美国人民展示这些阻碍者到底是什么人。**++The Democrats lack the 60 votes that would enable them to overcome any threat of a Republican filibuster in the 100-member Senate as they did in the House.**++在100名参议员组成的参议院，要像在众议院那样，化解共和党人阻碍议案通过的威胁，民主党需要获得60张选票的支持。**++Of course, these pages were less eager to abolish the filibuster when the idea was floated by the Republicans in 2005, but put that aside.**++当然，当共和党在2005年首次提出那问题的时候，论战并不急于废除冗长的政治演说陋习，不过这是后话。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1115', 'filter', '[fɪltɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=filter', '{n.}++(过)滤器，滤清器；滤纸**++适于过滤用的多孔物质(如砂、炭、毡、纸等)**++(香烟头上的)过滤嘴；[口语]有过滤嘴的香烟**++【物理学】**++滤波器**++滤光器；滤光镜，滤光片**{vt.}++过滤(液体或气体)：**++用过滤法除去(固体粒子或杂质等)，滤出，滤清(常与off或out连用)：**++起滤器作用：**{vi.}++漏过，滤过，透过：**++渗，渗入：**++(消息等)走漏，泄露，慢慢传开：**++[英国英语](分流车道上的车辆)根据绿色箭头灯所示行驶，限阈通行**{adj.}++[口语]过滤嘴的**', '++You need to filter the drinking water.**++你需要把饮用水过滤。**++The crankcase has to drain before you put on the new filter.**++在安放新过滤器之前，曲轴箱必须滴干。**++At this time of day you need to filter out the red light to take a good photo.**++在一天的这个时候，你需要过滤掉红光才能把相照好。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1116', 'finale', '[fɪnæli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=finale', '{n.}++[意大利语]**++【音乐】(连章乐曲的)最后乐章；每幕歌剧的最后一首歌曲，终曲**++(戏剧、文娱节目的)最后一场；最后一幕**++结尾，结局，结果，收尾，最后部分**', '++How do you feel about the season finale?**++你对第二季结局的感觉怎样？**++Well, how do we feel now about the finale and why?**++我们对最终乐章感觉如何,这感觉从何而来**++Sometimes what you don@t do means a thousand times more than what you do, as the film@s bittersweet finale proves.**++有时候，你什么也不做比你做了的一千倍更甚（我这一句翻得好绕口啊），就像电影苦乐参半的结局一般。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1117', 'finesse', '[fɪnɛs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=finesse', '{n.}++纤细，精细；灵巧，机敏；微妙**++手腕，手段；技巧**++谋略，巧计，计谋；诡计**++【桥牌】飞牌，飞张(虽有高分的牌但先出较低分的牌保留好牌以冒险赢的手法)**{vt.}++施巧计，耍权术，动用策略；巧妙处理：**++【桥牌】用(牌张)飞**{vi.}++施展巧计**++【桥牌】飞牌,飞(常与 for, against 连用)**', '++Clearly, some sort of finesse is required.**++显然，还需要一些更好的策略。**++This can take some finesse to get the desired size.**++这样可以使一些策略获得理想的大小。**++Finesse the situation thing by asking "what is the one thing you would change or improve about your experience with us or our product ?**++巧妙地处理这种情况通过问，“根据你的经历，你想改变或者改进你或者产品的一样东西是什么？”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1118', 'finicky', '[fɪnɪki]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=finicky', '{adj.}', '++They all look the same to you (red), but Marslings are very, very finicky about shades of red in a way that you never imagined.**++他们在你看来都一样（红色的），但火星人就是非常非常讲究红色的那种细微变化，这是你所永远无法想象的。**++Whether dealing with a demanding boss, difficult client or finicky users, you have to impress them with your attitude and service.**++无论是与要求过多的老板、难处的客户还是吹毛求疵的客户，你应加深他们对你态度与服务的认可。**++No matter who you@re shopping for and how finicky their tastes, we@ve landed some truly exceptional surprises—from patterned pillows (hello auntie!) to cool wooden tools and slick minaudieres.**++不管你为谁买东西，还是他们的品味有多挑剔，我们列出了一些真正意外的惊喜——从各式枕头到清凉木制工具和手袋。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1119', 'fitful', '[fɪtfəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fitful', '{adj.}++不规则的；间歇，断断续续的；一阵阵的**++不定的**', '++When he slept it was short and fitful and then he would awaken, crying again.**++当他睡着时，有片刻间歇，可一当他醒来，就会接着哭。**++Such sleep as she got was naturally fitful; she fancied she heard strange noises, but persuaded herself that they were caused by the breeze.**++她这样睡觉自然是断断续续的；她总觉得听见了奇怪的声音，但是她又劝自己说，那些声音只不过是由风引起的。**++Yet I know that I must be content in my love, with what is fitful and fugitive.**++我明白我必须满足于这短促的爱情，因为我们不过是在路途中邂逅相逢。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1120', 'flaccid', '[flæsɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flaccid', '{adj.}++(肌肉等)不结实的，松弛的，松软的**++无力的；软弱的，虚弱的**', '++Globally, polio surveillance is at historical highs, as represented by the timely detection of cases of acute flaccid paralysis.**++就全球而言，从及时发现急性弛缓性麻痹病例可以看出，脊灰监测工作已达到历史最高水平。**++On 4 April WHO Yemen was informed by Hudeida governorate health authorities of a cluster of acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) cases in children, the first cases of which had occurred in February 2005.**++4月4日，荷台达省卫生部门向世卫组织驻也门办事处通报了儿童中急性弛缓性麻痹病例的群集，这是2005年2月发生的第一批病例。**++These additional cases were expected, as a significant increase in acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) cases had been detected since the start of the outbreak.**++自暴发开始以来随着发现急性弛缓性麻痹病例显著增加，预料到会发生这些增加病例。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1121', 'flag', '[flæg]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flag', '{n.}++旗；旗帜；国旗**++军旗；团旗；军舰旗，旗舰旗，司令旗；(骑兵队或摩托化部队的)队旗**++[复数](鸟、猎鹰的)胫羽；次级飞羽**++【狩猎】(塞特科猎狗或鹿的)茸尾；鹿尾**++【音乐】符尾**++【新闻学】**++(印有报刊名的)报头(栏)**++(介绍报纸杂志的名称、发行者姓名以及编辑人员姓名、广告收费、订费等的)报头栏，报头**{vt.}++悬旗于…；用旗装饰(或表示)：**++用旗或其他信号使(人、汽车等)停下(常与down连用)：**++用信号发送(消息、情报等)：**++在档案、卡片等上用指引卡作标志，用标记表明**++(挥旗或旗状物)诱捕(如猎物)**++[美国英语]【军事】给…贴上有色旗号标志，加旗号(指将一面有色小旗放在一个档案或卷宗夹上，以防止任何改动)，在(卷宗等)上放置特殊标志色的小旗(以防止被篡改等)**++【计算机】用标记标明，给(存储者的数据、程序等)做标记，加旗号于(存储的数据或程序等)**{n.}++=flagstone**{vt.}++用石板铺(路等)，铺石板**{n.}++【植物】**++有长刀状叶子的植物的总称，如鸢尾；菖蒲；香蒲**++= sweet flag**++= cattail**++鸢尾花(或叶)；菖蒲花(或叶)；香蒲花(或叶)**{vi.}++(精神)萎靡；(人)衰颓；(草木等)凋谢：**++变衰弱，疲倦；(力气、兴趣、热情等)衰退，减退：**++失去吸引力；变得枯燥无味**++变慢：**{abbr.}', '++The girl was draped in the flag.**++这个女孩裹在旗子里。**++Some plants flag in hot, dry weather.**++一些植物在干旱的天气里会枯萎。**++You can get anything of these prizes,if you can string this flag up on the top of the flagpole.**++如果你能把这面旗子挂到旗杆顶部，你就可以拿这些奖品中的任何一件。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1122', 'flamboyant', '[flæmbɔɪənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flamboyant', '{adj.}++灿烂的，醒目的，惹眼的**++火焰似的；火红色的；(色彩)鲜明的**++夸张的，浮夸的，浮华的，虚饰的，奢华的**++【建筑学】火焰式的**{n.}++【植物】凤凰木**', '++But one day flamboyant sin will be back to help Mr Goodman and his city out.**++但是有一天，奢华的罪恶会重新回来，那将挽救古德曼先生和它的城市。**++Horns have a certain appeal to the more flamboyant among us, but I@ve never liked them.**++角对我们之中那些更加引人注目的人有一定的吸引力，但我从来都不喜欢角。**++However, nothing has shaped his colorful reputation more than his flamboyant fashion sense.**++然而，没有比他奢华的时尚感更能塑造他多彩的人性了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1123', 'flatter', '[flætɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flatter', '{adj.}{vt.}++向…谄媚，阿谀奉承，恭维，过分夸奖：**++(用赞扬或关照)使高兴；讨好，巴结，迎合，殷勤取悦：**++使比真容(或实物)似乎更好(或更吸引人)，(画、肖像等上的形象)胜过(真人或实物)：**++(利用献殷勤或恭维话)使感到高兴(或荣幸)，使喜悦，使满意，满足…的虚荣心：**++使显得优点突出：**++(尤指由于成功或某种行为，某个场合)使(自己)感到满足，自己感到得意**++(尤指虚伪地)鼓励，怂恿**{vi.}++奉承；说恭维话；作谄媚的举动**++引起奢望**{n.}++敲平工，弄平的人或物**++【机械工程】扁条拉模，拉扁钢丝模**++【机械装置】平(面)锤；压平机；扁平槽**{adj.}++平的，小平的，平坦的；无凹凸的**++平卧地上的；倒下的；伸平的，平展的，展开的**++平放的，平靠着的**++薄的，扁(平)的，浅的 **++(鞋)平跟(或无跟)的，平底的**{adv.}++断然地，突然地，干脆地，直截了当地**++平直地，水平地，平坦地**++完全地，彻底地，全然地**{n.}++平的东西，扁平之物**++平地；平原**++低沼泽；平滩，浅滩**++(主要供小孩用的)版面大的薄本书**++【园艺学】(栽培秧苗的)浅箱；浅苗床**++平底船 **++平台甲板**{vt.}++使变平**++【音乐】使(音调)下降，尤指降半音**{vi.}++逐渐变平**++【音乐】以降调唱(或奏)**++【航海学】将(帆)收近龙骨线，把(纵帆)的后下角尽量向船中央拉(与in连用)[亦作flatten in]**', '++Of course to flatter someone is to say nice things about them.**++当然了，奉承某人就是指对某人说中听的话。**++I say no at first, but they persist. They promise to work around my schedule; they flatter me.**++一开始我说“不”，但是对方坚持，保证按我的日程安排，还奉承我，对我说，“我们需要你！”**++In William Shakespeare’s play Julius Caesar it is said that a sure way to flatter Caesar is to remind him how he hates flatterers.**++在剧作《凯撒大帝》中，莎士比亚写道，奉承凯撒大帝最稳妥的方法就是，告诉他他是如何地憎恨奉承者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1124', 'flaw', '[flɔ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flaw', '{n.}++碎裂；裂纹，裂缝，缝隙**++瑕疵，缺点**++(使证件、程序等无效的)缺陷，毛病，不完备**{vt., vi.}++(使)有裂纹；(使)有裂缝；(使)有瑕疵，(使)有缺陷；使无效**{n.}++一阵(常伴有雨或雪的)狂风；短暂的风暴[亦称作 windflaw]**++短时间的恶劣天气**++[废语]一阵激情、愤怒等，勃然大怒**', '++So they flew through a flaw in the flue.**++就这样，它们就飞越了烟道里的一条裂纹。**++It was a large diamond, but it had a flaw.**++这是颗大钻石, 但它有一点瑕疵。**++Your goal with a "Who I Am" story should be to reveal some type of flaw about yourself or mistake that you@ve made.**++“我是谁”这个故事的目的应该是向你的成员们透露一些你的缺点或你以前曾经犯过的差错。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1125', 'fledgling', '[flɛdʒlɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fledgling', '{n.}++刚生羽毛(或刚会飞)的小鸟**++新手，缺乏经验的年轻人，初出茅庐者**', '++We see Christianity,this fledgling movement, starting to imitate the structures of the Roman Empire.**++看到了基督教形成，这个萌牙的运动，开始模仿罗马帝国的结构。**++Avatar communication has the potential to change that, and this potential defines the potential of our fledgling industry.**++虚拟交流有改变的潜力，这种潜力揭示了我们这个新兴产业发展的潜力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1126', 'fleet', '[flit]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fleet', '{n.}++舰队(为战术或其他目的海军舰只编成的最大单位)**++舰队(由一人指挥的军舰编成的最大单位)**++(运送兵员的)舰队**++[the fleet] 海军**++(统一指挥下的或一起行动的)船队，卡车队，公共汽车队，机群**++[英国英语]有100只钩子的钓索；渔网阵(连成一排的捕鱼网具)**{vi.}++迅速移动，飞逝而过**++[古语](像溪流)漂流，流过；漂泊**++[古语]消逝；消失，消散**++[废语]漂浮，漂流**++[废语]游泳**++【航海学】(船员)变换位置，移动**{vt.}++[罕用语]消磨(时间)**++【航海学】变换(索、缆等)的位置**{adj.}++迅速的，快速的；敏捷的**++[诗歌用语]短暂的，瞬息即逝的**{n.}++[英国方言]小(海)湾，海湾；小港**++[方言]下水道，阴沟**++[the Fleet]**++(伦敦)弗利特河(流入泰晤士河，现已成阴沟)**++【历史】弗利特河畔的债案犯监狱[亦作 Fleet Prison]**', '++They maintain a very powerful fleet in Oriental waters.**++他们在远东海域保持着一支非常强大的舰队。**++Our warships bottled up the enemy fleet in the harbour.**++我方军舰把敌方舰队围困在港口内。**++An enormously powerful fleet was concentrated at Pearl Harbour.**++一支极其强大的舰队集结在珍珠港。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1127', 'fleeting', '[flitɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=fleeting', '{adj.}', '++Time is fleeting.; Time flies.**++时光飞逝。**++At the deepest level, in the core of her soul, even fleeting connections with others seem to interfere with what she desires most.**++在心灵的最深处，灵魂的最核心，甚至与他人转瞬即逝的接触，对她内心的渴望也是一种打扰。**++Previously its popularity has proved fleeting - will this time be any different?**++从前它的流行总是转瞬即逝——这次会有什么不同吗？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1128', 'flexible', '[flɛksəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flexible', '{adj.}++易弯(曲)的，柔韧的，可弯曲的**++易被说服的，易受影响的；柔顺的，温顺的**++易适应的，可变通的；有弹性的；灵活性的**', '++In this way, you can be flexible in understanding the binding requirements.**++以这样的方式，在理解绑定需求的时候你可以很灵活。**++This flexible framework allows any object to be translated into another type.**++这一灵活框架让任何对象都可被转换到另一类型。**++What if we were more flexible with what we could do with our time?**++如果我们更灵活的处理我们可利用的时间会怎么样？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1129', 'flinch', '[flɪntʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flinch', '{vi.}++退却，缩回： **++(因疼痛等)退缩：**{vt.}++[古语]从…退缩，对…畏缩不前**{n.}++退缩，畏缩**++【牌戏】弗林奇(把纸牌按规定顺序叠放在桌上的游戏)**{vt.}', '++This is a well-established method of measuring instinctive attraction to an image, given that those in a more upbeat frame of mind flinch less.**++这是一种已被大家广泛接受的测量对照片的本能吸引性的方法，即假定那些看照片时感觉更快乐的人，对噪声更少感到畏惧。**++I stand for this. If we meet the world with eyes that do not flinch and hearts that are open, we will find ourselves capable of what is asked of us.**++我坚信，如果我们用无所畏惧的眼睛和开放豁达的心灵和世界相遇，我们会发现自己拥有着所应具备的东西。**++And if we stick with it, if we don@t flinch in the face of some difficulties, then I feel absolutely convinced that we are going to get this economy back on track.**++如果我们坚持不懈，如果我们面对困难不退缩，那么，我坚信不疑：我们一定会把目前的经济重新纳入轨道。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1130', 'flippancy', '[flɪpənsi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flippancy', '{n.}++无礼；鲁莽，傲慢；轻率**++[复数]-cies无礼的举动(或言论)**', '++To those outside the company, it may be interpreted as a sign of flippancy or lax discipline.**++对外人而言，我们的习惯可能会是轻率的和纪律松懈的表现。**++F: To the outside world, our custom may be interpreted as a singn of flippancy or lax discipline.**++对外人而言，我们的习惯可能会是轻率的和纪律松懈的表现。**++Nothing could be in worse taste than misplaced flippancy; and he answered somewhat stiffly: "Yes, you have been away a very long time."**++没有什么东西比不合时宜的轻率更有伤大雅了。 他有点生硬地回答说：“是啊，你离开这儿已经很久了。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1131', 'flirt', '[flɝt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flirt', '{vt.}++急速摆动；急挥(尾巴)，挥动(尾巴、折扇等)：**++[罕用语]急速投，突然扔掉，急扔：**{vi.}++卖弄风情，卖俏，调情，调戏(with)：**++玩弄，戏弄；做着玩；不认真地对待(或考虑)(with)：**++颠簸(或不稳定)地移动，摆动；飘动；急冲；拍动：**{n.}++急扔；急动；急掸；(尾巴等的)快速摆动；急挥**++调情者，卖俏者，卖弄风骚者**', '++If you flirt with me, I’ll have to leave.**++如果你要跟我调情，我立刻就走。**++Knows how to flirt.**++知道如何调情。**++He@ll shamelessly flirt with other women in front of you.**++他会在你面前毫不羞耻的跟别的女人调情！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1132', 'flit', '[flɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flit', '{vi.}++轻快地过去，掠过：**++轻快地飞过，作短距离飞行；(鸟)振翼：**++(如时间)飞逝：**++[苏格兰和英格兰北部方言](尤指不声不响地)迁居，搬家；偷偷溜走；去世，亡故**++[废语]转变，改变；背离**{vt.}++[苏格兰和英格兰北部方言]迁移，迁居；撵走，剥夺**{n.}++掠过；轻快的飞行；飞来飞去；迁移**++[美国俚语]男子同性恋者；脂粉气的男子**', '++You watch your thoughts, perceptions, and emotions flit through your mind without getting involved.**++你看着你的念头、感知和情绪掠过你的头脑而并不牵涉其中。**++When it comes to complex scenes, for example, Westerners focus on central objects but East Asians also flit their eyes across the backgrounds.**++比如，当人们遇到复杂的场景，西方人会专注核心的物体，而东方亚洲人的目光还是会掠过那些背景信息。**++Although thoughts which flit through the mind may be good, bad, or indifferent -- mostly the latter -- the mind does not usually hold on to any one of them sufficiently long to learn its nature.**++虽然，在脑海中掠过的想法是好的或者是无关紧要的——大多数是后者——大脑往往不能对它们中的任何一个坚持足够长的时间去认识它的本质。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1133', 'flock', '[flɑk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flock', '{n.}++畜群；兽群；鸟群(指在一起喂养或聚居的同种动物，如羊、山羊、绵羊等牲畜或飞禽)**++一大群人；一大批东西；一班学生；一家的子女**++(对牧师而言)教会内的全体教徒**++(对基督而言)全体基督教徒**++[古语]一队人，一帮人，一伙人**{vi.}++成群结队而行，群集；聚集；簇拥；蜂拥：**++成群结队而行，群集；聚集；簇拥；蜂拥：**{n.}++毛束，棉束，棉丛**++[有时作复数](填塞沙发垫、椅垫、褥垫、床垫等用的)毛屑，棉屑，布屑，废棉**++[有时作复数](供植绒用的)短绒**++= floc**{vt.}++用毛(或棉)屑填塞(或填充)**++用短绒覆盖(或装饰)为…植绒**', '++A few sheep have been lost from the flock.**++羊群里少了几只羊。**++A flock of sheep are ranging over the grassland.**++一群羊在草原上来回走动。**++The shepherd re-collected his flock and went down the hillside.**++牧羊人把他的羊群重新集合在一起，走下山坡。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1134', 'florid', '[flɔrɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=florid', '{adj.}++(脸色)红润的，微红的，血色好的，玫瑰色的**++(文艺风格、装饰等)华丽的，绚丽的；炫耀的；华美的**++[废语]用花装饰的；像花似的；多花的**++[古语]健康的**++【医学】(病症)充分发展的，显示出全部典型临床症状的**', '++So we@ve got the root here of the--and then the trunk and then up above, this florid canopy would musically be the what?**++我们来看看这里的根，然后是树干再往上，样华丽的树冠在音乐上被称为什么呢？**++The world is urgent with bursting life, with the wild exciting beauty of youth, but it is an impetuous beauty of the senses racing impatiently into the florid and surfeited luxury of summer.**++春天的世界里满是焦燥爆长的生命，满是年轻疯狂的美丽，然而这是一种感官的轻薄的美丽，随即便浮夸地堕入华丽奢侈、狂喝滥饮的夏天。**++In her face were too sharply blended the delicate features of her mother, a Coast aristocrat of French de¬scent, and the heavy ones of her florid Irish father.**++因为她母亲是个法兰西血统的海滨贵族。 父亲是个皮色深浓的爱尔兰人，所以遗传给她的质地难免不调和。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1135', 'flounder', '[flaʊndɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=flounder', '{vi.}++(在水、泥泞或深雪中)挣扎，肢体乱动；踉跄地走(常与about， along， on， through等连用)：**++(因糊涂而)犯错误；笨拙、错乱地说(或做)：**{n.}++挣扎，踉跄行走；笨拙而错乱的行动(或言语)**{n.}++【鱼类】**++川鲽(欧洲川鲽属比目鱼,Platichthys flesus)**++除鳎以外的比目鱼总称**++任何相似的非欧洲产的比目鱼的统称**', '++Why It@s Bad: This group of fish includes flounder, sole, and halibut that are caught off the Atlantic coast.**++它有害的原因 ：这类鱼包括在大西洋海岸捕获的比目鱼、鲳鱼以及大比目鱼。**++The guests were seated at the table when their host strode in with a platter, holding the biggest flounder they@d ever seen.**++客人已在餐桌边就座完毕，这时主人大步地走进来，手里端着一个托盘，托盘上是一个他们所见过的最大的比目鱼。**++Sadly they are likely to flounder unless the Americans do more than just nudge them along.**++然而不幸的是，除非美国做更多的工作，双方将继续挣扎。**');
