insert into GREWordBook values ('1285', 'hamstring', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hamstring', '{n.}++【解剖学】 绳腱**++＝ hamstring muscle**++抑制力；取缔**{vt.}++切除(或割断)…的腱，(割断腘绳肌腱)使致残，使残废**++[比喻]阻碍；使丧失活力；破坏…的效能(或作用)，使不起作用，使无效；削弱，减弱…的活动能力:**', '++Meanwhile, work on strengthening and stretching your hip, hamstring and lower-back muscles.**++与此同时还要拉伸和增强你臀部、腿筋和腰背部的肌肉。**++However, if you have an existing hamstring injury, be sure to introduce these poses gradually.**++如果你已经有腘绳肌损伤，一定要循序渐进地进行这些练习。**++Far more telling was the correlation between the various runners’ tight or loose hamstring muscles and their running economy, a measure of how much oxygen they used while striding.**++进一步讲，不同跑步者腿筋肌的松紧和步伐频率是有联系的，这是一种对他们在跨步行进时耗氧量的评估。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1286', 'hangdog', '[hæŋdɔɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hangdog', '{adj.}++卑鄙的；卑躬屈膝的，下贱的**++羞愧的；感到有罪的**++鬼鬼祟祟的**{n.}++卑鄙的人，下贱的人；畏怯的人**', '++Right. When the criminal appeared in the court with a hangdog look, all the people were standing up excitedly .**++是呀。当他带着愧疚的神态出现在法庭时，所有在场的人都激动地站了起来。**++The beaming Betty Crockers, hangdog dowdies and parochial prudes who call themselves feminists want men to be like women.**++令人愉快的贝蒂汽车保养，令人愧疚的邋遢女人和眼光狭隘的保守女人，她们称女权主义者希望男人变得跟女人一样。**++A man sat at a bar, had the saddest hangdog expression.**++一个男人坐在酒吧里，伤心至极。 。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1287', 'hanker', '[hæŋkɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hanker', '{vi.}++渴望，热望，追求(常与after， for或不定式连用):**++渴望，热望，追求(常与after， for或不定式连用):**{n.}++= hankering**', '++So people who hanker to express their own views find that their voices are muffled.**++于是那些渴望表明自身观点的人发现他们的声音是如此含混不清。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1288', 'haphazard', '[ˌhæphæzərd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=haphazard', '{adj.}++偶然的，随意的，任意的，无计划的**{adv.}++偶然地，随意地**{n.}++偶然性，随意性**', '++Yes, that seems to express the rapidity of life, the perpetual waste and repair; all so casual, all so haphazard.**++对了，这些比拟可以表达生活的飞快速度，表达那永不休止的消耗和修理；一切都那么偶然，那么碰巧。**++All the master had to do was shake the tree a little and the garden was full of leaves again, spread out in haphazard patterns.**++大师什么都没有做，只是摇了摇树。 花园又重新被凋落的树叶覆盖了，整个花园展现出随意的样式。**++After wrangling my hair into a knotty, haphazard bun, I made my way to class. I was nearly trampled as perfectly coiffed women scurried past me to the room.**++把头发缠绕成一个多节随意的发束之后，我向课堂走去，还差点被一个向教室冲进去的打扮漂亮的女人从身上踩过去。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1289', 'harangue', '[həræŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harangue', '{n.}++(长篇)演讲，慷慨激昂的演说**++高谈阔论，冗长的说教(或训话、文章等)**{vt.}++向…作长篇演讲；大声训斥:**++向…作长篇演讲；大声训斥:**{vi.}++高谈阔论；慷慨陈词**', '++They will hesitate to come to the manager with the problem again, because they won@t want to sit through another harangue.**++被咆哮者再次遇见问题时将会犹疑着去报告经理，因为他们不想耐着性子听完另一次长篇大论。**++Russia@s state-run television, which frequently airs news flattering of Russia@s leadership, broadcast Mr. Medvedev@s harangue without showing Mr. Kudrin@s reply.**++俄罗斯国有电视台播出了梅德韦杰夫的长篇大论，但没有播出库德林的回应。 俄罗斯国有电视台经常播出讨好俄罗斯领导人的新闻。**++EVEN as America’s politicians harangue the bankers, the bankers are sniping back.**++正如美国的政客抨击银行家一样，银行家现在正在回击。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1290', 'harass', '[hærəs, həræs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harass', '{vt.}++(不断地)骚扰，扰乱，烦扰:**++使痛苦，使苦恼；使困乏:**++侵略，掠夺**++【军事】(以间断性的攻击)侵扰**', '++Never, ever threaten or harass in your letter.**++千万不要在你的信中表示威胁或抱怨。**++You know your mistress@s nature, and you encouraged me to harass her.**++你知道你的女主人的性格，而你还鼓励我去惹她生气。**++And what about abolishing the Transportation Security Administration, which has done so much to harass those who travel by commercial air and to violate their Fourth Amendment rights?**++废除美国运输安全局怎么样？ 该部门侵扰了许多坐商务机旅行的人们，并违反了第四修正案中规定的这些人的权利。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1291', 'harbinger', '[hɑrbɪndʒɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harbinger', '{n.}++通报者，预告者；先锋；先驱**++预示，先兆；预言者**++【历史】(王室、军队等的)先遣人员，先行官，先头部队**{vt.}++告知…的到来，为…作先驱；预告，预示:**++告知…的到来，为…作先驱；预告，预示:**', '++Kendrick is convinced that I am a harbinger of a new species of human, as different from everyday folks as Cro-Magnon Man was from his Neanderthal neighbors.**++肯迪克确信我是一个新的人类物种的先驱，作为有别于人类的克鲁马努人就是从他的邻居尼安的特人而来的。**++Yet, each is just a harbinger of what@s to come this year, as data of all sorts is assembled instantly by compelling applications.**++而这每一个示例都只是今年的趋势的一个预兆，所有类别的数据都会被应用程序即时组装在一起。**++In itself, this was just an example of the Big Unfriendly Giant flexing its muscles, but it could be a harbinger of things to come.**++例子本身只是说明这位不友善的巨人是如何展示他的肌肉的，但它也许可以被看作一个预兆。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1292', 'harbor', '[hɑrbɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harbor', '{n., vt., vi.}++[美国英语] = harbour**++[1150前]**', '++She stands on a small island in New York harbor, near the great city.**++她竖立在纽约海港的一座小岛，并紧挨着纽约这座大城市。**++At first, my father slept outside, near the harbor, where hundreds of other men also camped out, most of them refugees like him.**++起初，父亲睡在外面，靠近海港，那里有几百人搭着帐篷，绝大多数都是像他一样的难民。**++As for people who love us but whom we do not love, we may be indifferent, or at least would not harbor such a deep overall concern.**++至于爱我们但我们不爱的人，我们可能是不关心的，或者至少不会怀有这样一种深切的全面关心。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1293', 'hard-bitten', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hard-bitten', '{adj.}++(经过痛苦)磨炼的，顽强的，强悍的，冷酷的；现实主义的**++(犬等)咬起来凶狠的**++= hard-boiled**', '++Left a hard-bitten stone alone.**++一个破碎的石子，独自痛哭。**++It requires a firm knowledge, a quick brain, a hard - bitten determination, a noble personality and great spirit as well as a very practical attitude.**++发挥创造性不仅要有深厚的知识功底、敏锐的头脑、坚韧不拔的意志，而且还要有高尚的人格、崇高的精神和实事求是的科学态度。**++When you had fallen to the bottom of your life, every people around you would tell you: Be hard-bitten and be happy!**++当您下落了对您的生活底部，每人在您附近会告诉您： 是不易对付的并且是愉快的！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1294', 'hardy', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hardy', '{adj.}++习惯吃苦的，能吃苦耐劳的**++坚强的；强壮的**++大胆的，勇敢的；鲁莽的，蛮干的**++【园艺学】耐寒的；有抗性的**{n.}++强壮的人**++【园艺学】耐寒植物**{n.}', '++So over the next six months CEO Roger Hardy and his senior team called customers each week to see whether they had any ideas.**++因此，接下来的六个月，首席执行官罗杰•哈迪和其高管层每周都给客户打电话，看看他们有何想法。**++I would have preferred the Hardy Boys, preferred to gallop alongside the Riders of the Purple Sage, but I was afraid of teachers then, and so I read.**++我本可以选择看《哈迪男孩》，我本可以选择看《紫艾灌丛中的骑士们》，但当时的我太怕老师，所以还是读了《杀死一只知更鸟》。**++John and Cynthia Hardy founded an eco-friendly school that provides students with quality education in one of the most beautiful places on the planet.**++在我们星球其中最美丽的一个地方，约翰和辛西娅哈代创建了一所给学生提供素质教育的生态学校。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1295', 'harmonious', '[hɑrmonɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harmonious', '{adj.}++【音乐】和声的**++音调和谐的，声音好听的，悦耳的**++谐和的，调和的，协调的，匀称的**++和睦的，融洽的**', '++Things may not be as harmonious as you would like with colleagues or employers this week.**++这周你与同事或老板间的关系并不太和谐，你一定要小心应付。**++For every student， an educational treasure every opportunity to better each lesson， do everything to promote the health of every student， harmonious， all-round development.**++面向每一个学生，珍惜每一个教育机会，上好每一堂课，做好每一件事，促进每一个学生的健康、和谐、全面的发展。**++You can harmonious development of society on the passion and friendship.**++你们能够和谐地发展，社会就充满热情与友爱。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1296', 'harness', '[hɑrnɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harness', '{n.}++马具，挽具**++(织机)综𪩞； 通丝具**++[古语] (人、马的)甲胄，铠甲**++挽具状带子(如汽车的安全带等)**++【航空学】降落伞吊带**++装置，装备；工作设备**++【电工学】线束；组合配线**++【航天学】(飞船上的)导线(系统)**++大钟悬挂装置**++职守，日常工作**++[美国俚语]**++警察制服**++(电工或摩托车手的)全套衣帽装备**{vt.}++套(马)，给…上挽具；栓住，系住:**++控制…以产生动力，利用:**++抑制，约束，驾驭:**++[古语]给…穿上甲胄(或铠甲)**', '++You just need to know how to harness them.**++你只是需要懂得如何好好驾驭它们。**++We must harness the rivers which overflow annually.**++我们必须治理那些每年泛滥的河流。**++Now, what we are worried about in commercial nuclear power is our ability to harness the energy of a fission and this chart explains where that energy comes from.**++现在，我们要担心的，在商业,核能里的是，我们能够驾驭裂变能量,的能力，这个图表解释了,那个能量是从哪里来的。**');
