insert into GREWordBook values ('1298', 'harry', '[hæri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harry', '{vt.}++烦扰，骚扰；折磨，使苦恼:**++抢劫，掠夺；蹂躏；(不断)袭击:**++强使前进，推(某人)前进:**++[苏格兰英语]抢走**{vi.}++抢劫，掠夺:**++抢劫，掠夺:**{n.}++烦扰；烦恼，痛苦**++掠夺；袭击**{n.}++恶魔，恶鬼**++(下流)胡闹的年轻人，野小子**++[俚语]伦敦佬**', '++Harry is for our plan and Jim is against it.**++哈里同意我们的计划而吉姆反对它。**++If I were you, I would explain to Harry what happened.**++如果我是你，我会去向哈利解释事情的经过。**++I debated upon the question with Harry.**++我与哈里辩论过此问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1299', 'harsh', '[hɑrʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=harsh', '{adj.}++粗糙的，毛糙；手感粗糙的**++刺耳的，难听的，不和谐的**++喘哮的；喘哮声的**++刺目的**++粗陋的，不优美的**++(气味)难闻的，刺鼻的**++(味道)苦涩的，难吃的**++严厉的，严酷的，严峻的，苛刻的；无情的；艰苦的，艰巨的**++不平的，崎岖的，多岩石的**++(土地)荒芜的**', '++Ten days ago, I received some pretty harsh criticism.**++十天前，我受到了一些颇为严厉的批评。**++The harsh truth is that if you build a website for everyone, it will appeal to no one.**++严酷的事实却是：如果你为所有人建立一个网站，你就一个人都诉求不到。**++But, if we are well trained, the underwater part of things is not really as harsh as you might think.**++但是，如果我们受到良好的训练，水下部分的事情可能就不会真的像你想像的那么严酷。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1300', 'hasten', '[hesn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hasten', '{vt.}++催促；使赶快，使赶紧:**++加速，加紧:**{vi.}++赶快，赶紧；急忙:**++赶快，赶紧；急忙:**', '++Do thou hasten to the king@s side.**++你赶快到国王这边来。**++The crisis gives us the opportunity to hasten this process.**++这次危机使我们有机会加速这一进程。**++Its shareholders will soon have a chance to hasten the process.**++它的股东们将很快有一个机会来加速这一进程。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1301', 'hasty', '[hesti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hasty', '{adj.}++急促的；急速的，匆忙的**++仓促完成的，匆忙赶制的**++草率的，轻率的**++性急的，急躁的；易激动的；动怒的**++激动(或动怒)时所说(或做)的；不耐烦的**++急切的；短暂的**++[古语]迅捷的**', '++A brave man would see catharsis in all this misery; a wise man would not be so hasty.**++一个勇敢的人能看到他不幸中的万幸，而一个聪明的人却不会如此轻率。**++But he was too hasty and too zealous in ways that were as damaging to his client as his colleagues` Nazi tirades were to theirs.**++但他在态度上太过与草率和热情，这就像他的同行的纳粹党人激烈的长篇大论一样，对他的当事人有害无益。**++A senior UK executive says the news should be digested over more than just a “few lazy summer weekends” and “hasty judgements must be avoided”.**++英国一名高层管理人员表示，这个消息远不止是“几个懒散的夏天周末”这么简单，而且“必须避免草率的判断”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1302', 'haunt', '[hɔnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=haunt', '{vt.}++常去，常到(某处):**++缠住(某人):**++常与…交往:**++(思想、回忆等)萦绕在…心中；缠扰，使苦恼；使担忧:**++布满，洋溢在:**++(鬼魂等)常常出没于；老是附在…身上:**{vi.}++经常逗留；存留:**++交往(后与 with 连用):**++(鬼魂等)经常出没，作祟**{n.}++常去的地方**++(动物的)栖息处，生息地**++(坏人等的)巢穴，老窝**++／hɔ:nt，hænt／ [主方言]幽灵，鬼**++[古语]风俗，习惯(作法)**', '++People say ghosts haunt that old house.**++据说那座老宅子有鬼魂出没。**++The Wanglang Preserve in western Sichuan is the haunt of the giant panda.**++川西的王朗自然保护区是大熊猫出没的地方。**++One reason that is not so farfetched: transgenerational effects are showing up not only in lab rats but also in people, as if the ghosts of our ancestors haunt our very genes.**++有一个理由是靠不住的：继代影响不仅传现在实验室老鼠身上，也出现在人类里。 就好像我们先辈的幽灵经常出没于我们特有的基因里。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1303', 'hauteur', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hauteur', '{n.}', '++Various explanations are offered for Obama@s unfeeling hauteur and Europe@s consequent heartache.**++对奥巴马的冷酷傲慢，以及给欧洲带来的伤心，有多方面的解释。**++A deeper shade of hauteur overspread his features, but he said not a word, and Elizabeth, though blaming herself for her own weakness, could not go on.**++一阵傲慢的阴影罩上了他的脸，可是他一句话也没有说。 伊丽莎白说不下去了，不过她心里却在埋怨自己软弱。**++In those days everything from furniture to festivity was designed to be enjoyed by the many, so that whatever of pomp or magnificence there might have been did not savour of hauteur.**++在那些日子里，从家具到节庆，一切都是为众人的享用而设计，因而无论有多么富丽堂皇，都没有倨傲的气息。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1304', 'haven', '[hevn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=haven', '{n.}++港口，停泊处**++安全的地方，避难所；安息地**{vt.}++使入港，使停泊：**++为…提供庇护所：**', '++We haven@t enough evidence to prefer charges.**++我们没有进行起诉的充分证据。**++The party was a haven of quiet amid the noise and bustle of the streets outside.**++外面街道上熙来攘往，一片喧闹嘈杂之声，那个公园坐落其间，真是安静的世外桃源。**++We haven@t enough money to buy a new apartment, so we@ll just have to do without.**++我们没有足够的钱买一套新公寓房间，所以只好将就了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1305', 'havoc', '[hævək]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=havoc', '{n.}++(天灾、战争等造成的)大破坏，大毁灭**++[口语]大混乱，杂乱**++[古语](向士兵发出的)洗劫号令**{vt.}++损毁(某物)，严重破坏：**++损毁(某物)，严重破坏：**{vi.}++损毁，严重破坏：**++损毁，严重破坏：**', '++The earthquake wreaked havoc on the city.**++地震对这座城市造成了大破坏。**++The earthquake wreaked havoc on the city.**++地震对这个城市造成了大破坏。**++He points out that some past offenders in Michigan have been released only to cause havoc and end up in jail again.**++他指出，过去密歇根释放的一些犯人只是与造成严重破坏的人有关，而且最后又都重新回到监狱里。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1306', 'headlong', '[hɛdlɔŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=headlong', '{adv.}++头朝前地**++倒栽葱地，倒立地**++急速地，猛然地，迅猛地**++鲁莽地，轻率地，仓促地**++一往无前地**{adj.}++头向前的**++头朝下的**++迅猛的，急速的**++鲁莽的，轻率的**++[古语]陡峭的**', '++An unfortunate mistake that many organizations make is to jump headlong into J2EE without really understanding what it is.**++许多组织都犯了一个很不幸的错误，就是很轻率的就跨越到 J2EE，但是并不真正理解它是什么。**++For Obama that transition has been sobering and daunting — a headlong collision with the reality of the White House and a political culture more resistant to change than he ever imagined.**++对于奥巴马来说，这一转变不仅透心凉也是惊心魄——莽莽撞撞地与白宫及一种超出他想象的对变革有所抗拒的政治文化发生了抵触。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1307', 'hearken', '[hɑrkən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hearken', '{vi.}++[书面语]倾听，留意，留心(常与 to 连用)**{vt.}++[古语]**++倾听；留心**++听明白，听出；听后得知 [亦作 harken]**', '++Hear now my reasoning, and hearken to the pleadings of my lips.**++请你们听我的辩论，留心听我口中的分诉。**++Wherefore, Job, I pray thee, hear my speeches, and hearken to all my words.**++约伯阿，请听我的话，留心听我一切的言语。**++The household went to bed; and I@ too anxious to lie down, opened my lattice and put my head out to hearken, though it rained: determined to admit them in spite of the prohibition, should they return.**++全家都去睡了，我急得躺不住，便把我的窗子打开，伸出头去倾听着，虽然在下雨，我决定只要是他们回来，我就不顾禁令，让他们进来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1308', 'hearten', '[hɑrtn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hearten', '{vt.}++使振作，鼓舞，鼓励；使有勇气:**++使振作，鼓舞，鼓励；使有勇气:**{vi.}++振作起来(常与 up 连用):**++振作起来(常与 up 连用):**', '++To inspire with hope, courage, or confidence; hearten.**++鼓励，鼓舞以希望、勇气或信心等鼓舞；使振作。**++The Grand Admiral even attempted in vain to hearten his dispirited colleague Ishin-Il-Raz, lending him a copy of the sacred book Secrets of the Dark Side.**++这位帝国元帅甚至借给伊欣—伊尔—拉兹圣卷《黑暗之秘》的副本，徒然地试图振作他沮丧的同僚。**++He said a lot to hearten me.**++他对我说了许多鼓励的话。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1309', 'heartrending', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=heartrending', '{adj.}', '++With Cosette, and behind her, there had entered a man with white hair who was grave yet smiling, though with a vague and heartrending smile.**++在珂赛特后面陪着她进来的是一位白发老人，态度庄重，但含着微笑，可这是一种捉摸不定和沉痛的微笑。**++And, heartrending to say, there, behind the pile of stones, in front of the tree with the sheet of zinc, was freshly turned earth, a pick-axe, abandoned or forgotten, and a hole.**++而最使人痛心的是，在那堆石块后面，钉有锌牌的树脚下，有刚刚翻动过的泥土，留下的是一把被遗忘或被抛弃了的十字镐，还有一个土穴。**++The heartrending story of the massacre in Nanjing, shortly after it fell to Japanese in late 1937, commonly known as "the rape of Nanking", is the subject of two movies, which premiere a week apart.**++相隔一周的时间，两部记载1937年日军占领南京后的悲惨大屠杀题材的电影先后公映。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1310', 'heckle', '[hɛkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=heckle', '{vt.}++质问，诘问，责问(演说人、表演者等)，诘难；对…起哄；困扰，使难堪:**++【纺织业】栉梳(亚麻纤维等)**{n.}++责问(或起哄)的行为**++【纺织业】**++手工梳麻台**++(栉梳机的)针排**', '++I heard some of the audience heckle me with loud whistles.**++那天，我听到观众中有人大声吹口哨向我起哄。**++You should encourage audience members in mock-ups to heckle you and ask the toughest, meanest questions imaginable .**++在“演习”时，你应该鼓励听众刁难你，提出最艰涩、残酷的问题。**++“I couldn’t believe that he was so accessible that I could literally shake his hand and heckle him about needing to suit up because his team was losing, ” Mr. Clark said.**++科拉克说，“他如此平易近人，真是难以相信。 说实在的，我可以和他握手，也可以要他穿起衣服，因为他的队已经输了。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1311', 'hedonism', '[hidənɪzəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hedonism', '{n.}++追求享乐，享乐主义，享乐主义生活方式**++【哲学】快乐论**', '++But haven@t yet asked, should we accept hedonism?**++但我们还没问，是否应该接受享乐主义？**++Hedonism is a version of the neutral container theory.**++快乐主义就是中性容器理论的一种。**++America@s infamous bastion of dirty feel-good hedonism dishes out some seriously sinful culinary creations.**++美国那臭名昭著的自我感觉良好的快乐主义堡垒创造出了一些罪恶的菜肴。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1312', 'hegemony', '[hɪdʒɛmoni]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hegemony', '{n.}++支配，统治**++支配权，统治权，领导权**++盟主权；霸权**++霸权国；拥有支配权的政府**', '++To what extent it is capable of leveraging these powers to upend Western hegemony of technology is a truly fascinating question.**++中国会在什么程度上利用这些力量来推翻西方的技术霸权，这确实是一个引人遐思的问题。**++This belief was exploited with success by neoconservatives and others in the Bush government, who hoped to cement a permanent US global hegemony.**++布什政府里的新保守派和其他派系成功地利用了民众这一信念，他们希望巩固美国永久的全球霸权。**++The mega-trend in the background is the rise of China and the relative decline of the US - and the expression of this will be the gradual challenge to American military hegemony in the Pacific.**++第四 国际格局的大趋势是中国实力的增长和美国的相对衰落，而这一趋势的表现是中国将会一步步地挑战美国在太平洋地区的军事霸权。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1313', 'heinous', '[henəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=heinous', '{adj.}++可恨的，可恶的；凶恶的**++(罪行、罪犯等)十恶不赦的，令人发指的**', '++“This is a heinous act that undermines the fairness that should be the basis of the university entrance system,” Japan@s largest daily, the Yomiuri Shimbun, warned in an editorial on Monday.**++“这种可憎的行为破坏了高考体系的公平性。” 日本最大的日报读卖新闻在星期一的社论中警告说。**++In the sequel to the 2008 animated megahit, a heinous peacock named Lord Shen (Gary Oldman) invents a weapon that could do just that.**++在2008年的动画佳作续集中，一个令人发指的孔雀沈王(加里配音)发明一种武器可以那么做。**++The idea that any country may take action against pirates is the precursor to the idea of “universal jurisdiction” used to prosecute heinous crimes such as genocide.**++任何国家都有权采取行动对抗海盗的理念也是“普遍管辖权”的前身（这种权利被用来起诉一些极恶的罪行，如种族灭绝）；**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1314', 'herald', '[hɛrəld]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=herald', '{n.}++(旧时)皇家信使；传令官，(比武大会等的)宣令调度官；掌礼官；使节**++报信者；使者**++通报者，报道者**++预告者，预报者；先驱，前锋**++预兆，先兆**++【英国历史】司宗谱纹章的官员**{vt.}++预告；宣布，报告…的消息：**++引进；引领：**++为…欢呼；欢迎：**', '++He was assembling a complication that sent a little gilded boy with a trumpet through a door in the clock face to herald the birthdays of its owner@s family.**++他正在组装一个复杂的钟，这个钟里面要安装一个镀金的小男孩，手里拿着一支小号，从钟面上的一扇门出来，通报主人家人的生日。**++While working as a secretary for the publisher of Washington State@s Inland Herald, she criticized his prose so vocally that he replaced her and made her an editorial writer instead.**++在身为秘书，替华盛顿州的内陆先驱出版社的出版商工作时，她直言不讳的批判了他的散文，以至于他调动了她的工作，干脆让她去做社论了。**++The New York Herald, meanwhile, proposed that the federal government should wait until the war ended and sell all the slaves back to their owners, at half-price, to finance its cost.**++纽约先驱报在当时也建议联邦政府应该等到战争结束，然后把这些奴隶再卖会给他们的主人，可以半价出售来支持其战争成本。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1315', 'heresy', '[hɛrəsi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=heresy', '{n.}++异教，异端；异教邪说**++信奉异教；持异端邪说，离经叛道**++信奉异教者，离经叛道者**', '++To not do so was almost heresy.**++不这样做的话，就是异教徒。**++Ministers began to preach sermons against "Ephemera," and one, who too stoutly stood for much of its content, was expelled for heresy.**++牧师们开始布道，反对《蜉蝣》，有一个牧师因为坚决维护那诗的内容，竟被以异端罪逐出了教会。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1316', 'heretical', '[hərɛtɪkəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=heretical', '{adj.}++异教的，异端的；左道旁门的，离经叛道的**++信奉异教的，持异端的；持左道旁门观点的**++异教徒的，持异端者的**', '++It@s such a heretical idea that it@s not even up for discussion.**++这是一个如此异端的想法，以至于它根本不会被讨论。**++Still, the Emerging Church movement is treading on ground that traditionalists call unorthodox, if not heretical.**++但是，新兴教会运动所走的路即使不被传统派看作是异教，也被看作是非正统的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1317', 'hermetic', '[hɝmɛtɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hermetic', '{adj.}++密封的，密闭的；不透气的**++炼金术的；魔术的**++神秘的，奥妙的；难以理解的**++隐居的，独居的；不受外界影响的**++[常作H-]赫耳墨斯特利斯墨吉斯忒斯(著作、学说)的**++(诗的内容玄妙，深奥的)玄奥诗的**{n.}++炼金术士**++赫耳墨斯特利斯墨吉斯忒斯学说阐述者 [亦作hermetical]**', '++The TMA-5 undocked at 10:44 p.m. Moscow time on Sunday, after a four-minute delay caused by problems with the hermetic seals on Vittori@s spacesuit, Mission Control officials said.**++控制中心的官员说，莫斯科时间周日晚上10点44分，“TMA-5”号宇宙飞船飞离空间站，之前由于维托里的太空服的真空密封层出现了问题，起航行动延迟了4分钟。**++The last few months have been something of a challenge for Apple, known for maintaining a kind of hermetic seal around itself and its products.**++苹果一直把自己和自己的产品都密闭起来，而这前几个月给苹果带来了一些挑战。**++We also found pins blindfolded and read papers on our discoveries to the Hermetic Society that met near the roof in York Street.**++我们还蒙上眼找钉子，或是在报纸上阅读有关我们“秘术学会”的新发现。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1318', 'hesitance', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hesitance', '{n.}', '++In this society in particular, there is a hesitance to touch one another.**++在这种特定的社会，触摸彼此总是让人犹豫不决。**++Hesitance and a nay-saying mentality will be asvisible as a red tie and seen as a negative.**++犹豫和拒绝的心态将会是赫然醒目的，消极的信号。**++The offer is seen as part of an effort to ease tension over U.S. military strikes recently on the Pakistan side of the border, and U.S. impatience with Pakistan@s hesitance to fight insurgents.**++此举被认为是为了缓和美国最近对巴基斯坦边境一侧发动军事袭击以及不满巴基斯坦在打击激进分子上行动迟缓所引发的紧张关系。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1319', 'heterodox', '[hɛtərədɑks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=heterodox', '{adj.}++异教的，异端的**++非正统的，离经叛道的，特异的**++信奉异教的；持异端见解的**', '++None of these heterodox options are available to Ireland, say the wise heads.**++头脑聪明的人说，对爱尔兰俩来说，这些非正统的选项连一个都不存在。**++The only thing that matters is the salvation of the incorporeal, the bodiless soul, but Milton is so unorthodox, or at least heterodox, in his insistence on the importance of the body in this poem.**++基督教强调只有非物质的非肉体的心灵的救赎，才是重要的，但弥尔顿是如此异端，至少不正统，在诗中一直强调肉体的重要性。**++I declined answering Mrs Dean@s question, which struck me as something heterodox.**++我拒绝回答丁太太的问题，这问题使我觉得有点邪道。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1320', 'hew', '[hju]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hew', '{vt.}++(用刀、斧等)砍，劈，剁：**++砍倒 (与 down 连用)：**++砍掉(与 away、 from、 off连用)：**++劈成，砍出；切成，凿成：**++开辟；奋力做出：**{vi.}++劈,砍(与 at、 among连用)：**++[美国英语]坚持；遵守(与to 连用)：**{abbr.}', '++Hew out of mountain of despair a stone of hope.**++从绝望之山上砍下来一块希望之石。**++And ye shall overthrow their altars， and break their pillars， and burn their groves with fire； and ye shall hew down the graven images of their gods， and destroy the names of them out of that place.**++也要拆毁他们的祭坛，打碎他们的柱像，用火焚烧他们的木偶，砍下他们雕刻的神像，并将其名从那地方除灭。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1321', 'hidebound', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hidebound', '{...}++...**', '++The hidebound health-care systems of the rich world may resist new technologies even as poor countries leapfrog ahead.**++在发展中国家跨越式发展的同时，发达国家保守的医疗体系则可能会抵制新技术。**++The Southern Newspaper Group was an oasis of open-minded thinking in the state’s hidebound media empire, and it was known for pushing the limits within the propaganda apparatus.**++在中国墨守成规的媒体版图里，以思想开放著称的南方报业集团是一块绿洲，在身为宣传工具的同时，却也在不断试探底线。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1322', 'hideous', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hideous', '{adj.}++极丑陋的；可怕的**++令人厌恶的；令人惊骇的，骇人听闻的**++令人局促不安的；令人沮丧的**++荒谬可笑的**++[口语]庞大的**', '++Every article on the breakfast table was fetched away with a hideous crash.**++早餐桌上的每件物品随着可怕的撞击声移动了位置。**++People might think you have a hideous bowel disease or perhaps a fiber fetish.**++人们可能会认为你有一个可怕的肠道疾病或者纤维恋物癖。**++Don@t be afraid to ask someone that same question whose color you think is hideous, so you know where not to go.**++不要害怕问同一个问题关于一些人谁的颜色你认为可怕，因此你才知道什么地方不应该去做。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1323', 'hie', '[haɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hie', '{vi.}++赶紧，赶快；快走，急行(常与 to连用)：**++赶紧，赶快；快走，急行(常与 to连用)：**{vt.}++使赶快，催促；使急行(常与 one 或 oneself 连用)：**++使赶快，催促；使急行(常与 one 或 oneself 连用)：**', '++Why don@t you hie home?**++你怎么还不赶快回家?**++It forms the basis for most Health Information Exchange (HIE) implementations.**++它形成了大部分健康信息交换 (HIE) 实现的基础。**++Objective To study the application of ultrasound diagnosis of various brain injury caused by hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy (HIE).**++目的探讨超声诊断在新生儿缺氧缺血性脑病（HIE）各种脑损伤中的应用价值。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1324', 'hierarchical', '[,haɪərɑrkɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hierarchical', '{adj.}++等级制度的；等级森严的**++等级分类的，分类体系的**++圣职等级制的；教主的**++主教团的，僧侣统治集团的**++僧侣统治的**++有政治权的；有影响的**++【宗教】天使的[亦作 hierarchic]**', '++The mapping table is a common construct that allows you to map one hierarchical structure to another.**++映射表是一种常见的构造，允许您将一个分层结构映射到另一个中。**++Unlike other side-by-side mapping tools, the mapping table does not provide full mapping power of any hierarchical structure to another.**++不同于其他并行映射工具，映射表不提供将任何分层结构映射到另一结构的完整映射功能。**++For larger clusters, a hierarchical approach is needed, with the management node being connected to two or more service nodes and the compute nodes being provisioned from the service nodes.**++对于一个较大的集群，则需要一个分层的方式，且管理节点要连接到两个或多个服务节点，计算节点要从这些服务节点得到供应。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1325', 'hike', '[haɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hike', '{vi.}++徒步旅行，远足；步行，长途步行；旅行：**++[口语](移动)上提；升高，飘起；扬起，飞起(常与 up连用)：**++[美国口语](价格等)上升，上涨(与up连用)：**++[美国俚语]在高空检修电线：**++【航海学】侧风行船**{vt.}++带…徒步旅行；使作徒步旅行：**++[美国口语](猛地)拉；提；举(与up连用)：**++[美国口语](尤指急剧地)提高，抬高，增加(数量、价格等)：**++[美国俚语]涂改(支票)的金额，加大(支票)的面额**{n.}++徒步旅行，远足；步行，长途步行；行走**++[美国口语]涨价；(数量、数额等的)增加，提高**++【美式橄榄球】中锋裆下开球**', '++He wants to hike round the world.**++他打算徒步旅行环游世界一周。**++You can hike there or drive through the park.**++你可以远足或驾车穿过公园到达那里。**++The bear leader bear-led a group of wealthy young men on a cross-country hike.**++家庭教师带领一组富家子弟作越野远足。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1326', 'hilarious', '[hɪlɛrɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hilarious', '{adj.}++高兴的，快乐的，兴高采烈的**++欢闹的，狂欢的**++引人发笑的，滑稽的**', '++The focus is solely on the shirts and the hilarious design.**++这些注意力完全放在衣服和欢闹的设计上了。**++But I love my awful life so much right now, that I find it hilarious when I am unable to convince anyone else of it.**++即时它摧毁了我的家，但现在十分我喜欢我糟糕的生活，当我不能使其他人确信是我发现它是欢闹的。**++So, again, we hear hilarious discussions on how to control the population.**++所以，我们再次听到了关于控制人口的滑稽的讨论。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1327', 'histrionic', '[hɪstrɪɑnɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=histrionic', '{adj.}++演员的；表演的，戏剧上的**++演戏似的，装腔作势的，矫揉造作的**++【医学】面部肌肉的**{n.}++演员**', '++Yet again, I find myself doubting tabloid claims of real mental illness and prefer to attribute bad behavior to spoiled narcissism or histrionic acting out.**++再一次地，我发现自己开始怀疑他们是真的精神疾病患者还是更喜欢做出消极的行为来满足自己的自恋癖或是表演欲。**++The committee would also do away with a few other less well-known problems, such as histrionic personality disorder, and add in a scale to rate the severity of such traits.**++委员会也废去了其他一些不知名的问题，如表演型人格障碍，在一定程度上加大了这些特点的严重性。**++Obama and McCain avoided a histrionic debate about China during the 2008 campaign and Obama probably thought he had a free hand on China policy.**++奥巴马和麦凯恩在2008年的选战中没有就中国进行做秀似的辩论，也许奥巴马就此认为他在对华政策上可以从心所欲。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1328', 'hive', '[haɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hive', '{n.}++蜂巢；蜂箱，蜂房**++蜂团，蜂群**++熙熙攘攘的人群**++蜂巢状物**++熙熙攘攘的场所，喧闹繁忙的地区**{vt.}++使(蜜蜂)入蜂箱**++贮存(密)于蜂箱中**++贮存，把…存起备用(常与up连用)：**{vi.}++(蜜蜂)进入蜂箱；(蜜蜂)生活在蜂箱中**++(像蜜蜂般)聚居，密集群居：**++藏身；隐居(常与 up连用)**{n.}', '++Remember to destroy every single structure in each Hive complex.**++记住要摧毁每个结构在每个蜂房复杂。**++What people must remember is that one hive quickly become two, two become four and four become eight.**++人们一定要记住的是，一个蜂巢很快会变成两个，两个变成四个，四个变成八个。**++Once they return to the hive, this can be detected, and a scan of the chip will reveal the appropriate location.**++一旦它们回到蜂巢，就能够检测到这些物质，扫描芯片也能显示其准确的位置。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1329', 'hoard', '[hɔrd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hoard', '{n.}++隐藏，贮藏**++聚藏的钱财；贮藏物；秘藏物**++(知识等的)宝库；(古代的)宝窟**{vt.}++聚藏，贮藏；隐藏：**++聚藏，贮藏；隐藏：**{vi.}++积聚钱财；贮藏货物：**++积聚钱财；贮藏货物：**{n.}', '++Do not hoard it.**++不要储藏它。**++They hoard them, trading them in for pity points when they find another victim—er, friend.**++他们在囤积它们，在找到另一个受害人（呃，朋友)时，用它们来换取怜悯。**++Regardless of the food supply, they will hoard it, not knowing how long they will be at sea.**++如果不管食物储备的话，他们就会储藏大量食物，因为他们不知道将会在海上呆多久。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1330', 'hoary', '[hɔri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hoary', '{adj.}++(年老而)头发变白(或变灰白)的；白发的**++年纪高迈的，老年的**++(头发等)白色的；灰白的**++陈旧的，古老的；陈腐的**++【植物学、昆虫学】生满灰白毛的，被灰白毛的**', '++But as the years have passed, what were once fresh ideas have hardened into hoary dogmas.**++但是随着时间的流逝，一度新鲜的观念也变成了陈腐的教条。**++Land rose from its womb, usurped its throne, and ever since the maddened old creature, with hoary crest of foam, wails and laments continually, like King Lear exposed to the fury of the elements.**++大地从它的腹中隆起，篡夺了它的王位。 从那以后，暴怒的老家伙就开始顶着灰白色的泡沫不断的哀号恸哭，一如暴风骤雨之中的李尔王。**++In spite of his hoary hair and beard he was as young as the youngest of us, his venerable exterior serving only as a white mantle for keeping his youth perpetually fresh.**++虽然他须发斑白，却和我们当中最小的那位一般年轻；他年高德劭的外表，却像一件雪白外衣使他青春永不褪色。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1331', 'hoax', '[hoks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hoax', '{vt.}++欺骗，戏弄：**++欺骗，戏弄：**{n.}++欺骗，愚弄，戏弄；恶作剧**++骗局，圈套**', '++I wish this was a hoax.**++我希望这是一次恶作剧。**++I researched both the video and the circumstances surrounding it, and provided a list of reasons why I concluded that the videos were "almost certainly a hoax.**++我研究了视频和它周围的环境，提出了一些为什么我推论这段视频几乎可以确定是一次恶作剧的原因。**++The colleagues who perpetrated the hoax lost their jobs and reputations over the scandal.**++那些设计骗局的同事则既丢了工作又因丑闻毁了名声。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1332', 'hobble', '[hɑbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hobble', '{vi.}++一瘸一拐地走路，跛行；蹒跚：**++摇晃不稳(或颠簸)地行进；不顺利地进行：**++结结巴巴地说话：**{vt.}++使跛行：**++把(牲口等)的腿捆绊住，捆绊(马腿等)：**++阻碍，妨碍；束缚：**{n.}++跛行，跛行步态**++【体育】(用以套住几匹定步速的马的)束套 **++捆绊牲口的绳索(或重物等)**', '++The Spain midfielder missed the midweek Champions League victory over Porto because of the hamstring problem which had seen him hobble out of the win against Burnley.**++西班牙中场在上周与伯尔利的比赛中蹒跚下场，正因为这次腿部的伤势使他错过了周中对阵波尔图的冠军杯比赛。**++This will hobble the development of cheaper sources of clean energy, delaying the much-needed expansion of clean energy markets and increasing costs for U. S. consumers.**++这将阻碍廉价清洁能源资源的开发，延迟迫切需要的清洁能源市场的扩大，并且会增加美国消费者的支出。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1333', 'hodgepodge', '[hɑdʒpɑdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hodgepodge', '{n.}++杂烩菜**++混杂物，大杂烩；混乱的一堆，一团糟**{vt.}++使混乱**', '++For years, a hodgepodge network of seed banks has been amassing seed and shoot collections.**++多年来，大杂烩般的种子银行网已累积了大量的种子和芽的收藏库。**++The animal is best described as a hodgepodge of more familiar species: the duck (bill and webbed feet), beaver (tail), and otter (body and fur).**++把这种动物形容为熟悉物种的大杂烩最恰当不过了：鸭子（喙形嘴和有蹼的脚），海狸（尾巴），和水獭（身体和毛皮）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1334', 'homage', '[hɑmɪdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=homage', '{n.}++尊敬，崇敬；敬意**++(封建制度下的封臣对君主的)效忠宣誓礼，效忠仪式**++(封建君臣间的)君臣关系，主仆关系，主从关系**++(表示效忠的)奉献物；效忠之举**++讨好的关心，献殷勤**', '++The friend left these pictures as an homage to the painter.**++那位朋友留下这些画,来表达对画家的敬意**++His work is a homage to the female body, often allowing his materials to direct the shape and curves of his subject.**++他的作品传达了对女性身体的敬意，这通常就使得他的作品主题都直指曲线与轮廓。**++If actual grandparents are not at hand, no family should have too hard a time finding substitute ones to whom to give unfeigned homage.**++如果实际生活中祖父母不在身边，没有哪个家庭会艰辛的为了找到替代祖父母们让我们给以真诚的尊敬。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1335', 'homely', '[homli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=homely', '{adj.}++像家一样的，舒适的，友好的，亲切的**++适合家庭(生活)的；家常的，简单的；平常的，普通的**++无装饰的，素色的**++朴实无华的，不做作的**++原始的，无饰的**++类似的，相像的**++[美国英语]相貌平常的，不漂亮的**++[古语]熟悉的，亲切友好的**', '++I like that restaurant because it has a homely feel.**++我喜欢那家餐馆，因为那有家的感觉。**++Members such as photographer Carl Warner stages pictures that at first look like homely painted landscapes – until you realise the trees are made of broccoli, the houses of ham.**++成员们，比如摄影师卡尔·华纳分阶段上演绘画作品，乍看起来就像家庭绘画场景——直至你意识到，树是用西兰花做的，房子是用火腿做的。**++Squat, homely, dwarfed by the stately oaks and poplars nearby and unnoticed by the tourists passing in horse-drawn carriages, it@s a tree that only birds and nut-hungry squirrels could love.**++它矮小平凡，旁边高大笔直的橡树和杨树让它相形见绌；坐着马车从它身边经过的游客都不会瞅它一眼，可能只有鸟儿和想吃松子的松鼠会喜欢它。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1336', 'homily', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=homily', '{n.}++说教；布道**++(令人讨厌的)道德说教；陈词滥调**', '++Earlier, the Pope prayed for peace as he delivered his traditional Christmas Eve homily.**++稍早前，教宗还在他传统性的平安夜训诫中，为世界和平祈福。**++During his  homily, Pope Benedict addressed the issue of unity, which has been a theme of his visit.**++教皇本尼迪克特在他的布道中谈到了合一的问题，这也是他这次来访的主题。**++In his homily, Benedict issued an appeal for children who are abused, forced to live on the street or serve as soldiers.**++教皇在布道时为那些受到虐待、被迫在流浪街头或者当儿童兵的孩子们发出诉求。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1337', 'homogenize', '[homɑdʒə,naɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=homogenize', '{vt.}++使均匀，使均质，使纯一；使类同：**++使(牛奶、奶油等中的油脂粒)分布均匀，使均质**{vi.}++变均匀；变纯一；变类同**', '++Homogenize the connectivity of assets and services to support the business processes, and**++同质化资产和服务的连接性以支持业务流程，以及**++This mapping allows WebSphere Integration Developer to homogenize any differences between a source and target service pairs.**++该映射使 WebSphere Integration Developer 可以同质化源和目标服务对之间的任何差异。**++He points out that when regulators impose rules, the people they regulate must follow them and that, therefore, the rules homogenize behavior and prevent diversity.**++他指出，监管机构实施监管规定后，受到监管的人就必须遵守规定；因此，规定让行为同质化，消灭了多样性。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1338', 'hone', '[hon]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hone', '{n.}++(尤指磨剃刀的)细磨石，油石**++(精细)磨孔器；珩磨机**{vt.}++(在细磨石上)磨；珩磨：**++用磨孔器精磨(或扩大)(某个孔等)：**++磨炼，锤炼；使精通：**{vi.}++[美国南部、中南部方言]想念；渴望：**++[古语]咕哝，抱怨；呻吟；哀鸣**', '++If ethics and morals go together, you have to hone your skills at reasoning critically about ethical and moral issues.**++如果道德和道德价值取向一致，你得锻炼你严格推理有关道德和道德价值问题的技巧。**++"I should have been more of an equal and helped him hone his social skills, which I feel he still lacks, " he says.**++他说：“我应该以一种更平等的方式帮助他磨练自己的社交技能。 这也是他现在正缺少的。”**++It is at that point that we begin to actively, intentionally hone our characters.**++只是在那个时候，我们在主动地，有意识地磨砺我们的性格。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1339', 'hoodwink', '[hʊdwɪŋk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hoodwink', '{vt.}++哄骗，欺骗；蒙蔽：**++[古语]**++罩住(马眼)**++蒙住(某人的眼睛)：**{n.}++掩目，蒙眼**', '++Fishermen, however, may not be able to hoodwink consumers for much longer.**++但是，渔民可能再也无法欺骗消费者了。**++One tried and tested way is to hoodwink equity analysts, according to a new study* of 1,300 corporate bosses, board directors and analysts.**++按照一份新的对1300名公司老板，董事和分析师的调查论文显示，欺骗股票分析师是一个可以尝试的办法。**++The kind of lies we find most detestable are those with a malicious intent of some kind: lies designed to swindle or hoodwink us, lies that will cause us some pain down the road.**++那些最为我们所憎恶谎言就是那些存心不良的：要么是那些用来诈骗或者蒙混我们的，抑或是那些在将来会给我们带来伤痛的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1340', 'hortative', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hortative', '{adj.}++劝告的，忠告的**++勉励性的，起激励作用的**', '++If you are admired by your success, my benison is warmly and hortative contemplation traversing congested crowd.**++假若你成功受景仰，那麽我的祝福就是穿越拥挤的人群给你温暖鼓历的注视；**++The print is a hortative drawing. It tells us that everybody has shortcoming and the power of the individual is smaller than group.**++这幅图片是一张勉励的漫画，他告诉我们每个人都有缺点，一个人的力量总是不如集体的力量的。**++This text will draw on the international roughness index to deduce the minimum hortative wavelength, so as to reduce the error during the model conversation and numerical calculation of roughness.**++本文将从国际平整度测量方法上推知路面激励的最小波长，以减少平整度模型转化和数值计算中的误差。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1341', 'hovel', '[hʌvl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hovel', '{n.}++茅舍，陋室**++肮脏杂乱的住处**++(饲养牲畜的)棚舍，圈，栏；外层，杂物间**++=tabernacle**++窑的圆锥形外壳**{vt.}++使住在茅屋(或陋室、脏乱的住所)；把(牲畜)拴入棚舍；把…置于杂物间内：**++使住在茅屋(或陋室、脏乱的住所)；把(牲畜)拴入棚舍；把…置于杂物间内：**', '++The same house in a neighborhood of $500, 000 homes may feel like a hovel.**++同样的房子换到50万美元的小区里，他会觉得自己住的是茅舍。**++She died, many decades later, in 2007, in a Paris at peace, caged in her own filthy, darkened hovel, consumed with hatred, sick with fear.**++数年后的2007年，在巴黎已经一片平和之时，她却走了，在黑暗的小屋中，埋葬了她的不堪，耗尽了她的怨恨，重病却依旧在害怕的回忆着那些日子。**++At that moment, the farmer@s own son came to the door of the family 6)hovel. “Is that your son?” the nobleman said.**++这时，农夫自己的儿子走到了他们家小屋的门前。“那是您的儿子吗？”贵族问道。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1342', 'hubris', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hubris', '{n.}++傲慢，自大，自恃**++[希腊悲剧用语]蔑视(或傲睨)神明，狂妄野心(最终导致自身毁灭)[亦作hybris， 参较sophrosyne]**', '++One is hubris, and the other is the lack of people skills.**++一个是傲慢，另一个是缺乏人际交往技巧。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1343', 'humble', '[hʌmbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=humble', '{adj.}++谦卑的，谦虚的，谦恭的，恭顺的**++(等级、身份、重要性等)低下的；粗劣的，粗陋的；微末的**++(自我感觉)卑微的；卑下的**++卑躬屈膝的，奴颜媚骨的**{vt.}++使谦恭，使谦卑；使温顺：**++压下…的锐气，使威风扫地：**++使卑贱；贬低；羞辱：**', '++Iris excused herself with humble words.**++艾丽斯用谦逊的言词为自己辩解。**++And he tries to "prevent" them with his humble ode.**++弥尔顿努力想用谦逊的颂歌来“阻止“他们。**++Defeat and failure make people humble.**++挫折与失败会使人谦卑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1344', 'humdrum', '[hʌmdrʌm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=humdrum', '{adj.}++平常的，平凡的；单调的，无聊的，乏味的**{n.}++平凡；单调，无聊**++凡人**++无聊的人，令人厌烦的人**++无聊的工作(或生活等)**{vi.}++单调乏味地进行**', '++Imagination raises a man above the humdrum of life.**++想象使人从单调无聊的生活中解脱出来。**++In normal times, the humdrum business of shifting widgets from one location to another gets little attention outside the supply chain management fraternity.**++平常时期，除了供应链管理协会，几乎没人会注意这样一项单调工作：将小部件从一个地点运至另一地点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1345', 'humiliate', '[hjumɪlɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=humiliate', '{vt.}', '++Their goal is to humiliate us.**++他们的目的是羞辱我们。**++They want to humiliate us.**++他们是要羞辱我们。**++"Every time they shoot a rocket, we should react without any proportion in a way that will not only hurt them but also humiliate them," he said.**++他说：“他们每一次发射火箭，我们都应该以某种方式做出反应，不仅要给他们造成伤害，而且还要羞辱他们。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1346', 'humility', '[hjumɪləti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=humility', '{n.}++谦逊，谦恭**++[用复数]谦恭的行为**', '++And I found a path of both, I think, humility and power to walk down.**++我发现了一条能够沿着走下去的，融合了谦卑和力量的道路。**++But learning requires humility.**++但学习需要谦逊。**++Without humility none of this will happen.**++没有谦逊，这一切都不会发生。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1347', 'humor', '[hjʊmɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=humor', '{n., vt.}', '++His remarks participated of the sense of humor.**++他的话里带有几分幽默感。**++You can find humor in just about any situation.**++几乎在任何情况你都可以找到幽默的。**++She loved everything about him -- his personality, his humor, the way he dressed.**++她爱他的一切——他的性格，他的幽默，还有他的衣着打扮。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1348', 'hurricane', '[hɜːrəkeɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hurricane', '{n.}++暴风，暴风雨**++【气象学】十二级风，飓风**++飓风般猛烈的事物，风暴**++(感情等的)爆发，激发**++[H-](第二次世界大战期间英军使用的)飓风式战斗机 [参较 tropical cyclone, typhoon]**', '++Many buildings were demolished by a hurricane.**++许多房屋被飓风摧毁。**++Many coastal towns were desolated by the hurricane.**++许多沿海城镇遭到飓风袭击而荒芜。**++That means the water in one hurricane weighs more than all the elephants on the planet. Perhaps even more than all the elephants that have ever lived on the planet.**++这就意味着飓风中所含的水比地球上所有的大象加到一起还要重，也许会超过地球上曾经有过的所有大象体重的总和。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1349', 'husband', '[hʌzbənd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=husband', '{n.}++丈夫，夫**++节俭的人**++＝ ships husband**++[古语]**++管家**++(酒窖等的)管理人**{vt.}++节俭，节约；有效地利用 ：**++节俭地管理(或经营)：**++[古语]使有丈夫；做…的丈夫，娶(妻)**++拥护；信仰：**++[古语]耕(地)；栽培(植物)**', '++She dunned her husband for some money.**++她为了要一些钱跟她丈夫纠缠不休。**++My husband joins with me in congratulating you.**++我与我丈夫一道向你祝贺。**++He attempted to lure her away from husband and family.**++他企图引诱她离开丈夫和家庭。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1350', 'husk', '[hʌsk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=husk', '{n.}++(某些果实或种子的)干燥外皮，外壳；荚**++[美国英语](玉米的)苞叶；角豆树荚**++瘪壳，空壳**++[美国俚语]男子，家伙**++支架**{vt.}++除去…的外皮(或壳、荚)：**++脱(衣服)，使裸体：**{n.}++(嗓音等的)嘶哑**{vi.}++(嗓音)变得嘶哑：**++(嗓音)变得嘶哑：**{vt.}++以粗哑的嗓音说(或喊、唱等)：**++以粗哑的嗓音说(或喊、唱等)：**{n.}', '++How can we remove the husk of the grains?**++我们怎样去掉谷物的外皮？**++Brown rice is the whole grain, with only the outer tough husk removed, and so takes longer to cook than white rice.**++糙米是全麦的，且外皮是很硬，所以在做糙米饭的时候要比做白米饭花费更长时间。**++All the days of his separation shall he eat nothing that is made of the vine tree, from the kernels even to the husk.**++在一切离俗的日子，凡葡萄树上结的，自核至皮所作的物，都不可吃。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1351', 'husky', '[hʌski]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=husky', '{adj.}++壳的；有壳的**++多壳的，满是壳的**++似壳的**{adj.}{adj.}++[主加拿大英语]爱斯基摩人的，因纽特人的**{n.}++= Siberian husky**++[主加拿大英语]爱斯基摩人，因纽特人**++[主加拿大英语]爱斯基摩语**++= Eskimo dog**{adj.}++魁梧的，高大强壮的**++庞大的；强大的**{n.}++魁梧的人，高大强壮的人**++强有力的机械**', '++Gossip Girl without Chuck Bass is like a world without sunshine and rainbows and…a handsome, husky-voiced young adult in dashing three-piece suits!**++《绯闻女孩》没有了Chuck Bass就像是生活没有了阳光和彩虹...和一个爱穿时髦西装、声音沙哑磁性的帅气青年。**++It may not entirely be a coincidence when in the afternoon we get in our speedy riverboat (it@s a bit like a wide minibus) and visit some husky kennels upriver.**++所以，我们下午的活动看来不完全是偶然的：乘有点像小巴的交通船去参观爱斯基摩犬的狗舍。**++He cut me off then, his voice husky and low, almost a whisper.**++随后他打断了我的话语，他的声音沙哑而低沉，几乎在耳语。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1352', 'hybrid', '[haɪbrɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hybrid', '{n.}++【遗传学】杂种，杂交种**++混血儿；受两种不同文化(或传统)熏陶的人**++混成物，混杂物；混合源物**++混合物；合成物**++【语言学】混合词，混种词**{adj.}++杂种的，杂交的；杂交而生的**++合成的；混合(源)的，混杂而成的**++【物理学】(电磁波)混合的**++【电子学】**++(电路)差动式的**++(集成电路)混合式的，混合型的**', '++These have since been plumped, but with hybrid instruments that do not count as pure equity.**++于是这些与一些不被视为纯资产的混合的工具一起取得了支持。**++However, you can define both static and dynamic searches for the same object class if you have a hybrid group with both static and dynamic members.**++不过，如果有包含静态成员和动态成员的混合组，您可以为同一对象类同时定义静态搜索和动态搜索。**++We will also motivate the need for a hybrid approach that combines elements of all of the disciplines, with a number of distinct, new elements.**++我们还将推动对混合方法的需求，这种方法把所有这些规则中的原理与许多独特的新原理组合起来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1353', 'hymn', '[hɪm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hymn', '{n.}++赞歌，颂歌**++欢乐之歌；凯歌**++【宗教】圣歌，赞美诗**{vt.}++为…唱圣歌，唱赞美诗赞美(上帝)**++赞美，颂扬：**++用赞歌表达：**{vi.}++唱赞美诗(或圣歌)**++称颂，赞美，唱赞歌：**', '++She deaconed off a hymn.**++她带头唱赞美诗。**++Then on my mother@s side, there were 10 kids, all Lutherans – so I had the whole Lutheran hymn influence on top of that.**++我妈妈那边的家庭有10个孩子，全都是路德教徒，所以路德教的赞美诗对我的音乐影响最深。**++At the end of a Passover meal, they sang a hymn.**++在逾越节筵席结束时，他们唱起了赞美诗。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1354', 'hyperbole', '[haɪpɝbəli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hyperbole', '{n.}++【修辞学】夸张法**++夸张法的运用**', '++For Vicky, the film managed to convey "the hyperbole of cheese" when people get married.**++对于维琪，这部电影设法表达了“奶酪夸张法”当人们结婚的时候。**++In New York and across America, we face similar problems in all of these areas, but with all the hyperbole about China, it@s easy to forget that we remain substantially ahead.**++在纽约和整个美国，我们在所有这些领域面临类似的问题，但由于那些关于中国的夸张说法，我们很容易忘记我们仍然大幅度领先。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1355', 'hypnotic', '[hɪpnɑtɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hypnotic', '{adj.}++催眠的；催眠术的**++易受催眠的**++(易)引起睡眠的；(药物)安眠的**++处于受催眠状态中的**{n.}++安眠药；催眠方法**++(易)受催眠者**', '++What does hypnotic method have?**++催眠的方法有哪些？**++The symptoms of almost any disease can be induced in you by hypnotic suggestion.**++几乎所有疾病的症状都能够通过你内部的催眠暗示作用产生感应。**++The harmonious singing and rhythmic beats of the drums can be hypnotic to an open mind.**++和谐的歌唱和有节奏的鼓点可以催眠到开阔思维的状态。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1356', 'hypocritical', '[,hɪpəkrɪtɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hypocritical', '{...}++...**', '++Is this hypocritical?**++这是否虚伪？**++He suggested that those who preach otherwise are hypocritical because they undoubtedly have female servants at home, so they are "contradicting" themselves.**++他指出，那些劝导别人不要这么做的人是伪善的人，因为他们家里无疑都有女性仆役，因此这种说法等于“自相矛盾”。**++I suppose, its just hard not be hypocritical about it sometimes...**++我想，有时候的确很难做到不那么虚伪......**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1357', 'hypothetical', '[,haɪpəθɛtɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=hypothetical', '{adj.}++假设的，假定的**++与假设相关的；以假设为特点的**++推测的；据推测存在的**++好猜想的，爱推测的**++【逻辑学】**++假言的，假说的**++有前提的**', '++"We were speaking of a hypothetical case," I reminded him frostily.**++“我们正在谈一个假设的案例。” 我冷淡地提醒他。**++So you do look at hypothetical accidents and failure but they are judged to be very unlikely.**++所以，你们观察这些假设的事故,和失败，但是他们是被认为不太可能发生的。**++After all, we have no clue about the nature of these hypothetical aliens, why assume they@re friendly?**++毕竟，我们对这些假设的外星人的本性毫不了解，为什么要假设他们是友好的呢？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1358', 'iconoclast', '[aɪkɑnəklæst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=iconoclast', '{n.}++反对崇拜偶像者**++反对崇拜圣像者**++破除传统观念习俗者**', '++Haggis was struck by another paradox: “Here I was in this very structured organization, but I always thought of myself as a freethinker and an iconoclast.**++哈吉斯被另一个悖论弄昏了头：“我身处组织严密的机构中，而我却还一直自以为是自由思想家、偶像破坏者。”**++I put some thought to this and I would describe it as probably part adventuralist, part problem-solver, part ejecable traits, sort of a touch of maverick, sort of a touch of iconoclast.**++我思考了一下，我可能会,描述成一部分是冒险家，一部分是问题解决者，一部分鲜明的个性，有那么点偏执，还有那么点反对偶像崇拜。**++In recognition of this iconoclast, pioneer, perfectionist and undisputed king of the tailored suit, we present five things you didn@t know about Armani -- the man and the empire.**++为了认识这位革新家、先驱者、完美主义者和西式套装界无可置疑的王者，以下告诉你五个乔治·阿玛尼的轶闻逸事——他本人以及他的帝国。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1359', 'idiosyncrasy', '[,ɪdɪəsɪŋkrəsi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=idiosyncrasy', '{n.}++(个人特有的)气质，特性，习性，癖好**++(作者)特有的风格**++【医学】(对药物、食物等的)特异反应，过敏；特异体质[亦作 idiocrasy，参较 allergy]**++【心理学】特异品质**', '++" He suggested that other researchers would need to also run their own tests to verify that the reported link was not "an idiosyncrasy of this particular sample of face images.**++他建议其他研究者们要再进行测试，以验证研究结果并不仅是“特定脸部肖像样本的气质”。**++Libraries have begun to experiment with these approaches, but individual libraries may not have the scale to iron out local or personal idiosyncrasy or emphasis.**++图书馆已经开始试验这些方法，但是单个图书馆的规模可能不足以解决本地或者个人的特性。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1360', 'idle', '[aɪdl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=idle', '{adj.}++空闲的；不忙的；闲散的；无活动的**++不在工作的，失业的**++懒惰的；懒散的；无所事事的**++闲置的；未利用的**++无价值的；无意义的**++徒劳的；无效的；无用的**++无根据的；无理由的**++【机械学】空转的；慢转的；怠速的**++【电子学】空载的；无功的**++不符合军人身份的**{vt.}++虚度；浪费(常与away连用):**++让(发动机等)空转：**++使空闲，使没事干：**{vi.}++闲逛；无所事事(常与away连用)：**++(发动机等)空转：**{n.}++(发动机的)空转；怠速**', '++Ragweed pioneers idle fields.**++豚草常是闲置耕地的先锋植物。**++The passenger@s idle thoughts were backgrounded by the drone of the plane@s engines.**++那位乘客的遐想似乎是由飞机发动机的嗡嗡声作伴奏。**++Idle thoughts floated through his mind.**++莫名其妙地想法浮现在他心头。**');
