insert into GREWordBook values ('1362', 'idyll', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=idyll', '{n.}++田园诗**++长叙事诗(常以史诗、传奇等为主题)**++适合田园诗的素材**++富于田园风光的情节(或场景)**++【音乐】牧歌；田园乐曲**', '++Last week the idyll seemed to be over.**++上周，这田园诗般的生活似乎要终结了。**++But time, unforgivingly, moves on. The idyll shows faultlines: infidelity, disease, age, loss, divorce.**++但时间无情地流逝，田园牧歌出现了断层：不贞、疾病、高龄、亏损、离婚。**++It was an upbringing he describes as "incredibly happy" – a Durrellian idyll near the New Forest in Hampshire.**++他的成长过程在他自己的描述里是“无比快乐”的——那是在汉普郡的新森林区，就像达雷尔风格的田园牧歌一样。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1363', 'ignite', '[ɪɡnaɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ignite', '{vt.}++使燃烧；点燃；点火于：**++使灼热，使发光**++使激动，使兴奋；刺激，引起：**++【化学】使灼烧**{vi.}++着火，发火；开始燃烧；变得灼热：**++着火，发火；开始燃烧；变得灼热：**', '++It can ignite your spirit and make you feel like you can do anything.**++它能点燃你的精神和使你感觉你能够做到任何事情。**++They give me energy and motivation; they ignite my creativity while maintaining a high level of productivity.**++清单给我能量和动力，它点燃了我的创造力，并且保持在一个高产级别。**++Furthermore, some flawed ideas may ignite your curiosity and imagination, both of which have the ability to change the dynamics of everything.**++而且，有时一些有瑕疵的想法可能会点燃你的好奇心和想象力，这两者都能够带来彻头彻尾的改变。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1364', 'ignominy', '[ɪɡnəmɪni]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ignominy', '{n.}++耻辱；污辱；不名誉；声名狼藉**++无耻行为，丑行**', '++Japan, Canada and Australia, among others, have suffered the ignominy of being downgraded from top credit ratings.**++日本、加拿大和澳大利亚等国都经历过从最高评级被下调的耻辱。**++How dreary looked the forest-track that led backward to the settlement, where Hester Prynne must take up again the burden of her ignominy, and the minister the hollow mockery of his good name!**++那通往居民区的林中小路看来有多么沉闷，一回到那居民区，海丝特·白兰就得重新负起她那耻辱的重荷，而牧师则要再次戴上他那好名声的空虚的面具！**++Never again willyou endure the ignominy of being out in public with no way to blow yournose.**++你们再也不用忍受外出在公共场合没办法擤鼻涕的耻辱了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1365', 'ill-bred', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ill-bred', '{adj.}++缺乏教养的；(举止)粗野的；粗鲁的，无礼的**++(动物等)劣种的**', '++SCARLETT: Oh, you really are the most ill-bred man to come here at**++思嘉：你真是太没有教养了，这种时候来说这个……**++There was once a church choir that was not ill-bred, but I have forgotten where it was, now.**++曾有过一个唱诗班不像这样没教养，可是我忘记那是在什么地方了。**++I knew very well it was ill-bred to chat for a while or watch TV in Daughter@s room taking advantage of the precious opportunity.**++我非常清楚，利用这个宝贵的机会在女儿的房间里和女儿聊一会儿天或看一会儿电视是没有礼貌的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1366', 'illiteracy', '[ɪlɪtərəsi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=illiteracy', '{n.}++文盲**++无知；未受教育**++[复数](因未受教育而产生的)语言(或文字)错误；语文差距**', '++"In the long-term we need to address poverty and illiteracy and that is what we are doing," Musharraf said.**++穆沙拉夫说：“长期来讲，我们必须处理好贫穷和文盲的问题。 这正是我们目前正在做的。**++Tackling corruption would be the fastest way to address problems like poverty, disease, and illiteracy, he contended.**++他认为，反腐败可能是解决诸如贫困、疾病和文盲等问题的最快途径。**++This great institution must work for great purposes -- to free people from tyranny and violence, hunger and disease, illiteracy and ignorance, and poverty and despair.**++这个伟大的机构必须努力达到伟大的目的──使人们摆脱暴政与暴力、饥饿与疾病、文盲与愚昧、贫困与绝望。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1367', 'illuminate', '[ɪlumɪnet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=illuminate', '{vt.}++照明，照亮；照射：**++启发；阐明，解释：**++用灯装饰：**++使容光焕发；使有光彩：**++用金色(或银色、色彩、图案等)装饰(书籍、手稿等)**++使受(雷达、声呐等)辐射探测**{vi.}++照亮**++用灯装饰**++兴奋**{adj.}++[古语]被照亮的**++[废语]受到启迪的**{n.}++[古语](自称)受到特别启迪的人，(自称)先知先觉的人**', '++Sanding off a protective coating on the flash unit allows the camera to illuminate its subject in UV.**++把闪光灯部件上的一层保护涂层磨去后，照相机就可以用紫外线照亮拍摄物了。**++Detailed guidance, in the form of concept descriptions, examples, and task performance guidelines, further illuminate the core method content.**++详细指南采用概念描述、示例和任务性能指南的形式，进一步说明了核心方法内容。**++This is sufficient to convince any one that we may be able to illuminate large public places with one light, but not the streets of a city, and still less whole cities.**++这个例子足以说明，我们可以用一个强光灯照亮公共场所，但是对一条漫长的街道而言，这个办法却是不足取的，更不用说整个城市了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1368', 'illuminati', '[ɪ,lʊmənetai]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=illuminati', '{n.}++[单数]-to ／-təu／**++(自称)受到特别启示的人，(自称)先知先觉的人**++【宗教】光照派**', '++what is the illuminati?**++什么是先觉者？**++Shadow monsters, bullet wounds, Pandora’s box, back-stabbing friends, the Illuminati… Lara’s survived them all.**++暗影怪，枪伤，潘多拉的盒子，出卖自己的朋友，先觉者…劳拉都幸存下来了。**++There are hundreds of different theories about the Illuminati, some of which say it@s the organization to which all other secret governments report.**++关于光照派，有数百种不同的理论，有些理论认为，这是一个所有其他秘密政府都要向其汇报的组织。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1369', 'illusory', '[ɪlusəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=illusory', '{adj.}++幻觉的，错觉的；梦幻似的；迷惑人的**++虚幻的；虚假的；不实际的**', '++Secondly, if the self is an illusion, then aren’t subjective insights from meditation illusory as well?**++其次，如果自我是错觉，那么来自于冥想的主观视角不也同样是错觉？**++MacKay first observed this effect on the wallboard of a BBC studio: the broadcasting staff had been annoyed by illusory shadows running up and down blank strips between columns of parallel lines.**++麦凯是在BBC的一个录音室里第一次看到这个效果的： 那位正在播音的职员被平行线柱上线条空白间上下跳动的阴影错觉搞得很不耐烦。**++Yet many fear that the calm is illusory.**++然而，许多人担心，平静是虚幻的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1370', 'illustrious', '[ɪlʌstrɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=illustrious', '{adj.}++卓越的，杰出的，著名的**++(事迹等)辉煌的，灿烂的**++[古语]发光的；有光泽的；明亮的**', '++It is a city whose past is more illustrious than its present, and there is a relief, an ease in this.**++这是一座其过去比现在更为辉煌的城市，而这带来一种解脱感和轻松自如。**++While the proud papa never captured an illustrious Super Bowl ring, both of his sons did so during the last five years.**++而他们的老爸在“超级碗”比赛中从未获得过著名的“超级碗”戒指，两个儿子在过去五年也是。**++Both Hasenöhrl and Einstein were at the famous first Solvay conference in 1911, along with most of the other illustrious physicists of the time.**++哈泽内尔和爱因斯坦都参加了著名的1911年索尔维物理学会议，与会的还包括那个时代的大量杰出物理学家。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1371', 'imbibe', '[ɪmbaɪb]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=imbibe', '{vt.}++喝，饮：**++吸收(养分等)，吸进(空气)：**++吸收(知识、思想等)，接受：**++[废语]浸，渍**{vi.}++喝，饮：**++吸收水分(或光、热等)**', '++These plants imbibe moisture through their roots.**++这些植物通过根部吸收水分。**++I see a coffee mug on the table, reach for a sip and, lo and behold, the vessel’s handle is soon in my grasp as I gingerly imbibe the hot liquid.**++我看着桌上的咖啡杯，端起喝了一小口，端详着杯子，不一会，我的目光落在了杯子的手柄上，我在小心翼翼地喝着这杯热咖啡。**++The entire process occurs without a gram of painkiller, although a few imbibe a noxious alcohol made from the fermented mash of acorns.**++整个过程中，一粒止痛药都没有，虽然有几个换生灵会喝一种用橡树汁发酵而成的酒，但这种酒对身体有害。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1372', 'imbroglio', '[ɪmbrolɪo]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=imbroglio', '{n.}++复杂混乱的局面；混乱状态**++乱糟糟的一堆**++纠缠不清的误会，纠葛[亦作 embroglio]**', '++In his first imbroglio, the commander in chief found himself trapped between gay-rights activists and his own Joint Chiefs of Staff.**++在他的第一纠葛 总司令发现自己被深陷于同性恋权利激进分子和自己的参谋长联席会议。**++Try to avoid the imbroglio on money.**++尽量不要在经济上有纠葛。**++He summarizes the Soviet imbroglio**++他总结出了整个苏联的纷纷扰扰。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1373', 'imitation', '[,ɪmɪteʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=imitation', '{n.}++仿效；模仿；模拟**++模仿的状态**++仿制品；仿造品；赝品**++【生物学】拟态**++【心理学】模仿**++【音乐】模仿**{adj.}++伪造的；仿制的；人造的；冒充的**++【宝石】仿造的,人造的[参较 assembled, synthetic]**', '++The use of language begins with imitation.**++运用语言是从模仿开始的。**++You know the cliché: imitation is the highest form of flattery.**++你知道那句陈词滥调：模仿是奉承的最高形式。**++Learn by Imitation – Kids observe the people around them with enthusiastic intensity.**++通过模仿学习 ——孩子带着强烈的热情观察周围的人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1374', 'immaculate', '[ɪmækjələt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=immaculate', '{adj.}++洁白的，纯净的；无污点的，无瑕的**++无误的；无缺点的；完美的**++(道德等)纯洁的，清白的；无罪的，无过失的**++【生物学】无斑点的；无杂色的**', '++You all have within you the power of God, and we call upon you to allow that recognition, that renewed self acceptance, that immaculate LOVE to wash over you.**++你们都有内在的神之力量，我们号召你们让那重识、那重获的自我接纳、那【完美的爱】（自由地）冲刷你们。**++@@But her style, deportmentand immaculate groominghave clearly won her an army of admirers, propelling her to the same heights as Princess Grace and Queen Rania.**++但她的风度、举止、以及完美的仪表无疑给她赢得了大批粉丝，使她在榜单中堪比格蕾丝王妃以及拉尼娅王后。**++As I try to imagine 19 people sleeping in this small space, it struck me how immaculate it was.**++我极力的想象这19个人在这样狭小空间里，怎样生活，而让我震惊的是这个地方太整洁了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1375', 'immanent', '[ɪmənənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=immanent', '{adj.}++内在的；固有的**++【哲学】(精神上)内在的，内涵的[参较 transeunt]**++【神学】(上帝)无所不在的[参较 transcendent]**', '++Despair is the state in which anxiety and restlessness are immanent to existence.**++在绝望的状态中，焦虑和不安是与生俱来的。**++In vice, the attraction of the abnormal creates a troubling anxiety: the spirit seems to have become blood and stirs in the flesh like an immanent force.**++在邪恶中，异常事物的吸引创造出令人不安的焦虑：精神似乎已经变成了血液，像一股无所不在的力量搅动着肉体。**++Since death is immanent in life, almost all of life is an agony.**++由于死固有于生，因此几乎所有的生活都是一种苦闷。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1376', 'immaterial', '[,ɪmətɪrɪəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=immaterial', '{adj.}++非物质的，无形的；非实体的；精神的**++无关紧要的；不重要的；无所谓的**', '++There are no immaterial objects like that.**++没有象那样的非物质物体。**++I know very little about how immaterial objects are supposed to work.**++关于非物质的物体是如何工作的我知道的很少。**++It is the psychology of those who have not bothered to learn psychology, and the psychotherapy of choice for those who believe in the power of immaterial mind over body.**++它是那些懒得去学习心理学的人的心理学，还有那些相信非物质的思想对身体的作用的人所选择的心理治疗。**');
