insert into GREWordBook values ('1518', 'intermittent', '[,ɪntɚmɪtənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=intermittent', '{adj.}', '++Reality: There are no intermittent bugs.**++事实：不存在间歇的程序错误。**++“Our moments of ecstasy have become far too intermittent,” she continued.**++“我们之间狂喜的时刻太断断续续了，”她继续说。**++These more complicated scenarios tended to expose more difficult bugs, which were harder to debug and sometimes were intermittent.**++这些较复杂的场景趋于暴露出较困难的故障，它们更难调试，并且有时是间歇的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1519', 'interregnum', '[,ɪntɚrɛɡnəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=interregnum', '{n.}++(旧统治者已死而继承人尚未即位的)空位期**++(新旧的政府更替的)过渡期**++间歇；中断；停顿**', '++But the interregnum was a time of debate.**++但现在这权力真空期就是争论的最佳时期。**++It’s true that the interregnum will be shorter this time: F.D.R. wasn’t inaugurated until March; Barack Obama will move into the White House on Jan. 20.**++这一次两个政府的交接当然不会用那么长的时间：富兰克林·罗斯福直到三月才就职；巴拉克·奥巴马将在一月二十日就入主白宫。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1520', 'interrogate', '[ɪntɛrəɡet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=interrogate', '{vt.}++审问；讯问；质问：**++【计算机】询问**{vi.}++审问；讯问；质问：**++审问；讯问；质问：**', '++The police took a long time to interrogate the offenders fully.**++警察花了很长时间对人犯进行了详细的审问。**++You can set and interrogate these properties using extensions to the existing ESQL vocabulary.**++您可以使用现有 ESQL 词汇的扩展来设置和询问这些属性。**++Many people go online via a router and typically only the computer directly connected to the device can interrogate it for ID information.**++很多人通过路由器上网，而只有直接和路由器相连的电脑才可以向路由器询问它的身份识别信息。**');
