insert into GREWordBook values ('1551', 'jaded', '[dʒedɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jaded', '{vt.}++jade<sup style="font-size: 60%">2</sup>的变形**{adj.}++疲倦的，精疲力竭的**++(因过饱或过多而)厌倦的，腻烦的；迟钝的**++淫荡的**++用旧了的**{n.}++劣马；弩马；老马；疲惫不堪的马**++荡妇；轻佻的女人**++[戏谑语]女人**{vt.}++使疲倦；使劳累**++使厌倦；使迟钝**++用旧**{vi.}++变得疲倦，精疲力竭**++变得迟钝；厌倦**', '++You may have been around for a while, but no one wants a jaded, world-weary person working for them.**++您也许已经找了好一段时间了，但没有人想要一个疲倦不堪、悲观厌世的人为自己工作。**++But it is easy to get a little jaded, quickly cubby-holing something new just because it acts like something already out there.**++但是很容易会有点厌倦，迅速的对一些新东西入门归类，那是因为它与一些已经问世产品类似。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1552', 'jape', '[dʒep]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jape', '{vi.}++开玩笑，说笑话；打趣；嘲弄：**++开玩笑，说笑话；打趣；嘲弄：**{vt.}++开…的玩笑；取笑，嘲弄**++捉弄；愚弄**{n.}++玩笑，笑话；笑料；嘲弄，愚弄**++逗笑的文学作品(或戏剧演出)**', '++You think this is a jape?**++你认为这是个玩笑？**++The jape is on you, Abel, you and your murdering whores.**++这次命运用你开玩笑了，你和你的婊子杀手门。**++It was only a jape, ser, she thought, but she sat on one of the pillows just the same.**++那只是个玩笑而已，爵士，她想，但是与此同时她还是坐了上去。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1553', 'jargon', '[dʒɑrɡən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jargon', '{n.}++莫名其妙的话，听不懂的话；语无伦次的话，胡言乱语**++难懂的、奇特粗俗的语言(或方言)，土语**++(词汇、语法等不纯正的)混杂语(如洋泾浜英语)**++行话，行业话；黑话；隐语(为某社会或职业集团使用、一般人听来晦涩难懂的一套术语和语词)**++装腔作势、句法复杂的文章，含混迂回的文章；喋喋不休**++[古语](鸟等)叽喳的叫声，啁啾声**{vi.}++讲难懂的话(或行话、黑话、混杂语)；写含混晦涩的文章**++喋喋不休**{n.}', '++Do not let the math jargon intimidate you.**++可别让这些数学术语把你吓倒。**++The context should not include the solution or any technical jargon.**++上下文不应包括解决方案或任何技术行话。**++I knew that in order to write these articles, I needed to learn the jargon that every project manager uses without even thinking.**++我很清楚，要写出这方面的文章，我就得先学会每个项目经理都能脱口而出的那些专业术语。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1554', 'jarring', '[dʒɑrɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jarring', '{vt.}++jar<sup style="font-size: 60%">2</sup>的变形**{adj.}++刺耳的**++不和谐的**{vt.}++摇动；震动；把…震得嘎嘎作响：**++使(意志、决心等)动摇，使不坚定：**++使发出刺耳声；使发出不和谐的声音**++使感到不愉快；刺激(神经等)：**++震伤；撞伤**{vi.}++发出刺耳声(或不和谐的声音)：**++给人不愉快的感觉；刺激(常与on，upon连用):**++震动；震荡；摇动：**++不和谐；不一致(常与with连用)：**++冲突；吵嘴；争执：**++(发出刺耳声地)撞击；摩擦(常与on，against连用):**{n.}++刺耳声；吱嘎声；轧轧声**++剧烈的震动；震荡，震摇**++(对神经、感情等的)刺激；震惊；不快**++不协调；不一致；不和谐**++冲突；争吵，吵架**', '++This was, easily, the most jarring part of his talk.**++这无疑是他的报告中最不和谐的部分。**++They may wish to seek the truth in a different way, or in a less mind jarring set of circumstances.**++他们可能希望用一种不同的方式，或在一些思想冲突较小的情形下寻求真相。**++The symphony of the streets—jarring jackhammers, bleating beeping of car horns and rumblings of subway cars beneath the sidewalk—was momentarily muted when the earth hiccuped on Tuesday afternoon.**++周二下午，当大地开始微颤时，由电钻震动、汽车咩咩地警笛声和人行道地下的汽车轰鸣声组成的街头交响乐也随即停止了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1555', 'jaundice', '[dʒɔndɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jaundice', '{n.}++【病理学】黄疸;黄疸病(俗指肝炎)[亦作 icterus,参较 physiologic jaundice]**++(由妒忌引起的)猜疑；偏见；厌恶**{vt.}++使患黄疸病**++使妒忌；使有偏见(或不满)：**', '++The "yellow" in the name is explained by the jaundice that affects some patients, causing yellow eyes and yellow skin.**++名称中的“黄”字由影响一些患者的黄疸使眼睛和皮肤颜色发黄而得到解释。**++Certain forms of hepatitis can easily be passed on in sex - for example by touching or sharing sex toys. There are often no symptoms, though it can cause jaundice (yellow skin) or nausea.**++乙型肝炎是一种病毒性传染疾病.它在激活的情况下很容易通过性传播.比如触摸或者共享性玩具.它通常没什么外显症状,尽管它能导致黄疸或者恶心.**++However, in a few cases, the disease enters a “toxic” phase: fever reappears, and the patient develops jaundice and sometimes bleeding, with blood appearing in the vomit (the typical "vomito negro").**++但是，在少数病例中，疾病进入“毒性”期：重新出现发热，病人形成黄疸并有时出血，在呕吐物中出现血液（典型的“黑色呕吐物”）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1556', 'jaunty', '[dʒɔnti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jaunty', '{adj.}++轻快的；活泼的；喜洋洋的；得意的**++时髦的，时兴的；漂亮的**++绅士风度的，斯文的，有教养的**{n.}++[英国口语](舰船或运输船上的)纠察队长**', '++There are some useful colour diagrams and photographs, and the prose is jaunty.**++书里有一些实用的彩图和照片，然而文字却是洋洋得意的口吻。**++With a pink lei on one shoulder and a jaunty cap on the other, the robot was surrounded by more than 100 young software engineers, each sitting with a wirelessly connected laptop.**++100多位年轻的软件工程师，各自坐在一个无线连接的笔记本前，簇拥着这个肩上有个粉红色的花环，戴着一顶活泼帽子的机器人。**++The photos include a black-and-white headshot of the future Monroe wearing a jaunty beret, another of her in a halter top and a color picture of her smiling in a striped bikini on the sand.**++此批照片包括两张黑白头像照，一张是“未来梦露”头戴活泼贝雷帽，另一张是她身着露背吊带衫；还包括一张她在沙滩身着条纹比基尼的微笑彩照（译注：实际有三张黑白照，第三张是梦露穿格子衬衫）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1557', 'jejune', '[dʒɪdʒun]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jejune', '{adj.}++缺乏营养的；(土地)贫瘠的，荒芜的，不毛的**++无趣的；枯燥乏味的；无生气的；空洞的**++不成熟的；幼稚的**', '++Then she was gone, leaving me in unexpectedly jejune loneliness.**++于是她走了，置我于意想不到的空虚孤独之中。**++His jejune approach to decision-making - know yourself but not necessarily the facts - is downright repellent.**++他那种幼稚的决策方法——了解你自己，而不必了解事实——是完全不能被人接受的。**++The jejune caption is cited just to emphasize the importance of a foreign correspondent@s knowledge of the country he covers to the writing of good stories. He has to speak the language of its people.**++举这一篇特稿的例子，只是为了凸显海外特派员必须对驻在国具备丰富知识的重要性，因为唯有如此，他才能写出引人入胜的报导。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1558', 'jeopardy', '[dʒɛpɚdi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jeopardy', '{n.}++危难，危险**++【法律】被判有罪的危险处境；(刑事案件中被告的)危险处境**', '++Poets, of course, have it easier than novelists, but the physical issues add another form of double jeopardy to the work.**++当然了，诗人比小说家要容易些，但是身体方面的问题又为这种职业增加了双重的危险。**++What places polio eradication most in jeopardy now is the funding gap, which we must deal with equally rapidly to ensure that children in the Horn of Africa and other high-risk areas are protected.**++现在对根除脊髓灰质炎造成最大危险的是供资方面的空白，我们必须同样迅速地予以处理，以便确保非洲之角及其它高危地区的儿童得到保护。**++In "Jeopardy!" players are given information in the form of an answer. They must give an answer in the form of a question.**++在“危险边缘”节目中，选手获得一个答案形式的信息，他们必须回答出符合这个答案的问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1559', 'jest', '[dʒɛst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jest', '{n.}++笑话，俏皮话**++戏谑，诙谐；打趣；嘲笑**++笑柄，笑料**++玩笑；滑稽事**++[废语]功绩，业绩[参较 gest]**++[废语]诗体故事，诗体传奇**{vi.}++玩笑；嘲弄(常与at连用):**++开玩笑；打趣(常与with连用):**{vt.}++戏弄，取笑，打趣：**++戏弄，取笑，打趣：**', '++She preludes her remarks with a jest.**++她开始讲话时先说一个笑话。**++He lit upon some jest books in the bookstore.**++他在书店偶然发现了一些笑话集。**++A young machine hand, attracted by her looks, made bold to jest with her.**++一位年轻的机工， 被她的美貌所吸引， 壮着胆子跟她开玩笑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1560', 'jettison', '[dʒɛtɪsn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jettison', '{n.}++(船舶、飞机等遇险时为减轻负担的)抛弃货物(的行动)**++抛弃的货物**{vt.}++(船舶、飞机等遇难时为减轻负担而)投弃(货物)**++把…作为废物抛弃，扔掉**++(飞机等在飞行时)投弃(炸弹、燃料等)**{vi.}++从飞机(或宇宙飞船)落下，被扔弃**', '++With a federal election due by September 2009 each partner in the grand coalition can do little but think of how to win by a margin wide enough to jettison the other.**++德国在2009年九月将进行联邦选举，使得大联合政府的每一位成员都想着如何才 能与对手拉开足够大的差距以赢得选举。**++With that deterioration comes a question: will the worsening conditions force the incoming president to jettison the economic strategy he laid out during the campaign and formulate a new one?**++随着恶化而面临的一个问题就是：越来越糟的形式是否会迫使新任的总统放弃竞选时的经济政策而设计一套新的政策？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1561', 'jibe', '[dʒaɪb]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jibe', '{vt.}++使(帆或桁)从一舷转至他舷；使(帆)改变方向**{vi.}++(帆或桁)从一舷转至他舷，转帆**++(船)改变航向使帆桁从一舷转至他舷，换向**{n.}++帆桁的自一舷转至另一舷，转帆[亦作 zibe，gybe，jib，jibb]**{n.}{vi.}', '++That doesn@t  jibe with one widely accepted model of planetary formation.**++这种情况跟一个被广泛接受的行星形成模型并不一致。**++It can lead to irritability, miscommunication, lack of interest -- three traits that don@t jibe well for three people trying to live together.**++这会导致易怒、误解、兴趣缺缺——而这三点让同处一个屋檐下的三个人很难和谐地生活在一起。**++Some people keep smoking while running, but I’ve seen tons of runners who quit smoking, because they know that smoking doesn’t jibe with their lifestyle.**++有些人跑步时也会吸烟，然而我已经看到了许多跑步爱好者戒掉了烟瘾，因为他们知道吸烟与他们的生活方式格格不入。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1562', 'jingoist', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jingoist', '{n.,adj.}{n.}', '++In short, the crime is a gift to the hard jingoist right, those who hope to use force to control their domains.**++总而言之，沙文主义者企图用武力掌控他们的领土，而这次袭击则恰恰是送给这些强硬右派的一份大礼。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1563', 'jitters', '[dʒɪtɚz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jitters', '{vi.}++[口语]**++紧张不安；紧张不安地行事**++抖动，颤抖；剧跳**{vt.}++紧张不安地说**++使激动；使紧张不安**++【无线电】使跳动，使晃动**{n.}++神经紧张；恐慌**++紧张不安状态；激动**++【无线电】图像跳动，图像晃动，(传真接收图像的)不稳定移动；速度偏差**', '++But her wedding jitters could be a thing of the past – if legislators get their way in Mexico City.**++如果市议员们让提案在墨西哥城成为法律，她可能不会在因结婚而紧张不安了。**++Many people feel that caffeine increases their mental alertness. Higher doses of caffeine can cause anxiety, dizziness, headaches, and the jitters. Caffeine can also interfere with normal sleep.**++许多人感觉咖啡因可以使他们的神智更加清楚。高剂量的咖啡可以引起焦虑、头晕、、头痛、紧张不安，亦会影响正常睡眠。**++One response to market jitters would be to guarantee all bank debt, not just the new stuff.**++对市场各方不安的回应就是担保所有的银行债，而不仅仅是新发行的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1564', 'jocular', '[dʒɑkjəlɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jocular', '{adj.}++爱开玩笑的**++打趣的；逗乐的**++滑稽的**', '++His jocular “you see a new man before you”, caused me to look up, and to smile shyly at a healthier and more peaceful looking man.**++他逗趣地说：“瞧，一个焕然一新的我站在你们面前”。 我抬起头，对着这个身体越发健康，面容祥和的男人露出羞涩的微笑。**++Her voice sounded unnaturally high; the brittle laugh she reserved for her boss@s jocular, unamusing jokes was even more forced than usual.**++她说话的声音高得不正常，听了老板说的那些诙谐但并不有趣的笑话后，她发出的硬梆梆的笑声甚至比以前更加勉强。**++His jocular, conversational tone will keep you interested as he describes mutual funds, bonds, and treasury bills.**++在描述共有财产、债券、以及国债的同时，他诙谐会话式的文风会一直吸引着你。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1565', 'jocund', '[dʒɑkənd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jocund', '{adj.}', '++In such a jocund company!**++在这样愉悦的友伴之中！**++Her jocund character made her the most popular girl in the county.**++她快乐的个性使她成为这个郡最受欢迎的女孩。**++However, today the fog is unusually thin, through which the soft golden sunbeams filter and cloak everything on the ground with a jocund hue.**++今天，难得雾是这么稀薄，空中融融地混合着金黄的阳光，把地上的一切，好像也照上一层欢笑的颜色。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1566', 'jog', '[dʒɑɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jog', '{vt.}++轻推；轻撞；轻摇：**++唤起(回忆等)；提醒：**++使颠簸；使颤动：**++使(马等)缓步前进**++【印刷】把(一叠纸)垛齐，撞齐**{vi.}++颠簸地移动(或前进)：**++缓慢而平稳地进行(常与along，on连用)：**++慢跑：**++缓慢度过时间：**++(马)缓步前进**++磨磨蹭蹭地走，拖着脚步走**++走，走开**{n.}++轻摇；轻撞；轻推**++慢步；缓行；慢跑**++唤起记忆的行为；暗示，提醒**++短途旅行**{n.}++(线、面等的)参差不齐；凹凸不平**++弯曲；急转弯**++【晶体学】割阶**{vi.}++1.凸出；凹进**++突然转向**', '++Walk or jog down.**++走或者慢跑下来。**++If you hate to jog, try a team sport or play some tennis.**++如果你讨厌慢跑，那就尝试团体性运动或打网球。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1567', 'jolt', '[dʒolt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jolt', '{n.}++摇动；摇晃；颠簸；震动**++突然的一击；猛击(尤指拳击)**++震惊；令人震惊(或失望的事)**++(意外的)严重挫折**++少量；一口(酒或提神的东西)**++[俚语]一剂毒品**++[俚语]监禁期**{vt.}++使震动；使摇动：**++使震惊；使慌乱：**++猛敲；猛然一击**++(粗暴地)干涉：**{vi.}++摇晃；震动；颠簸：**++[美国俚语]在臂部作皮下毒品注射**', '++There was a jolt, like a silent earthquake that left no physical impression.**++有一些震惊，就像一场安静的地震，没有留下任何创伤。**++"I lamented that they had not been blessed as I had, with this jolt to life," he writes.**++“他们没有我这样幸运，可以经历这一人生的突变，我为他们感到难过，”他写道。**++This huge jolt happened as the Nazca plate moved down and landward below the South American plate.**++这次巨大的摇晃发生在纳斯卡板块下移，向南美板块下的近陆移动。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1568', 'jot', '[dʒɑt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jot', '{vt.}++略记；草草记下；匆匆记下(常与down连用):**++略记；草草记下；匆匆记下(常与down连用):**{n.}++最少量，最小额，一点儿，微不足道的量**', '++Jot down the thought or idea and go back to what you were doing.**++简单记下想法或念头，然后回去做你刚才做的事情。**++As you organize your notes, jot down detailed bibliographical information for each cited paragraph and have it ready to transfer to your Works Cited page.**++在你整理你的笔记的时候，应该简单记录下每一段的参考信息，准备好写到你自己的作品的引用页上。**++Did you jot down his telephone number?**++你有没有把他的电话号码记下来?**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1569', 'jovial', '[dʒovɪəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jovial', '{adj.}++快活的，愉快的，高兴的，和蔼的**++主神朱庇特的**++【天文学】木星的**{n.}', '++Amidst the drumbeats and jovial chants, time passed.**++时间在鼓声和愉快的圣歌声中流逝。**++The Headmaster’s name was Mr.Ronald Broackes. He was a large rotund man with a very jovial nature and a compassionate disposition.**++校长名叫罗纳德.布罗克斯，是一个又高又胖的男人，天性快乐并富有同情心。**++Half a dozen jovial lads were talking about skates in another part of the room, and she longed to go and join them, for skating was one of the joys of her life.**++五六个快活的小伙子在房间的另一头大谈溜冰，她心痒难禁，恨不得也走过去参与，因为溜冰是她生活中的一大乐趣。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1570', 'jubilant', '[dʒubɪlənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=jubilant', '{adj.}++狂欢的，欢呼的；喜气洋洋的；兴高采烈的**++表达(或显示)欢乐的**', '++If he does, he will no doubt face jubilant crowds once again.**++如果他真的回来了，毫无疑问，他将再次看到欢呼的民众。**++They surged through cheering and shouting and were be met by jubilant West Berliners on the other side.**++他们蜂拥而至，欢呼着、叫喊着，和在墙另一边同样欢呼雀跃的西柏林市民相见。**++Every stop at traffic lights on the drive from the airport home was met by jubilant newspaper sellers, proudly showing us the front pages, pointing excitedly to photos of Obama.**++在机场到家的路上，每个因红灯停下的路口，都能看到欢呼的卖报者，自豪的向我们展示着头版封面，兴奋地指着奥巴马的相片。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1571', 'judicious', '[dʒudɪʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=judicious', '{adj.}', '++However, with some judicious changing, you can have a project that marries the best of both plans and achieves greater results.**++然而，作为明智的改变，你可以在项目中结合使用这两种方法的精华，这样就可以获得更好的结果。**++So we must be judicious about when we close off our work to the public, and we must review our standards frequently to make sure they are rigorous.**++因此，对于在什么情况下还不能向公众公布我们的工作内容，我们必须有明智的判断。 我们必须经常审查我们的标准，坚持严格的标准。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1572', 'juggernaut', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=juggernaut', '{n.}++[亦作 Jagannath]世界的主宰(印度教主神 Krishna 神像，传说印度教徒每年用车载此神像游行，许多人相信被神像车碾死即可升天，因而不惜投身车下)**++[常作 j-]骇人的毁灭力量，不可抗拒的可怕力量**++[j-]使人盲目崇拜(或为之牺牲)的事物**++[j-]大型载重车辆(尤指卡车)**', '++But no one has yet come up with a way to halt this military-industrial juggernaut.**++但到现在为止，没有人能够想出一个办法让军事工业的“战车”暂停下来。**++In fact, they succeeded beyond anyone’s wildest expectations, transforming the region into an export juggernaut and a model for the rest of China.**++但事实上，改革的成功超出了所有人最大胆的期许，这个地区成为了出口巨头和中国其他地区的榜样。**++Emotions tend not to be situation specific, so a small win, whether it is a compliment from a colleague or finishing two thirds of your tasks before noon can turn you into a juggernaut.**++情绪不会表现得很具体，因此一次小小的成功，无论是同事祝贺还是中午前就完成了任务的三分之二，都会让人你处于一种自我陶醉的状态。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1573', 'justify', '[dʒʌstəfai]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=justify', '{vt.}++证明…正当(或有道理、合理)；为…辩护：**++为…提供法律依据，证明(自己)有财力作保**++证明…无罪；开释**++【印刷】调整(铅字间隔)使齐行；整(版)，整理…的版面**++【神学】使称义**++【计算机】调整**{vi.}++【法律】证明有理，证明合法；(以充分的理由)辩解**++【法律】证明自己有资格作保证人(或保释人)**++【印刷】整版，调整铅字间隔使各行长度合适；排整齐**', '++Can you justify your conduct to me?**++你能向我证明你的行为是正确的吗?**++OK. How do we justify this formula?**++好的，我们如何证明这个公式？**++Why should we justify this kind of unhealthy development model?**++为什么我们要调整这种不健康的发展模式呢?**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1574', 'ken', '[kɛn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ken', '{n.}++视野，眼界；景象**++认识；理解；知识范围**{vt.}++[苏格兰英语]知道，晓得；熟悉**++[古语]看见，看到，望见**++[方言]认识；认出，看出**++【法律】承认…为法定继承人**++[废语]承认…属实**{vi.}++[苏格兰英语]知道，晓得(常与of， about连用)**{n.}{n.}{abbr.}', '++What they truly needed for the sake of "balance" was someone who could describe the "real Ken" to the folks back home.**++为着所谓的“平衡”，他们真正需要的是某个能够向那些家庭读者描述出“真正的肯”的人。**++Do they associate with Mary and Ken out of genuine affection, or because spending time with such miserable types makes them feel (and look) better?**++他们陪伴玛丽和肯恩真的是出于诚挚的感情吗？ 亦或是这些悲惨的人能令他们感觉（或是看起来）更好?**++"Across the evidence base, it seems that it@s tougher for women to lose weight than men, " affirms Ken Fox, professor of exercise and health sciences at Bristol University.**++“在整个证据的基础上，它似乎是更严格的妇女比男性失去的重量，”肯定肯福克斯，运动与健康科学教授在布里斯托尔大学。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1575', 'kidnap', '[kɪdnæp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=kidnap', '{vt.}++诱拐(儿童等)**++绑架；劫持**{n.}++诱拐**++绑架；劫持**', '++The police balked the attempt to kidnap the child.**++警方挫败了诱拐小孩的企图。**++His behaviour could just as easily have been explained by problems in his personal life as being an insider on the kidnap plot.**++他的那些被认为是绑架阴谋的内在行为可能只是简单的解释为他自己个人生活的问题。**++My father had become such an important figure in the struggle that he had been told that political opponents might kidnap one of his children or even murder members of his family.**++我的父亲成为了这场斗争中的一个重要人物，以至于他被告知政治对手可能会绑架他的一个孩子，甚至谋杀他的家人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1576', 'kindle', '[kɪndl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=kindle', '{vt.}++使燃烧，点燃；点(火)：**++引发，激发(情感)： **++鼓动，鼓舞；煽动；使(某人)激动：**{vi.}++着火，燃烧起来：**++(人或感情)激动起来：**++发亮，放光；变得明亮：**{vt., vi.}++(动物)生殖，产(仔)(尤指兔子)**{n.}++一胎所生的小兔(或小猫)**++[废语]幼小动物**', '++The wet wood wouldn@t kindle easily.**++湿木头不容易烧着。**++Also Thursday, Amazon said that it was working on making the titles for its popular e-book reader, the Kindle, available on a variety of mobile phones.**++周四，亚马逊公司也表示电子书读者越来越多，他们正致力开发能用在各种手机上的名为“点燃”的便携式阅览器。**++But just as camera phones have not replaced digital cameras, smartphones are not likely to replace dedicated e-book readers like the Kindle or the Reader from Sony, analysts said.**++分析者认为，因为带摄像头的手机还未完全取代数码相机，职能手机也不一定能取代像“点燃”和索尼阅读器这样的电子书阅读器。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1577', 'kindred', '[kɪndrəd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=kindred', '{n.}++[总称]亲属，家属，亲戚**++宗族，种族，家族**++血缘关系，亲属关系**++(性质)相似，类似；同质**{adj.}++有血缘关系的；同族的，同宗的**++同源的，同系的**++相似的，类似的；同类的**', '++A special connection between two kindred souls needs to be grieved just as a marriage or committed partnership.**++两个相似灵魂之间的特殊关系像婚姻或坚定的伙伴关系一样需要忧愁。**++Nor does one become a Christian by a negative attitude toward life, that is, refraining from drinking, smoking, swearing, adultery, idolatry, or kindred sins.**++一个人也不可能通过消极的生活态度成为一名基督教徒，也就是说，不要喝酒、吸烟、咒骂、奸淫、盲目崇拜，或者同类的罪恶。**++These and kindred questions need discussion, and need it urgently, in the few years left to us before somebody presses the button and the rockets begin to fly.**++这些以及同类的问题需要讨论，而且迫切地需要讨论，就在某个人按下按钮火箭起飞之前给我们留下的这几年里讨论。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1578', 'knack', '[næk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=knack', '{n.}++诀窍；窍门；技巧；妙法**++才能；技能；能力；本事**++(言语、行动等的)习惯；癖**++需要技巧的工作**++[古语]玩具；小玩艺儿；小摆设**', '++He has a knack of teaching arithmetic.**++他教算术有诀窍。**++On some days, it is the only substantial communication between us, because our kids have an uncanny knack of interrupting all of our conversations.**++某些日子里，这就是我们之间仅余的实质性联系，因为孩子们有着不寻常的本领，能将我们之间的交谈统统打断。**++Four-year-olds have a knack for bringing the whole world around them into the realm of play.**++四岁的小孩有一个本领，将他们周围的整个世界带进自己的游戏领域。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1579', 'knead', '[nid]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=knead', '{vt.}++揉，捏(面粉，陶土等)：**++捏制，捏成，揉成： **++揉捏使形成，塑造：**{vi.}++揉，捏**++(猫)用爪轻抚**', '++For best results. Continue to knead milk containers.**++要达到最佳效果，最好持续按摩挤奶包。**++‘He began to knead my whole body as if it were clay, while from him emanated a heat which scorched me and melted me.’**++他揉捏着我的身体就像揉捏着黏土，迸发出的热情将我炙烤融化。**++Then, the whole spectacle gets even worse when you have to knead germicide into the contents.**++然后更糟糕的事是你必须自己动手把杀菌剂均匀的揉进那些东西中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1580', 'knit', '[nɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=knit', '{vt.}++编织；编结；针织；把(毛线等)织成：**++皱(眉头)，皱紧，紧锁：**++[多用于过去分词]使严密，使紧凑；使结实：**++使紧密结合；粘合；拼合：**++使团结，使联合：**++缔结(协议等)：**++[古语]捆扎，捆缚**{vi.}++编织；编结；针织：**++(眉头)皱起，皱紧：**++(折骨)愈合，接合(常与together连用):**++紧密结合(常与together连用)**++变得结实**++[英国方言](植物)生长，结果实；(果实)结子；(蜂)蜂拥，成群**{n.}++编结；编织；针织**++编织品，针织品，织物；编织衣物**++编织式样**', '++Best of all, you can even knit yourself into the wedding party.**++最好的就是你甚至可以把自己也编织进这个婚宴中去。**++We and the world are knit together by Einstein@s thinking in ways that astonish me.**++通过爱因思维的思维，我们和世界是编织在一起的，这让我大吃一惊。**++If your body is game enough to knit itself back together after a hard physical lesson, to make scar tissue, that means you’re still alive, means you’re on the path toward healing.**++如果你的身体敢作敢为，在经历严重的身体创伤之后，还能够重新把你编织起来，形成疤痕组织，那就意味着你还活着，意味着你正在恢复之中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1581', 'knotty', '[nɑti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=knotty', '{adj.}++有结(或节的)；多结(或节的)**++难解决的，棘手的；使人困惑的**', '++Ah yes, the knotty business of slaughter.**++啊，屠宰中棘手的问题来了。**++The next knotty question -- and the one probably on your mind at the moment -- is how you input text in non-ASCII fonts.**++下一个棘手的问题 —— 也可能是现在正出现在您脑海中的问题 —— 是我们如何以非 ASCII 字体的形式来输入文本。**++He spent much of a presentation discussing the @surprises@ the company has faced pursuing projects outside China, such as land purchase challenges in Africa and knotty water rights in South America.**++金霄光的发言大部分在谈五矿有色在国外收购项目时碰到的各种“意外”，比如在非洲买地遇到的挑战，以及在南美洲碰上的棘手的水权问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1582', 'kudos', '[kudɑs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=kudos', '{n.}++kudo的变形**++[单数复数同][口语]名声；威信；声望**{n.}++[口语]**++(对成就等的)赞扬；称赞，表扬；赞词**++荣誉；光荣；奖赏**', '++When a solider was refused his earned due, or kudos, it was considered a very serious insult.**++如果一个士兵拒绝接受他应得的报酬或荣誉，那可以说是一种很严重的侮辱。**++As well as improving transport for commuters, he envisages Slim Ride could also add kudos to the city as a unique transport of mode for tourists.**++轻便铁路换乘系统不但可以改善乘客运输，诺伊兰还设想，它作为一个独特的交通系统可以吸引游客，为城市增添荣誉。**++Although (as you will see) the basics of sketching are easy to master, the kudos you will receive from clients for being a ‘proper designer’ makes it worthwhile!**++虽然（像你可能看到的）草图的基础很容易掌握，你从客户那得到的关于你是个合格设计师的称赞让这一切都值得！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1583', 'labile', '[lebɪl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=labile', '{adj.}++【化学】不稳的；易变化的**++【电工学】不安定的，滑动的**{n.}++【心理学】心境不定**', '++Sex is used by histrionics to prop up their self-esteem and to regulate their labile sense of self-worth.**++演献症患者用性行为来支持她们的自尊，调节她们不安定的自尊感。**++According to the study, reactivation of a memory returns it to a labile (unstable) state allowing it to be reinforced or updated.**++根据这项研究，重新激活记忆，会使记忆回到不稳定状态，从而有可能被增强或者更新。**++For compounds with potentially labile metabolites, the stability of analyte in matrix from dosed subjects (or species) should be confirmed.**++对于有潜在不稳定代谢物的物质，应确认制剂后基质中分析物稳定性。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1584', 'laborious', '[ləbɔrɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=laborious', '{adj.}++辛苦的；费力的；艰难的**++努力的；勤勉的**++(文体)欠流畅的；矫揉造作的；煞费苦心的**', '++So, it is a very laborious process.**++因此， 这是一个非常艰苦的过程。**++He assumed the only way to read thoroughlywas by the laborious method of reading one word at a time.**++他认为彻底阅读的道路只有一条：一次阅读一个单词这样让人费劲的办法。**++Note that this should not be a laborious and lengthy process; the goal is to get to a smaller and lighter initial process framework and validate the decisions with real work efforts.**++请注意：这不应当成为一个艰苦的和冗长的处理过程；它的目标是得到一个更小型的和更轻便的初始化处理过程框架，并且通过实际的工作努力验证该决定。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1585', 'labyrinthine', '[,læbərɪnθɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=labyrinthine', '{adj.}++迷宫的**++迷宫似的，曲折的，费解的，令人困惑的，错综复杂的**++【解剖学】迷路的[亦作labyrinthian, labyrinthic]**', '++In any of these cases, people could do with a local expert to help them navigate the labyrinthine American health-care system.**++在这些情况下，民众可以利用一位当地的专家来帮助他们进入这如迷宫般的美国健康保险系统。**++In one shack, deep inside the labyrinthine slum, her team found a weeping child whose parents had left her at home alone while they worked.**++在迷宫似的贫民区深处一个简陋小屋里，她的小组发现了一个哭泣的孩子，她的父母出去工作时把她独自留在家里。**++Some days later, as the ship threaded its way through the labyrinthine passages of the Great Barrier Reef, it holed itself on the coral and began slowly sinking.**++几天后，船小心翼翼地穿行在大堡礁迷宫般的航道时，在珊瑚上撞了个洞，开始慢慢下沉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1586', 'lacerate', '[læsəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lacerate', '{vt.}++撕裂；扯破；割碎(肌肉、软组织等)：**++伤害(感情等)，使…伤心，使…痛苦：**{adj.}++撕破了的；弄伤了的；割碎的了**++【植物学】(树叶)有缺裂边缘的，边缘有切口的**', '++They are brutal. They can snap each other@s jaws, tails, flippers, lacerate blowholes.**++他们非常残酷，他们全方位攻击对手：咬咽喉、尾巴、鳍肢，撕裂呼吸孔。**++Lacerate: This ability now deals additional damage based on the attack power of the Druid.**++割裂：这个技能现在从德鲁伊的攻击强度获得额外的伤害加成。**++The cats must unsheath their claws and lacerate the kings, ripping away their regal pretensions.**++猫必须伸出爪子去抓挠国王，撕破他们帝王式的自命不凡。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1587', 'lachrymose', '[lækrɪmos]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lachrymose', '{adj.}', '++There still are those lachrymose liberals who can@t stop welling up every time they see a black face in their vicinity.**++那些容易掉泪的自由主义者，每当看到附近有个黑人时，他们的泪水就会喷涌而出。**++Glenn Beck, a lachrymose Fox News pundit, turned Hayek’s “The Road to Serfdom” into an unlikely bestseller earlier this year.**++福克斯新闻的煽情评论家格伦•贝克使哈耶克的《通往奴役之路》出人意料的成为今年早些时候的畅销书。**++Nor did any lachrymose letter in the Times predict a speedy downfall of the Empire for this apathy of its local guardians.**++《泰晤士报》上也没有刊登任何令人痛哭流涕的读者来信，预言说因为殖民地监护人的漠不关心，帝国就要迅速地倾覆②。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1588', 'lackluster', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lackluster', '{...}++...**', '++Last week, Hewlett-Packard pointed to double-digit revenue growth in China as a rare bright spot in an otherwise lackluster earnings report.**++上星期，惠普公司在中国的收入增长达到两位数，是暗淡无光的收益报表里少有的一缕亮色。**++Many blamed the lackluster showing on   No Child Left Behind, the 2001 federal law that requires schools to test students in math and reading, but not science.**++许多人归咎于死板的2001年的联邦法律，不让一个孩子掉队，要求学校测试学生数学和阅读，而不测试科学。**++Last season felt lackluster at times, but with each day bringing little teases like this, we find ourselves getting more and more excited for the upcoming fifth season.**++在上一季中，我们会时不时感到乏味，但是伴随着每天这样的小挑逗，我们发现我们越来越为即将到来的第五季而感到兴奋不已。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1589', 'laconic', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=laconic', '{adj.}', '++The laconic General Kayani has mostly kept out of domestic politics, but he has left no doubt who is in charge.**++说话简洁的基亚尼不大关心国内政治，但是他并没有让人怀疑是谁执掌大权。**++Henry@s date was very laconic, only saying two sentences the entire evening.**++亨利的约会十分简洁，整晚他只说了两句话。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1590', 'lag', '[læɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lag', '{vi.}++落后；拉下；拖延：**++滞后；延迟；慢腾腾地走：**++(渐渐)松懈；(力量、强度)变弱；衰退；减退：**++【弹子戏】向地上标界投掷弹子以决定弹击顺序**++【台球】撞球(以决定开球顺序)**{vt.}++落后于(某人或某事)：**++【统计学】随…而变：**++将(弹子、筹码或钱币等)掷向目标**{n.}++落后；滞后；延迟：迟缓**++落后程序；(两个相关事件间的)间隔时间**++落后者；掉队者；最差者**++【电子学】(两件事之间)相隔的时间；延迟；迟滞**++【机械学】滞后**++向地上标界投掷弹子以决定弹击顺序**{vt.}++[英国俚语]**++关押犯人，流放犯人；放逐罪犯**++逮捕**{n.}++[英国俚语]**++犯人；囚犯；苦役犯；前科犯人**++刑期；流放期；苦役期限**{n.}++桶板；套板**++(锅炉或气缸等的)外壳，外套；护板；防护套**{vt.}++给…加防护套(或绝热层)**', '++I have seen development lag because the poor do not have access to markets and finance.**++我目睹了由于穷人无法进入市场，没有融资渠道而造成的发展滞后。**++We must achieve modernization of science and technology, otherwise we will lag behind other nations.**++我们必须实现科学技术现代化，否则我们要落后于其他国家。**++But to many, at least as far as science is concerned, it is the countries that were doing well that are now doing better, whereas those at the bottom continue to lag significantly behind.**++但是对于许多人而言，至少在科学方面，正是那些在过去做的很好的国家现在正在做的更好，而那些位于底层的国家的科学继续落后。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1591', 'lambaste', '[læmbest]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lambaste', '{vt.}++[口语]**++狠打，痛揍；(用鞭子)狠抽：**++责骂，训斥，严厉申斥：**', '++Teacher@s silent half point at me and lambaste after ring:You are a smelly rascal!**++老师沉默半响后指着我又大骂：你就是一个臭流氓！**++The cool president has turned hot on the stump, stripping to shirtsleeves to lambaste doubters in New Jersey Thursday.**++周四，一向冷静的总统发了火，在新泽西的演讲台上把质疑者们一顿痛骂。**++After an exhausting primary season, the Democratic Party gathers in Denver to anoint its presidential candidate and lambaste the Republicans.**++在经历令人筋疲力尽的初选后，民主党在丹佛正式推出该党候选人，同时批评共和党。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1592', 'lament', '[ləmɛnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lament', '{vi.}++悲痛，伤心，哀悼，悔恨 (for， over):**++悲痛，伤心，哀悼，悔恨 (for， over):**{vt.}++哀悼；为…而悲痛，为…而伤心：**++为…感到遗憾；惋惜：**{n.}++悲哀的表现；悲痛之情；恸哭；哀悼**++哀乐；挽歌；悼词**++抱怨；苦衷；牢骚**', '++We lament （over） his death.**++我们哀悼他的逝世。**++We lament its loss.**++我们哀悼它的消失。**++The essay goes on to lament that lack of inquiry, despite the universality of the phenomenon.**++文章接下来在这种现象的普遍性背景下继续为疑问的缺失“哀悼”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1593', 'lamentable', '[læməntəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lamentable', '{adj.}++可悲的；伤心的；令人惋惜的；不幸的**++(表演)拙劣的；(质量)低劣的**++[罕用语]表示悲痛的；哀伤的**', '++Western countries inclined to take issue with this external empire-building, or with Russia@s lamentable internal democracy and human rights deficit, have been told to save their breath.**++倾向于对其表露于外的帝国建设或其可怜的内在的民主以及人权赤字表达不同意见的西方国家被告知省省吧。**++War with all our might and with all the strength God has given up, and to wage war against a monstrous tyranny never surpassed in the dark and lamentable catalogue of human crime.**++我们的政策就是用我们全部能力，用上帝所给予我们的全部力量，同一个在人类黑暗悲惨的罪恶史上所从未有过的穷凶极恶的暴政进行战争。**++My parish, when I first arrived, was in a lamentable state.**++我的教区，当我第一次到达时，处于破烂的状态中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1594', 'lampoon', '[læmpun]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lampoon', '{n.}++(针对个人的、尖刻的)讽刺文；讽刺作品**{vt.}++用讽刺文章嘲弄；讥讽；奚落：**++用讽刺文章嘲弄；讥讽；奚落：**', '++His cartoons mercilessly lampoon the leading politician of the day.**++他的漫画无情地讽刺了当今的政界要人。**++I mean, you were once, I think - didnt you refer to yourself as a leftist, hippie-loving, "National Lampoon" satirist?**++我的意思是你有一次，我认为，自称为左倾嬉皮士，“国家讽刺”杂志的讽刺家吗？**++It is one thing to attack the stupidity of others, to draw attention to wrong doings, and to lampoon those deserving of it.**++能够攻击别人的愚蠢，对他们错误的言行引起注意，讽刺那些本应该属于那些的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1595', 'lance', '[læns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lance', '{n.}++长矛**++矛状器具；捕鲸矛；捕鲸枪**++＝lancer**++【冶金学】喷枪**++【医学】(外科用)柳叶刀；双刃小刀**++[复数] 枪骑兵；长矛轻骑兵**++【军事】撞杆(旧时装填大炮的弹药杆)**{vt.}++用柳叶刀切开：**++用矛刺穿**++投掷**{vi.}++急速前进**++【历史】持枪矛与某人进行马上比武(中世纪武士的比武方式)**', '++Byron resisted, saying that there had been @more deaths by lancet than by the lance@, but gave in when warned that the disease could ‘deprive him of reason@.**++拜伦起初拒绝这样做，说这世界上“死于手术刀下的人，多于死于长矛下的”，在被警告病症可能使他失去理智后，他还是屈服了。**++Mass demonstrations by unarmed citizens, nearly everywhere facing repression by gas, water and lead with exemplary courage and discipline, have been the lance of the uprisings.**++没有武装的公民进行的群众游行示威，几乎在哪里都遇到了以惩戒性的勇气和规训进行的瓦斯，水枪和铅弹的镇压，它们是起义的长矛。**++Finally, my best friend, Lance, said, “Berk, why didn’t you answer us?**++最后，我最好的朋友兰斯问我：“伯克，你怎么不回答我们？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1596', 'languid', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=languid', '{adj.}++倦怠的；萎靡不振的；无活力的**++无精打采的，懒洋洋的**++缺乏兴趣的，不关心的**++懒散的，迟缓的**', '++The small talk had come, however, in bed, in the languid aftermath of erotic occasions.**++可是这些嘘寒问暖的话过去在床上、在性爱后的倦怠里都会说的。**++On the horizon, where it vanished and melted into the sky, there was the languid glow of a cold autumn sunset. . . .**++在土地溶入天空的地平线处，有一抹倦怠的冰冷的秋季落日。。。**++These languid animals make an easy target for coastal hunters, and they were long sought for their meat, oil, skin, bones, and teeth.**++这些懒洋洋的动物成为沿海猎人容易击中的目标，他们长期来搜索它们的肉、油、皮肤，骨骼和牙齿。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1597', 'languish', '[læŋɡwɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=languish', '{vi.}++失去活力；变得衰弱无力；枯萎，凋谢：**++受折磨；受苦；呻吟：**++松懈，松弛，懈怠：**++焦虑，苦思；渴望：**++显得亲切伤感的样子，做出含情脉脉的伤感之态：**', '++Many sickly ones have there always been among those who muse, and languish for God; violently they hate the discerning ones, and the latest of virtues, which is uprightness.**++在那些无声祷告、为神憔悴的人群中间，总混有许多病态的家伙；他们极端憎恨有洞察力的人，憎恨那些最近得道、坦诚的人。**++The cactus… well, that will have to languish in the bathroom until next Spring.**++仙人掌……，在春天到来前都应该把它放在浴室里。**++They also languish at least six months behind their counterparts in Australia, Canada, New Zealand, Singapore, Japan and Hong Kong.**++与澳大利亚、加拿大、新西兰、新加坡、日本和香港的同龄人相比，他们也落后了六个月。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1598', 'languor', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=languor', '{n.}++疲倦，倦怠，软弱无力；(精神上的)消沉**++精神萎靡，无精打采；无兴趣，漠不关心**++柔情**++呆滞；懒散；沉闷；不活泼**{vi.}++变得衰弱无力，失去活力**', '++It was very like a sea, this deadly languor, that rose and rose and drowned his consciousness bit by bit.**++这种要命的疲倦，就像大海一样，一浪又一浪地涨过来，一点一点地吞噬着他的意识。**++They suspect that the shortened nights of springtime are also responsible for a change in human attitudes and that special languor which we call "spring fever".**++对自然界的生物来说，这是它们生长、繁殖的好时机。 他们还猜想春季夜晚的缩短导致人类心理状态发生变化和睡眠不足，由此引发“春烧”症状。**++Last among the classic aphrodisiacs are those foods that, owing to cost and rarity, connote wealth, luxury and sexual languor.**++最后一类传统催情食品，是那些价格不菲，而且稀罕的东西。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1599', 'lank', '[læŋk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lank', '{adj.}++(头发)平直而软弱的，不卷的**++瘦长的；稀疏的**', '++This is partly out of practical necessity: it is indeed thin and lank.**++当然这里面有实际的必要性,我的发质稀疏平直。**++All lank and bone, the boy stands at the corner with his younger sister, waiting for the yellow bus that takes them to their respective schools.**++一个骨瘦如柴的男孩和他的妹妹站在街角，等着黄色的校车把他们带到他们各自的学校。**++"He was . . . exceedingly lank, with narrow shoulders" (Washington Irving).**++“他…非常瘦，两肩窄小” （华盛顿·欧文）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1600', 'lapse', '[læps]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lapse', '{n.}++(时间的)流逝，间隔；逝去的时间**++失言，口误；笔误；记错**++过失，错失，小错，小疵；失检**++(尤指气温、气压的)跌落，下降**++放弃信仰；违背教义**++废止，中断**++【法律】(由于未能履行义务或行使权力而导致权利或特权的)失效，终止，丧失**++(因继承人死亡而导致的)遗产继承权失效**++(由于未按时交纳保险金而引起的)保险中止**{vi.}++(时间)流逝：**++滑入；陷入(某种状态)：**++倒退；退步；没达到(标准、期望等)：**++终止，结束：**++【法律】(权利、所有权、契约等的)失效；丧失；消灭：**++放弃信仰，背离正道：**{vt.}++废止，使失效；丧失：**++废止，使失效；丧失：**{abbr.}', '++Remind me to renew the driver@s license.It will lapse next month.**++提醒我更换驾驶执照，它下个月就失效了。**++The subscription would lapse after, say, 24 hours, or that could be passed in as a parameter.**++订阅将在一段时间后失效，比方说，24小时，或将其作为一个参数传入。**++Also, the time lapse nature of part of the video causes clouds to appear to jump about and fade in an unfamiliar fashion.**++而且，视频中有一部分的时间流逝从本质上导致了那些云看起来像是在跳跃着，以一种陌生的方式出现。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1601', 'largesse', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=largesse', '{n.}++慷慨的赠予(或赐予)**++赠品，礼品；慷慨赠送的礼物；(巨额)赏金**++[废语]慷慨，大方，大度**', '++But now China is facing the consequences of its largesse.**++但是中国现在要面对着这一慷慨大气的后果。**++Unfortunately, this gesture of largesse comes with a price tag much bigger than that $100 bowl.**++不幸的是，这种慷慨大度的姿态却有比100美元一碗更高昂的价签。**++If you stick with forest squirrels or those that have been subsisting on your garden largesse, you know exactly what that beastie has been snacking on.**++如果你关注那些森林松鼠，或者慷慨地提供给它们你的花园让他们觅食，你就能确切地知道这种动物一直以什么为食。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1602', 'lash', '[læʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lash', '{n.}++鞭子；鞭梢**++鞭打，猛然抽打**++快速掠过**++(波浪、风、雨等的)猛烈拍击；冲击**++讽刺；痛斥，严厉斥责**++(眼)睫毛**++【机械学】(齿轮等的)空隙，余隙**{vt.}++鞭打，抽打：**++猛烈摇动(尾巴等)：**++(波浪、风雨等的)猛烈拍击；冲击：**++抨击；斥责：**++激起；煽动：**++【棒球】打，重击**{vi.}++猛烈抨击；严词谴责；痛斥：**++用鞭子抽打，猛击：**++(波浪、风、雨等的)猛烈拍击；冲刷：**++急速摆动(或扭动)：**{vt.}{n.}{n.}', '++I could work as much and eat as much as a man – when I could get it – and bear the lash as well!**++我干的活一点不少于男人，吃的也不少于男人──只要我能够这样做──而且同样遭受鞭打！**++Conservative treatment involves plucking the offending eyelashes and administering lubricant drops, but many patients will require surgery to either destroy or reposition the lash and follicle.**++保守治疗包括拔除“捣乱”的睫毛，以及使用润滑液，但是许多病人都需要手术来破坏或者矫正睫毛和滤泡的位置。**++From his easy chair he hears the wind lash his house and the rain pound the street outside his home.**++他坐在安乐椅上，只听得呼啸的大风猛烈地冲击着他的屋子，大雨击打着屋外的街面。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1603', 'lassitude', '[læsətʊd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lassitude', '{n.}', '++A dangerous lassitude takes over…China is the world@s second largest economy.**++取而代之的是危险的懒散……中国可是世界上第二大的经济体啊。**++Southern Europe now constitutes a zone of lassitude that extends from Portugal and Spain through the south of France, Italy, the former Yugoslavia, Greece, and Bulgaria.**++现在南欧成了毫无活力的地区，该地区从葡萄牙和西班牙延伸至法国南部、意大利、前南斯拉夫、希腊和保加利亚。**++That supreme effort had exhausted him. His lassitude was now such that he was obliged to pause for breath every three or four steps, and lean against the wall.**++最后的一把劲使他精疲力尽，现在他每走两三步就要靠在墙上喘口气。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1604', 'latent', '[letnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=latent', '{adj.}++潜在的，潜伏的；隐而不见的**++【植物学】潜伏的；休眠的；不发达的**++【心理学、医学】潜在的，隐性的**', '++Once he found his latent abilities he left the island by ship.**++一旦他发现了自己潜在的能力，他就乘船离开了小岛。**++Are the organisms actually doing this in Mono Lake, or do they have the latent ability to do so?**++那些生活在莫诺湖中的有机体实际上是否是这样生存的呢，或者它们是否有着这种潜在的能力呢？**++Load related problems can be found in several areas: validation of ability to meet response and scalability criteria, determination of scaling factors, and the search for latent bugs.**++与负载有关的问题可以在几个地方发现：验证能力是否满足响应和可伸缩性标准、确定扩展因素以及搜索潜在的错误。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1605', 'latitude', '[lætɪtud]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=latitude', '{n.}++【地理学】纬度**++纬度地区**++宽容度；活动余地；(言语、行动等的)回旋余地**++=Astronomical Latitude,celestial latitude**++[古语]范围[参较 Longitude]**', '++Each card has not only a date but the latitude and longitude, salinity measures, temperatures and depth of each data point.**++每个卡片不仅记有日期，还有每个数据点的纬度和经度，盐度，温度和深度的测量。**++Research shows that the latitude of your birthplace and how much solar radiation you were exposed to in the womb affects your health, wealth, happiness, longevity and creativity.**++研究显示，你的出生地的纬度，也就是说，你在子宫中会受到多少太阳的照射，会影响你的健康、财富、幸福、寿命甚至是创造力。**++I thought at this Time the Rain felt Cold, and I was something chilly, which I knew was not usual in that Latitude.**++我感到这回的雨有点寒意，身子感到有点发冷。 我知道，在这个纬度上，这是不常有的事。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1606', 'laudatory', '[lɔdətɔri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=laudatory', '{adj.}', '++There was a nice write-up in the paper, even a laudatory editorial.**++报纸上刊登了一篇捧我的文章，甚至还加了一段赞扬性的社论。**++The cultural and historical significance of Xian, as well as the abundant relics and sites, help Shaanxi enjoy the laudatory title of @Natural History Museum@.**++西安的文化和历史意义，以及丰富的文物和遗址，都使得陕西享有自然史博物馆的美称。**++The first of the three, the 88-floor, 420-meter Jin Mao Tower opened in 1998 to laudatory reviews for its stainless steel pagoda-like design.**++上海未来的天空轮廓线第一座摩天大厦是1998年竣工的420米高的金茂大厦，这座88层高的大楼因不锈钢宝塔形设计获得了一致赞赏。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1607', 'lavish', '[lævɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lavish', '{adj.}++过分慷慨的，大手大脚的，不吝惜的，浪费的，挥霍的**++充裕的，过多的，异常丰富的**{vt.}++滥花，滥用；挥霍，浪费；过分慷慨地给予：**++滥花，滥用；挥霍，浪费；过分慷慨地给予：**', '++Socialize with friends, but don@t overspend on lavish entertainment.**++与朋友进行交往，但不要因奢侈款待而超支。**++After all, in a nation where each group is intent on securing its interests, who is most suitable to rule if not the richest and most lavish man around?**++毕竟，在这个国家里，各个党派各个团体都在追逐自己的利益，如果不让最有钱，最铺张的人来当领袖，还有谁更能胜任呢？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1608', 'lax', '[læks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lax', '{adj.}++马马虎虎的；不严谨的，不严格的；松懈的**++不认真的；放纵的**++松弛的，不紧张的；散漫的**++宽松的，易通便的；腹泻的**++(纺织品)质地疏松的**++【植物学】(花簇)疏松的**++【语音学】(元音)松弛的(如 mel 中的e；hill中的i等)[参较 tense]**{n.}++【语言学】松元音**{n.}{n.}', '++Many are caused by negligence and lax safety procedures.**++原因常常是疏忽大意和松懈的安全措施。**++Concerns with security and IP protection, especially in outsourcing situations in countries where IP laws are more lax, can restrict infrastructure and organizational decisions.**++对安全性和 IP 保护的关注，特别是在 IP 法律较松的国家中外包的情况下，会限制基础结构和组织的决策。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1609', 'leaven', '[lɛvən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=leaven', '{n.}++酵母；发酵剂；面肥**++潜在作用；潜移默化的影响，引起渐变的因素**++色调；色彩；性格**{vt.}++(加发酵剂)使(面团等)发酵：**++影响；使渐变：**{vi.}++渐变**', '++But I make this matzo without leaven in my wood-burning oven under the prescribed 18 minutes from start to finish.**++但是我做这些未发酵面包，不用发酵剂，在木头做燃料的烤箱里，从开始到结束用不了犹太教规定的18分钟。**++As you look through and see the faces of people coping with loss, consider this a leaven to today@s news that the Chinese economy is just now passing Japan@s in total output.**++当你浏览图片，看到人们面对死伤时的表情，把这些当作是对今天新闻的一种影响，而今天的报道中称中国经济在总产出上超越日本。**++Therefore let us keep the feast, not with old leaven, neither with the leaven of malice and wickedness; but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.**++所以，我们守这节不可用旧酵，也不可用恶毒（或作阴毒），邪恶的酵，只用诚实真正的无酵饼。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1610', 'leer', '[lɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=leer', '{n.}++秋波；媚眼；(含敌意或淫意的)一瞥**{vi.}++送秋波；使媚眼；(含敌意或淫意地)斜睨：**++送秋波；使媚眼；(含敌意或淫意地)斜睨：**{vt.}++以(目光)挑逗**{n.}{adj.}++[英国方言]**++饿得发昏的；饥肠辘辘的**++无负担的**', '++It also has its own consumer brands, like Van Houten and Van Leer. Listed on the Zurich stock exchange, its shares have soared more than 50 percent this year.**++它也拥有自己的消费者品牌，比如Van Houten 和Van Leer，它已经在苏黎世证券交易所上市，今年股票上涨了超过50%。**++But as he pressed toward the door he saw the larger gangster waving to him, a leer on his square face, and Kostya did not resist.**++不过，就在他向门口挤去的时候，他看到了那个大块头在向他招手，他的方脸上挂着一丝暧昧的神态。 克斯特亚没有拒绝。**++Her father gave a lazy leer.**++她父亲懒懒的瞥了她一眼。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1611', 'leery', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=leery', '{adj.}++提防的；留神的；猜疑的；对…有戒心的(常与 about，of连用)**++送秋波的；使媚眼的；斜眼看的**++(服装等)浮华的**++(行为等)浮夸的，华而不实的**++[古语]狡猾的；机敏的；警觉的**{adj.}', '++That helps keep them hidden from the public eye by companies leery of publicizing breaches in corporate security.**++这有助于它们在企业安全中通过狡猾的宣传漏洞逃出公司公众眼底。**++I’m not as confident those graphs are going to hold up for fields besides computer science, so I’d be leery of betting on a date.**++偶可不那么相信这些图表还能在包括计算机科学内的其他领域继续嚣张下去，所以偶在日期上打赌做文章。**++Be very leery of the results of any performance measurement that does not involve a realistic program load over a long period of time.**++对于那些没有包含什么实际的程序负荷，测试时间不够长的性能测试的结果，一定要非常当心。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1612', 'legacy', '[lɛgəsi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=legacy', '{n.}++遗产；遗赠(物)**++[比喻]遗产；传统；祖传的东西**{adj.}++【计算机】(软件)使用时间过长而难以维护的**', '++One proviso  is attached to this legacy.**++这个遗赠附带一项限制性条款。**++These books are his legacy to the college.**++这些书籍是他给学院的遗赠。**++We are the keepers of this legacy.**++我们是这个遗产的保存者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1613', 'legend', '[lɛdʒənd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=legend', '{n.}++传奇，传说[参较 myth]**++民间传说，民间故事；传说故事，传奇文学；稗史**++传奇人物**++传奇人物的业绩**++(钱币、盾形纹章等上的)镌刻文字，刻印文字；刻字；铭文**++(插图、照片、地图、图表等上的)文字说明；题目；标题；凡例；图例；符号一览表**++[口语]香饽饽(特受欢迎的人)**++[废语]圣徒生活故事集；圣贤集**', '++This legend still spreads abroad among the people.**++这个传奇故事依然在民间广泛流传。**++If you are filtering a graph, the label is a legend in the graph.**++如果您过滤的是一个图表，这个标签是图表中的图例。**++To many, a legend must be a story, with characters and some sort of plot.**++其中绝大部分人认为都市传奇必须是一个有人物有情节的故事。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1614', 'legion', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=legion', '{n.}++【罗马历史】古罗马军团(通常由约3 000至6 000名步兵组，并辅以骑兵)**++众多的士兵；大批的部队；大军；军团**++大量；大批；众多**++[常作 L-](半)军事性单位、协会(或团体)**++[L-] American Legion, Foreign Legion 的缩略形式**{adj.}++大量的；大批的；众多的**', '++Outside the church door, veterans from the British Legion form a guard of honor.**++在教堂大门外，有来自英国军团的退伍老兵组成的仪仗队。**++She asked her legion of fans -- whom she calls "Little Monsters" -- to buy a bracelet on her website saying, "We Pray for Japan," for donations of $5 or more.**++她号召被她称作小恶人的众多的粉丝,都参与到她的网站来，“捐出5美金甚至更多的善款的同时让我们为日本祈福“。**++It keeps you in touch with the people you already know. It lets them know you haven’t died or joined the French Foreign Legion.**++这让你和你早已认识的人保持联系，让他们知道你还活着或是没有加入法国外籍军团。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1615', 'lenient', '[linɪənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lenient', '{adj.}++宽大的；宽容的；宽厚的；厚道的；仁慈的；怜悯的**++[古语]镇痛的；缓和性的；减轻痛苦的；起镇定作用的；润泽的**', '++The judge was lenient with the wrongdoer.**++法官对这个犯人很宽大。**++And I must say, Mum was pretty darned lenient defining those two categories. Maybe she just hoped that the lesson would rub off eventually.**++然而我必须说，母亲是如此优雅有理，仁慈的定义这那两款类型。也许她仅仅是希望教训会最终抹掉。**++Germany had to ask, humiliatingly, for lenient implementation of the Stability Pact it had insisted upon, and the European Union agreed.**++德国只能低声下气地乞求他曾一再坚持的《稳定公约》能够对其宽大处理，而欧盟同意了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1616', 'lethal', '[liθl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lethal', '{adj.}++致命的；(会)致死的**++死亡的；有死亡征兆的**++毁灭性的；杀伤性的；危害极大的**++[美国英语]为购买武器进行的；(外援)以武器形式进行的**', '++In situation like this, she wish she have a gun or some lethal weapon.**++在这种情况下，她真希望自己有一把枪或什么致命武器。**++But scientists have yet to figure out what causes the mutations, when they will occur and what makes certain viruses more lethal than others.**++但科学家迄今尚未找出突变原因、它们什么时候会发生和为什么某些病毒比其它病毒更致命。**++But if we use it to attack others, it immediatly becomes an lethal weapon.**++但如果我们用它攻击其他人的话，那它马上就会成为致命的武器。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1617', 'lethargic', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lethargic', '{adj.}++昏睡的；嗜睡的；患嗜睡症的；懒散的；懒洋洋的；无精打采的**++叫人昏昏欲睡的；催人昏睡的；使人懒洋洋的[亦作 lethargical]**', '++The cat became lethargic and had trouble breathing.**++这只猫整天昏睡而且呼吸困难。**++The koala seemed to be asleep, and I wondered for the first time just how one went about startling such a lethargic creature.**++那只树熊似乎睡着了。 第一次干这活儿，我真不知怎么去惊吓一只昏睡的动物。**++The other bonus of getting on with some tidying is that you’ll get a sense of achievement from it – a great spur to doing more, if you’re feeling lethargic or lazy.**++整理和收拾产生的另外一个作用就是会让我们产生一种成就感，因为当您感到困倦或者懒洋洋的时候，我们可以从中获得一种鼓舞和满足的感觉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1618', 'levelheaded', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=levelheaded', '{adj.}', '++Remain calm and levelheaded.**++保持冷静和明智。**++A:  I am knowledgeable and levelheaded.**++我知识丰富、头脑冷静。**++The picture emerging is a mirror image of the traditional gender map: men and markets on the side of the irrational and overemotional, and women on the side of the cool and levelheaded.**++这种景象是传统性别图示的生动反映：男性和市场的关系是非理性和情绪化的，而女性和市场的关系是冷静和稳健的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1619', 'levity', '[lɛvəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=levity', '{n.}++(言谈举止的)轻率，轻浮，轻佻**++轻率(或轻浮、轻佻)的举止或表现**++变化无常，多变；不稳定；三心二意**++[罕用语]轻**', '++I am sure foreigners must think our levity is baffling.**++外国人肯定认为我们的轻浮举止不可理喻。**++It also reintroduces much-needed levity to an act that can be overbearingly self-serious.**++它也再次对这可能会是不可一世的惺惺作态之举（overbearingly self-serious），引入急需的轻率。**++Of course I can understand why they might consider tourists frolicking with his likeness to be a display of inappropriate levity.**++我当然能理解他们为什么会觉得游客对希特勒肖像的嬉戏是不适当的轻浮表现。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1620', 'liability', '[laɪəbɪləti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=liability', '{n.}++(应负的)责任；(应履行的)义务**++倾向[亦作 liableness]**++不利条件，碍事的人(或物)；缺点**++可能性**++[复数] 【会计学】债务，欠款，负债**', '++On the other hand, your debt is an asset to the bank, but it is your liability.**++在另一方面，你的债务是银行的一种资产，但它却是你的债务。**++Your savings are a liability to the bank even though those same savings are an asset to you.**++你的储蓄对银行来说是一种债务，虽然这些储蓄也是你的一种资产。**++When guests come onto your property, you legally take on a certain amount of liability for their safety.**++当客人来到你家，你在法律上为他们的安全承担了一定数额的赔偿责任。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1621', 'liberal', '[lɪbərəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=liberal', '{adj.}++大方的；慷慨的；愿大量给予的**++大量的，丰富的；丰盛的；充足的，充裕的**++心胸宽阔的；能采纳不同意见的；不受传统观念束缚的**++宽容的；容忍的；无偏见**++开明的；主张改革的(尤指主张政治改革、个性解放的)**++自由主义的**++[L-](英国、加拿大等国)自由党的**++代表制政府的；共和政体的(区别于君主制和贵族制)**++大学文科的；文科教育的**++[美国英语]不拘泥于字面意义的；自由随便的；不苛刻的**++[古语]自由民的，适合自由人的；不受限制的**++[废语]放肆的；吊儿郎当的**{n.}++开明的人；自由主义者**++[L-](尤指英国或加拿大等国的)自由党党员**', '++They disagreed on how to define “liberal”.**++他们对如何解释“liberal”一词的词义有不同意见。**++Anyone who does not agree with the liberal side of Hollywood does not deserve to work in Hollywood!**++谁要是不站在好莱坞的自由主义者这边，谁就别想再好莱坞混！**++As for the content, I can tell you that on average people in Zurich have a liberal attitude to this reform.**++至于内容，我可以告诉你们，普遍来说，苏黎世人民对待这次改革都采取了自由主义的态度。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1622', 'libertine', '[lɪbɚtin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=libertine', '{n.}++(道德或性方面)放荡不羁的人，浪子，浪荡子，放荡的人，淫荡的人**++我行我素的人**++[古语] 【宗教】自由思想家；怀疑论者**++(古罗马)获得自由的奴隶**{adj.}++放荡不羁的，放荡的，淫荡的；放肆的；无法无天的**++自由自在的，不受约束的**++持自由思想的**++[古语]无限制的，无控制的**', '++All this explains why Berlusconi’s libertine reputation isn’t a political impediment, as it would be in the United States.**++这一切便解释了为何贝鲁斯科尼的放荡名声不会是他的政治绊脚石，在美国则不然了。**++When a landowning libertine takes a fancy to her, she begins an affair which ends when he abandons her on the eve of their elopement.**++当一个放荡的地主看上她时，她开始了一段婚外情，直到这个人在他们私奔前期抛弃了她。**++After the aristocratic libertine, Rodolphe, first sees Emma, he goes home certain that he is going to get his way with her.**++在鲁道夫，一个贵族浪荡子，第一次见到艾玛之后，就已经确信可以把她搞到手。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1623', 'license', '[laɪsns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=license', '{vt.}++许可；特许；准许；批准；发许可证(或执照)给…：**++许可；特许；准许；批准；发许可证(或执照)给…：**{n.}++[美国英语]＝licence**', '++The lack of a license was pinching me.**++没有执照我感到很不安**++No special license will be regranted to anyone from now on.**++特殊许可证今后不得向任何人再行发放。**++The next time the client connects to the server, it will obtain another license.**++在客户端下一次连接到服务器时，它将获得另一个许可证。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1624', 'licentious', '[laɪsɛnʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=licentious', '{adj.}++放荡的；淫乱的；纵欲的**++放肆的；越轨的；不道德的；无法无天的**++破格的；漠视常规的；不顾约束的**', '++She felt a little upset about her licentious behavior.**++她对他放肆的行为感到有点不舒服。**++She felt a bit comfortlessness to his licentious behavior.**++她对他放肆的行为感到有点不舒服。**++Saint Augustine, as you know before he became a Christian, had quite a kind of licentious life, sexually, and lived with women and … that kind of thing.**++我们都知道圣奥古斯丁在信主前过着一种性生活非常放纵的生活，诸如和很多女人同居之类。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1625', 'liken', '[laɪkən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=liken', '{vt.}', '++The authors of The Power of Nice liken those positive impressions to seeds that you plant.**++《友善的力量》的作者把这种正面的印象比作是您预先撒下的种子。**++Ostriches are descendants of dinosaurs, and the researchers liken ostrich movements to those of bipedal dinosaurs.**++鸵鸟是恐龙的后裔，研究人员将鸵鸟的运动比作两足恐龙的运动。**++But while some were tempted to liken the past few days to the depths of the financial crisis, investors pointed out key differences.**++不过，尽管一些人很想把过去几天比作金融危机最深重的时候，投资者却指出了重要的不同点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1626', 'limber', '[lɪmbɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=limber', '{adj.}++易弯曲的；柔软的；柔韧的；灵活的**++可塑的；思想灵活的**{vt.}++使柔软 (常与 up 连用)：**++使柔软 (常与 up 连用)：**{vi.}++变得柔软；使自己柔软；(赛前)做准备活动 (常与 up 连用)：**++变得柔软；使自己柔软；(赛前)做准备活动 (常与 up 连用)：**{n.}++【军事】(野炮拖车或弹药车的)前车**{vt.}++把(火炮等)系于前车(准备拖车)**{vi.}++连接前车和火炮 (常与 up 连用)；上架：**++连接前车和火炮 (常与 up 连用)；上架：**', '++You should limber up your wits before the test.**++在测验之前你该动动脑筋。**++Here, we@re talking about a regular stretching program to keep your legs limber and injury-free.**++这里，我们要谈论的是一个常规的伸展训练以保持你的四肢柔软，不轻易受伤。**++But his bow remained steady, his strong arms stayed limber, because of the hand of the Mighty One of Jacob, because of the Shepherd, the Rock of Israel**++但他的弓仍旧坚硬， 他的手健壮敏捷，这是因以色列的牧者，以色列的磐石，就是雅各的大能者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1627', 'limp', '[lɪmp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=limp', '{vi.}++一瘸一拐地走，跛行，蹒跚：**++慢腾腾地进行；缓慢费力地进行：**++进展缓慢；几乎无进展；停滞不前**++(诗歌)韵律紊乱**{n.}++跛行**++慢腾腾的前进**{adj.}++柔软的；易曲的；松沓的**++疲倦的；疲乏的；劳顿的；无生气的；软绵绵的**++(性格)软弱的**++(封面装订)软面的；非硬纸板的**', '++For the rest of his life, he walked with a limp and sometimes used a cane.**++在之后的人生里，车祸造成他一只脚跛行，有时他还会使用拐杖。**++Your muscles are feeling loose and limp, so relaxed, so deliciously serene, so wonderfully lazy.**++你的肌肉放松且柔软，如此的放松，如此平静至极，如此懒散至极。**++The pain increases as you continue running and will typically cause you to limp.**++这种疼痛感随着继续跑步愈发厉害并将会典型地导致跛行。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1628', 'limpid', '[lɪmpɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=limpid', '{adj.}++(水、空气等)清澈的；透明的**++平静的；无忧无虑的**++(文体等)清晰的，明朗的，畅达的**', '++Regards joyfully the innovation, lets the chaos becomes limpid, he has made the catalyst for China.**++把创新当成快乐，让混沌变得清澈，他为中国制造了催化剂。**++At the foot of the mountain, limpid water of the lake follows the wavy terrain and becomes a serene river flowing east.**++山脚下，清澈的湖水随山形地貌演变为一条宁静舒缓的河流，宛转而东去。**++Her writing is so beautiful, so steady and even and limpid, that she might have evaded confronting these tribalisms head-on, but she doesn@t.**++她的行文优美平稳，平淡清澈，她满可以绕绕弯子，不直面宗族主义这类棘手问题，但她没有，她选择了勇敢面对。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1629', 'linger', '[lɪŋɡɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=linger', '{vi.}++徘徊；继续逗留；留恋；流连；闲荡：**++历久犹存；缓慢消失：**++苟延残喘：**++沉思；沉湎于**++延误；拖延；迟缓；磨蹭**++漫步；闲逛**{vt.}++混日子，消磨，挨过(时间等)(常与 away 或 out 连用)：**++[口语]拖长，拖延**', '++There they linger for two or three weeks, maybe four.**++它们在那里消磨两、三个星期，或四个星期。**++The night would linger long enough for what would come or not come.**++夜晚还会逗留足够长的时间以至于发生什么或者不发生什么。**++Instability is allowed in this environment, but should not be allowed to linger.**++这个环境中允许不稳定，但是不允许构建版本停留太长时间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1630', 'lionize', '[laɪənaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lionize', '{vt.}++把…捧成名人；把…作为名流看待**++[英国英语]游览(某地的)名胜；引导(某人)游览(某地的)名胜**{vi.}++结交名人；巴结名流**++[英国英语]游览名胜，观光[英国英语亦作 lionise]**', '++The press began to lionize him enthusiastically.**++媒体开始狂热地吹捧他。**++And if they continued to lionize him in a public fashion, that these kinds of public demonstrations can only have a profoundly negative effect on our relationship.**++而且，如果他们继续大张旗鼓地欢迎此人，这种公开展示的方式只能对我们的关系产生深远的负面影响。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1631', 'lissome', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lissome', '{adj.}++(尤指身体)柔软的；易弯曲的**++敏捷的；灵活的；轻快的**', '++As an 18 year-old high school student, a picture taken at a track meet in New York showed the olive-toned, lissome athlete in a white tank top and black shorts.**++一个18岁的高中生，在纽约田径运动会上展示高调的橄榄风采，穿着白色坦克上衣和黑色热裤。**++Her foot touches the plate and sets off the trap, but so swift and lissome is she that her ankles evade the clash of the serrated iron jaws as they spring together.**++她的脚稍微碰了一下盘子便引燃了预设的陷阱，幸好她的动作快捷敏锐，这些满地碎落飞散的锯齿铁刄才没弄伤她的脚踝。**++It seems Toto has his second kiss from a lissome banker@s daughter, a rainstorm buss worthy of Anna Magnani.**++似乎托托的二吻给了一个灵巧的银行家的女儿，安娜马格娜妮暴风雨般的吻。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1632', 'list', '[lɪst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=list', '{n.}++表；一览表；目录；名单**++=list price**++(交易所)全部上市证券**++一系列；一连串**{vt.}++把…编列成表；把…列入名单中；登记：**++列举：**++自称(常与as连用)：**++(在证券交易所)将(证券)列入上市证券表**++[古语]征募，使服兵役**{vi.}++被列入价目表：**++[口语]从军；应召入伍[现用 enlist]**{n.}++布边，边条，织边**++布条，(其他材料的)狭条**++(任何类型的)条，带**++(动物身上的)有色条纹**++木条，树皮条，边材木条**++【建筑学】边饰；嵌条**++(头发或胡须的)分缝**++[美国英语]田埂，犁沟，垄沟**++[复数] 【英国历史】(中世纪竞技场的)栅栏；竞技场，比武场；竞争场所**++[废语]边界；界线；境界 —enter the lists 1.参加竞争(或竞选、辩论等) 2.挑战，应战(常与against 连用)**{vt.}++给…加布边**++把(布条等)拼成一块**++(沿狭板、厚板等边缘)截下窄木条**++犁地；耕地；起垄；作田埂**{vi.}++用起垄机耕地**{adj.}++用布条制的；用织边制的**{n.}++(船只等的)倾侧；倾斜**{vt.,vi.}++(使)倾侧；(船只等)倾斜：**++(使)倾侧；(船只等)倾斜：**{vt.}++list,listed,第三人称单数现在式 list或listeth  ／listiɵ／  [古语]**++称…的心，中…的意；讨…欢心；使喜欢：**++想要；喜爱**{vi.}++想要，愿意；喜欢；希望：**++想要，愿意；喜欢；希望：**{n.}++意愿；意向；倾向**{vi.}++[古语]听，留神听**{vt.}++倾听；听见**', '++I marked out an item in the list.**++我从清单上划掉了一个项目。**++No one could phony a list like that.**++没有人能够假造像这样的一份清单。**++You should check each item off as she dictates the list.**++她念清单时你应当逐项核对并打勾。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1633', 'lithe', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lithe', '{adj.}++柔软的；易弯曲的**++轻快的;敏捷的[亦作 lithesome ]**', '++Just an impression of graceful, lithe forms. Then nothing.**++印象中除了优美、轻盈外，别无其他。**++Six boys and five girls, lithe and thin, their skin dusky from the sun and a film of dust and ash.**++六个男孩，五个女孩，柔软、纤细，皮肤因为日晒和尘灰而色泽发暗。**++Made of carbon fiber (developed in partnership with Callaway Golf), it@s both light and more lithe.**++由于周身由碳纤维制成，它不光轻盈而且柔软。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1634', 'loath', '[loθ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=loath', '{adj.}', '++As much as we might be loath to admit it, what the Internet is saying about us matters.**++不管你多么不情愿承认，互联网上关于我们的信息已经与我们切身相关了。**++Alas, I am loath to cheapen her existence and dignify the city’s anti-cat stance by creating a dog-like defense for her.**++哎，我讨厌用狗一般的姿态保护玛贝尔，这简直就是在贬低她的存在，助长这个城市讨伐猫咪的声音。**++The renminbi could be an alternative in the far future -- but after the 2008 financial crisis, China is loath to open up its capital markets.**++在遥远的未来人民币可能成为另一种储备货币──然而在2008年金融危机之后，中国并不愿意全面开放资本市场。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1635', 'loathe', '[loð]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=loathe', '{vt.}', '++I loathe it; I would not live alway.**++我厌恶生命，我不愿意永远活着。**++But I loathe this term and want all or nothing.**++但是我厌恶这个术语，要么获得一切，要么一切都不要。**++But then I started to loathe myself for giving in and wasting so much time on it.**++但随后我便开始厌恶自己的投降；厌恶自己在这上面浪费了如此多的时间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1636', 'lofty', '[lɔfti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lofty', '{adj.}++极高的；高耸的；巍峨的**++高尚的；崇高的**++高傲的；傲慢的；优越感强的**++高级的；高贵的；地位高的**++(作品或演讲)风格高超的；玄虚的；高深莫测的**++【船舶学】桅杆特高的**', '++The voice conveys  the common wish and the lofty idea of mankind.**++呼声传达了一种普通的愿望和人类的崇高理想.**++So do you have an inspiring peer group of people around you with equally lofty ideals and goals?**++那么你周围有没有和你一样拥有崇高理想和目标的同龄人呢？**++Let us work together with wisdom and courage to build such a new order and advance the lofty cause of peace and development for mankind.**++让我们拿出智慧和勇气，为推动建立这种新秩序，为人类和平与发展的崇高事业，团结奋斗，携手共进。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1637', 'loll', '[lɑl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=loll', '{vi.}++懒洋洋地倚靠(或躺)着：**++(懒散地)闲荡，闲逛：**++(舌头等)垂伸：**++(头等)垂下：**{vt.}++把(头、手、脚等)懒洋洋地倚靠着**++使垂下；使悬垂；把(舌头)伸出：**{n.}++[古语]**++依靠；闲逛**++闲逛者；游手好闲的人**++悬垂，下垂**++悬垂物；下垂的东西**', '++Now, come on, Loll. You@re a big boy now.**++别这样，听话，劳尔，你现在都是一个大男孩了。**++When Ramona on The Real Housewives of New York reaffirmed her marriage vows, she rented a yacht for her girlfriends to loll about on.**++罗蒙娜在《纽约真正的主妇》节目中重申了她的结婚誓言，她租用了一艘游艇让自己的女友们在上面休闲。**++Her hips were large, thighs stout like banana stalks, on the whole a mattresslike creature on which a patron could loll all night without a scrap of covering—"Awful monster!**++她臀部硕大，大腿很结实，像香蕉梗一样。 她整个人就像一个大棉垫，他的男人们可以一丝不挂地整夜安睡此上。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1638', 'lopsided', '[,lɑpsaɪdɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lopsided', '{adj.}++一边倒的；向一侧倾斜的**++偏重的；不平衡的；不匀称的；不对称的**', '++They aim to give this lopsided world a greater degree of balance, in opportunities, in income levels, and in health.**++其目的是在机遇、收入水平和健康方面，为这一不平衡的世界提供更大程度的平衡。**++Its particular molecular structure involves a lopsided arrangement of fluorine atoms on one side and hydrogen atoms on the other.**++其特殊的分子结构在于一侧是氟原子而另一侧是氢原子的不平衡排列。**++Data from the spacecraft orbiting the tiny planet indicate it has a lopsided magnetic field, a surprising abundance of sulfur and unusual @hollows@ on its surface.**++围绕这颗微小行星飞行的航天器发回的数据显示 它有一个不平衡磁场 其表面拥有令人惊讶的丰富硫磺和奇特洞穴。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1639', 'loquacious', '[ləkweʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=loquacious', '{adj.}++多话的，话多的，饶舌的，喋喋不休的，过于健谈的**++冗长的**++(水)潺潺不息的；(鸟)啁啾不休的**', '++Would you guess women are more loquacious?**++你会认为女人更健谈吗？**++For example, you could describe someone as"Tautologically loquacious".**++例如，你可以描述一个人‘同义反复地罗嗦’。**++He said that despite older adults being less “loquacious” or talkative than their younger adult counterparts, they elicit much more vocal responses when calling.**++他说，不管老人不太“饶舌”还是比年轻同伴更多话，他们呼叫时都能激发更多的语音回应。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1640', 'loutish', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=loutish', '{adj.}', '++I can hear those loutish grunts of protest.**++我能听见一些粗鲁又愚蠢的抗议声。**++Where children respect a parent and know that he or she demands good behavior in school, even mediocre or loutish teachers can pull off the trick④of producing modestly literate and numerate children.**++如果孩子尊重父母，并且知道父母要求自己好好上学，即便是平庸的或是很笨的老师也能够成功地教出一般水平的能读会算的小学生。**++Children cannot learn in classes where loutish behaviour and disrespect for others are the norm.**++他指出，这些“问题孩子”不能够在普通的学校学习，因为他们总是不尊敬老师和影响其他同学。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1641', 'lubricate', '[lubrɪket]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lubricate', '{vt.}++上油；给…注润滑油；给…涂润滑剂：**++使平滑；使滑润；用润滑剂：**++使顺畅；对…有帮助：**++[美国俚语](为使事情顺利进行等)向…劝酒；对…行贿；收买：**{vi.}++充当润滑剂；起润滑作用：**++[俚语]饮酒；喝一杯；喝醉**', '++Literally. Tears not only lubricate our eyeballs and eyelids, they also prevent dehydration of our various mucous membranes.**++从字面上看，泪水不仅润滑我们的眼球和眼睑，还可以防止各种黏膜脱水。**++Abstainers seem to have a harder time making strong friendship bonds, perhaps because they don@t have alcohol to lubricate their social interactions.**++不饮酒的人似乎更难以建立牢固的友谊，这可能是因为他们在社会交往中没有酒作为润滑剂。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1642', 'lucid', '[lusɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lucid', '{adj.}++透明的；清澈的**++明白的；明晰的；易懂的；可理解的**++理智的，有头脑的，头脑清醒的，神智清醒的**++[诗歌用语]光辉的；明亮的**++【植物学、动物学】光滑的；有光泽的**++【天文学】肉眼可见的**', '++You have to be lucid and in control.**++你必须保持清醒和控制力。**++It is lucid thought that provokes it, but in that very act that thought repudiates itself.**++正是清醒的思想激发了它，但是又是在这种行为之中，思想否定自己。**++For an absurd work of art to be possible, thought in its most lucid form must be involved in it.**++为了让荒谬的艺术作品成为可能，思想必须以它最清醒的形式赋在作品之中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1643', 'ludicrous', '[ludɪkrəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ludicrous', '{adj.}', '++I have to assume that other designers actually work like this in order for someone to get that ludicrous idea in their head.**++我必须假设其他设计师事实上以这样的方式按部就班地为某人工作，以获得某人脑袋瓜中的滑稽主意。**++There was unfortunately no one there but I who could realise the atrociously ludicrous way in which the Behaga mode combined with those absurd verses.**++不幸的是，那时候除了我之外，没有人能听得出贝阿伽曲调和那可笑的诗句结合在一起，是如此的滑稽有趣。**++Newspapers publish some ludicrous stories every year, although some of them are actually true.**++报纸上每年都会刊登一些荒唐的故事，尽管其中有一些是真的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1644', 'lug', '[lʌɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=lug', '{vt.}++用力拉，使劲拖：**++[口语]将(题外话)硬扯进去：**++(帆船)在大风中不顾危险张过量的帆**{vi.}++用劲拉，使劲拖**++拖动；沉重地移动**{n.}++(用力的)拉；拖；用力搬重物**++[美国口语]被拖的东西**++[美国英语]运水果箱**++[美国俚语]笨蛋，笨家伙**++[美国俚语](政客、警察等)敲诈勒索的钱财[主要用于 put the lug on (向…敲诈)]**{n.}++[苏格兰英语]耳朵**++(用作柄或把手的)耳状物**++(马具上的)皮环**++【电学】焊片；接线片**++【机械学】突缘；凸起部**{n.}{n.}{abbr.}', '++As with some of the other tribal groups in Yunnan, women carry firewood up the dirt paths and  lug rocks at construction sites.**++这里跟云南其他一些少数民族地区一样，泥土路上扛着柴火的、盖房子时拉石头的都是女人。**++Later insults included fitchcock, muckworm, whiffler, ramscallion, squinny and snool, not to mention such 20th-century additions as tripe-hound, shite-poke, roach and lug.**++后来，人们用fitchcock, muckworm, whiffler, ramscallion, squinny 和 snool来侮辱彼此。 到了20世纪，此类词汇又有了新成员加入：tripe-hound, shite-poke, roach 和 lug。**++So these roller bags that make it easier to lug your junk around airports are in keeping with etymology stretching back more than 600 years.**++有了这种装有滚轮的箱包，你在机场就能轻松地拖着大堆杂物四处行走，这种形象也和它600多年前的词源相一致。**');
