insert into GREWordBook values ('1666', 'maladroit', '[,mælədrɔɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=maladroit', '{adj.}', '++At Trinity College at the University of Toronto, he was even more socially maladroit. He assumed the pose of young Republican and put a poster of Ronald Reagan on his wall.**++在多伦多一个大学的三合一学院里他在社交方面显得更加笨拙，他拒绝参加任何的青年团队社团，并在他的墙上贴着Ronald Reagan 的图片。**++A mix of live action and CG animation, the story starts in the Middle Ages, when the maladroit sorcerer Gargamel (Hank Azaria) finally discovers the location of Smurf Village.**++混合真人实景和计算机绘图动画，这个起源于中世纪的故事，笨拙的巫师格格巫（汉克 阿扎利亚）最终发现了蓝精灵村的所在地。**++We knew that he had some problems somewhere from his maladroit movements.**++从他笨拙的动作我们就知道了他身体某处有问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1667', 'malaise', '[məlez]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=malaise', '{n.}++(发病前或初病时的)身体不适**++不舒服；不快；抑郁；浑身虚弱**++(由于社会风气或道德观念的败落而产生的)模糊的不满意识**', '++But like many of my friends and I, these people are putting their wallets away and hunkering down for years of economic malaise.**++但就像我的很多朋友和我一样，这些人正在收起自己的钱包，做好准备迎接长达数年的经济不景气。**++I think we@re in for a longer trend of either malaise or just a down channel.**++我想我们或者面临较长期的疲软趋势,或者是处在下行通道内.**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1668', 'malcontent', '[mælkəntɛnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=malcontent', '{adj.}++不满的；不满现状的；不平的**++反叛的，反抗的**{n.}++不满者；不满现状者**++反叛者，反抗者**', '++All the trouble are caused by a handful of malcontent.**++这些是非都是由一小撮不满分子搬弄的。**++Jason Kidd was once a gifted malcontent who essentially quit on the Nets to get himself traded to Dallas.**++贾森·基德在篮网队效力时表现出了不满的情绪，最后主动要求交易到小牛队。**++Very public notice by employees will likely continue, with younger workers more apt to broadcast their malcontent, workplace experts say.**++一位职场专家认为，随着年轻雇员更倾向于发泄出他们的不满，更多的辞职秀会上演。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1669', 'malevolent', '[məlɛvələnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=malevolent', '{adj.}++含有恶意的，敌意的，恶毒的**++存心不良的，报复的，邪恶的**++坏的，有害的，伤害的**', '++Then he is malevolent.**++那么他是恶毒的。**++Fortunately, they can be beaten, as indicated by the liberation of the Procyon people from these malevolent, self centered, self-serving... life draining entities.**++幸运的是，它们被击败，我们被南河三人从这些恶毒的、自私自利的、以自我为中心的......生命枯竭的实体手中解放。**++But be wary, for the most basic tenets of rationalism, openness and freedom that nourish you now and seem so unassailable are about to be harried and besieged by malevolent, mad and medieval minds.**++但要谨慎，那些对你而言最基本的信条：理性主义、开明思想和自由权利将会被恶毒的，暴跳如雷的老古董滋扰。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1670', 'malicious', '[məlɪʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=malicious', '{adj.}++恶意的，恶毒的；蓄意的，预谋的**++【法律】蓄意的，恶意的**', '++You ought to kick back at such malicious slander.**++你应当对这种恶意诽谤进行反击。**++The malicious rumours compromised her good reputation.**++恶毒的谣言使她的好名声受到损害。**++Of these three, theft is the most obvious because the act itself is malicious.**++在这三种之中，盗窃是最明显的，因为其行为本身就是恶意的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1671', 'malign', '[məlaɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=malign', '{adj.}++邪恶的；有害的；不良的**++恶意的，敌意的，恶毒的**++极有害的；致命的；恶性的；癌的**{vt.}++中伤；诽谤；诋毁；诬蔑**', '++We still dwell in the Valley of the Shadow, lurk in its desolate places, peering from brambles and thickets at its mad, malign inhabitants.**++我们依旧在影子的峡谷里生存，埋伏在荒凉的地方，从荆棘和丛林中凝视着，去诽谤那里的居民。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1672', 'malignant', '[məlɪgnənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=malignant', '{adj.}++恶意的；恶毒的**++邪恶的；非常有害的**++【医学】恶性的；致命的；有毒的；癌的**++[废语](对政治状况等)不满的；有谋叛之心的**{n.}++[古语]叛逆者；(对政治现状)不满者**', '++A cancer is a malignant tumour.**++癌是一种恶性瘤。**++Though lumps are not all malignant, or cancerous, early discovery is always an advantage.**++尽管“块煤”并不一定是恶性或癌性的，但尽早发现总归是件好事。**++In today@s market, we find a whole series of products deprived of their malignant properties: coffee without caffeine, cream without fat, beer without alcohol.**++我们可以从今天的市场中发现一系列被消除了有害属性的产品：无咖啡因的咖啡，无糖的奶油，无酒精的啤酒。**');
