insert into GREWordBook values ('1736', 'minatory', '[mɪnə,təri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=minatory', '{adj.}', '++How eliminate this kind of harmful information " is content minatory "?**++如何消除这种有害信息的“内容威胁”？**++If can raise the vitamin D level inside him body effectively, what can let millions person every year avoid to die is minatory .**++如果能够有效提高自己体内的维生素D水平，则每年可以让数百万人避免死亡的威胁。**++Stoke City were this week’s roadkill and, if anything, this ruthless execution was more minatory than any number of six-goal massacres.**++斯托克城队则成为本周比赛的牺牲品。 甚至可以说，这场不留情面的比赛比任何一场打进六球的狂胜都让人胆寒。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1737', 'mince', '[mɪns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mince', '{vt.}++将(肉)切碎，剁碎，切细，(用绞肉机)绞碎：**++细分；再分小；因细分而破坏：**++[贬义]假斯文(或扭扭捏捏)地迈着小步走(路)：**++假装高雅(或彬彬有礼)地说；装腔作势地发(词的)音**++客气地说，委婉地说，欲言又止，吞吞吐吐，温和地表示：**++[古语]掩饰；使看来显得不重要：**{vi.}++假斯文(或扭扭捏捏)地迈着小步子走：**++装腔作势，假装高雅地说话**++吞吞吐吐地说，遮遮掩掩地说：**{n.}++切碎的食物**++= mincemeat**++[美国英语](百)果馅**++[美国俚语、青少年用语]落伍的人，背时的人，无聊的人**', '++Use this knife to chop, slice and mince; the side of the blade can be used for crushing garlic and some spices.**++厨师刀可以用于剁碎、切片或切碎物体，刀片侧面可以用于压碎大蒜和其他东西。**++I go the step further and mince, dice, chop, slice, mix and prepare so I don’t have to deal with it when I cook the next day.**++我会多做一点，把菜切碎、切丁、剁开、切成薄片、搭配在一起并准备好，这样我就不必在第二天要做饭时再处理它们了。**++The history of the mince pie may have contributed to its unusual reputation.**++这种肉馅饼的历史可能让其有着不同寻常的声誉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1738', 'mingle', '[mɪŋɡl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mingle', '{vt.}++使混合，使掺和，使相混：**++使结合，使联合：**++[罕用语]合成，配制**{vi.}++混合起来，相混合：**++相交往；相往来：**', '++He used to train in a local park and mingle with other runners.**++他过去常在地方公园里锻炼，并与其他跑步的人相交往。**++In both types of surgery beauty and mental healing subtly mingle, he claims, and both benefit health.**++所有的手术类型中，美和心灵治疗微妙地混合，他声称，都有益于健康。**++The current winter season gives influenza viruses an opportunity to inter-mingle and possibly exchange their genetic material in unpredictable ways.**++此一冬季使流感病毒有机会混合，并有可能以难以预测的方式交换其遗传物质。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1739', 'minimize', '[mɪnɪmaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=minimize', '{vt.}++使减少(或缩小)到最低限度，使减至最少，使缩到最小：**++把…说成极不重要；极度轻视；不认真对待；对…作最低估计：**{vi.}++达到最低值[英国英语亦作 minimise]**', '++It might do us good to consider what we can do to minimize it.**++考虑一下我们怎么做才能让它最小化，这是很有好处的。**++This article discusses how to minimize privileges, so you can apply the same ideas to your programs.**++本文讨论了如何最小化特权，您可以将同样的 思想应用到您的程序中。**++But at least some part of a secure program has to have code involving security, so you can@t just minimize privileges and ignore everything else.**++不过，至少一个安全的程序的 一些 部分必须有涉及安全的代码，所以您不能只是最小化特权而忽视所有 其他。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1740', 'mint', '[mɪnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mint', '{n.}++铸币厂**++[M-]铸币局**++巨额；大量**++[比喻]制造所，创造所；来源**++[废语]硬币，一块钱币**{adj.}++铸币厂的**++崭新的；无瑕的；完美的；无污损的**++[美国俚语]绝妙的，了不起的**{vt.}++铸造(硬币)；把(金属)铸成硬币**++创造；制造；发明；伪造；臆造：**{vi.}++铸币：**++铸币：**{n.}++【植物】**++薄荷属(Mentha)草本芳香植物**++唇形科(Labiatae)植物[参较 mint family]**{adj.}++【植物】**++唇形科的**++薄荷属的**{vt.}++加薄荷香于，使有薄荷香**{vt.}++[主苏格兰英语]**++打算，决意：**++试图，尝试：**++把打击对准**++暗示**{vi.}++假装，装样子：**++渴望；祈求；暗示(at):**++对准一击，瞄准射击**{n.}++尝试，企图**', '++The mint is coining pennies.**++造币厂正在铸造每枚价值一便士的硬币。**++They learned to mint from the Greeks.**++他们从希腊人那里学会铸币。**++Or, how about Mint?**++或者是薄荷味的？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1741', 'minute', '[mɪnɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=minute', '{n.}++分；六十分之一；尤指**++一分钟，六十秒**++一度的六十分之一**{vt.}++以分钟计算…的时间；精确地计算…的时间**++将…记入议事录：**++草拟：**++以备忘录方式通知(某人)**++摘录…的要点；把…记入备忘录：**++[口语]正确测定…的时间；准确测定速度：**{adj.}++易烹调的，快熟的**{adj.}++很小的，微小的，异常小的，极小的**++微不足道的，无足轻重的，不重要的**++仔细的；缜密的；详细的；精确的**', '++He dingoed on his comrades at the last minute.**++他在最后一分钟出卖了他的同志们。**++The lighthouse flashes  signal twice a minute.**++灯塔一分钟发两次闪光信号。**++With this instant film the picture develops in only one minute.**++用这种快速胶卷，照片仅用一分钟就会显影。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1742', 'minutia', '[maɪnjʊʃɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=minutia', '{n.}', '++Distractions –Deadlines keep you focused on the objective and away from minutia.**++分散注意力-期限能够使你将注意力集中在一个目标上面，避免一些无关紧要的细枝末节。**++Personal Minutia: I rarely talk about waking up, eating lunch, or starting my car, instead, I want to add value.**++鸡毛蒜皮的个人琐事：我很少在Twitter上说我起床了，吃饭了，或者开车呢，相反，我想提升价值。**++If you are interested in the minutia of the subject, please explore the References and Further Information at the end.**++如果你更关心细节实现则完全不必耐心看完本文，后面参考文档和更多深入阅读部分可能是你更需要的内容。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1743', 'mirage', '[mərɑʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mirage', '{n.}++海市蜃楼；幻景**++幻想；妄想**{vt.}++使蜃景似的显现**', '++But now I have core principles and I’ve overcome the status mirage of a car.**++但现在我有自己的中心原则，我已经克服了购买汽车那种虚无缥缈的幻想。**++Seen from a distance on this sunny day, however, the bright autumn light made it hazy and golden, like a mirage in a fairy tale.**++然而在这样一个晴朗的天气从一定距离看去，明亮的秋季光线使它看上去朦胧而辉煌，就像童话中的海市蜃楼。**++Without that understanding, we will not know whether Global Zero is a vision — or a mirage that may lead us to an even more perilous situation than exists today.**++缺乏这份了解，我们就无从得知全球零核是否可以称为远见，否则可能成为一种妄想，可能使我们陷入比今天更危险的处境。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1744', 'mire', '[maɪɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mire', '{n.}++沼泽地带；沼泽地**++泥潭，泥坑，淤泥，烂泥，污泥**{vt.}++使陷入泥坑；使成为沼泽：**++使陷入困境；使受困扰：**++使溅满泥污；[比喻]玷污：**{vi.}++陷入泥坑，陷入困境，掉进泥坑**', '++"Why have you got us into this mire?, " he asked.**++为什么要让我们陷入这样的泥沼中？**++The second is that there is no chance of the housing sector leading the present economy anywhere, except deeper into the mire.**++第二点是，美国楼市目前不可能带领经济走出衰退，而只会把经济推入更深的泥潭。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1745', 'mirth', '[mɝθ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mirth', '{n.}++欢笑；快活地笑**++高兴，欢乐**', '++It was for this very reason perhaps that he ever recommended mirth and hopefulness.**++也许正是出于这个原因，他才倍加向往欢乐和希望之事。**++Banter is a poetry form of mirth to make light of the happenstance of the day. Banter is associated with dragon lore dreamtime.**++欢唱是一种欢乐的诗歌形式，用以创造一天的光之偶发事件，欢唱是在龙之奥义的梦想时间发生的。**++Am I alone in hearing, amidst the prevailing ghostly disquiet, the spectral weirdness, a hint of derision, even disrespectful mirth, in the dialogue between the piano left hand and bassoon?**++我是否被包围在肆意可怕的忧虑、离奇的命运、嘲笑的暗示，甚至无礼的欢乐当中，独自倾听钢琴与巴松管的对答？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1746', 'misanthropic', '[,mɪsənθrɑpɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misanthropic', '{adj.}++厌恶人类(者)的；憎恨世人(者)的**++遁世的，不与他人交往的，孤独的[亦作misanthropical]**', '++But I also confess to being misanthropic -- I don@t much like most people.**++但我也承认自己是个厌世者 -在大多数人眼里我很另类。**++When you’re feeling down, chatting to friends is a great way to perk up. Even if you’re feeling misanthropic, why not give someone a ring and arrange to meet up for a coffee?**++当您心情低落的时候，与朋友畅谈一番也是鼓舞士气的一个不错的方法，甚至，当你有产生避世的想法时，为什么不给你的朋友打个电话，约会一下、喝个咖啡呢？**++The other hero, and the series@ salvation, is Lisbeth Salander, a young computer genius whose abusive childhood has left her a misanthropic nihilist.**++另外一位是这系列小说的救世主，Lisbeth Salander. 她是一位年轻的电脑天才，儿时受到虐待导致她成为一名厌世的虚无主义者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1747', 'misapprehension', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misapprehension', '{n.}', '++You’re operating under a huge misapprehension and we have to tell you about our first case together.**++你误解挺深的，咱得跟你讲讲咱俩的第一个案子先。**++On rereading your letter it seems to us that you are laboring under the misapprehension that we pay for unsolicited manuscripts.**++拜读来翰，先生似有所误会，以为我处对未约写之稿亦付稿酬。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1748', 'misbehaving', '[,mɪsbɪhev]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misbehaving', '{vt.}{vt.}++行为不端，使举止不检点：**++行为不端，使举止不检点：**{vi.}++(尤指在两性关系方面)行为不端，举止不检点：**++举止失礼，行为粗鲁：**++表现卑怯(或与军人身份不相称)：**++出现意外(或不良)情况**', '++Now they were saying, We’ll stop misbehaving if you give us the White House back.**++眼下，他们却说“只要你把白宫交出来，我们就会停止不规矩的行为”。**++It is a handy resource for determining how your application is using the resources available, and can also provide information pointing to misbehaving remote resources.**++这款工具使用非常方便，可以用于确定应用程序使用可用资源的方式，还可以提供针对行为不正常的远程资源的信息。**++What impressed me so much, though, was his sincere response every time I had to correct him for misbehaving. "Thank you for correcting me, Sister!"**++不过，令我印象深刻的是，每当我不得已指出他的过错的时候，他都非常诚恳地对我说：“谢谢你指出我的问题，修女！”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1749', 'mischievous', '[mɪstʃɪvəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mischievous', '{adj.}++(人、行为等)恶作剧的，爱捣乱的，好捣鬼的，戏谑的**++淘气的，顽皮的**++有害的；伤害的；造成危害的，恶意中伤的**', '++You@d speak to your little son;he@s too mischievous.**++你得管教一下你的小儿子了，他也太淘气啦。**++He was charismatic, with large dimpled cheeks framing a permanent, mischievous smile, and he’d been going abroad since 2004, so others in the group deferred to him.**++他风度翩翩，有一双酒窝的脸上总是带着淘气的微笑。 他早在2004年就开始出国，所以团里其他人对他言听计从。**++On the earth’s surface the artificial divisions that we have made between living and non-living, biotic and abiotic, organic and inorganic, are not only false but mischievous.**++在地球表面，我们对生物和非生物、生命体和非生命体、有机物和无机物所作的人为划分不光是错误而且是有害的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1750', 'misconstrue', '[,mɪskənstru]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misconstrue', '{vt.}++曲解，误解；误会：**++误解…的意思(或意图)：**', '++One reason people misconstrue teenage sexual behavior is that the system of dating and relationships has changed significantly.**++导致人们对青少年性行为曲解的原因之一是约会与性关系的模式有了明显的改变。**++Mostly because they failed to work through what Seth Godin identifies as "The Dip" and proceed to misconstrue community values and attitudes.**++主要是由于他们未能闯过塞思·戈丁认为的“斜坡”，并且进而误解社区的价值和姿态。**++Any discussion of weight and breast cancer is a politically sensitive topic, for some may misconstrue that as the medical establishment blaming victims for getting breast cancer.**++关于体重和乳腺癌之间关系的任何讨论都是一个政治敏感（政治不正确）的话题，因为一些人可能会误解为，是医疗机构在责备乳腺癌受害者患上乳腺癌（即乳腺癌是女性自己引起的）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1751', 'miscreant', '[mɪskrɪənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=miscreant', '{adj.}++堕落的；罪恶的，坏的，极不道德的，邪恶的，卑劣的**++[古语]信异教的，信邪教的；不信教的**{n.}++恶棍，歹徒，无赖**++[古语]不信教者，异教徒，异端者**', '++Mr Godoy Toscano@s desafuero may not mark an end to impunity in Mexican politics, but it does symbolically put every miscreant politician in the country on notice.**++罢免托斯卡诺先生可能并不能代表墨西哥政治豁免的结束，但是它却象征性地让该国的政治恶棍们开始留神了。**++These were certainly on the mind of one miscreant as he broke into a home in Lanzhou, a city in northwest China, in May of 2010.**++当2010年5月他破门而入一个兰州房间时，顶上这些想法，肯定出现在下面这个恶棍的脑海中过。**++The argument went that Col Gaddafi had watched the fate of fellow miscreant Saddam Hussein, hanged by Iraqis after a US-instigated legal process, and had learnt a sobering lesson.**++都说这种转变发生的原因在于卡扎菲上校目睹了流氓萨达姆，在美国主导的一场法律审判后，让伊拉克人绞死的下场，他如同大梦初醒。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1752', 'misdemeanor', '[,mɪsdɪminɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misdemeanor', '{n.}', '++They are charged criminally with reckless conduct, a misdemeanor.**++她们被指控犯了不良行为罪，一种轻罪。**++It was passed unanimously by the Las Vegas City Council as part of a bill making it a misdemeanor to go to the bathroom in public.**++这条法令由拉斯维加斯市理事会全体成员一致通过，它与在公共场所洗澡将被处以轻罪的法令同属一法案。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1753', 'miserly', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=miserly', '{adj.}++守财奴(似)的；吝啬鬼(似)的**++爱钱如命的，贪财的，小气的，吝啬的**', '++And in these earlier studies, people often used their money to punish the richest and most miserly players.**++在这些早期实验中，人们常常利用自己的金钱惩罚最富有、最吝啬的玩家。**++The Solution: While I agree that you shouldn’t be a miserly Scrooge and save every penny because it physically hurts you to spend it, going the other extreme is just as bad.**++策略：我同意说你不该是个吝啬的守财奴，存下每一分钱，一花钱你就觉得受到伤害，但是走向另一个极端也是不好的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1754', 'misfortune', '[mɪsfɔrtʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misfortune', '{n.}++不幸，晦气；厄运；逆境；灾祸**++不幸事故，灾难，横祸**', '++Some misfortune must have befallen him.**++某种灾难必降临在他头上了。**++It is said to be an omen of misfortune.**++那被认为是一种不幸的先兆。**++Don@t gloat,the same misfortune may happen to you one day.**++不要幸灾乐祸，说不定同样的不幸会落到你的头上。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1755', 'misgiving', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misgiving', '{vt.}++misgive的变形**{n.}++[常作复数]疑虑；担忧；害怕**{vt.}++使疑虑；使担忧；使害怕：**++使疑虑；使担忧；使害怕：**{vi.}++产生疑虑；担忧；害怕：**++[主苏格兰英语]**++出毛病，失败**++(火器)不发火**', '++Also, people really like hearing their name, and if you say it in a slightly misgiving way – like a mom scolding her child – they’ll always laugh.**++而且，人们很喜欢听自己的名字，如果你用一种带着些许担忧的方式说出它-就像母亲斥责她的孩子-她们经常是会笑的。**++However, as the moment for the girl@s setting out drew nigh, when the first excitement of the dressing had passed off, a slight misgiving found place in Joan Durbeyfield@s mind.**++不过，姑娘动身的时刻越来越近了，当初梳妆打扮的兴奋一消失，琼·德北菲尔德太太的心里就出现了一阵担忧。**++It@s a freedom that, of course, Parliament had pushed for, but now that they@ve got it there is some misgiving.**++当然，这是一种议会推崇的自由，但是现在他们得到的只是疑虑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1756', 'mishap', '[mɪshæp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mishap', '{n.}++不幸事故；灾难**++[罕用语、古语]不幸，晦气，灾祸**', '++This mishap reminded me of a traffic accident I once experienced.**++这次不幸事故使我联想起我过去经历的一次交通事故。**++When Church talks about mirror life’s quirky advantages, invulnerability to this kind of mishap is high on his list.**++在谈论镜像生命无可比拟的优势时，丘奇将这种不幸事故当作反面教材拎了出来。**++He had a black patch over his right eye socket, a prosthetic left arm and a deformed right hand, the result of injuries from an explosives mishap during an old operation against the Soviets in Kabul.**++他右眼罩着一只黑色眼罩，左臂安着义肢，右手畸形---这些都是过去他在喀布尔跟苏军打游击时，因一次意外爆炸事故而留下的纪念。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1757', 'misrepresent', '[,mɪs,rɛprɪzɛnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=misrepresent', '{vt.}++歪曲报道，不如实地叙述(或说明)，诈称，误传：**++不适当地代表；不称职地代表**{vi.}++作虚假陈述；说假话：**++作虚假陈述；说假话：**', '++The mass media consistently misrepresent science and medicine.**++大众媒体在不断地歪曲科学和医学。**++In fact, I think the tests themselves misrepresent their real function.**++事实上，我认为考试本身歪曲了其真正的功能。**++These agents also often misrepresent or conceal their U. S. affiliations.**++这些中介还常常歪曲或是隐瞒自己在美国的关系。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1758', 'mite', '[maɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mite', '{n.}{n.}++小量，一点点，微小的东西**++[口语]小孩；小东西**++力所能及的微小贡献；极少的一笔钱**++(不再通用的)小硬币，小铜币 **++【历史】法兰德小值铜币**{adv.}++[口语][a mite]一点儿，稍许，几分**', '++The researchers propose that the lice, which outcompete or feed on mites, first be introduced into a flock of mite-infested hens so that the lice can get rid of all the mites.**++研究人员介绍说首先把比鸡螨强势或以鸡螨为食的虱子放进到一群已经感染了鸡螨的母鸡中，这样虱子会把所有鸡螨都消灭掉。**++One key driving force behind bee destruction in Europe and North America has been a type of mite, the varroa destructor pest, which attacks bees and that beekeepers struggle to control, Neumann said.**++欧洲、北美的蜜蜂面临的毁灭背后一个关键性的驱动力是一种叫做瓦螨的小虫，它们向蜜蜂发起进攻，而养蜂人则极力想要控制它们，诺依曼说。**++This winter@s losscontinues the trend of large losses in recent years, as pesticides usedto protect bee populations against the varroa mite are becoming lessand less effective.**++今冬的蜜蜂损失是近几年大量蜜蜂损失趋势的继续，这是由于用以保护蜂群防止螨虫的杀虫剂越来越不起作用了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1759', 'mitigate', '[mɪtɪɡet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mitigate', '{vt.}++使缓和，使温和，使镇静：**++减轻(痛苦、惩罚)：**{vi.}++缓和下来；减轻**', '++Identify and mitigate risks.**++识别和减轻风险。**++It can improve future disaster management and help mitigate the effects of these catastrophes.**++它可以改善未来的灾害管理，并帮助减轻这些大灾害的影响。**++In order to bring risks under control, you must have a sense of what risks you face and when you expect to mitigate them.**++为了使风险在掌控之下，您必须有高度的意识来判断您所面临的风险以及您期望什么时候可以减轻它。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1760', 'mobile', '[məʊbl;mobil]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mobile', '{adj.}++可动的，活动的，移动式的**++流动的**++流性的；低黏度的**++多变的；易变的**++机动的，能快速移动的**++多方面的，适应性强的**++[口语]有交通工具可供使用的**++【社会学】个人(或社会阶层)流动的，(在职业、地区中或之间)流动的**++活动雕塑的**{n.}++活动雕塑**++活动部件；活动物体**++[美国英语] =automobile**++=mobile library**++活动餐室**++巡警**++[澳大利亚、新西兰英语]活动栅栏**++手机，移动电话，手提电话**++[口语] mobile home**++【艺术】(抽象派)动态作品**', '++And in this mobile world, you have to carry it along with you.**++在这个流动的世界里，你还得一直带着它们。**++The doctors take turns at participating in the mobile medical team.**++医生们轮流参加巡回医疗队。**++Because while waiting for him, I was texting another friend on my mobile!**++因为在等他的时候，我就用我的手机给另一个朋友发短信！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1761', 'mockery', '[mɑkəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mockery', '{n.}++嘲笑，讥笑；嘲弄**++嘲笑对象，笑柄；嘲弄的场合**++嘲笑行为，嘲笑言论**++拙劣可笑的模仿，冒牌**++徒劳无益；白费心机**++恶劣的假冒，歪曲**', '++The question is a mockery of a travesty of a sham.**++这个问题是对模仿骗子行为的一种嘲弄。**++Words of humiliation, mockery, judgment, criticism, etc. may take their root deeply in you.**++羞辱，嘲弄，指责，批评等等字眼，可能在你的心里生了根。**++Was there just a hint of mockery in his voice or was it herfancy?**++他的话里暗含着嘲弄的意味么，抑或只是她的想象而已？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1762', 'moderate', '[mɑdərɪt; (for v.,) mɑdərˌeɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=moderate', '{adj.}++适度的，有节制的，不过分的，不大不小的**++温和的，稳健的，不激进的**++中等的；普通的，一般的；平庸的**++(价格)适中的，公道的，公平的**++(颜色)中等深浅的，中等色度的**++有限的，不大的**{n.}++温和主义者，持温和观点的人，稳健的人**++[亦作 M-](政党中的)稳健派，温和派**{vt.}++使和缓，减轻，减弱；节制：**++主持(会议)**++【核物理学】使(中子)减速；慢化(反应堆)；给反应堆添加缓和剂**{vi.}++变弱；变温和，变得和缓：**++主持会议，主持节目(或讨论)：**++[古语]作调解人**', '++Moderate exercise subserves digestion.**++适度锻炼有助于消化。**++She should moderate her language when children are present.**++在孩子面前，她说话应该节制。**++Baldwin said the girl has thrived in school and has no learning problems, although she has moderate asthma.**++鲍尔温说这个女孩在学校表现出色没有学习问题，虽然她有适度的哮喘。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1763', 'modicum', '[mɑdɪkəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=modicum', '{n.}', '++At a minimum, she hopes for at least a modicum of attraction.**++至少，她希望能遇到一个对她有一点点吸引力的人。**++In the life of Afghanistan’s villages even a modicum of democracy is worth something.**++在阿富汗的乡村生活中，哪怕一星半点的民主，也是难能可贵的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1764', 'mollify', '[mɑlɪfaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mollify', '{vt.}++抚慰，使平静，安抚，使平息怒气：**++缓和，减轻：**++使变软，使变温柔**{vi.}++[古语]变温和；息怒：**++[古语]变温和；息怒：**', '++The company has made tweaks to its search engine to mollify rivals and head off a possible legal clash with antitrust authorities.**++公司开始调整其搜索引擎来平息竞争者的不满，并尽可能避免和反垄断组织的法律冲突。**++So far, Beijing has used its clout as a major foreign investor and the world’s biggest importer of raw materials to mollify or intimidate its potential critics.**++到目前为止，北京利用其作为主要外国投资者和世界最大的原材料进口国的影响力来安抚或恐吓其潜在的批评方。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1765', 'mollycoddle', '[mɑlɪkɑdl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mollycoddle', '{n.}++娇生惯养的人，娇弱的人，脂粉气的男人，懦夫**++假正经的人，伪善的人，假虔诚的人**{vt.}++娇养；纵容；宠坏**', '++You shouldn@t mollycoddle your kids.**++你不应该溺爱你的孩子。**++It@s just a small operation, I cant mollycoddle myself, life must go on!**++只是一个小手术，我不能溺爱自己，生活还要继续。**++To put it simply, women mollycoddle children and animals to a ridiculous extent.**++简单地说，女人会宠爱孩子和动物到一个荒唐的地步。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1766', 'molt', '[molt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=molt', '{vt.,vi.,n.}', '++Small birds molt once or twice a year, and they replace their 9 or 10 primary flight feathers a few at a time over the course of a few weeks.**++小型鸟类一年进行一到两次换羽，在换羽期间，它们一次会替换掉9到10根左右的飞羽，而这个过程将持续几周时间。**++So what if you want to fly? University of Washington scientists say it depends on how fast you can replace your flight feathers when you molt.**++那么，你如果想飞，你的体重该保持在什么水平上呢？ 华盛顿大学的科学家们说，这取决于你在换羽期间更换飞羽的速度。**++He said emperor penguins can spend months at a time in the ocean, coming ashore only to molt or rest, but did not know what might have caused this particular one to become disoriented.**++他说帝王企鹅能在海水里生活几个月，只有在换毛和休息的时候才上岸，但是现在人们还不知道这只企鹅是怎么迷路的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1767', 'momentous', '[momɛntəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=momentous', '{adj.}++重大的；重要的**++[罕用语](人物)重要的；有影响的**', '++This is a momentous development, for two reasons.**++这是一个重大的发展，原因有二。**++And this is a really momentous occasion because we’re celebrating the 50th Anniversary of the Peace Corps and you are part of that 50th Anniversary group.**++这是一个十分重要的时刻，因为我们正在庆祝和平队成立50周年，而你们是在和平队庆祝50周年之际加入的成员。**++So this is a momentous day in the history of Libya.**++所以，这是利比亚历史上的重大一天。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1768', 'momentum', '[momɛntəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=momentum', '{n.}++【物理学】动量，冲量**++动力；动向；冲力；冲向**++力量；势头**++【哲学】要素，契机**', '++No one wants this momentum to stall.**++没有人希望这一势头停滞不前。**++The spinning top was losing momentum.**++旋转的陀螺正在失去动量。**++Once the excitement, the motivation and the initial momentum subside (and they will), what will keep you doing what you need to do, to create the change you want to see in your world?**++人一旦兴奋，动机和最初的动力就会减弱（他们会这样），什么会让你保持做你要做的，去创造出这种在你的世界里你想看到的改变？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1769', 'monarch', '[mɑnɚk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=monarch', '{n.}++君主；国王；皇帝；女皇；最高统治者**++王，大王**++帝王般的人(或物)**++【昆虫】大斑蝶(Danaus plexippus)[亦作 monarch butterfly]**{vi.}++[常与 it连用]称王**', '++The monarch was ousted by a military coup.**++那君主被军事政变者废黜了。**++Country is governed by an elected legislature and prime minister, with a monarch as a symbolic head of state.**++国家由选举产生的立法机关和首相治理，由一个君主作为国家的象征性领袖。**++People bring nothing when given birth, and go away also with nothing when dead. Whether you are a prisoner or a monarch, a rich or a beggar, there is no exception.**++人赤条条来到世间，也赤条条离开世间，生时没有带来任何东西，死时也带不走任何东西，无论你是君主还是囚徒，是富豪还是乞丐，概莫能外。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1770', 'mongrel', '[mʌŋɡrəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mongrel', '{n.}++杂种狗；杂种动物；杂交植物**++乱七八糟的大杂烩**++[贬义]杂种(指人)**{adj.}++杂种的；杂交的**++混杂的，混血的**', '++The only reason of the attack - he’s a mongrel.**++那次攻击的唯一原因是——他是个混血儿。**++Stop the application services in the cloud environment in preparation for the data migration by killing your mongrel processes.**++通过终止您的 mongrel 进程来停止云环境中的应用程序服务，为数据迁移做好准备。**++And fear not, you’ll still have access to the raw mongrel request if you want to do fancy stuff like streaming or deferred rendering outside the mutex.**++不用害怕，当你想做一些奇妙的东西比如流化或在互斥以外延期渲染的时候，你依然可以访问原始的mongrel请求。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1771', 'monochromatic', '[,mɑnəkrəmætɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=monochromatic', '{adj.}++单色的，单频的；产生单色光的**++【植物学】单色的**++【病理学】全色盲症的**', '++However, if you want to wear a print, choose a print that@s low in contrast and monochromatic in color.**++然而，假如你实在想穿喷绘衣服，那就选择一件单色、低对比度的。**++Monochromatic vision is very rare among land species, because color vision is a tool for survival in terrestrial habitats.**++单色视觉能力在陆地生物中非常罕见，因为分辨颜色的能力是陆地生物生存的一项工具。**++This hologram, if later illuminated with the same wavelength of laser light, reproduced a 3D (but monochromatic) image of the object.**++这幅全息图，如果用（与拍摄时）相同波长的激光照明，会再现出物体的3D图象（不过是单色的）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1772', 'monologue', '[mɑnəlɔɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=monologue', '{n.}++滔滔不绝的讲话；长篇大论**++【戏剧】独白；独白词；独角戏；独角戏剧本**++单独朗诵**++独白体诗[亦作monolog]**', '++As they describe Capote@s effervescent monologue, you can almost see him sitting on the beige cloth couch, legs crossed, waving his arms around as if starring in his own movie.**++在他们描述卡波特兴奋独白的时候，你似乎可以看到在那米色布沙发上，卡波特跷起腿，挥动着他的手臂，就像在导演自己的电影一样。**++Within the first 5 minutes there is  monologue via the  holographic billboards, and within 20 minutes Eve and Wall-E have dialogue.**++电影前5分钟只有全息公告栏上播出的独白，前20分钟只有伊娃和瓦力的对白。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1773', 'monopolize', '[mənɑpəlaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=monopolize', '{vt.}++垄断；获得对…的专利；实行…的专卖：**++独占；全部占有，完全控制：**', '++She tried to monopolize his time.**++她想独占他的时间。**++This little-known candidate carries in it the seeds of a method for some company to monopolize Internet authentication services.**++这种少有人知的候选方案将方法种子引入其中，使一些公司垄断网际网路认证服务。**++A "pacted" transition requires that a critical mass of the ruling elite come to prefer "democracy with guarantees" over the costs of continuing to forcibly monopolize power.**++这样协议的转变需要有起关键作用的一群统治阶级里的精英，他们要敢于付出继续强制垄断权利的代价而选择“有保证的民主”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1774', 'monotonous', '[mənɑtənəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=monotonous', '{adj.}++(声音)单调的，无抑扬顿挫的**++单一得令人厌倦的；毫无变化的**', '++She has a very monotonous voice; she should have it modulated.**++她的声音很单调，应该加以调整。**++This could be anything ranging from a boring lecture or sermon, to a monotonous conversation with people.**++这可以是任何东西，一次枯燥的演讲或布道，或者是人们单调的一段对话。**++You take everything one step at a time, you concentrate on the present moment of cooking, you do some monotonous activities (like chopping or stirring) that calm your body and mind.**++你一步一步做这一切，专心于目前烹饪的这一刻，做一些单调的活动（像切和搅拌）可以使你的身心平和稳定。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1775', 'montage', '[,mɑntɑʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=montage', '{adj.}++【电影、电视】蒙太奇的，剪辑的**{vt.}++用蒙太奇手法处理，剪辑，组合**', '++You can use this for displaying a montage of images that are each partly hidden, but that the user can reveal fully by hovering over it.**++你可以使用这个技术为照片的隐藏部分使用蒙太奇效果，但当用户将鼠标悬停在上面是就会显示全部。**++Ilkka Halso@s "Museum of Nature," a digital photo montage, turns the environment we know now into a sterile comodity -- as forests and wildlife move indoors to become museum exhibits.**++伊尔卡·哈尔索的数字蒙太奇照片“自然博物馆”，把我们熟悉的环境变成了不毛之地——森林和野生物移进室内成了博物馆展品。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1776', 'moratorium', '[,mɔrətɔrɪəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=moratorium', '{n.}++【法律】(债务人的)延缓偿付(权)；延缓履行债务(权)**++延缓偿还期**++暂停，中止；禁止，暂停活动**', '++Moreover, it is not clear which fissile material is supposed to be subject to the moratorium.**++此外，在“暂停产”概念下，到底指的是停产哪些裂变材料，也不清楚。**++I told him that, after I left Arkansas the previous summer, I did some work for the Vietnam Moratorium in Washington and in England.**++我告诉他，在先前的一个夏天，离开阿肯色州后，我在华盛顿和英国为“暂停越战”运动作了一些工作。**++Hansen said he was taking part in the Coventry demonstration tomorrow because he wants a worldwide moratorium on new coal power stations.**++汉森说他将参加明天在考文垂的示威活动，因为他希望在全世界范围内暂停新的燃煤电站。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1777', 'morbid', '[mɔrbɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=morbid', '{adj.}++疾病的，生病的，由疾病所致的，由疾病引起的，致病的**++(精神等)病态的，不健全的，病态处理的；[口语]忧郁的**++病变部位的，患处的；病理的**++可怕的，恐怖的，令人厌恶的，令人毛骨悚然的**', '++He was disenthralled from morbid fantasies.**++他被从病态的幻想中解脱出来。**++This way of being sometimes becomes morbid and definitely requires treatment.**++这种生存方式有时会变得病态，绝对需要治疗。**++If anyone lift the cloth from the face of that unpleasant thing it will be in gratification of a mere morbid curiosity.**++如果谁将这个不悦的玩样儿脸上的布掀开，那它会因为一种病态的好奇而心感满足。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1778', 'mordant', '[mɔrdnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mordant', '{adj.}++尖锐的；讽刺的；刻薄的，尖刻的**++【冶金学】腐蚀的**++烧灼般的**++【化学】媒染的，染色的**{n.}++【化学】媒染剂；染色剂**++【冶金学】腐蚀剂，酸洗剂**++【印刷】(凹印的)腐蚀液**++(金属箔)黏着剂**++【音乐】= mordent**{vt.}++【化学】媒染**', '++A US Marine Corps junior officer told me recently of the latest mordant joke in Afghanistan: “The Americans have the watches, but we have the time.”**++美国海军陆战队的一位下级军官最近告诉我一个阿富汗最新的尖酸笑话：“美国人有手表，但我们有时间。”**++Gaidar, a diminutive and tubby figure with a mordant and self-deprecating sense of humour, emerged as the dominant thinker and natural leader of his group.**++盖达尔身形矮胖，带有一种讽刺和自嘲式的幽默感，是他所在派别居于主导地位的思想家和天生的领袖。**++A mordant helps fix the dye to the material.**++酸洗剂帮助染料粘附在素材上。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1779', 'moribund', '[mɔrɪbʌnd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=moribund', '{adj.}++垂死的，奄奄一息的**++濒临消亡的，渐将被废弃的**++停滞不前的，不进展的**{n.}++垂死的人**', '++Imperialism is monopolistic, parasitic and moribund capitalism.**++帝国主义是垄断的、寄生的、垂死的资本主义。**++You do not have to be a member of the moribund Socialist Labour Party of America to see the political appeal of that.**++想要见识到这一观点的政治吸引力，你根本没有必要成为垂死的美国社会主义劳工党的一员。**++The opposition appeared to be uniting against the military leadership, breathing new life into a youth-led protest movement that had grown moribund during the summer.**++反对派似乎是在集结力量以反对军方的领导，并为今年夏天已经垂死的青年领导的抗议活动注入新的力量。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1780', 'morose', '[məros]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=morose', '{adj.}++忧郁的；孤僻的；脾气不好的**++显得忧郁的，流露出忧郁的**++古板严厉的；愠怒的**', '++They spoke of sending their children to work just to get them out of the house and of husbands who grew morose and violent.**++她们谈到之所以要把孩子送出去做工，就是为了让他们别老憋在家里，同时离自己阴郁又暴力的丈夫远点儿。**++Her once-sunny disposition turned morose, and her vigorous workouts declined to a measly 20 minutes of walking a day.**++她曾经阳光的性格因此变得阴暗，高强度的体育锻炼也只剩下每天20分钟的散步。**++“Yeah.” He sounded morose. “It@s been a bad year.” He seemed to wilt.**++“是的。”听起来有些忧郁，“这将是糟糕的一年。”他好像在畏缩。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1781', 'mosaic', '[mozeɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mosaic', '{n.}++镶嵌；镶嵌工艺**++马赛克，镶嵌细工；镶嵌画；镶嵌图案**++马赛克般的东西，拼成的东西，镶嵌画般的东西**++【植物病理学】花叶病[亦作mosaic disease]**++航摄相片镶嵌(地)图[亦作aerial mosaic, photomosaic]**++【电视】嵌镶面**++【生物学】嵌合体**{adj.}++马赛克的；镶嵌的，拼花的；拼成的**++马赛克式的**++【生物学】镶嵌性的；(卵裂)镶嵌的**{vt.}++使马赛克般地结合**++把…构成马赛克；镶嵌构成**++以马赛克装饰**{adj.}{n.}', '++Now I think of it there@re 500 to show dealing with children and young people. Their ideas fit together like a giant mosaic.**++我想起来有500个例子，都是小孩以及年轻人打交道的,他们的想法结合起来像一个巨大的马赛克。**++With your current framework and example mosaic movie, you can build interesting examples for your promotional videos or home movies.**++用您当前的框架和示例马赛克影片，您可以构建有趣的示例，用于推广视频或家庭影片。**++If you put in three hundred lira—twenty-five cents—for a brief moment spotlights are turned on near the ceiling, bathing the stones of the mosaic in fresh white light.**++如果你往里面放进三百里拉——二十五分钱——靠近天棚的聚光灯便短暂地闪亮起来，将马赛克制作的瓷砖沐浴在鲜明的灯光里。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1782', 'mosque', '[mɑsk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mosque', '{n.}', '++Would you go to church or the synagogue or the mosque?**++你会去教堂，犹太教会，或者清真寺吗？**++Tell the congregation of a church or mosque that existence is too vulgar an attribute to fasten onto their God, and they will brand you an atheist.**++告诉教堂或清真寺的会众们，存在，是强加在他们的上帝身上的一种过于庸俗的属性，他们将会指责你为无神论者。**++A red sandstone mosque stands on one side.**++一座红色砂岩清真寺耸立在一旁。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1783', 'moth-eaten', '[mɔθ,itən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=moth-eaten', '{adj.}++虫蛀的；蛀坏的**++虫蛀了似的；千疮百孔的；破烂的；(头发)蓬乱的；(房屋)废圮的；不整洁的**++陈旧的，老掉牙的，过时的**', '++The sweater is moth-eaten.**++毛衣让蛀虫咬坏了。**++Today when cleaning out the attic, I found my ice skates, slightly moth-eaten but the blades in perfect condition.**++今天在整理阁楼的时候，我发现了我的溜冰鞋，虽然说有一点旧了，但是冰刃的状况却仍然很好。**++Amid the multitudes in sleek evening garb, the molting birds had the look of disheveled bounders or tipplers in moth-eaten raccoon coats.**++在大量有光泽的晚礼服中，脱毛企鹅看起来就像穿着被虫蛀的浣熊皮外套的邋遢莽汉或者醉鬼。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1784', 'motile', '[motɪl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=motile', '{adj.}++【生物学】能动的**++【心理学】运动表象型的**{n.}++【心理学】运动表象型(指以运动表象为特征的人)**', '++Men who smoked had normal numbers of sperm, but they were less motile than those of nonsmokers.**++抽烟的男性精子数量基本正常，但精子活性不如不抽烟的男性。**++On the other hand, men who drank alcohol and those who were overweight had less numerous and less motile sperm.**++另一方面，经常饮酒和过度肥胖的男性精子数量相对稀少且活性不足。**++Men whose diets were higher in fruit and grains like oats and wheat had more numerous and more motile sperm.**++日常饮食中喜欢水果、谷物如燕麦、小麦等的男性精子充足且活性强。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1785', 'motivate', '[motəvet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=motivate', '{vt.}++使有动机，使产生动机；构成行为的动机，激起(行动)，促动：**++激发…的积极性(或学习兴趣)：**++使(学习等)生动有趣：**++[妓院行话]强迫自己做(即女孩强迫自己接客)**', '++They motivate others.**++他们激励他人。**++They motivate you and teach you safe workouts you can do at home.**++在教练的激励和指导下，你可以在家安全的完成训练。**++To do that, you need to motivate them, listen to them, connect with them, and support them when they need it.**++要做到这一点，你需要激励他们，倾听他们的心声，保持联络，并且在他们有需要时支持他们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1786', 'motley', '[mɑtli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=motley', '{adj.}++杂色的，五颜六色的**++穿杂色衣服的**++混杂的，成分杂乱的**{n.}++杂色呢；杂色布**++杂色衣，(小丑穿的)杂色服装；小丑装束**++丑角，小丑**++混杂的人群；混杂物；成分杂乱的东西**{vt.}++使成杂色；使杂乱**', '++Motley: I am assuming the customer, or the voice of the customer like the product owner, is there?**++马特里：我猜想客户，或则客户的代表如产品负责人会出现在那里，对吧？**++The picture that emerged is a motley conglomeration of people with widely varying goals -- and some with no clear-cut goals at all other than to denounce greed.**++由此看到是形形色色的人们聚合在一块，彼此的目标相去甚远，有些人除了谴责贪婪以外完全没有清晰的目标。**++When I parse my body’s motley parade of scars, I see them as personal runes and conversation starters.**++当我剖析自己身体上各种疤痕的时候，我把它们看做是私人的符号，是开始谈话的话题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1787', 'mottle', '[mɑtl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mottle', '{vt.}++使呈杂色；使呈斑驳状**{vi.}++呈杂色；呈斑驳状：**++呈杂色；呈斑驳状：**{n.}++杂色；斑点，斑纹；斑驳**++= mosaic disease**', '++Looking up at the sky, that touch of blue, turned into a long face, stranded in the clear rain mottle.**++抬头看天，那一抹微蓝，幻化成思恋的容颜，搁浅在清雨斑驳的彼岸。**++Of the 304 patients, the 21 peoplewith pepper mild mottle virus in their feces were more likely than theothers to present those symptoms.**++在这304名病人中，21位（7%）在其粪便中发现存在胡椒轻微斑点病毒的病人，与其他病人相比，更可能出现上述症状。**++Clean and pure glass with bright red color, with some distant and vague awareness, stimulate some far scenery in the mind and ready to continue, unprovoked, fragmented mottle.**++洁净纯粹的琉璃染上了鲜红的色彩，惊醒着某种遥远而模糊的意识，刺激着一些飘远的风景在脑海里又蠢蠢欲动，继续无端，支离斑驳。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1788', 'motto', '[mɑto]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=motto', '{n.}++(刻在印章、硬币、旗帜上的)题词；警句；铭词**++座右铭；格言；箴言**++“甜格言”(指其包装纸上印有格言的一颗糖果)[亦作 motto kiss]**++【音乐】警句 [亦作 motto theme]**', '++Serving the people is my motto.**++为人民服务是我的格言。**++His motto: come fly with me.**++他的座右铭是：跟我一起飞！**++My motto is "no laments".**++我的格言是‘没有悲痛’。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1789', 'mournful', '[mɔrnfl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mournful', '{adj.}++悲哀的，悲伤的，伤心的**++令人悲痛的；令人惋惜的**++忧郁的；消沉的，沮丧的**', '++Hill: "I never in my life experienced anything so profoundly mournful."**++小山： “我在我的生活中未曾体验深刻地悲哀的任何东西那么”。**++But thinking of the poor woman@s mournful facial expressions, I believed that as I offered her my timely help I would not feel conscience-stricken over this matter in my later years of life.**++但是，想到这名贫困妇女脸上凄凉的表情，我坚信这种雪中送炭的帮助，在我以后的生命里也不会后悔什么，也不会在对待这个问题上有什么良心上的谴责。**++"We really appreciate all you@ve done for us, but now you need to let us die," intoned a 170-ton blue whale through a series of deep and mournful vocalizations.**++“十分感谢你们为我们所做的一切，但现在希望你们让我们死吧，”一头170吨重的蓝鲸用深沉而又悲伤的声音说道。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1790', 'movement', '[muvmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=movement', '{n.}++行动；移动；行进；运动**++动作；姿势；举止**++[常用复数]行动；活动**++【军事】(部队、舰艇、飞机等的)调动，调遣**++迁居，迁移；(人口的)流动**++(物价等的)变动**++(事件的)急剧进展**++(文艺作品中情节的)发展，变化**++(绘画、雕塑中人物的)动作，动势，动态感**++(事物的)动向；趋势；发展**++(政治、社会、思想等方面的)运动，开展运动的团体**++(钟表等的)机件；机械装置**++屎；拉屎，大便**++【音乐】乐章；节奏；拍子**++【韵律学】韵律结构；韵律特点**', '++They disintegrated the labour movement.**++他们瓦解了工人运动。**++They collect funds to finance the movement.**++他们为这一运动筹募基金。**++He led them in launching a patriotic movement.**++他领导他们开展了一场爱国运动。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1791', 'muddy', '[mʌdi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=muddy', '{adj.}++多泥的，泥泞的；沾满烂泥的**++浑浊的，不清澈的**++(光、色)暗淡的**++(头脑)糊涂的，混乱的**++模糊的，朦胧的**++(表达)含混不清的；暧昧的**{vt.}++使粘上污泥；把…弄脏：**++使浑浊：**++使混乱；使模糊不清：**++诽谤，中伤，破坏…的名誉：**{vi.}++变得泥泞；变得浑浊**', '++The muddy road careened the truck.**++卡车行驶在泥泞的路上歪斜不稳。**++The old car was labouring along the muddy road.**++那辆旧车在泥泞的路上吃力地朝前开着。**++We were swagging on the muddy road when we saw a small village.**++我们在泥泞的道路上一直颠簸着，终于看见了一座小村庄。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1792', 'muffle', '[mʌfl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=muffle', '{vt.}++包裹，裹住；(用围巾)围住(常与 up 连用)：**++蒙住…的头(使看不见东西)；捂住…的嘴(使不出声)：**++使(声音)低沉；消灭(声音)：**++抑制，压抑(感情等)：**{vi.}++(用衣服等)裹住自己**{n.}++包裹物；覆盖物；围巾；头巾；面纱**++低沉的声音**++隔焰窑；隔焰室**{n.}', '++In London, winter and spring are barely distinguishable, because the clouds muffle both seasons.**++伦敦的冬天和春天几乎无法区分，因为这两个季节都是阴云笼罩。**++In reality, some people are vocal and may moan and groan, other folks may muffle any sounds with a pillow, and yet others may not make a single peep.**++真实之中，有些人作声，可能叫唤或呻吟，其他某些人则可能用枕头把骚声闷住，还有一些人则可能不单是叽咕叽咕喃呢作声。**++Boeing and Lockheed Martin have submitted futuristic concepts that look similar to the Concorde, but aim to muffle the annoying and potentially damaging sonic boom problem.**++波音和洛克希德马丁都提出了类似于协和式飞机的未来概念，更致力于抑制扰人的和潜在的破坏性音爆问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1793', 'mulish', '[mjulɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mulish', '{adj.}', '++A giant mulish horse team saved city of sweet day heart to set out from Qinghai.**++一支庞大的骡马队伍从青海省香日德城出发了。**++It would be mulish not to admit to a feeling of relief that Russia has accepted these changes without too much ill grace.**++俄罗斯已经不太勉强地接受这些改变，如果我们不承认一丝安慰，那就太顽固了。**++You mulish guy, what the hell are you seeking?**++你这顽固的人，你究竟追求什么东西？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1794', 'mumble', '[mʌmbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mumble', '{vi.}++含糊地说；喃喃地说：**++(如因缺齿而)困难地咀嚼；(以无齿的牙床)瘪着嘴嚼**{vt.}++含糊地说；喃喃地说：**++如无齿地咀嚼；瘪着嘴咀嚼：**++吻**{n.}++咕哝；含糊不清的话**{interj.}++(表示犹豫等)嗯；是啊**++(表示反对等)算了吧；不会吧**{n.}++(低沉连续的)沙沙声；潺潺声；低语；细语**++怨言；牢骚；嘀咕**++【病理学】(心脏等的)杂音 [亦作heart murmur]**++【语言学】弱元音；低语元音 [亦作murmur vowel]**{vi.}++发低沉连续的声音；沙沙地响：**++小声说，私语：**++低声抱怨；嘀嘀咕咕(与against或at连用)：**{vt.}++低声说：**++低声抱怨(与that连用)**', '++May: (Mumble) I want to be like her.**++阿美：（喃喃自语）我想像她一样。**++What! "Frickin@ Tax Man", you mumble to yourself.**++什么！ 你咕哝了一声“该死的税赋！”**++When I ask how much they had to rely on their emergency store during the famine of 1984, they bow their heads and mumble a response before falling completely silent, their eyes welling with tears.**++当我问及1984年饥荒时他们有多依赖他们的紧急仓库时，他们都垂下了脑袋，嗫嚅着，到了最后，完全没了声音，泪水夺眶而出。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1795', 'mundane', '[mʌnden]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=mundane', '{adj.}++现世的，世俗的，尘世间的；日常的**++世界的；宇宙的**', '++I find it humorous sometimes that even the most mundane occurrences can have an impact on our awareness.**++我发现生活有时挺诙谐的，即使是最平凡的事情也能影响我们的感知。**++For some, it may be just another mundane aspect of work life — putting on a game face to hide your inner unhappiness.**++对有些人来说，那也许只是职场生涯中，世俗的另一面——披戴上一副游戏面孔，藏起内心的不快。**');
