insert into GREWordBook values ('1803', 'myriad', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=myriad', '{n.}++无数**++无数的人(或物)**++[诗歌用语]万，一万**{adj.}++无数的；大量的**++各种各样的；形形色色的**++[诗歌用语]一万的**', '++A myriad of lights twinkled like stars in the distance.**++远处有无数盏灯像星星一样闪烁。**++Every day, wittingly or unwittingly, we make a myriad of connections with people around the world.**++每天，无论是有意还是无意，我们都会和周围的人有无数的联系。**++We developed an example integration scenario that could be enabled by any of the myriad of coexistence mechanisms.**++我们开发了一个示例集成场景，该场景可以由无数的共存机制所支持。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1804', 'nadir', '[nedɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=nadir', '{n.}++【天文学】天底**++最底点；情绪的最低点；最不幸的时刻**', '++Why not move to one of the most economically depressed cities in America during the nadir of a recession?**++那么干嘛不趁着美国经济衰退的最低点到一个最不景气的城市去呢？**++This little-travelled region may represent the global nadir for herbivores.**++这个小旅游地区里，食草动物在全球处于最低点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1805', 'naive', '[naɪiv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=naive', '{adj.}++幼稚的，天真的；朴实的，朴素的**++轻信的，缺乏经验的**++(画家)未经正规训练的；(绘画)非专业画家画的**++情报不充实的；缺乏判断力的**++未有过经验的；未服用过麻醉毒品的**{n.}++天真的人**++幼稚轻信的人 [亦作 naïve]**', '++This is a naive argument, because other nations will not see the US action in this light.**++这是个天真的论点，因为别的国家不会从这样的角度看待美国的行为。**++The days of the naive approach -- where we believe that if a system is object-oriented (or pick your technology), then it@s good -- are over.**++天真方法的日子——我们相信如果一个系统是面向对象的（或选择你的技术），那么它是好的——结束了。**++Consider me naive, but I believe the majority of companies actually like their customers and users and want to provide them with a valuable service.**++恕我天真，但是我相信大多数的公司确实喜爱他们的顾客和使用者，并且希望给他们顾客提供良好的服务。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1806', 'narcissism', '[nɑrsɪsɪzəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=narcissism', '{n.}++自我陶醉；孤芳自赏**++【心理学、精神分析】自恋欲，自恋癖[亦作narcism]**', '++But can they measure our narcissism?**++但是，他们能否测出我们的自恋？**++This is one of the many points at which narcissism becomes indistinguishable from masochism.**++这正是自恋狂和受虐狂正变得无法区分的众多原因之一。**++And many of the people diagnosed with narcissism seemed to have other personality disorders, too.**++许多被确诊患有自恋的人似乎还有其他方面的人格障碍。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1807', 'nascent', '[næsnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=nascent', '{adj.}++初生的，刚诞生的；年轻的，正在发展的**++【化学】(分子)初生态的，新生态的；(元素)新生的**', '++No and No! There is a nascent profession perhaps, but it is not there yet.**++两个问题的答案都是：不！ 可能在初期有这样的职业，但现在已经不再有了。**++It is believed that the moon formed when the nascent Earth and Theia collided, sending materials out into space.**++人们认为当初期的地球和忒伊亚相碰撞时，把物质洒向太空时，月球形成了。**++Perhaps she knew the real "magic" was the nascent power within her.**++可能她知道真正的“魔法”是她里面所蕴含的稚嫩的力量。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1808', 'natty', '[næti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=natty', '{adj.}++(衣着、外貌)整洁的，漂亮的**++利落的，灵巧的，灵活敏捷的**', '++In the village, Mr. Breivik caught the attention of locals for his natty attire, formal ways and lack of farming knowledge.**++在那个村庄，布雷维克因其整洁时髦的着装、彬彬有礼的举止并且缺乏务农知识而引起注意。**++I had plenty of testing under my belt with the alpha and beta releases and decided Natty should be labeled (to that point) a huge success.**++我通过对alpha和beta测试版的充分测试确定Natty可以称为（在某种程度上）一次巨大的成功。**++The code named Natty Narwhal, Ubuntu 11.04 is slated for release in April 2011.**++这次开发的代码是Natty Narwhal，Ubuntu11.04预计于2011年4月发布。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1809', 'nauseate', '[nɔzɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=nauseate', '{vt.}++对…感到恶心，使恶心：**++使感到厌恶；憎恶：**{vi.}++感到恶心，想呕吐(与 at 连用)：**++感到厌恶：**', '++He was afraid that it might nauseate him and he would vomit and lose his strength.**++他害怕那些东西会让他反胃呕吐，因为吐了之后就没有体力了。**++I still want to know what cow colostrum is doing in the dairy section (you know, the stuff that mothers--of all species--produce before their milk comes in--sorry, don@t want to nauseate you!)?**++我还想知道母牛的初乳在乳品部是怎样做的（你知道，就是那种所有的母亲--包括所有物种在内--在她们真正出乳之前分泌出来的东西--抱歉，不想让你感到恶心！）**++Finally, all those delicacies from mountain and sea began to nauseate me.**++那些山珍海味吃到最后，简直令人翻胃。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1810', 'nautical', '[nɔtɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=nautical', '{adj.}++海上的，航海的**++船舶的**++海军的**++海员的，水手的**', '++Attempting an unprecedented shift in human behaviour without the input of psychologists is like setting sail for a faraway land without the aid of nautical maps.**++想要一个史无前例的人类行为的转变却没有心理学家的参与，无异于扬帆欲去远方却没有航海地图的帮助。**++Techniques for conserving and stabilising metals recovered from nautical environments have been developed and tested but have never been applied to a complete aircraft.**++为保护稳定的航海环境，金属回收技术已经开发和测试，但从来没有被应用到一个完整的飞机上。**++It is, however, interesting to note a recurring nautical theme throughout the shortlist.**++然而，很有趣的是，航海主题一而再的贯穿于整个提名名单。**');
