insert into GREWordBook values ('1853', 'obdurate', '[ɑbdərət]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=obdurate', '{adj.}++执拗的，倔强的**++顽固的，顽固不化的**++冷酷无情的**++坚硬的**++牢固的**', '++At the G-20 summit in November, the U.S. drive to deal with "global economic imbalances" was essentially thwarted by China@s obdurate refusal to change its currency policy.**++在十一月份的G-20峰会上，美国着手解决全球失衡问题，但是由于中国顽固地拒绝改变其汇率政策，此议题受阻。**++Massive, irritating and even scary expressions of it were vital in shaking an obdurate Government, contemptuous of public opinion, from its determination to pursue war ad infinitum in Vietnam.**++大规模的，刺激性的，甚至害怕表示其目的是为了推翻一个极其顽固的政府，蔑视公众舆论，美国发动了史无前例而漫漫无期的越南战争。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1854', 'obedient', '[obidiənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=obedient', '{adj.}', '++What if they hadn@t been faithful and obedient to do their part?**++如果他们没有信靠和服从去做他的那部分工作那会怎么样？**++What if the person who brought you the Gospel hadn@t been obedient?**++如果那位带给你福音的人是不服从的那会怎么样？**++True, you haven’t moved the rock, but your calling was to be obedient, to push and exercise your faith and trust in my wisdom, and this you’ve done.**++的确，你没能移动那块石头，但你的任务是服从，是去推石头，锻炼你对我的智慧的信心和信赖，而这点你已经做到了。**');
