insert into GREWordBook values ('1892', 'orthodox', '[ɔrθədɑks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=orthodox', '{adj.}++正统的，正宗的**++信奉早期基督教义的**++(信念、态度、行为标准等) 传统的；符合社会习俗的**++(手段、方法)惯常的；标准的**++(意见、学说)正确的(尤指理论或宗教方面)**++[主美国英语]【基督教】三位一体说的**++[O-] 【犹太教】(教会、教民)正统派的**++[O-]东正教(会)的**++[O-]【宗教】教友派的**{n.}++正统的人；正统的事物**++正统派**++[亦作O-]＝Orthodox Jew**++[O-]东正教信徒**', '++But don@t expect this to be endorsed by orthodox medicine   there@s no profit in it.**++但是不要指望这个道理被正统医学支持——因为它没有任何利润可寻。**++If reason should lead you to orthodox conclusions, well and good; you are still a Rationalist.**++如果理性可以引领你到达传统的结论，那很好，你仍然是一个理性主义者。**++For example, even orthodox Darwinists have always recognised that there are plenty of cases where fitness doesn@t increase over time.**++譬如，即使是正统的进化论者也常常认识到，在很多情况下适应性并不随时间而增加。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1893', 'oscillate', '[ɑsɪlet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=oscillate', '{vi.}++摆动；振动：**++动摇；犹豫：**++上下波动：**++【数学】(函数、序列等)振动**++【物理学】振荡**++【无线电】发电磁波，发杂音**{vt.}++使摆动；使振动**++使动摇**++使波动**++【物理学】使振荡**', '++That makes sense, smaller animals will need to oscillate faster to generate forces large enough to dry themselves.**++这言之有理，动物越小，身体就需要摆动越快，才能产生足够大的力量甩干自己。**++The essential point is that the blue waves oscillate much faster than the red waves, and the yellow and green waves are somewhere in between.**++关键是发现蓝色光波的振荡频率远高于红色光波，黄色和绿色光波的振荡频率介于两者之间。**++The associated cross-peak amplitude also appears to oscillate.**++相关的交叉峰的幅度也在振荡。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1894', 'ossify', '[ɑsɪfaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ossify', '{vt.}++使骨化，使成骨：**++使僵化，使固执，使极端保守**{vi.}++骨化，成骨**++僵化，变得保守：**', '++This disease will make her tendons ossify and her body paralyzed into a statue.**++她肩膀两侧长出额外骨头，病情会令她的肌腱继续骨化，身体逐步瘫痪，最终变成一尊雕像。**++But the risk that the recent homeward flow of bank assets will ossify into a less efficient, less flexible cross-border banking system is real and growing.**++然而，最近银行资产向母国回流的趋势正在朝低效、僵化的跨国银行系统越滑越深，这一风险是实实在在的，而且在不断加大。**++In addition, she said, “what this has tended to do is ossify terms and conditions when we need more flexibility about how we do things”.**++除此之外，她说，“久而久之，这只会硬化员工待遇条款，而我们在做事方式上要更为灵活。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1895', 'ostensible', '[ɑstɛnsəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ostensible', '{adj.}++外表的，表面的，貌似真实的；自称的，假装的，诡称的**++明显的，显而易见的**', '++The ostensible reason was to set a good example, but I knew White was hoping I wouldn’t do it.**++表面的理由是树立一个好榜样，但我知道怀特其实希望我不敢接受测试。**++The ostensible goal is to prevent welfare fraud, but the psychological impact is to turn poverty itself into a kind of crime.**++表面上这是为了防止福利欺诈，但是这让人们从心理上觉得贫穷本身成了一种罪行。**++This year the artist and her family will move back downtown. The ostensible reason is to enroll Jiazhen in a top school, but Zhang also wants to give her daughter a deeper sense of identity.**++今年，张的家庭准备搬回市中心去，表面的原因是想让女儿嘉真进一所好学校，但内心里，张更希望女儿能对自己的身份获得更强烈的感受。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1896', 'ostentatious', '[,ɑstɛnteʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ostentatious', '{adj.}++夸示的，卖弄的，炫耀的**++招摇的，豪华的，铺张的**++惹人注目的，显眼的**', '++Officials from all of Spain’s big parties are being investigated for corruption, but the PP cases reveal a taste for ostentatious luxury.**++西班牙所有大党的官员都在接受贪污调查，但是人民党案件揭露了对铺张奢侈品的偏好。**++In an era of growing green consciousness and global warming fears, environmentalists are increasingly critical of this ostentatious display, calling it as unnecessary and wasteful.**++但随着环保意识加强、全球变暖恐惧升温，越来越多的环保人士谴责这种卖弄性的做法，称其是不必要的浪费。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1897', 'ostracize', '[ɑstrəsaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ostracize', '{vt.}++放逐，流放：**++(古希腊)以贝壳(或陶片)放逐制放逐**++排斥；把…排除在外：**', '++" I@ve even seen managers allow their teams to ostracize or marginalize the top performer so that other people won@t "feel bad.**++有一些领导甚至允许他们的团队排斥或者边缘化这种高手以使其他人不会感觉很糟糕。**++You can see that our word ostracize comes from this “sending away for a decade” which in turn takes its name from the shell-like fragments.**++至此，您可以看出，单词ostracize来源于这个“放逐十年的法令”。 而该法令本身的名字又取自于那些像是贝壳的碎片。**++In the podictionary episode on the word ostracize I talked about how the shells of oysters found their way into that word meaning “to shun” someone.**++在对于《每日一词》ostracize 的介绍中，我曾经提到过，牡蛎的外壳是如何发展出“回避”某人（“toshun” someone）的意思。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1898', 'oust', '[aʊst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=oust', '{vt.}++驱逐，撵走；免去…的职务，罢黜，废黜(常与from， of连用)：**++取代：**++【法律】剥夺，夺取**', '++I @m sorry to say nothing could oust a computer.**++很遗憾，什么也不可能取代计算机。**++Some wonder whether the objective should be to oust Colonel Gadhafi.**++有些人怀疑,其目的是否是驱逐卡扎菲。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1899', 'outgoing', '[aʊtgoɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outgoing', '{vt.}++outgo的变形**{adj.}++往外去的，离去的**++即将离职的**++友好的；乐于助人的；爽直的**++(外卖食品等)准备外运的，外卖的**{n.}++外出；离去；外出物**++[复数][主英国英语]支出，开销**{n.}++外出，出去，离去；流出**++外出物，流出物；流出量**++支出，开支；消耗**++出口**{vt.}++超过；超越**++胜过，优于**++[古语]走得比…快**', '++Each outgoing Sequence Flow has a condition that will be evaluated to determine whether or not it occurs.**++每个流出序列流都有一个条件，将通过评估此条件来确定对应序列流是否发生。**++To speak a letter (outgoing), you need to apply to yet another room.**++要说出一个字母（输出），你还需要向另一个地方申请。**++To be an entrepreneur you need to be an independent,  outgoing risk taker as you establish your own business or company.**++要成为一个企业家，在开创你自己的公司的时候你必须成为独立的、外向的风险承担者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1900', 'outgrowth', '[aʊtɡroθ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outgrowth', '{n.}++发展；结果，产物**++附随结果；派生物；副产品**++长出；滋生**++长出物，生成物；分枝，侧枝；赘生物**', '++In China itself, the Somalia mission is seen as a natural outgrowth of its return to great-power status.**++就中国自身而言，这次索马里行动是该国重返大国地位的自然结果。**++The summit meeting is an outgrowth of the Global Tiger Initiative, introduced two years ago by the World Bank president, Robert B. Zoellick.**++此届峰会是全球老虎倡议的结果，两年前由世界银行行长罗伯特 B. 佐利克首倡。**++Is this really an inequity or injustice in the voting procedure or merely an outgrowth of the fans selecting the starters, which has taken place since 1975?**++这真的是投票过程的不公正和不公平还仅仅是自1975年以来球迷选择先发自然发展的结果呢？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1901', 'outlandish', '[aʊtlændɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outlandish', '{adj.}++(服装、习俗等)稀奇古怪的，奇特的**++外国模样的；异国风情的；外国腔的**++偏僻的，边远的**++[古语]外国的**', '++Surtees was tragically unlucky; Massa was more fortunate but he believes the coincidence of two outlandish accidents is a warning.**++瑟蒂斯的不幸非常可悲；马萨更幸运，但他相信这两起古怪的事故的巧合是一个警告。**++Once upon a time it was the province of philosophy to propose ambitious and outlandish theories in advance of any concrete evidence for them.**++这曾经是物理学的领域，可以提出炫耀和古怪理论而不用管是否真的有任何具体的证据。**++Although he continued to refine the theory, he was reluctant to publish, either because he feared ridicule for such an outlandish suggestion, or because he worried about a reaction from the church.**++尽管他不停地完善理论，他却极力不去发表，一是因为他害怕这个古怪的提议会被人嘲笑，二是因为他担心教堂会对此有所作为。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1902', 'outmaneuver', '[,aʊtmənʊvɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outmaneuver', '{vt.}', '++In sports where limber, prepubescent bodies can outmaneuver more mature athletes, kids can be designated as older than they are.**++在那些以灵活性取胜的项目中，年轻的选手比成熟的更轻巧，孩子们就会被虚报年龄。**++In a business where information is the most valuable commodity, traders with the smartest, fastest computers can outfox and outmaneuver rivals.**++在信息是最有价值的商品的行业中，交易者用最聪明最快的计算机武装，可以智慧和机动灵活战胜竞争者。**++Infectious bacteria have evolved through the loopholes in almost every drug we@ve created, thanks to our own misuse and overuse. But we may yet outmaneuver them.**++致病菌能钻过我们制造出来药物的一个个漏洞并不断进化，这多亏了我们自己对药物的错用滥用。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1903', 'outmoded', '[,aʊtmodɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outmoded', '{vt.}++outmode的变形**{adj.}++过时了的，不再流行的**++废弃了的，不再被接受的；不再使用的**{vt.}++使过时，使废弃；使变得老式**{vi.}++变得过时；变得无用**', '++Too often our suspicions are based on outmoded ideas or impressions.**++往往我们的猜疑是基于过时的想法或印象。**++No doubt it is the fate of all cutting-edge technology to eventually turn blunt, dull and outmoded, but that is a concern for another day, another era.**++毫无疑问，所有尖端科技最终都无法逃脱愚钝、沉闷和过时的命运，但那是在另一个时代另一个日子里才需要面对烦恼。**++The latest attempt to remove the outmoded rule was in 2003, when a Right-wing MP from President Nicolas Sarkozy@s UMP party wrote to the minister in charge of gender equality.**++最后一次尝试废除这一过时的法令是在2003年，那时萨科奇总统领导人民运动联盟政党中的一名右翼议员致信给负责性别平等的部长。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1904', 'outset', '[aʊtsɛt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outset', '{n.}++开端，开始**++=outsert**', '++At the outset of his career he was full of optimism but not now.**++一开始他对事业充满了信心，但现在不再是这样了。**++In any case, as I said at the outset, a full discussion of memory allocation is beyond the scope of one column.**++不管怎样，就像我开始所说的那样，有关内存分配的详细内容已经超出本专栏讨论的范围。**++David advised him over and over not to produce it without an overall market research . the boss@s ability was very outstanding at the outset of his career .**++戴维一再建议，如果没有全面的市场调查就不要生产它。老板的能力在它事业开端的时候很突出，但现在他没有一盎司的常识。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1905', 'outwit', '[,aʊtwɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outwit', '{vt.}++以智慧、机敏胜过；使上当：**++[古语]在智慧(或知识)上超过**', '++The real question, Luca,is how shall I outwit you this time?**++卢卡，关键的问题是，这回我怎样才能在智慧上胜过你。**++Just try Outwit for such purposes and you will see what I mean.**++那就试试 Outwit 来做这些事情吧，你就明白我的意思了。**++You can for example extract the data from a table and export it as excel spreadsheet or as SQL statements in just a few clicks from within Outwit Hub.**++例如你可以从一个表格中提取数据，导出为excel表格或者SQL语句，在 Outwit Hub中只需要几次点击就可以了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1906', 'overbearing', '[,ovɚbɛrɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overbearing', '{vt.}++overbear的变形**{adj.}++压倒一切的，极其重要的**++专横的，盛气凌人的；傲慢的**{vt.}++(靠力量或重量)压住，压倒；制服，镇住：**++压服；胜过：**++否定，否决：**++专横地对待，威压：**++在重要性(或重量、价值等上)超出**++【航海学】比…处于有利地位**{vi.}++结果实过多；繁殖过度**', '++Same goes for the teacher, overbearing neighbor, or your mother-in-law.**++对老师、傲慢的邻居或者你的婆母也一样。**++Do not be to overbearing at the outset, otherwise you will not have any followers.**++不要一开始就搞专制，否则你不会有任何追随者。**++Just be extra careful not to pull the stereotypical overbearing-parent thing and make them rebel against ever doing the same thing in their own careers.**++只是要额外注意，不要做专横的父母做作的事情也不要迫使他们以至于他们永远不愿做与父母相同的职业。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1907', 'overlap', '[ovəlæp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overlap', '{vt.}++与…互搭，与…重叠，部分叠盖住：**++盖过，伸展越过(某物)：**++与…部分一致(或巧合)；与…有共性；与…部分同时发生：**{vi.}++交搭；重叠：**++部分一致(或巧合)；部分相同：**{n.}++交搭；重叠；部分相同(或同时发生)**++交搭处；重叠处**++重叠部分**++交搭量(或程度)；重叠量(或程度)**++(帆船比赛中的)并排**++【地质学】超覆**', '++But they do not always overlap.**++但它们并不总是重叠的。**++While you cannot plan for every disaster, many of the recovery procedures overlap.**++虽然您无法为每个灾难做计划，但是许多恢复过程是重叠的。**++I will also lump administration and monitoring tools together in this discussion because, at least for the administrators, the two functions have a lot of overlap.**++我还将在本讨论中同时讨论管理和监视工具，因为至少对管理员而言，这两项功能有很多重复的地方。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1908', 'override', '[,ovɚraɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=override', '{vt.}++践踏，蹂躏；奔过：**++把(马等)骑得过累**++压垮**++不顾，无视；拒绝:**++撤销，使无效；推翻：**++权力高于；对…有最后发言权：**++压倒；优先于：**++超驰(自动控制)，用手控方式来消除(自动控制)的作用**++伸展在…的上面：**++(浮冰、骨折端等)重叠**++(猎狐中)骑马过紧跟在(猎犬)后面**++[美国英语]付给(总代理商、销售部经理等)佣金(或酬金)；按销售额向(分代理商、推销员等)收取佣金(或酬金)**{n.}++[美国英语]代理佣金，酬金 **++付给商品经营者的老板过多的补偿**', '++What you should not do is prevent or override it unnecessarily.**++您不应该做的是不必要地阻止或重写它。**++If you believe the decision of the group is wrong, you must have the courage to override it and withstand the group\\\\\\\@s reaction.**++倘若你认为集体的决策是错误的，你就必须拿出勇气来推翻它，而且还要能抵挡得住大家的反应。**++You can override all the parameters on the command line, if you want to experiment with the net to discover how it does with various options -- each run might take a while, though.**++如果打算试验网络从而发现对于这些不同的选项它是如何做的，您可以覆盖命令行中的所有参数，但每一次运行还是会耗费一些时间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1909', 'overshadow', '[ovɚʃædo]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overshadow', '{vt.}++使失色，使显得不重要，使相形见绌；夺去…的光辉；使丢面子：**++遮暗，遮蔽，使阴暗不明：**++给…蒙上阴影，使阴郁，使郁闷：**++[古语]庇护；保护**', '++And she says while the world is right to be concerned about a possible flu pandemic, it should not let these worries overshadow or interrupt other vital health programs.**++她还说，尽管世界目前担心可能发生的流感疫症，这些担忧不应该遮挡或者干扰我们实施其它生命攸关的健康计划。**++At the same time, though, we do not want our story to overshadow the critical plight of these desperate defectors.**++同时，我们不希望我们的故事掩盖了那些绝望的出逃者的严重的生存困境。**++The researchers think that this occurred about a century ago, just when commercial agriculture was replacing subsistence farming and maize started to overshadow indigenous crops in Africa.**++这组科学家认为这发生在大约一个世纪之前，就在商业农业取代生存农业、而玉米开始取代非洲本土作物的时候。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1910', 'overt', '[ovɝt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overt', '{adj.}++明显的，显而易见的**++公开的，公然的**++【法律】**++明显的**++蓄意的**', '++They explain the antagonism created by overt criticism of China’s growth model, however justified.**++它们把这种明显由中国的增长模式导致的对立解释为合理的。**++Currently the only drugs available for the syndrome treat the overt symptoms, such as anxiety and aggression.**++目前只有一种药物可以治疗综合症的明显征兆，如焦虑感和侵略性。**++Perhaps humans have simply entered a new stage of evolution in which we have abandoned chocolates, door holding, flowers or any overt gesture of interest for a new and unnatural order of things.**++也许人类仅仅是进化到了一个新阶段，我们为了一个崭新的不自然的事物顺序，抛弃了送巧克力，扶着门框，送花或者任何明显展露爱意的姿势。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1911', 'overture', '[ovətʃʊr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overture', '{n.}++[常用复数](为开始谈判、建立友好关系等而做出的)主动表示，提议；姿态**++【音乐】序曲，前奏曲**++序诗；序言；事件的开端**++【基督教】(长老会)向最高教会法庭(或地方教会法庭)提出问题(或建议)；提出的问题(或建议)**{vt.}++作为一种主动姿态提出：**++向…提出建议，向…做主动表示：**++为…奏前奏曲(或序曲)**', '++In a second overture to the Russians today, the Nato military alliance proposed a joint missile defence system to counter the danger of rocket attacks from countries like Iran.**++今天，在向俄罗斯提出的又一个提议中，北约军事联盟提出建立一个联合导弹防御系统，抵御来自某些国家（例如伊朗）火箭袭击的威胁。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1912', 'overwhelm', '[ovɚhwɛlm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overwhelm', '{vt.}++(尤指以军事力量)压倒，压服；击溃；粉碎：**++制服；使不知所措；使受不了：**++使承受(过量之物)，授予；对待：**++覆盖；淹没：**++[古语]使倾覆；推翻**', '++We try not to think about it because it would overwhelm us to an extent that we would just vegetate.**++我们尽量不去想它，因为在某种我们能够想像到的程度上他会压倒我们。**++It should not overwhelm you with raw HTTP traffic dumps, and it goes far beyond simply providing a framework to tamper with the application by hand.**++用户不会再被大量原始的HTTP流量数据淹没，而且这个工具远不仅仅是一个人工干预应用程序的框架。**++For example, in a situation in which several bystanders need to band together to overwhelm a perpetrator, they will be more likely to act collectively than to act alone.**++例如, 就有这样一种情况， 在只有几个旁观者需要联合起来才能压倒一个罪犯的情况下, 他们就可能会更多地采取集体行动。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1913', 'overwrought', '[,ovɚrɔt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=overwrought', '{adj.}++过度兴奋的；神经质的，过度紧张的；过分激动的**++(文体等)过分雕琢的；过分讲究的；不自然的**++(因兴奋或激动而)疲惫的；过分劳累的**++【计算机】重写的**', '++When you@re emotionally overwrought, it can be hard to remember exactly what was said.**++在情绪过度劳累时，要准确地记住说过的话往往会很难。**++Many overwrought workers eat junk food, drink excessive alcohol or zone out in front of the TV, he says.**++他说，很多员工劳累过度了就吃垃圾食物、大量喝酒，或是在电视前昏昏沉沉。**++Her temper  overwrought me, ] And I edged to shun her view For I felt assured she thought me One who should drown him too.**++她的性情，诗人接着说，让我紧张烦恼，我慢慢的避开她的观点，离开月光,因为我断言，她认为我,应该也会溺死他。**');
