insert into GREWordBook values ('1933', 'pandemic', '[pændɛmɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=pandemic', '{adj.}++(疾病)流行性的；传染于(全国、全洲、全世界)的**++普遍的，一般的；全世界的**{n.}++洲际流行病；大流行病**', '++What about the pandemic risk?**++大流行的风险如何？**++Is there anyone who should not have the inactivated pandemic vaccine?**++是否有任何人不应当接种大流行性流感灭活疫苗？**++By good fortune we have had time -- and still have time -- to prepare for the next global pandemic, because the conditions for it have appeared before the outbreak itself.**++幸运的是，我们已有时间而且还有时间为下一次全球疾病大流行做准备，因为在疾病暴发之前已可看到它所需的条件。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1934', 'pandemonium', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=pandemonium', '{n.}++大吵大闹；一片混乱**++混乱的地方(或场面)；闹哄哄的场所**++[P-]魔窟；地狱；阎王殿；(英国诗人弥尔顿的长诗《失乐园》中的)地狱都城**', '++Then the first blast went off, and the grim quiet erupted into pandemonium.**++接着第一声爆炸响起，肃静瞬间变成一片混乱。**++Many choose to simply pay the fine, but their flights can cause pandemonium when the planes crop up on airport radar screens.**++很多人干脆选择直接付罚款，但当他们的飞机突然出现在机场的雷达屏幕上时，这种飞行就会引起一阵混乱。**++"The workers at Chernobyl had no idea that they were walking into an intense radiation field," said Professor Wakeford. "It was pandemonium; there was no monitoring, no idea of the risks.**++“诺尔切贝利的工作不知道他们正步入剧烈的核辐射区域，”韦克福德教授说：“一片混乱，那里没有监测，也对危险毫无认识。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1935', 'panegyric', '[ˌpænədʒɪrɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=panegyric', '{n.}++颂词(指演讲或文章)**++推崇备至；过分夸奖**', '++On abuse, on reproach, on calumny, it is easy to smile; but painful indeed, is the panegyric of those we contemn .**++面对谩骂、非难，中伤而一笑置之，那是容易的；可是，老实说，要藐视这些颂词却是需要费点儿力气的。**++Nevertheless people have a panegyric on the eight phenomena. Therefore the spirit of this world is distorted. it has become a stubborn disease and beyond cure.**++然而，世人对这八种现象却是推崇备至。因此，这个世界的精神层面，早已扭曲纷乱，成为陈年痼疾，根深柢固，而不可救药矣！**++My little friend grildring; you have made a most admirable panegyric upon your country .**++我的小朋友，格立锥格，你对你的祖国献上了一篇极其堂皇的颂词。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1936', 'panoramic', '[,pænəræmɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=panoramic', '{adj.}{n.}++回转画；活动画；全景画**++连续转换的画景**++全景；全貌；全图**++概述；概论**++范围**++一系列形象；一连串景象(或事件)**', '++From a distance, up close with you in it, panoramic from the top, maybe–maybe–some architectural shots.**++从远处，站在下面仰视，站在顶端的全景，或许或许是一些一些建筑摄影。**++Panoramic roof systems are a new type of multi-panel moon roof that offer openings above both the front and rear seats.**++全景天窗系统是一种新型的多层面板月光车顶，它可为前排和后排座椅都提供敞开式天窗。**++Others argue that collecting samples from the seafloor is easier when a person is in the pilot’s seat, and that no machine can replicate the panoramic scope of human vision.**++其他科学家认为，如果由人坐在驾驶位上就更容易从海底收集标本，而且没有机器可以复制像人类视野这样的全景视角范围。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1937', 'parable', '[pærəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=parable', '{n.}++(道德说教性的)寓言；比喻**++[古语]格言**++[美国俚语]大话；吹牛**', '++Hear ye therefore the parable of the sower.**++所以你们当听这撒种的比喻。**++His story became a parable for the fickleness of art and life.**++他的故事成为一个说明艺术与生活变化无常的寓言。**++And he said unto them, Know ye not this parable? and how then will ye know all parables?**++又对他们说，你们不明白这比喻吗。 这样怎能明白一切的比喻呢。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1938', 'paradigm', '[pærədaɪm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paradigm', '{n.}++范例；示例；模范；规范**++【语法学】(名词、动词等的)词形变化表**++【哲学】理论框架(模式)，范式**++聚合体**', '++However, the space shuttle paradigm is only one model of space access.**++如论如何，航天飞机的范例只是太空旅行的一种模式。**++However, we have seen one other fundamental paradigm shift during the past two decades.**++然而，我们在过去二十年中已经见到另一个基本范例变动。**++The paradigm of SQL is that the user (or application) just tells the database system what to do and the system itself figures out the best way how to do it.**++SQL 的范例是，用户（或应用程序）只需告诉数据库系统要 做什么，系统自己就会得出 如何做 这件事的最佳方法。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1939', 'paradise', '[pærədaɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paradise', '{n.}++[P-]伊甸乐园；天国[见E-den]**++天堂；乐园**++地上乐园，乐土，极乐世界；至福**++(养有鸟兽的)公园，苑**++【建筑学】(教堂里)前院；门廊二楼**++灵薄狱**++【俚语】(戏院的)顶层座位**', '++The bird of Paradise is fabled to have no feet.**++相传天堂的鸟没有脚。**++On that rainy night, I dreamed to fly to my paradise.**++在那个落雨之夜，我梦想着飞向我的天堂。**++If you were a child, it was paradise.**++如果你是个孩子，这里就是天堂了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1940', 'paradox', '[pærədɑks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paradox', '{n.}++(与通常的见解相对立的)反论，悖论**++似矛盾(而可能)正确的论点**++自相矛盾的话(或事)**++充满矛盾的人(或事)**++【物理学】佯谬**', '++Or is this a paradox of faith?**++又或者,这是个信仰的悖论吗？**++The method is based on “the friendship paradox” — the counterintuitive idea that your friends have more friends than you do.**++这种办法是建立在“友谊悖论”的基础上——这种违反直觉的观点就是说：“你的朋友比你有更多的朋友”。**++What if Europe should accept the paradox that its democratic openness is based on exclusion – that there is "no freedom for the enemies of freedom", as Robespierre put it long ago?**++如果欧洲应该接受这样的悖论，即它的民主开放是以排他主义为基础的——“自由的敌人没有自由”，就像罗伯斯庇尔很早以前说过的那样？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1941', 'paragon', '[pærəɡɑn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paragon', '{n.}++(尽善尽美的)模范(或典型)**++优秀的人(物)；逸品，殊品，完人**++(100克拉以上的)无瑕钻石；(不寻常的)圆形大珍珠**++【印刷】 20点(磅)西文活字**{adj.}++极好的；完美的**{vt.}++[古语]把…作比较(with)**++[古语]彼比同上；使较量(with)**++[废语]胜过**++[废语]把…视作典范**++[废语]作为…典范**', '++Today we appear to have excelled the hypochondriac cultures of the past by elevating the morbidly self-involved to the level of paragon.**++如今，我们似乎已经超越了过去那种把病态地自我关注说成是完美典范的强迫症文化。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1942', 'paramount', '[pærəmaʊnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paramount', '{adj.}++最高的；至上的；首要的；卓越的**++拥有最高权力的**++胜过…的；(比…)优秀的**{n.}++最高掌权者；元首**++最高；至上；主要**', '++This duty is paramount to all the others.**++该义务是至高无上的。**++Better understanding of the population structure of the fishery is therefore of paramount importance.**++对渔业种群结构的更深入了解因此具有至高无上的重要性。**++It is paramount that we understand. So that we can change the things we need to, and live with what we have to live with.**++我们能够充分了解此事是非常重要的，这样我们就能改变我们需要改变的，忍受我们必须忍受的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1943', 'paranoid', '[pærənɔɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paranoid', '{adj.}++像患妄想狂的**++类似偏执狂的，处于高度偏执状态的；极度害怕的；超出常情地害怕的 [亦作 paranoidal]**{n.}++患妄想狂的人[亦作paranoiac,paranoeac]**', '++Not all applications need to be so paranoid.**++并不需要对所有的程序都如此偏执。**++Paranoia on the train » Extremes of paranoid thinking are associated with mental illness, but we all have paranoid thoughts from time to time.**++» 列车上的妄想狂 »偏执的想法走向极端就是精神疾病了，但我们所有人时不时地都会有偏执型的想法。**++What is the most depressing day of the week? How do you deal with queue-jumpers? Do you have paranoid thoughts while travelling on an underground train?**++一周当中，最让你郁闷的是哪一天？看到有人插队，你会怎么办？在乘坐地铁的过程当中，你是否有过偏执的想法？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1944', 'paraphrase', '[pærəfreɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paraphrase', '{n.}++改说；改写**++释义；意译**++[苏格兰英语]圣经韵律译文**{vt., vi.}++(将…)释义；意译：**++(将…)释义；意译：**', '++Paraphrase this article in 250 words or less.**++用不到 250 个字意译出这篇文章。**++So we had to paraphrase arguments to complete these tests.**++所以我们要改写论点来完成这些测试。**++This time away offered me some perspectives on how – to paraphrase Henry David Thoreau – I had become a tool of my tools.**++这一次逃离让我进一步洞察到我是怎样——套用亨利·大卫·梭罗的话——成了我的工具的工具。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1945', 'parch', '[pɑrtʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=parch', '{vt.}++烘(干)；烤干(谷类、豌豆等)**++使焦；使干透；使燥热：**++使极渴：**++使冷得干瘪；使冷得枯萎**{vi.}++焦干；干透；烤干：**++口渴；心烧**', '++These grains may parch , but they will not pop.**++这些谷物能够烤，但他们不能爆。**++No heat, no drought can parch that river, “the streams whereof make glad the city of God.”**++没有热，没有旱能叫那道“使神的城欢喜”(诗四十六篇四节)的河干涸。**++If the air-dry wood on tuyere Office, the wood will quickly lose moisture, surface parch and split, the emergence of small cracks.**++如果把木材放在风口处风干，木材内的水分会迅速失去，表面干裂，出现细小裂纹。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1946', 'parenthesis', '[pərɛnθəsɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=parenthesis', '{n.}++【语法学】插句；插入语；插入成分**++圆括号**++间歇**++(复题的)插话；插曲；穿插**', '++Groups are subpatterns in the regular expression that are surrounded by parenthesis.**++组是正则表达式中的子模式，它们包含在圆括号中。**++In line 11, after the value of variable _X is a closed parenthesis ()) highlighted in red.**++在第 11 行上，变量值 _X 后面是一个用红色突出显示的后圆括号（)）。**++The marker@s first number represents time in abstract units; the second optional number enclosed in parenthesis is the number of requests that terminate at this point.**++标记的第一个数字表示以抽象单位计算的时间；第二个使用圆括号括起的可选数字表示在该点终止的请求数。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1947', 'pariah', '[pəraɪə]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=pariah', '{n.}++[P-]贱民(印度等的受压迫的处在社会低等级或不列级的成员)**++为社会所遗弃者；流浪者**++受鄙视的人(或动物)**', '++First, simply, it was a matter of face, of reducing its pariah-state image —a tangible symbol of being welcomed back into the global community.**++首先，简单地说，这是面子问题，可以弱化它的贱民国家形象——一个欢迎它回归国际社会的切实象征。**++While the report was not confirmed, it is consistent with China@s increasing desire to distance itself from pariah states in Africa and elsewhere that used to be treated as old friends.**++尽管这些消息没有得到证实，但它符合中国越发渴望与非洲及其他地方的贱民国家（在过去，它们被当作老朋友对待）保持距离的愿望。**++He had been known as the ruthless leader of a pariah state, a butcher, a delusional man divorced from reality.**++他就是被人称为一个贱民国度的残忍领导人，一个屠夫，一个脱离实际只会妄想的男子汉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1948', 'parity', '[pærəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=parity', '{n.}++(数量、地位、性质的)相等，同等，均等；平等**++类似；一样；相同**++(与另一国家的货币)折合对等价值；平价**++(两方兵力的)对峙，相持；均势**++[美国英语]平价制度(通常受到官价支持的农产品价格)**++【物理学】宇称(性)；奇偶性**++【数学】奇偶性，奇偶校验位**{n.}', '++Increasingly, reaching parity against the U.S. dollar is a question of when, not if, and whether it can stay there.**++市场越来越觉得,加元兑美元达到平价只是时间和能否保持的问题,而非能否实现的问题.**++The costs of each complication were estimated in purchasing power parity dollars (I$) for 2008 and discounted at 3%.**++每项并发症的成本以2008年购买力平价美元（$）为单位进行估算，贴现率为3%。**++So economists try to smooth out these differences by figuring the size of an economy on a \\\"purchasing power parity\\\" basis.**++为了消除这些差别，经济学家试图通过以“购买力平价”为基础描绘一个国家的经济情况。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1949', 'parody', '[pærədi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=parody', '{n.}++(为嘲弄某作者或某作品而作成的)模仿滑稽作品**++拙劣的模仿**++模仿诗文**{vt.}++通过模仿嘲弄：**++通过模仿嘲弄：**', '++And so it began to pile up until one day I collapsed from the strain of it, becoming an empty shell, a parody of who I used to be.**++所以它开始慢慢地堆积起来，知道有一天我在那些压力中崩溃了，变成一个空壳，变成过去的一拙劣的模仿品。**++But his critics say he risks turning into a parody of Soviet leader Leonid Brezhnev who ruled the USSR from 1964 until his death in 1982.**++但是他的批评者认为普京是在拙劣地模仿从1964年直到1982年去世一直统治前苏联的领导人勃列日涅夫。**++But regardless of her argument against Christianity, a number of commentators have said "parody or not" her remarks were wildly insensitive given the devastation happening in Japan.**++但是虽然她的辩驳是反对基督教的，仍有一些评论者说“模仿或者不模仿”她的言论对于日本发生的破坏都是极度冷血的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('1950', 'paroxysm', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paroxysm', '{n.}++(疾病等的)突然发作；阵发**++(笑声、怒声等感情的)突然爆发；一阵发作**', '++All we have left is paroxysm, and when it subsides, there will be just one wisp of smoke . . . our inner fire will ravish all.**++我们已经离开是突然发作，我们内心之火将迷住一切。**++Linton had sunk prostrate again in another paroxysm of helpless fear, caused by his father@s glance towards him, I suppose: there was nothing else to produce such humiliation.**++林惇又在一阵无能为力的恐惧中伏在地上，我想这是由于他父亲瞅了他一眼的缘故：没有别的可以产生这种屈辱。**++I swept it along the carpet, and then memory burst in: my late anguish was swallowed in a paroxysm of despair.**++我顺着桌毯一拂，记忆跟着就来了：我原来的悲痛被一阵突然的绝望吞没了。**');
