insert into GREWordBook values ('1970', 'pedagogue', '[pɛdəɡɑɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=pedagogue', '{n.}++(小学)教师，教员；(儿童)教育者**++卖弄学问的教师；学究式教师**{vt.}++教，教授**', '++Does anybody have pedagogue in your Greek translation there at 3:24?**++谁有3：,对pedagogue的希腊译文？**++Look what he says in 3:24, "Therefore the law was our disciplinarian until Christ came so that we might be justified by faith." Well the word "disciplinarian" there is the Greek word "pedagogue."**++看3：,“这样律法是我们训蒙的师傅，引我们到基督那里,使我们因信称义“,“师傅“这个词译自希腊语“pedagogue**++But parents and prosecutors alike are nonetheless asking why the female version of pedagogue perversion seems more common on their peninsula compared with other places.**++尽管如此，学生家长和起诉人还是在疑问，为什么这种女老师和学生的艳事在这个半岛上会比别的地方更加普遍。**');
