insert into GREWordBook values ('2251', 'rapt', '[ræpt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rapt', '{adj.}++欣喜若狂的**++全神贯注的**++着迷的；销魂的**++[罕用语]心驰神移的**', '++In fact, he was rapt, glassy-eyed, having at last some profound insight as to how to think about gravity.**++事实上，他全神贯注凝视着，最后像是对怎么 理解地心引力有什么深刻看法似的。**++There, I would explain why the dinosaurs disappeared and how mankind evolved from our primitive forebears. She seemed rapt.**++在哪里，我给她讲述为什么恐龙会灭绝和人类是如何从原始祖先进化来的，她似乎听的全神贯注。**++No wonder she held people in rapt attention at dinner parties, in line at the market, at bus stops.**++难怪晚餐聚会，超市排队中，汽车站，她总是吸引人们全神贯注的注意力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2252', 'rarefy', '[rɛrə,fai]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rarefy', '{vt.}++使稀薄：**++使纯净；使精炼：**{vi.}++变得稀薄；变得稀少：**++变得精炼，变得精妙深奥**', '++Everyone ought to rarefy his spiritual life.**++人人都应当纯洁其精神生活。**++The insertion of an inner rod into the waveguide can rarefy the spectrum of the competing modes in the vicinity of the operating mode and restrict the mode competing effectively.**++在圆柱腔体内插入一个内导体将会使工作模式附近的模谱变稀，从而有效的抑制模式竞争。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2253', 'rash', '[ræʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rash', '{adj.}++匆促的；草率从事的；轻率的，不顾后果的**++急躁的；性急的；鲁莽的**++[废语]见效快的，立竿见影的 4 [古语]要求迅速对付的**{n.}++【医学】皮疹，疹子**++突然大量出现的事物**++[俚语](因钟情而)神魂颠倒的小伙子**', '++The excitement brought her out in a nervous rash.**++激动使她全身出神经过敏的皮疹。**++In 6% of cases an inverse distribution may occur, with rash mostly on the extremities.**++6%的患者会发生相反的分布，而是在四肢发生大部分皮疹。**++It would be rash to try an exam like BEC Higher withoutshavingsdone any preparation at all, even if your English is very good.**++即使你的英文很好,但是在没有任何准备的情况下去参加象高级商务英语的考试都会是轻率的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2254', 'raspy', '[ræspi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=raspy', '{adj.}++(声音)粗重刺耳的；恼人的**++焦躁的；易怒的**', '++a raspy female voice hollers from behind us.**++一声刺耳的女人的喊声从我们背后传来。**++RaSPy: a robot that plays rock, scissors, paper**++RaSPy：玩石头、剪刀、布的机器人**++Stress is to the human condition what tension is to the violin string: too little and the music is dull and raspy; too much and the music is shrill or the string snaps.**++压力对于人的身体状况就像拉力对于小提琴的琴弦一样。 拉力太小，发出的乐音又闷又刺耳。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2255', 'ratify', '[rætɪfaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ratify', '{vt.}', '++We will work to ratify and bring into force the test ban treaty.**++我们将为使《禁止核试验条约》获得批准并生效而努力。**++A key to any agreement is for the US Senate to ratify a climate bill before the country@s negotiators go to Copenhagen.**++达成任何协议的关键是，美国参议院需要在该国谈判代表前往哥本哈根之前，批准一部气候法案。**++But first it will have to ratify the treaty.**++但是首先美国必须批准该条约。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2256', 'ratiocination', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ratiocination', '{n.}{vi.}', '++Mr Bush is a convert to an evangelical Christianity that emphasises emotion—particularly the intensely emotional experience of being born again—over ratiocination.**++布什皈依基督教福音派，该派强调主观情绪，尤其是狂热的再生体验，要凌驾于推理之上。**++Mr Bush is a convert to an evangelical Christianity that emphasises emotion-particularly the intensely emotional experience of being born again-over ratiocination.**++布什皈依了福音基督教会，强调重感情（尤其是重生的感情经历），轻理性。**++Maths is not only a knowledge system but also a rational thinking and argument system. It is a systematism theory knowledge summation by height abstract and strict logic ratiocination.**++数学既是一个知识体系，又是一个理性的思辩体系，它是经过高度抽象和严格的逻辑推理形成的系统化理论知识总和。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2257', 'ration', '[ræʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ration', '{n.}++(食物等的)配给量；定量；口粮**++一份配给物品**++[复数]【军事】给养；口粮**++应得份额**{vt.}++定量供应，配给：**++向…定量供应，对…实行配给：**++俭约使用，约束，节制**', '++He has held the ration cards of some migrants for seven years.**++有些移民的配给卡甚至被卡汉“保管”了七年之久。**++As one revered judge, Learned Hand, said in 1951, “If we are to keep our democracy, there must be one commandment: thou shalt not ration justice.**++正如德高望重的勒恩•汉德法官1951年时所说：“如果我们想要延续民主体制，必须遵守一条戒律——正义不能配给。”**++Elephants, which have no predators, must roam widely to get their daily ration of as much as 52 gallons (200 litres) of water and about 300 kilograms (660 pounds) of grass, leaves and twigs.**++没有天敌的大象必须在广袤的大地上四处漫游，才能解决它们每日的口粮问题——52加仑（合200公升）水及约300公斤（合660磅）的草、树叶及树枝）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2258', 'rational', '[ræʃnəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rational', '{adj.}++推理的**++有理性的；有推理能力的；明事理的**++合理的；有理智的**++【数学】(数、函数式等)有理的；有理数的**++主张理性的，反对感情用事的**{n.}++合理的事物**++=rational dress**', '++Rational, unemotional, self assessment should tell us whether or not we have the skills and ability to do something.**++理性的不参杂感情的自我评价应该能告诉我们自己是否有能力和技巧去做些什么。**++And so we have to come to some kind of rational and fair agreement.**++所以，我们一定要达成一些理性和公平的协议。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2259', 'rave', '[rev]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rave', '{vi.}++胡言乱语，说胡话：**++大发雷霆；破口大骂：**++热烈谈话；极力赞扬：**++(风暴等)呼啸，怒号：**++跳锐舞**{vt.}++语无伦次地胡说：**++[rave oneself]叫嚷得…：**++(风暴等)肆虐一阵后停息下来(常与 out 连用)：**{adj.}++[口语]赞扬的**{n.}++胡言乱语；口出狂言；发疯**++狂乱**++[美国口语]吹捧，赞扬；溢美之辞[常用作定语]**++鲜明的展示，光彩夺目的展出**++[英国俚语](一时的)风尚，时尚**++五光十色的一片**++= rave-up**++锐舞 **++锐舞舞会，大型电子乐狂舞会，热舞会**{n.}', '++The drunkard began to rave again.**++这酒鬼又开始胡言乱语了。**++As I would eat the great meal, I would rave about it and praise my mother.**++正如我会吃大餐，我会赞扬它，并赞美我的母亲。**++Now I understand why readers rave about this book.**++我现明白读者为何对这本书赞不绝口了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2260', 'ravel', '[rævl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ravel', '{vt.}++使纠缠；使错综复杂：**++拆开；拆散(常与 out 连用)：**++解开；理出…的头绪(常与 out 连用)：**++弄清楚；解决(常与 out 连用)：**++使(路面)松碎**{vi.}++(编织物等)变松散；散开；开线：**++(问题等)得到解决(常与 out 连用)：**++[古语]变得错综复杂；纠结在一起**++(路面)松碎，剥落**{n.}++(编织物等的)开线部分；散开部分**++乱缠在一起的东西；纷乱的一团；错综复杂的一团**', '++We also learned from Ravel@s Bolero that nobody actually plays the beat-- that@s too basic but our mind, hearing all of these complex rhythms, extrapolates the beat from this complexity.**++通过拉威尔的《波莱罗》我们还知道,没有人专门负责敲打节拍,那太简单了,但听到那些复节奏时,我们的大脑会自动推断出节拍**++Maurice Ravel was a French composer writing in the early twentieth century.**++莫里斯·拉威尔是法国作曲家,是二十世纪早期的**++Her favourite piano music includes Mozart@s piano concerto No 23, as well as the Rachmaninov Preludes and Maurice Ravel@s Piano Concerto in G major.**++她最喜欢的钢琴曲包括莫扎特第23号钢琴协奏曲，以及拉赫曼尼诺夫的序曲和拉威尔的G大调钢琴协奏曲。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2261', 'ravenous', '[rævənəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ravenous', '{adj.}++贪吃的；饿极了的；狼吞虎咽的**++渴望…的；一心想得到…的**++贪婪的；贪得无厌的**', '++When it comes to unexpected heartache and tragedy, our appetite for unraveling the meaning of these ambiguous "messages" can become ravenous.**++当牵涉到意外的心痛和悲剧的时候，我们会贪婪的想要阐明这些模糊“信息”的含义。**++To paraphrase Thucydides, the realpolitik of zombies is that the strong will do what they can and the weak must suffer devouring by reanimated, ravenous corpses.**++套用修昔底德的话来说就是，活僵尸的权力政治是：强者将会作他们所能做的，而弱者只能忍受复活了的、贪婪的僵尸们的折磨。**++Now people go out in a mad rush to shop, like ravenous vampires feasting on new blood.**++现在人们都加入到疯狂购物的大军中，和贪婪的吸血鬼饕餮着鲜血无异。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2262', 'ravish', '[rævɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ravish', '{vt.}++[多用于被动语态]使(某人)欣喜若狂；使陶醉；使入迷：**++强奸：**++[古语]抢去；强夺；劫掠：**', '++She said. @It@s only people who ravish things.**++她说，“这是人类把一切事物奸污了。”**++My creed is love and you are its only tenet – you have ravish@d me away by a power I cannot resist.**++我的信经就是爱，而你就是它独一的信条。 你用我没法抵御的气力将我完全捣毁。**++All we have left is paroxysm, and when it subsides, there will be just one wisp of smoke . . . our inner fire will ravish all.**++我们已经离开是突然发作，我们内心之火将迷住一切。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2263', 'raze', '[rez]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=raze', '{vt.}++拆除；摧毁；夷为平地：**++刮去；抹掉：**++[古语]擦伤[亦作rase]**', '++The government wants to raze the slums, move millions of poor people to high-rise buildings and let developers build expensive flats.**++政府想要把贫民窟夷为平地，让数百万计贫困居民迁到高楼大厦中，并且让开发商建造昂贵的公寓。**++Bing’s radical plan is to shrink Detroit in order to save it: Raze decaying neighborhoods and cut public services and the crushing fiscal deficit.**++宾的基本计划是缩减底特律的开支以对其实施拯救：将被废弃的小区夷为平地、削减公共服务项目、缩小破坏性的财政赤字。**++The next goal is to amass a battalion of troops that can quickly raze infested Terran structures during your brief windows of daylight.**++下一个目标就是聚集一支能够极快的在白天时间段扫光被感染的人类建筑的部队。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2264', 'react', '[riækt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=react', '{vi.}++产生作用；作出反应(常与 to 连用)：**++对…起反应；对…有影响；对…起作用(常与 on，upon 连用)：**++反抗；反动(常与 against 连用)：**++【化学】起化学作用，产生化学反应 **++【物理学】起反应(常与 with， on 连用)：**{vt.}++使起反应，使发生作用(常与with连用)：**++使起反应，使发生作用(常与with连用)：**', '++To do this you need to react quickly.**++要做到这一点，你需要快速反应。**++I shouted at her,but she didn@t react at all.**++我向她大声喊叫，但她毫无反应。**++An acid can react with a base to form a salt.**++酸与碱产生化学反应而形成盐。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2265', 'reactionary', '[rɪækʃənɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reactionary', '{adj.}++反动的；极端保守的**{n.}++反动分子;反动派[亦作re actionist]**', '++Accounts of cruel tortures in the jails of the reactionary government would curl one@s hair.**++关于反动政府监狱里酷刑情况的介绍听了会叫人毛骨悚然。**++He was free from all sycophancy or obsequiousness in the face of the reactionary ruling class.**++他在反动统治阶级面前没有丝毫的奴颜与媚骨。**++Riddled with a thousand gaping wounds, this reactionary clique is now beset with difficulties and contradictions both in internal and external affairs.**++今天， 这个反动集团百孔千疮， 内外交困， 矛盾重重。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2266', 'ream', '[rim]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ream', '{n.}++令(纸张的计数单位)**++[常作复数]大量**{vt.}++(用铰刀等)扩孔(或修孔)；铰大(枪等的)口径**++钻孔**++铰除(疵点等)**++[美国英语](从柠檬等水果中)挤出汁来**++掏(烟斗)**++[美国俚语]欺骗；骗取**', '++The Platinum Crystal in Arkansas is uniquely programmed to interface with Parallel Universes and the Angelic Ream of anti-matter.**++在阿肯色州的白金水晶受独特的编程而成为平行宇宙与反物质的天使界之界面。**++He was allegedly captured on camera walking to the tenant@s restaurant with a ream of toilet paper, pulling his pants down, squatting and defecating.**++切雷托，来自马士菲，据称，独自放下包裹，被摄像头拍到带着大量厕纸径直走入房客的旅店，脱下裤子，蹲下并排便。**++That stirring sunlight, plentiful vine, and wine in the kiln urn with wine bottle, played to ring the ream the glad music in mind.**++那撩人的阳光，茂盛的葡萄藤，以及窑中的酒缸和酒瓶，奏响了令心灵愉悦的音乐。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2267', 'reap', '[rip]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reap', '{vt.}++收割，从(地里)收割庄稼；收获：**++获得；得到：**{vi.}++收割；收获：**++得到报偿；受到报应**{n.}++(柔道中的)扫荡腿绊对方的动作**', '++The peasants leaned down to reap wheat.**++农民们俯身收割小麦。**++You work hard after you learn how to work smart and as a result, reap the best benefits of both worlds.**++在你知道怎样精明的工作以后再去努力工作，你就会在这两个世界里获得最大利益。**++But it cannot happen just like that, you need to believe in some basic principles of success so that you automatically reap success every moment.**++但是它并会想想象中的那样容易，你需要了解一些成功的基本原理，使得你在任何时刻都可以自动的获得利益。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2268', 'reassure', '[,riəʃʊr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reassure', '{vt.}++重新向…保证**++使恢复信心；打消…的疑虑**++[英国英语] = reinsure**', '++But if your clinic would reassure me that I would not be at risk, then I would happily donate.**++但是，如果诊所让我放心，保证我不会有危险，那么，我将愉快地捐赠。**++You have sought to reassure us that despite the 14% cuts across all government spending in the next few years we will still be spending at 2006 levels.**++你试图让对此我们感到安心：虽然在新的几年内削减了14%政府投入，我们对此的投入仍然处在2006年的水平。**++That will not reassure everyone.**++那并非让每个人都放心。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2269', 'rebuff', '[rɪbʌf]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rebuff', '{n.}++(对建议等的)断然拒绝**++挫折；阻碍；抵制**{vt.}++断然拒绝；漠视：**++挫败；阻止：**', '++His rebuff thoroughly deflated me.**++他的断然拒绝使我心灰意懒。**++Cumulatively these transcribed minutes help us to see the gradual changes in policy when both sides were willing to risk rebuff.**++这些点点滴滴的记录叠加起来，让我们看到当双方都愿意甘冒风险，不怕回绝时，政策是如何逐渐转变的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2270', 'recalcitrant', '[rɪkælsɪtrənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recalcitrant', '{adj.}++不服从的，不顺从的；执拗的**++难管束的；难对付的**{n.}++执拗的人；倔强的人**', '++Even then it took a sympathetic bankruptcy judge to convince a group of recalcitrant lenders that it was in their best interest to drop their opposition.**++尽管当时表现出同情的破产判断确信一部分负隅顽抗的贷方，这样对贷方有利，所以放弃了他们的反对。**++And Beijing may be where the market is headed. Chinese energy officials made fast friends among the world’s most recalcitrant regimes because they had the capital and didn’t ask the questions.**++北京已经在领导着市场，中国的能源官员能够与世界上大多数流氓政权国家很快交上朋友，因为他们有雄厚的资本实力而且不挑毛病。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2271', 'recant', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recant', '{vt.,vi.}', '++We should recant all opinions which are in conflict with those proclaimed by the central leadership.**++我们应当放弃所有与中央领导所宣布的有抵触的意见。**++For form’s sake, Luther was first invited to recant.**++出于形式，路德先是被要求公开认错。**++My political activist friends have called me on this, and I promised to recant any suggestion on these pages that political activism is a waste of time and energy.**++我的政治活动家朋友们已经这么指责我了，我答应收回认为发挥政治能动性是在浪费时间和精力的任何意见。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2272', 'recessive', '[rɪsɛsɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recessive', '{adj.}++后退的；退回的；有倒退倾向的**++【遗传学】隐性的(dominant之对)**++【语法学】逆行的**{n.}++【遗传学】**++隐性性状**++具有隐性性状的生物[参较dominant]**', '++New genes emerge as dominant, no longer recessive or latent, and organisms change.**++新的基因出现并支配，不在隐性潜伏，然后生物就突变了。**++Eye colour is inherited, however brown eyes are dominant across the world while blue eyes are a recessive trait.**++眼睛的颜色是天生的，世界上褐色眼睛占主导地位，而蓝色眼睛是一种隐性特征。**++Several studies have shown that exome sequencing can be used to identify inherited recessive mutations in Mendelian disorders.**++一些研究显示，外显子组测序能用于鉴定孟德尔疾病中的隐性遗传突变。**');
