insert into GREWordBook values ('2274', 'reciprocate', '[rɪsɪprəket]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reciprocate', '{vt.}++互给；互换：**++报答；酬答；报复：**++使(机件等)往复运动**{vi.}++互给；互换；酬答：**++往复运动；互换位置：**++[古语]相应；相等**++相符合，切合**', '++Some day I will reciprocate your kindness to me.**++总有一天我会报答你对我的恩德。**++Some day I will reciprocate your great kindness to me.**++总有一天我会报答你对我的厚爱。**++This is because when you express affection towards someone else, they are likely to reciprocate.**++这是因为当你对别人表达情感的时候，他们很可能回报你。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2275', 'reckless', '[rɛkləs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reckless', '{adj.}++不在意的；不顾虑的**++粗心的；鲁莽的；不顾后果的；草率的**', '++He apologized for their reckless behavior.**++他对他们的鲁莽行为道了歉。**++His reckless driving accounted for the accident.**++他开车鲁莽，引起了这场事故。**++The accident was the consequence of reckless driving.**++这场事故是鲁莽驾驶的结果。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2276', 'recluse', '[rɛklus]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recluse', '{adj.}++[亦作reclusive]隐居的;遁世的**++偏僻的；孤寂的**{n.}++[亦作incluse]隐士；遁世者**', '++Visitors who caught sight of him in New Hampshire where he lived described an unkempt  recluse.**++曾有访客在其居住地新罕布什尔州见过他，把他描绘成一位不修边幅的隐士。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2277', 'recoil', '[rikɔɪl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recoil', '{vi.}++后退；退缩；退回：**++(弹簧等)弹回；(枪、炮等)产生后坐力；对…产生反作用(常与on或upon连用)：**++报应，回报(常与on 或upon连用)：**{n.}++后退；退缩**++弹回；后作用(力)；(枪、炮的)后坐(力)；反冲(力)**++后坐距离**', '++Let evil recoil on those who slander me; in your faithfulness destroy them.**++他要报应我仇敌所行的恶。 求你凭你的诚实灭绝他们。**++There was a powerful recoil after each shot which hurt his shoulder and he then had to go to the trouble of reloading.**++每次射击完之后都有一股强大的后座力弄痛了自己的肩膀，而且自己还得麻烦地重新上膛。**++“I walk down the street analyzing the force of a boy on skateboard or the recoil of a carpenter using a nail gun, ” he wrote.**++现在，我走到街头，看见一个男孩玩滑板，或者木匠钉钉子，都会停下来分析他的作用力反作用力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2278', 'reconcile', '[rɛkənsaɪl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reconcile', '{vt.}++使和解，使和好：**++调解，调停：**++调和；使一致；使和谐：**++[reconcile oneself]使顺从;使能适应;使甘心于(常与to连用)：**++【会计】调节；核对：**', '++How do we reconcile that?**++我们如何协调这些？**++How do you reconcile this choice with liberalism?**++你如何调和这个选择与自由主义？**++The teacher in charge of our class had to reconcile disputes among the students.**++我们的班主任必须调解学生中的纠纷。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2279', 'recondite', '[rɛkəndaɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recondite', '{adj.}++深奥的**++晦涩的，难懂的**++隐秘的**++鲜为人知的**', '++If nothing else, having a few recondite words at your disposal can be a great defense against the pedantry of others.**++假如无太多影响，在你的表达中使用一些深奥的词语对于其他人的卖弄学问可是一种很好的防卫。**++There are a huge number of these environment variables; many of them are recondite variables intended for debugging, and it@s pointless to try to list them all.**++这样的环境变量数不胜数；对调试来说它们很多都是晦涩的变量，并且将它们全部列出也是无济于事的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2280', 'reconnoiter', '[,rikənɔɪtɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reconnoiter', '{vt.,vi., n.}', '++Google Earth has given scientists a way to scout terrain and cheaply reconnoiter habitats likely to produce new finds.**++谷歌地球（Google Earth）使科学家能够廉价地侦察地形，探索那些有可能出现新物种的栖息地。**++The ark also comes to rest on a mountaintop, the hero sends out a bird to reconnoiter the land, to find out if it@s dry yet.**++方舟停在山顶上,英雄派一只鸟出去查看大地的情况。**++Malicious users can use this information to reconnoiter the naming schema in your organization and attack key infrastructure services.**++恶意用户可以使用这个信息来侦察您的组织机构的名计划，并攻击关键基本设施服务。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2281', 'reconstitute', '[,rikɑnstətut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reconstitute', '{vt.}++改组；重新组成：**++使还原；(通过加水)恢复(脱水食物的)原状：**', '++You can also use DITA maps after migration to reconstitute hierarchies by defining nesting for the converted topics.**++还可以使用 DITA 映射，在迁移之后通过定义转换后主题之间的嵌套关系来重新建立分层结构。**++Rather than continue waiting for a more positive outcome, I believe it is time to let Oracle reconstitute things under some other umbrella, if they so choose.**++我不会继续等待正面的信息，只是觉得现在是要让Oracle在另外保护伞下重新组建的时候了，如果他们这么选择的话。**++Figure 7 shows the critical portion of our example Data Access Object (DAO) code, demonstrating how to retrieve and reconstitute ACL information from strings stored in a properties file.**++图 7 显示了示例数据访问对象（Data Access Object，DAO）代码的关键部分，并演示了如何从属性文件中存储的字符串检索和重新构建 ACL 信息。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2282', 'reconvene', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reconvene', '{vi.}++重新开会；再集会：**++重新开会；再集会：**{vt.}++再召集；再召开：**++再召集；再召开：**', '++You: "Can we reconvene next week?**++您：“我们下周再召集一次如何？**++Large Wall Clock: so all can see when the stand-up will start or when meetings will reconvene.**++大型挂钟：通过它所有的人都能知道立会何时开始，或何时召集会议。**++Though they did not reach a consensus on all the details the group will reconvene in January to hammer out further specifications and potentially get the interest of NASA.**++虽然他们并没有在所有细节上达成一致，研讨会将会在一月再次召开，对更多的细节进行商讨并尽可能引起NASA的关注。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2283', 'rectitude', '[rɛktɪtʊd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rectitude', '{n.}++正直；刚正不阿**++(判断、方法等的)正确**++[罕用语]直，笔直**', '++IT WAS a rare victory for fiscal rectitude.**++这是财政清廉的一个罕见的胜利。**++Speaking candidly to Playboy of his lust for women other than his wife, he endorsed a new standard of sexual openness while simultaneously upholding a model of sexual rectitude.**++他坦率地对《花花公子》说,他对其他女人比对妻子更有兴趣,他赞成一种公开的性行为标准,同时也支持诚实的性行为模式。**++The public mood in the US has also been shifting as the Republicans score points with calls for a return to fiscal rectitude.**++由于共和党因为呼唤回归财务清廉得分，美国公众情绪也被转移。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2284', 'recumbent', '[rɪkʌmbənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recumbent', '{adj.}++躺卧的；斜靠的**++休息的；不活动的**++【生物学】横卧的；斜倚的**{n.}++斜靠式自行车**', '++Fashion is having a recumbent moment, with models down all at once at Valentino, Miu Miu and Marc Jacobs, too.**++时尚正处在卧躺时刻，在华伦天奴，缪缪和马克雅各布的广告中，模特们也纷纷选择了躺倒。**++Mochet@s recumbent gave cyclists a more aerodynamic position, moving them closer to the ground, with the seat back allowing the riders to recline.**++莫切特的卧式自行车让骑手拥有更流线型的位置，移动时更接近于地面，而且座椅靠背还可以让骑手仰着。**++He dropped the gun onto the recumbent form of Tompkins and marched away across the damp lawn.**++他把枪扔到已经昏倒地汤普金斯旁边，快步的穿过潮湿的草丛。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2285', 'recuperate', '[rɪkupəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recuperate', '{vt.}++使恢复；使复原：**++弥补(损失等)；挽回；回收：**{vi.}++复原；恢复健康；休养：**++得到补偿；挽回损失；恢复元气：**', '++And now Sandel would recuperate in the minute of rest.**++现在，桑德尔只要休息一分钟就会恢复过来。**++The patient did not recuperate as rapidly as the doctor had expected.**++这位病人并没有像医生所期望的那样很快就复原。**++Sleep is important but there is a lot of confusion about how we can get this sacred time to rest, recuperate and reenergize.**++睡眠对于我们如此重要，但对于如何利用有限的休息时间恢复体能，人们有很多的误解。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2286', 'redeem', '[rɪdim]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=redeem', '{vt.}++赎回；买回：**++重获；收回；挽回；恢复：**++偿还；付清：**++弥补；补救；改善：**++开垦；开拓：**++赎出；解救；拯救：**++履行(诺言等)：**++[美国英语]把(纸币)换成硬币；变卖(证券)成现款；兑换(息票或商品赠券)：**', '++She is going to redeem her diamond ring.**++她将赎回她的钻石戒指。**++He had no way to redeem his furniture out of pawn.**++他无法赎回典当的家具。**++Once they do, they’re presented with a tamper-proof reward screen they can show the retailer to redeem the prize.**++一旦他们完成了任务，屏幕上就会出现防篡改的奖励画面，他们可以将它出示给零售商兑换奖励。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2287', 'redolent', '[rɛdələnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=redolent', '{adj.}++芬芳的，馥郁的**++有…气味的(常与of连用)**++使人联想(或回想)起…的；充满…气氛的(常与of连用)**', '++Underneath, visitors can stroll unaccompanied along a redolent sluiceway.**++在这座博物馆底下，游客可以在无人陪伴的情况下独自沿着一条气味浓烈的泄水道漫步。**++In the evening or after the rain, the whole earth, its womb moist with a seed redolent of bitter almond, rests after having given herself to the sun all summer long.**++黄昏时分或阵雨过后，这片大地带着湿气，孕育着有苦杏仁味芳香的种子。 在迎合了这长夏骄阳之后，她会恬然休憩。**++Four young men, each wearing white Tyvek coveralls, topped some of the redolent mixture with topsoil, put tarps over the rest and left for the holiday weekend.**++当时，四个身穿白色泰维克工作服的年轻人将带有芳香气味的骨粉团与表层土混在了一起，盖上防水布，然后就度周末去了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2288', 'redoubtable', '[rɪdaʊtəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=redoubtable', '{adj.}++可怕的；厉害的；令人惊骇的**++令人敬畏的[亦作redoubted]**', '++A redoubtable method, and one which, united with genius, rendered this gloomy athlete of the pugilism of war invincible for the space of fifteen years.**++那种锐不可当的方法，加上他的天才，便使战场上的这位沉郁的挥拳好汉在十五年中所向披靡。**++Said spoke of him reverentially - of his "redoubtable medical expertise and remarkable humanity" that kept him going during his darkest times, and there were many.**++说，以他的虔诚-他的“可怕的医学专业知识和出色的人类”，那让他去他最黑暗的时代，有很多。**++Whose only defense is their will and redoubtable spirit.**++他们唯一的国防是他们的意志和可怕的精神。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2289', 'redundant', '[rɪdʌndənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=redundant', '{adj.}++过多的，过剩的；多余的**++冗长的，累赘的**++(信息等)重复的**++大量的**++[英国英语]被解雇的，失业的**++千篇一律的**++【宇宙航行学】(可靠性)余度的；(为提高可靠性而)重复的**', '++This word is redundant, it can be left out.**++这个字是多余的， 可以去掉。**++But that is what the two men sitting in this office are saying: they are making me redundant.**++但这正是坐在这间办公室的两个男人所说的话：他们认为我是多余的。**++The target input pins could have been set too, but this would be redundant.**++目标输入帧也可以得到设置，但是这可能会是多余的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2290', 'reel', '[ril]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reel', '{vi.}++倒退；退缩；站立不稳；趔趄：**++蹒跚；踉跄：**++摇摆，摇晃：**++眩晕；震颤：**++旋转：**++(军队)溃退：**{vt.}++使退缩；使摇晃；使眩晕；使旋转**{n.}++步履蹒跚；摇晃；踉跄**++眩晕；旋转**++倒退**{n.}++里尔舞(轻快的苏格兰双人舞)；里尔舞曲**++Virginia reel 的缩略形式**{n.}++(棉纱、电缆等的)卷轴；卷筒**++(磁带、电影胶片等的)卷盘**++(钓竿上的)绕线轮**++(棉纱等的)一卷；(磁带等的)一盘**++(割草机上的)滚刀；(机器内的)卷轴装置**++手纺车；摇纱机**{vt.}++卷；绕；缠(常与in，up连用):**++收挠(钓丝等)；收绕钓丝钓起(常与 in， up连用)：**++放出(钓丝)(常与out连用)：**{vi.}++卷；绕；缠**++收绕钓丝(常与 in 连用)：**', '++First,reel out the electric cable carefully.**++首先，把电缆小心地从卷筒上放出来。**++Ah, I see. One reel of thread, cotton, black, what size?**++啊，好”写下；“让我看看：一卷棉线，棉花，黑色，尺寸多少？”**++Afterwards it strikes me what that movie is, and I reel out of the cinema like a suitor at the end of a misbegotten date.**++之后，一个念头突然闪在我的脑中：这究竟是哪部电影。 我蹒跚着走出影院，如同经历蹩脚的约会后的求婚者一般。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2291', 'referee', '[,rɛfəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=referee', '{n.}++受委托人，受委托处理者；公断人，仲裁人**++【体育】(足球、篮球等运动的)裁判员**++【法律】(受法庭委托的)鉴定人；审查人；公断人**{vt.}++为…担任裁判；为…作鉴定：**++为…担任裁判；为…作鉴定：**{vi.}++作仲裁人；作审阅人；作鉴定人；作裁判：**++作仲裁人；作审阅人；作鉴定人；作裁判：**', '++The centre forward of our school team was sent off the field by the referee for roughing.**++我们校队的中锋因动作粗野被裁判判罚出场。**++He was suspended for one year because he head-butted the referee after the match for being dissatisfied with his judgment.**++由于对裁判的判决不满，比赛结束后他用头撞了那名裁判，为此他受到停赛一年的处罚。**++I was so disappointed with the referee, he should get punished by FIFA.**++我对那个裁判太失望了，他应该受到国际足联的处罚。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2292', 'refine', '[rɪfaɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=refine', '{vt.}++精炼，提纯，精制：**++使精致；使完美；使高尚，使文雅；使优美：**++除去缺点；改善：**', '++Their daily work is to refine crude oil.**++他们每天的工作是精炼原油。**++For if many groups or individuals change and refine their energy field, this will attract another energetic reality to earth.**++因为如果许多群体或个人改变并精炼他们的能量场，这就会吸引又一个积极现实来到地球。**++One way to extend this application is to add a keyword or location field, for example, either of which would allow you to further refine searches.**++扩展此应用程序的一种方式是添加一个关键字或地址字段，而二者均能让您进一步精炼搜索。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2293', 'reflect', '[rɪflɛkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reflect', '{vt.}++反射(声、光、热等)：**++反映，反照；映出：**++给…带来，博得；蒙受(名誉或耻辱等)：**++显示，表明，反映：**++考虑；想到；认识到；悟及(that)[后跟从句或用于插入语]：**++折转；反折[常用作过去分词]：**{vi.}++反射出(声、光、热等)，折回：**++(声、光、热等)反射回来(back):**++映出，被映出：**++认真思考，对…深思熟虑；沉思反省(on或upon):**++带来耻辱；指摘，责备；损及(on 或upon):**++使…受到影响；产生…影响(on或upon):**', '++His actions reflect his thoughts.**++他的行为反映他的思想。**++Their actions clearly reflect their thoughts.**++他们的行动清楚地反映了他们的思想。**++What he said did not reflect back the views of the people.**++他的话没有如实地反映人民的观点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2294', 'refractory', '[rɪfræktəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=refractory', '{adj.}++(人或动物)倔强的；执拗的；难驾驭的**++(矿物或金属)耐高温的，难熔化的**++(疾病)难治的；(肌肉、神经、机体等)不起反应的**++对疾病有抵抗力的，抗感染的**{n.}++难驾驭的人(或动物)；倔强的人**++耐熔金属(或矿物)；耐火材料**', '++The question is, how is some of this converted into refractory compounds?**++但问题是，部分溶解有机物是如何转化成难熔化合物的。**++The reason this matters is that 95% of dissolved organic matter seems to be refractory.**++这很重要的原因是因为95%的溶解有机物貌似是难熔的。**++For example, Dr Jiao and his colleagues want to map the abundance, composition and distribution of refractory molecules in more detail.**++例如，焦博士和他的同事们想要制作更详细的这些难熔分子的富集、成分和分布图谱；**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2295', 'refreshing', '[rifrɛʃɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=refreshing', '{adj.}++使精力恢复的；使精神振作的；使人清爽的**++清新悦目的**', '++Trust me, this is a refreshing way to live.**++相信我，这是一种很清爽的生活方式。**++What better reason to pop open a refreshing beer on a hot day, at a backyard BBQ or for no reason at all other than bubbly, hoppy goodness?**++有什么比在大热天，后院的烤肉旁来一杯凉爽的啤酒更好的理由？ 或者根本不需要别的理由，只为了充满泡沫的啤酒花？**++We find it refreshing to see other people in this business do the same.**++我们看到这个行业里还有其他人也是如此感到很高兴。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2296', 'refulgent', '[rɪfʌldʒənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=refulgent', '{adj.}', '++"Lange" wants to create more refulgent tomorrow in the field of decoration.**++“兰格”在装饰领域要创造更加辉煌的明天。**++"Gloriously played and refulgent engineered, this (The Bruch Violin Concerto) is one of the finest pieces so far Sarah Chang given us. " By Classic FM Magazine.**++“莎拉·张演绎的布鲁赫《小提琴协奏曲》辉煌而光彩夺目，堪称是她目前演奏得最完美的作品之一。”——《古典音乐频度杂志》。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2297', 'refute', '[rifjʊt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=refute', '{vt.}++反驳；驳斥(某人)：**++驳倒；推翻(论据等)：**', '++We can easily refute his argument.**++我们可以很容易地驳倒他的论点。**++You can point out ,if you are man, a majority of poets and scientists are male; you could refute, if you are woman, most criminals are male as well .**++如果你是男子，你可以指出，大多数诗人和科学家都是男性；如果你是女子，你可以反驳说大多数罪犯也都是男人。**++Future housing data will confirm or refute whether the housing market@s pain is starting to fade.**++未来的住房行业数据将加强或者驳斥房屋市场的疼痛是否会开始逐渐消失。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2298', 'regenerate', '[rɪdʒɛnəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=regenerate', '{vt.}++使(精神上)新生：**++改革；更新；重建：**++使恢复原状；重新产生；复兴：**++【生物学】重新生出：**++【化学】使再生；还原：**++【电工学】使再生；恢复**++【机械工程】使回热(或回电等)**++【物理学】还原；使再生**{vi.}++再生；更新：**++新生；恢复：**{adj.}++(精神上)新生的**++更新的；革新的；再生的**{n.}++／ridʒenərit／**++再生物；再生部分**++改过自新的人**', '++If we can regenerate the brain, that would be interesting.**++如果你能再生大脑，那才是令人感兴趣的事。**++Like shark and dinosaur teeth they would break, but then regenerate.**++它们就像鲨鱼和恐龙的牙齿一样会断裂，但也会再生。**++"It is our first step towards the goal -- to regenerate organs that could replace damaged or lost ones, " he said.**++“这是我们迈向目标的第一步——再生器官以取代受到损伤或失去的器官，”他说。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2299', 'regimen', '[rɛdʒɪmən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=regimen', '{n.}++【医学】摄生法，养生法；疗程**++常规强化训练**++[罕用语]统治；政体；政权；社会制度**++(气象等的)情势、情态**++(河道情况等的) 变化特征**', '++This regimen will improve your focus and concentration, which in turn, helps you be more efficient and productive.**++这种养生法将改善你的注意力和专注力，这些反过来有助于你更有效率。**++Just one workout can have an effect, but adopting a regular workout regimen can have a lasting impact on your mood.**++仅仅一次运动便可以产生效果，但是采取有规律的锻炼养生法可以对你的情绪产生持久的影响。**++Although this diet is not physically harmful, and can be helpful in some instances, it’s generally not wise to adopt this regimen.**++虽然这个减肥法在身体上没有伤害，在某些情况下还有帮助，但是采用这个养生法一般是不明智的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2300', 'regress', '[rɪɡrɛs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=regress', '{vi.}++退回；回归：**++【天文学】退行；逆行**++倒退；退步；退化**{vt.}++使倒退**{n.}++／ri:ɡres／**++退回；倒退；回归；复归**++复归权**++退步；退化**', '++Once proper test cases have been created for your application, your project will never regress without your knowledge.**++一旦为应用程序创建了正确的测试用例，没有您的知识项目将无法回归。**++The more you direct your life towards Falsehood, Apathy and Powerlessness, the more you’ll regress in your life instead of improve.**++你越是把生活指向谎言、冷漠和无能为力，你的生活就会倒退得越多而不会有所改善。**++"Children with autism can succeed and do very well, or they can regress and not reach their potential, so the best intervention we have is education, " she said.**++她说：“自闭症儿童是可以成功的，他们能做得很好，反过来，他们也可能倒退，无法实现自己的潜能，而我们能采取的最好的干预方法就是教育。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2301', 'rehabilitate', '[,riəbɪlə,tet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rehabilitate', '{vt.}++恢复…的地位(或权利、财产等)：**++恢复名誉：**++修复；翻修；整顿；复兴：**++(通过医疗、心理治疗等)使恢复健康(或恢复正常生活等)；(通过职业训练等)使(残疾人或低能者)有就业机会：**++改造(罪犯等)：**{vi.}++被修复；复兴**++接受康复治疗；接受职业训练**++从战时体制恢复到正常**', '++For another thing, as another failed president, Richard Nixon, might advise, there’s nothing like writing to rehabilitate a sullied reputation.**++另外,另一位失败的总统——尼克松，可能会建议：没有什么事比写书以挽回名声更艰难的了。**++But they can definitely determine how they plan to grow as more people move in, and also how they want to rehabilitate areas that need regeneration.**++但它们确实可以决定怎样在更多的人迁移进来的同时计划它们的增长，以及它们希望怎样修复需要重建的区域。**++Farmers who previously harvested one crop from every four sowings were now reaping each time they planted and even began buying new patches of desert to rehabilitate and expand their fields.**++那些先前四次播种只能收获一次的农民们现在变成了有耕种便有收获，他们甚至开始购买新的沙漠土地用来改造，以扩张自己的土地。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2302', 'rehearsal', '[rɪhɝsl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rehearsal', '{n.}++复述；详述**++排演；彩排；排练；演习**', '++We’ll be discussing it this evening, in between drama rehearsal and a PTA meeting.**++今晚在餐桌上，除了戏剧排演和家长会之外，我们会讨论这个话题。**++As president of English Club, I organized the rehearsal of Snow White for an English party.**++作为英语俱乐部的主席，我为英语晚会组织排演了《白雪公主》短剧。**++These are great moments to give to your son for a wedding present - at the rehearsal dinner.**++对你的孩子来说，有关这些时刻的记忆是婚礼排演晚餐上最好的礼物。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2303', 'reign', '[ren]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reign', '{n.}++王权；君权；统治**++支配；主宰；盛行**++统治时期；(帝王的)在位期；极盛期**++[古语]王国**{vi.}++(君主等)统治；称王：**++支配；主宰：**++盛行；占优势：**', '++It is the place where all is at peace, where joy and unconditional love reign, where there is no hatred, anger or fear.**++它就是此处，只有全然的平和，全然的喜悦和无条件之爱的支配，这里没有任何的憎恨，愤怒或者恐惧。**++And once people started paying for their health care themselves, you’d see more attention paid to bad behavior and more political pressure for the government to reign in costs.**++而且一旦人们开始给他们自己买健康保险，你会把注意力更多的投入在坏的行为和政府更多的政治压力上，以此来支配成本。**++He took measures to bring the disorders of king Stephen reign to an end.**++他采取措施结束了史蒂芬森国王统治时期的混乱局面。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2304', 'rein', '[ren]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rein', '{n.}++缰绳[通常作复数，见harness]**++[复数]钳制；控制；驾驭**++[复数]控制权；控制手段**{vt.}++(用缰绳等)勒住；勒住(缰绳)使(马)转向：**++驾驭：**++控制：**{vi.}++(勒住缰绳)使马缓行(或转向、止步等)(常与 in或 up连用)：**++控制：**++[古语]服从驾驭：**', '++It is difficult to rein a fiery horse.**++脾气暴躁的烈马是难于驾驭的。**++Now I had to rein in my ego and remember not to get carried away by all the praise and positive press.**++现在我却必须控制我的自负，牢记不要因为所有这些赞美和媒体的肯定性报道而飘飘然。**++You don@t have free rein in the Registry, but you do have access from a common root node for all your applications.**++您虽然不能够对注册表自由控制，但您的确可以通过一个公共根节点访问所有的应用程序。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2305', 'reiterate', '[rɪɪtəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reiterate', '{vt.}', '++I want to reiterate that we welcome all riders on our system.**++我想重申一下，我们欢迎所有乘客使用我们的运输系统。**++It should expand on, not just reiterate, the most relevant skills and experiences from your résumé.**++它应该扩大,而不只是重申,最相关的技能和经验来自你的简历中。**++A: I reiterate that we hope the US and the DPRK properly settle this issue.**++答：我重申，我们希望美朝双方能够妥善解决这一问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2306', 'rejoice', '[rɪdʒɔɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rejoice', '{vi.}++欣喜，感到高兴(常与at，in或over连用)：**++欣喜，感到高兴(常与at，in或over连用)：**{vt.}++使…高兴，使…欣喜：**++使…高兴，使…欣喜：**', '++But wait a minute: Should we rejoice in the death of another human being?**++但是，请再想想：我们该为另一个同类的死亡而高兴吗？**++This should be wonderful news for... well, for all women born in 1979 and 1980, who can rejoice in the realisation that they are – or are about to be – at their peak.**++这对所有在1979 和1980 年出生的女人来说应该是一个很棒的消息，她们会为自己正处于或即将处于人生的黄金时刻而感到高兴。**++Just knowing that life was still in tact was all I needed to rejoice.**++只要知道小生命还在得体地持续，那就是我高兴的理由。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2307', 'relapse', '[rɪlæps]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=relapse', '{vi.}++重新陷入；再次堕落；故态复萌；旧病复发：**++重新陷入；再次堕落；故态复萌；旧病复发：**{n.}++重新陷入；重犯**++旧病复发**', '++If you relapse, start the process over.**++如果复发，从头开始上述步骤。**++Experts who study how people change have discovered that relapse is to be expected.**++研究人们如何改变的专家已经发现人们是期待故态复萌的。**++They should continue taking the medication for the time specified by their doctor, even if they are feeling better, in order to prevent a relapse of the depression.**++即使他们正感觉好起来了，但是为了避免抑郁复发，他们也应该按他们的医生规定的时长继续服用药物。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2308', 'release', '[rɪlis]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=release', '{vt.}++释放；解放：**++放出；放松；排放：**++豁免；免除；解除：**++发泄；发挥：**++减轻(痛苦等)；解脱：**++准予发表(或发布、发行等)：**++准许…离职度假：**++【法律】放弃；让予(财产、权利等)：**{n.}++释放；解放；放出；松开**++豁免；免除；解脱；解除**++豁免证明；释放证**++解除(痛苦等)；消除(紧张情绪等)**++发泄；发挥**++【机械学】擒纵装置；排放装置；释放装置；(照相机等的)保险扣**++(消息、影片等的)发布(或发行)**++发布的新闻；发行的影片**++【法律】弃权；让渡；让渡证书**++【音乐】释音；淡释**', '++We have to release the news before 5 o@clock tomorrow morning.**++我们必须在明晨五点以前将这条新闻发布出去。**++Profile class and enumerations are not supported in this release; therefore, they do not show up in the wizard.**++配置文件类和列举在这个释放中是不被支持的；因此，它们不会显示在这个向导中。**++In this situation, you can either catch up the resource from the stream, release your version of the resource to the stream, or merge your work and the stream resource.**++在这种情况下，您可以捕获来自流的资源，将您制订的该资源的版本发布到流中，或者也可以把您的工作与流资源合并起来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2309', 'relentless', '[rɪlɛntləs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=relentless', '{adj.}++无情的；严酷的；不宽容的；残忍的**++坚韧的；不懈的；百折不挠的**', '++In the relentless busyness of modern life,we have lost the rhythym between action and rest.**++在这个无情、繁忙的现代生活中，我们已经在工作和休息之间失去了平衡。**++So the system has released this relentless innovative energy, but it@s out of human control, and every so many years, there@s a crisis.**++因此，这个制度释放的是一种残酷创新的活力，但它并不受人类的控制，而且每若干年，就要有一次危机。**++This is the design philosophy that leads to overstuffed websites that resemble Times Square in their relentless attack on the senses.**++就是这种设计哲学导致了类似时代广场这种冗长的网站，给人类感官以无情的打击。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2310', 'relevant', '[rɛləvənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=relevant', '{adj.}++有关的；确切的；中肯的；适当的**++相关联的；相应的**++有重大意义的；有重大关系的**++对当前重大问题关注的；与当前重大问题密切相关的**', '++As for your second question, we have noticed relevant reports.**++关于第二个问题，我们注意到了有关报道。**++But all of the registers might not be relevant for all of the signals.**++不过并非所有的寄存器都是与所有的信号有关的。**++I will read anything they write, because I know it will be both relevant to me and an enjoyable reading experience.**++我会去阅读他们所写的任何东西，因为我知道它会与我以及我的令人愉快的阅读经历有关。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2311', 'religion', '[rɪlɪdʒən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=religion', '{n.}++宗教；信仰**++宗教信仰；宗教活动**++宗教生活；修道生活；修行**++一心追求的目标；虔诚的追求**', '++Maybe religion should help to straighten him out.**++也许宗教信仰可以使他改邪归正。**++Their interest localized on the subject of religion.**++他们的兴趣集中在宗教问题上。**++Though he was forced to change his religion,he would not recant.**++虽然强迫他改变宗教信仰，但他绝不改变。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2312', 'relinquish', '[rɪlɪŋkwɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=relinquish', '{vt.}++放弃：**++让与(财产、权利等)：**++松手，放开：**++撤离：**', '++Do you view mothers who relinquish custody differently than fathers who do the same?**++你认为放弃监护权的母亲与同样做法的父亲有一样吗？**++But why would you willingly relinquish control over your resources and allow them to virtually exist in the cloud?**++但是，为什么您会心甘情愿地放弃对自己资源的控制，而让它们虚拟地存在于云中呢？**++It was, of course, a tough decision to relinquish my citizenship from Kenya, but I think it was the best decision for me.**++当然，放弃肯尼亚公民身份是一个困难的决定，但我认为这是我能作出的最佳选择。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2313', 'relish', '[rɛlɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=relish', '{n.}++味道，滋味；美味**++特殊的味道；风味**++意味；含意；少量**++食欲；兴趣；乐趣；爱好**++饶有趣味的事；吸引力**++小菜，(主菜前的)开胃食品；拼盘；调味品，作料**{vt.}++喜好；乐于：**++欣赏；玩味；品尝：**{vi.}++具有某种滋味(或风味)：**++味道好吃，可口：**', '++People like me who relish political theater of the absurd will miss the “Leader;” but most of his people, I suspect, will not.**++我这样喜欢品味荒谬政治舞台的人将会怀念这位“领导人”，但是我想，他的绝大多数民众却不会怀念他的。**++Break out of this guilt and let yourself relish in your sense of accomplishment for what you have gotten done instead of what there is still to do.**++摆脱这种负罪感，放下没做的事情，享受做完事情的成就感。 想把所有事情都处理好不过是虚幻的目标，因为总有事情要做。**++In Bombay [Mumbai], I was just was one of the girls, nothing special, but sometimes now I enjoy being that outside voice, I sometime relish it.**++在孟买，我不过是女孩子之一，没有什么特别的，但是有时我喜欢成为那个局外的声音，我有时喜欢，有时讨厌。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2314', 'reluctant', '[rɪlʌktənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reluctant', '{adj.}++不愿意的[后接不定式]**++勉强的**++[罕用语]反抗的；反对的**', '++Even if the child is reluctant, he knows that the time is reserved for reading.**++即使孩子们不情愿，他也会知道那个时间是为了阅读留出来的。**++If the company is reluctant to give you a list, do some research on your own (Google it).**++如果公司不情愿给您名单，那您可以独自地做一些调查(谷歌它)。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2315', 'remiss', '[rɪmɪs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remiss', '{adj.}++粗心的；疏忽的；不负责的**++马虎成性的**++[罕用语]倦怠的；懒洋洋的；无精打采的**', '++One planned backend is supposed to be led by me -- but I have been remiss in developing initial versions.**++一个已经规划好的后端被期望由我来负责 ― 但是在开发最初的版本时，我有点懈怠。**++I have never used them myself, nor been in projects that used them in earnest, so I cannot comment on their worth, but I would be remiss if I did not mention their existence.**++我自己从来没有用过这些工具，也没有在项目中用过，所以我说不好其价值，但是我要是不提及其存在就是我的不对了。**++Before closing, I would be remiss not to mention performance.**++在结束之前，如果不提一下性能就是我的失职了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2316', 'remnant', '[rɛmnənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remnant', '{n.}++剩余；残余；残余物**++[常用复数]残存者；残余部分**++残迹；遗迹**++零布头儿；边脚料**{adj.}++剩下的；残余的**', '++I will sell this remnant to you, at cost.**++我愿将此剩货照成本卖给你。**++It is the remnant of a supernova that was recorded by Chinese and Arab astronomers in 1054.**++早在1054年，中国和阿拉伯天文学家就有关于它是超新星残余的记载。**++The LORD hath said concerning you, O ye remnant of Judah; Go ye not into Egypt: know certainly that I have admonished you this day.**++所剩下的犹大人哪，耶和华论到你们说，不要进入埃及去。 你们要确实地知道我今日警教你们了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2317', 'remodel', '[,rimɑdl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remodel', '{vt.}++重塑，重新塑造**++改造；重建；改组：**', '++It also plans by 2013 to remodel 80% of its existing outlets.**++此外，它还计划到2013年对其80%的现有门店进行改造。**++"It is extremely useful to have a brain that can remodel and rewire itself, " says Professor Blakemore.**++“一个可以自我改型，自我重构的大脑极其有用”，布莱克莫尔教授表示。**++But in animal experiments, exercise seems to remodel the metabolic pathways that determine how the body stores and utilizes food.**++然而，我们可以通过动物来进行实验，运动似乎可以改变体内储存与食物利用的代谢途径。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2318', 'remonstrance', '[rɪmɑnstrəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remonstrance', '{n.}++抗议；抗辩；规劝；告诫；进谏**++抗议书；告诫文；进谏书**', '++They laid their objections to paper in a document called the Flushing Remonstrance.**++抗议者起草了一份文件，称为《法拉盛抗议书》。**++This time India has shown admirable forbearance. There has been remonstrance but no sabre-rattling.**++那次印度已表现了令人钦佩的忍耐力，双方一直抗议，但并没有剑拔弩张。**++Sometimes Madame Magloire essayed a remonstrance in advance, but never at the time, nor afterwards.**++马格洛大娘有时试着在事先劝劝，但从不在事情进行时或事后多话。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2319', 'remorse', '[rɪmɔrs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remorse', '{n.}++懊悔，悔恨；自责**++怜悯；同情**', '++I felt grief, pain and remorse, Why had I not been there for him?**++我感到悲伤，心痛，懊悔。 为什么我不在他的身边？**++“If I had heard this information earlier, I would not have divorced my wife,” he said with remorse.**++“如果我早点得知这种信息，我就不会和我的妻子离婚”，他懊悔地说。**++For most of us, when we do something wrong to someone else we feel guilt, regret and remorse.**++我们中的大多数在对别人做错了事儿之后会有罪恶感、会后悔还会自责。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2320', 'remunerate', '[rɪmjunəret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remunerate', '{vt.}', '++The company will remunerate you for your travelling expenses.**++公司将给你报销旅费。**++End, I found out a to remunerate a big work also by excellent result graduation.**++最终，我以优异的成绩毕业并找到了一份报酬丰厚的工作。**++I will remunerate you my debt for gratitude.**++我要报答我对你的感激之情。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2321', 'rend', '[rɛnd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rend', '{vt.}++撕裂;扯破(常与 from,off,away 连用)：**++劈开；割裂；分裂：**++[比喻](声音)刺破，划破；响彻：**++(因忧伤等)扯衣服(或头发)：**++夺去；抢走；摘下：**++使烦恼；困扰；撕裂(心等)：**{vi.}++撕裂；扯碎**++破裂；分裂；分开：**', '++The winter@s frost must rend the burr of the nut before the fruit is seen.**++只要冬天的寒霜撕碎了坚果的芒刺，才能看到果实。**++The integrated country will rend into several independent regions sooner or later.**++那个完整的国家早晚会分裂成几个独立的地区。**++And who are you that men should rend their bosom and unveil their pride, that you may see their worth naked and their pride unabashed?**++你又凭什么？ 他们就该为你袒露胸膛，显露出他们的矜持，以便让你看清他们真实的价值和他们的尊严？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2322', 'renegade', '[rɛnɪɡed]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=renegade', '{n.}++叛教者**++脱党者，变节者，叛徒**{adj.}++叛教的；背叛的；变节的；不忠诚的**{vi.}++叛教；背叛；变节**', '++But the stance of aggressive unoriginality is still evident in The Proletarian Revolution and the Renegade Kautsky, written in late 1918.**++但是在引 用时咄咄逼人的姿态仍然可以在1918年的《无产阶级革命与叛徒考茨基》中清晰可见。**++"Although it is primarily to deal with renegade aircraft, there is nothing to prevent it being used in search and rescue/emergency situations, too," he added.**++他补充说，“虽然它主要是处理叛徒的飞机，但是没有什么可以阻止它也会被用于搜索和救援/紧急情况下。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2323', 'renege', '[rɪniɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=renege', '{vi.}++食言，背信；违约(与 on 连用)：**++【牌戏】(手里有牌却)违例不跟**{vt.}++[古语]否认；拒绝；放弃**{n.}++【牌戏】违例不跟**', '++What@s more, you could damage the relationship you have with a recruiter if he or she believes you and you later renege on your promises.**++而且, 如果猎头相信了你、而事后你却食言的话, 你跟对方的关系也就毁于一旦了。**++The trading system will have much more trouble if the United States starts to renege on its traditional leadership role.**++但如果美国背弃了原来自由贸易领导者的形象，世界贸易体系将会遇到更大的困难。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2324', 'renounce', '[rɪnaʊns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=renounce', '{vt.}++宣布放弃(要求、权力、信仰等)；抛弃；摈弃：**++中止；退出：**++与…断绝关系；拒绝承认：**++【牌戏】垫牌**{vi.}++【法律】放弃权利(或财产等)**++【牌戏】垫牌**{n.}++【牌戏】垫牌**', '++In support of Western policy aimed at bolstering Fatah and at forcing Hamas to recognise Israel and renounce violence, Egypt has joined with Israel to enforce its blockade on Gaza.**++西方的计划是支持法塔赫，迫使哈马斯承认以色列和宣布放弃暴力对抗行动，埃及为支持西方的这项政策 而加入到以色列对加沙的封锁行动中。**++For this, we never renounce the use of force, as it is common aspiration and sacred mission of the people of China to safeguard China’s sovereignty and also to reunify our motherland.**++为此，我们不承诺放弃使用武力。 维护中国主权和领土完整，实现祖国的完全统一是全体中国人民的共同愿望和神圣使命。**++People say: for us to believe in you, you must renounce everything that is yours and also yourself.**++人们说：要我们去相信你，你必须抛弃一切，你所有的一切，也包括你自己。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2325', 'renovate', '[rɛnəvet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=renovate', '{vt.}++革新；更新：**++整修；翻修；修理：**++使恢复精力；使振作：**', '++Your responsibility it to confess it. Let it renovate your life.**++你的职责是宣告这些，并且让它们更新你的生命。**++The report described, in detail, apparent North Korean moves to renovate a missile testing site on its east coast.**++报道详细描述了北韩有试图修复其东岸一个导弹试验基地的明显动向。**++They are going to renovate the old furniture.**++他们准备将旧家具整修一番。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2326', 'repartee', '[,rɛpəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repartee', '{n.}++机敏的回答；妙语**++巧辩；机智的反驳**++机敏应答的能力；辩才**', '++But you always get a smile and some witty repartee from him that provides an uplift.**++但柏利总是笑容可掬，妙语如珠，让你精神一振。**++Two of the biggest laughs I get in my performances come from my imitation of a bit of child repartee.**++在我的演出中，令人两次开怀的大笑是源于我模仿一点孩子们的机敏应答。**++Casablanca’s Oscar-winning screenplay, penned by Julius Epstein, Philip Epstein and Howard Koch, offered up unmatched repartee and some of the most memorable lines in movie history.**++这一赢得奥斯卡奖的剧本由朱利叶斯-爱泼斯坦、菲利普-爱泼斯坦与霍华德-科克编写。 该剧本为电影史贡献了无与伦比的机智妙语答复和一些最让人难以忘怀的言辞。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2327', 'repatriate', '[,ripetrɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repatriate', '{vt.,vi.}', '++China could, of course, repatriate all the dollars its exporters earn by selling stuff to the U.S.**++当然，中国可以将出口商们通过将商品挣来的美元都遣返回美国。**++So maybe it@s time to "repatriate" those industries that were off-shored years ago, along with their jobs.**++因此，把那些几年前出境的产业，连同与它们一起出境的就业岗位“遣返回国”，也许需要时间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2328', 'repeal', '[rɪpil]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repeal', '{vt.}++撤销；废止：**++[废语](从流放地)召回**++放弃；拒绝承认**{n.}++撤销；废除**++[废语]召回**', '++In some states, the centralization of districts into towns went through waves of passage and repeal.**++而在有些州，将区并入城镇的努力也经历了通过与废除相互交织的多舛命运。**++Therefore, he said, a committee of top officials would work to repeal the report and minimize "the great damage" it has done to the state of Israel.**++所以他说，一个由高级官员组成的委员会将致力于撤销这份报告，并将它已经对以色列造成的“极大伤害”降低到最小。**++Mr. Frank’s name did come up repeatedly as a villain in the crisis, and not just in the context of the Dodd-Frank financial reform bill, which Republicans want to repeal.**++在这次危机之中，弗兰克先生的名字作为恶人的确反复出现，不光是在共和党人要废除的多德-弗兰克金融改革法案的背景下出现。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2329', 'repel', '[rɪpɛl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repel', '{vt.}++击退；抵挡住；驱除：**++拒绝；排斥：**++不接待；不理睬：**++使厌恶；使反感；使(昆虫等)不敢接近：**++抗；防：**{vi.}++抵制；排斥：**++引起反感：**', '++In an attempt to disgust and repel these vile oppressors, I once again induced myself to vomit on their favourite chair ...**++为了恶心并击退这些可恶的统治者们，我又在他们最喜欢的椅子上吐了个一塌糊涂......**++Why This Works: Many plants – including the ones listed – give off a strong scent to repel ants and other insects in the wild, and it works just as well in your home.**++为何如此：许多的植物——包括我上面列的单子——可以发出强烈的令蚂蚁和其它野外的昆虫害怕的气味，这样可以击退它们，不过对你的家庭却无害。**++This would have brought the largely lawless areas near Afghanistan into mainstream society or helped them see it as in their interest to repel militants.**++本来这些会有助于阿富汗附近基本上无法无天的地区融入主流社会，或者帮助他们发现抵制武装分子是符合他们的利益的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2330', 'repertoire', '[rɛpɚtwɑr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repertoire', '{n.}++(已准备好可随时演出的)节目(或剧目)；保留节目(或剧目)**++(某剧作家、作曲家创作的可供演出的)全部节目(或剧目)**++[美国英语](某个人的)全部技能；(某个领域的)所有组成部分**++【计算机】指令表，指令集合，指令系统[亦作 répertoire]**{n.}', '++We increase the number of tools in our repertoire so that when we need that special tool or technique, we are well-prepared to use it.**++我们不断地增加清单中的工具数量，使得当我们需要某种特定工具的时候，我们已经为使用它做好了准备。**++These simple yet powerful ideas are key to effective SOA design, and you now have these conceptual tools in your repertoire of skills...**++这些简单但强力的概念是有效的SOA设计的关键，现在你的技能库中已经有了这些概念工具……**++This SSL repertoire defines the location of the key file and trust file that will be used by these transport chains, when establishing SSL connections with clients or servers.**++此 SSL 配置表定义密钥文件和信任文件的位置，这些传输链将在与客户端或服务器建立 SSL 连接时使用这两个文件。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2331', 'repine', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repine', '{vi.}++不满；烦恼；抱怨(常与 at，against 连用)：**++渴望，向往(常与 for 连用)：**', '++I thank living before love ,it broght me repine ;**++爱情之前我感谢生活,它给我向往;**++This is the common fate of mortal men, useless it is to repine .**++这是凡人的共同命运，抱怨也没有用。**++But the wife of Mr. Darcy must have such extraordinary sources of happiness necessarily attached to her situation, that she could, upon the whole, have no cause to repine.**++可是做了达西先生的太太必然会享受到莫大的幸福，因此，归根结底，完全用不到懊丧。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2332', 'replenish', '[rɪplɛnɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=replenish', '{vt.}++重新装满；补充：**++添加(燃料等)：**++使住满人**++补偿；替代：**++充注精力：**{vi.}++充满；被装满：**++充满；被装满：**', '++Replenish your army with fresh troops before you make each move.**++你的军队与军队补充新鲜,先让每一个行动。**++Your body is in survival mode and needs food to replenish its energy.**++你的身体是在生存模式和需要食物来补充能量。**++These findings raise questions regarding whether the brain, after being taxed, attempts to replenish its energy (glucose) through urging the body to eat more.**++这些调查结果引发这样的问题，就是关于大脑活动后是否通过敦促身体吃得更多以补充能量（葡萄糖）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2333', 'replete', '[rɪplit]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=replete', '{adj.}++饱满的；供应充分的**++塞饱(肚子)的；酒足饭饱的**++充实的；完备的**++肥胖的**', '++But financial history is replete with bubbles and crashes.**++但金融的历史是充满泡沫和危机的。**++We can assume that this was a slow process replete with lots of hard focus.**++我们可以想象到这是一个缓慢的过程并充满了大量的硬焦点。**++For instance, a 15-minute short that has a cast of 500 actors, multiple costume changes and expensive sets replete with explosions and natural disasters isn@t likely to attract any buyers.**++举个例子，假如一部15分钟的短剧用到了500名演员，多次更换服装，并且充满了昂贵的爆炸和天灾场面，那它是很难吸引到制片人的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2334', 'replicate', '[rɛplɪket]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=replicate', '{adj.}++【植物学】(叶)反叠的**++反折的；折转的**++复制的**++复现的**{n.}++复制品**++【统计学】同样的实验(或样品)**++【音乐】高(或低)八度音**{vt.}++折转；弯回；反叠：**++重复；复制：**++[罕用语]回答；答复**{vi.}++折转；反叠**++复制，重复；自我复制：**', '++We should learn from these rather than replicate them.**++我们应该从这些错误中吸取教训，而非重复它们。**++Nothing has the capacity to replicate itself except DNA.**++除DNA外，什么东西也没有自我复制的能力。**++Then you go and try and replicate that finding in another population.**++然后你试试在另一人群中复制那个发现。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2335', 'repose', '[rɪpoz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repose', '{vi.}++躺着休息：**++休养：**++长眠，安息：**++静卧；蕴藏：**++安放在；坐落在：**++[古语]相信(常与 in 连用)；信赖；取决于…；建立于…之上(常与on或upon连用)：**++(记忆等)萦绕；停留(常与on连用)：**{vt.}++[repose oneself]使休息;使依靠：**++[repose oneself]使休息;使依靠：**{n.}++躺卧**++休息；睡眠**++长眠；长眠处**++(心绪)宁静；安详，泰然自若；(举止)镇静**++平静；静止；宁静**++(绘画等结构、色彩的)和谐；恬静**{vt.}++把(信任等)寄托在…：**++(把权力等)交…控制：**++[罕用语]放；置**', '++Near the Azores, just below the sunlit Atlantic surface, sperm whales float in vertical repose.**++在亚速尔群岛附近，大西洋表面太阳照射不到的地方，抹香鲸垂直着身体休息。**++It is but just to add that he had forgotten to include in his calculations the forced repose of Sundays and festival days during nineteen years, which entailed a diminution of about eighty francs.**++还应当指出，十九年中，礼拜日和节日的强迫休息大致要使他少赚二十四个法郎，他还忘了把那个数目加入他的账目。**++After the work is done, repose is sweet.**++工作到完毕，休息感甜蜜。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2336', 'reprehend', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reprehend', '{vt.}', '++For if our heart reprehend us, God is greater than our heart, and knoweth all things.**++纵然我们的心责备我们，我们还可以安心，因为天主比我们的心大，他原知道一切。**++Peter should withdraw and that St. Paul should publicly reprehend him, for the instruction of all.**++他们一致认为，应撤销圣彼得和圣保罗应当公开申斥他的指示所有。**++And they could not reprehend his word before the people: and wondering at his answer, they held their peace.**++他们在民众面前，不能抓到他的语病，且惊奇他的应对，遂噤口不言。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2337', 'repress', '[rɪprɛs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repress', '{vt.}++抑制；忍住：**++镇压；制止：**++约束；限制：**++【精神病学】压抑；把(痛苦的想法、冲动等)压到潜意识；防止(潜意识的冲动等)达到意识水平【参较 suppress】**++【生物化学】使(基因等)受阻遏，约束**{vi.}++镇压；抑制**++【精神病学】经受压抑**', '++So the police must repress these freedoms.**++因此，警察必须镇压这些自由。**++However, because they don’t have the emotional tools to integrate the hurt caused by abusive adults, they often repress their feelings as their first line of defence.**++但是，实际上他们并不具备情绪调节的能力，可以去平复成年人对其虐待造成的伤害，他们抑制自己的情感，作为第一道防线。**++These hostilities against an abstract noun were used not only to fight abroad but also to repress at home.**++对一个抽象名词的战争不仅用来在国外打仗也用来镇压国内。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2338', 'reprieve', '[rɪpriv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reprieve', '{vt.}++缓刑(尤指缓期执行死刑)：**++暂减(痛苦、烦恼等)；暂时缓解：**{n.}++(尤指死刑的)缓刑**++缓刑令**++(痛苦、烦恼等的)缓解，暂缓**', '++Officials say that in the first half of this year it overturned 15% of death sentences. But police-killers are unlikely candidates for reprieve.**++官方人员表示，今年上半年中国已经推翻了15%的死刑判决，但这个杀害警察的凶手不太可能获得缓刑。**++Iran@s judiciary could reinstate her sentence of death by stoning, execute her by another means, or possibly even grant her a reprieve, according to human rights groups.**++根据人权组织的报道，伊朗司法的机构，以后可以恢复用石头砸死她的判决，也可以用另一种形式来执行死刑，或者，甚至可能给予她缓刑。**++As far as wild animals and plants on the edge of extinction goes, we may not entirely believe in a reprieve but it would be inhuman of us not to try for one.**++在野生动植物走向灭绝的今天，我们可能不会完全相信暂时的解救措施，但是如果我们不进行尝试的话，那就是不人道。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2339', 'reproach', '[rɪprotʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reproach', '{vt.}++责备；斥责；指摘(常与 for连用)：**++污辱；有辱…的名誉；使…丢脸：**{vi.}++指摘别人；怨天尤人**{n.}++责备；指摘**++责备的话，谴责之词**++耻辱；不名誉**++[废语]受责备的对象**++[the Reproaches,亦称作 Improperia]【天主教】(耶稣受难日礼仪时唱的)谴责曲**', '++...**++...**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2340', 'reprobate', '[rɛprəbet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reprobate', '{vi.}++谴责；斥责；非难：**++拒绝：**++【神学】(上帝)摈弃；注定…永世不得翻身**{adj.}++堕落的；放荡的；道德败坏的；罪恶深重的**++【神学】为上帝摈弃的；永世不能翻身的**{n.}++堕落者；放荡者；道德败坏的人；恶棍**++【神学】为上帝摈弃的人**', '++were likely to touch even such a hardened little reprobate as Becky.**++连蓓基这样一个铁石心肠的小无赖都感动了。**++Now as Jannes and Jambres withstood Moses, so do these also resist the truth: men of corrupt minds, reprobate concerning the faith.**++从前雅尼和佯庇怎样敌挡摩西，这等人也怎样敌挡真道。 他们的心地坏了，在真道上是可废弃的。**++Surely His pleading with the lost, His offers of mercy to the reprobate, and the call of the gospel to all who hear are all sincere expressions of the heart of a loving God.**++他对迷失方向的的人的恳求，他对堕落的人的同情，他对所有听到他声音的人施与福音，这一切真挚的表达都源于他充满爱的心。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2341', 'reproof', '[rɪpruf]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reproof', '{n.}++谴责；斥责；责备**++责备之词**{vt.}++【印刷】重新打样**++重新做防水处理**', '++Whoso loveth instruction loveth knowledge: but he that hateth reproof is brutish.**++喜爱管教的，就是喜爱知识。 恨恶责备的，却是畜类。**++Mrs Chick contented herself with a glance of reproof, and then proceeded with the thread of her discourse.**++奇克夫人责备地看了他一眼，也就罢了，然后接着刚才的话头，继续说下去。**++For, though your accusations were ill-founded, formed on mistaken premises, my behaviour to you at the time had merited the severest reproof.**++虽然你的指斥都没有根据，都是听到人家以讹传讹,可是我那次对你的态度，实在应该受到最严厉的责备。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2342', 'reprove', '[rɪpruv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reprove', '{vt.}++谴责；责备；指摘：**++[废语]驳斥，反驳**{vi.}++谴责；斥责**', '++He will surely reprove you, if ye do secretly accept persons.**++你们若暗中徇情，他必要责备你们。**++Yet let no man strive, nor reprove another: for thy people are as they that strive with the priest.**++然而，人都不必争辩，也不必指责，因为这民与抗拒祭司的人一样。**++Smite a scorner, and the simple will beware: and reprove one that hath understanding, and he will understand knowledge.**++鞭打亵慢人，愚蒙人必长见识。 责备明哲人，他就明白知识。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2343', 'repudiate', '[rɪpjudɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repudiate', '{vt.}++声明与…断绝关系:**++拒绝接受；拒不履行；否认…的权威(或效力等)；放弃：**++否定；不承认；驳斥：**++(尤指政府)拒付(公债、债款等)：**', '++Henry then appealed to Pope Alexander IV for dispensation to repudiate both provisions.**++后来，亨利向教皇亚历山大请求在法律上否定这两个条款。**++The implication was clear: he will repudiate and reverse security measures that many have criticized as breaches of our constitution and of the rule of law.**++言外之意很清楚：他会否定和重新制定国家安全措施，因为这些措施被许多人批评为违背了我们的宪法和法律。**++The rise of urban lit does not repudiate the black literary past, but it does suggest other ways and means of producing black literature and other ends for it as well.**++贫民区文学的兴起并不否定过去的黑人文学，而是建议用其他办法来造就黑人文学并达到其他目的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2344', 'repugnant', '[rɪpʌɡnənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repugnant', '{adj.}++矛盾的；不一致的；不相容的**++对抗性的，敌对的；相斥的**++令人厌恶的，使人反感的**', '++Furthermore, the whole concept of a minority (politicians) banning things for the majority is repugnant.**++另外，少数人（指一些政客）代替绝大多数人对一些东西发布禁令这个现象本来就是矛盾的。**++I have never beaten my wife and never will. I find assault of others completely repugnant, and assault of women especially so.**++我从没有也永远不会打我的妻子，我认为殴打他人的人非常令人反感，尤其是打女人。**++Of course the idea of the U.S. government "owning" every single asset of the American people is repugnant to our entire way of life, but let@s assume that for a moment.**++当然美国政府“拥有”美国人民的每一份财产的这个想法是让人恶心的，与我们整个的生活方式完全相反，不过让我们假设一下那种情况。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2345', 'repulse', '[rɪpʌls]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repulse', '{vt.}++击退；挫败；赶走：**++断然拒绝；(以冷淡、无礼等)排斥：**++憎恶；使产生反感：**{n.}++击退；赶走**++断然拒绝**', '++The enemy met with a repulse.**++敌人被击退了。**++Would you like John or Mary to go with you to Repulse Bay?**++你喜欢约翰或玛丽陪你去浅水湾还是你自己一个人去？**++If they are happy to have their audience shed hankies, they rarely if ever go so far as to repulse them with the more realistic connotations of divorce, ostracism or the loss of a loved one.**++如果情景剧导演们乐于看见观众们为他们的电影而泪流满面的话，他们就不会拿离婚，被人嫌弃抑或是痛失爱人诸如此类生活的、写实的一地鸡毛来恶心观众。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2346', 'repute', '[rɪpjut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=repute', '{vt.}++[常用被动语态]被认为；被称为：**++[常用被动语态]被认为；被称为：**{n.}++名声，名气**++荣誉；信誉**', '++The wine is in high repute worldwide.**++这酒在世界上享有盛名。**++A man of spiritual repute came to the Master and said, "I cannot pray, I cannot understand the Scriptures, I cannot do the exercises that I prescribe to others.**++一个在教会声望显赫的人来找大师并对他说 "我不会祈祷 我不懂圣经 我做不了我要求别人做的事情.**++In the past, red dyes were expensive, so red walls and fabrics suggested luxurious wealth, importance or ill repute.**++过去，红色染料都很昂贵，因此，红色的墙和织物意味着奢华、财富、重要性和坏名声。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2347', 'requisite', '[rɛkwəzɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=requisite', '{adj.}++需要的；必需的，必不可少的**{n.}++必需品**', '++"We must recognise the fact that adequate food is only the first requisite for life, " he said in his Nobel speech.**++他在诺贝尔奖的演说中说到：“我们必须得认识到这样一个事实，充足的食物只是人类生存的首要必需品。”**++It@s just a matter of determining the algorithm for instance launching, and making sure that new instances have all requisite dependencies installed.**++这只是一个关于为实例装载选择算法，并确保新的实例已有所有需要安装的依赖文件的问题。**++As a data modeler or a data architect, you may need to work not only with a data modeling tool, but also with version control tools, requisite tools, and multiple data models.**++作为一名数据建模师或数据架构师，不仅需要使用数据建模工具，还需要使用版本控制工具、一些必备工具和多个数据模型。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2348', 'requite', '[rɪkwaɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=requite', '{vt.}++报答；回报：**++酬答(某人)；向(某人)报复 ：**++清偿；满足：**++[罕用语]回赠**', '++We shall requite him for his insults.**++对于他的侮辱我们将进行报复。**++I thank you, and can but requite your good deeds with my prayers.**++我感激你，只有用我的祈祷来报答你的善行。**++But thou, O LORD, be merciful unto me, and raise me up, that I may requite them.**++耶和华阿，求你怜恤我，使我起来，好报复他们。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2349', 'rescind', '[rɪsɪnd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rescind', '{vi.}++废除；取消：**++撤回；撤销：**', '++So, sorry, creepy guys of New York (and beyond)—I think the libraries need to rescind this invitation.**++所以，很遗憾，纽约的风流小伙子们，恐怕这些图书馆要废除他们之前的这份“邀请”了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2350', 'reserved', '[rɪzɝvd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reserved', '{vt.}++reserve的变形**{adj.}++保留的；预订的**++储备的；留作专用的**++克制的，节制的**++拘谨的；缄默的；含蓄的**++【军事】后备的**{vt.}++储备；保存；留出:**++预订:**++推迟；留到以后：**++保留；留给:**{vi.}++预订；定座**{n.}++储备(物)；保存(物)**++[常作复数](矿物等的)藏量，储量**++[美国英语]专用地；禁猎区，自然保护区**++保留；保留条件**++[常作复数]【军事】后备军，预备役军人；后备部队**++【体育】预备队员，候补队员**++【金融业】(银行等的)储备金**++拘谨；沉默寡言**++(作品的)严肃；严谨；含蓄**++最低拍卖价格，保留价**{adj.}++保留的；有保留的**++后备的；预备的**++储备的；备用的**', '++But they are mostly reserved for the animals.**++但是它们主要是为了动物保留下来的。**++We have reserved seat 42A on flight 322 to New York with a chicken dinner for you. Can I help you with anything else?**++好的，我们为您预订了飞往纽约，航班为322，座位是42A及鸡肉晚餐，还有其他需要我为您服务的吗？**++If you need to have a particular room, and another person already has it reserved, you can easily get in touch with them and try to arrange a room swap.**++如果您需要拥有某特定房间，而其他人已预订了该房间，那么您可以很容易地与他们取得联系并设法安排一次房间交换。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2351', 'residual', '[rɪzɪdʒuəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=residual', '{adj.}++剩余的；残留的**++有后效的**++【地质学】残余的**++【数学】剩余的**{n.}++残余(物)；残渣**++[常作复数](疾病、手术等的)后遗症**++【地质学】剩余异常**++【地质学】残丘**++【数学】剩余**++[常作复数][美国英语](电视广告片、电视片)复播复映追加酬金，重演版权费(电视片等每次重映时给演员和作者的报酬)**', '++One of the best tools we have against malaria is indoor residual house spraying.**++我们拥有的抗击疟疾的最佳手段之一是室内残留喷洒。**++This will clear any residual notes that are still processing, even if they have faded to an inaudible volume level.**++这将清除仍在处理的所有剩余通知，即使它们已经减弱为听不见的音量级别。**++These, however, have been exposed to the digestive mercies of bacteria in the large intestine, and any residual goodies have been removed from them that way.**++然而这些是被暴露到大肠消化道寄生细菌产生的结果，并且任何剩余糖分都是通过这种方式被移除的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2352', 'residue', '[rɛzɪdu]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=residue', '{n.}++剩余物；残渣**++【化学】渣；沉淀物；残基**++【数学】余数，残数；余项**++【法律】剩余遗产**', '++The essence of pearl mixed with essence of men and a curious dark residue was precipitated.**++珍珠的价值与人的本质混淆在了一起，促成了一种奇怪的黑色残渣。**++Non-organic apples, strawberries, potatoes, and spinach have high levels of pesticide residue, even after washing.**++非有机的苹果、草莓、土豆和菠菜甚至在洗后也会残留很多杀虫剂残渣。**++This releases a mixture of hydrogen and carbon monoxide, known as syngas, and leaves a residue of amorphous elemental carbon called carbon black.**++这一过程产生氢气和一氧化碳的混合物，也叫做合成气，剩余的是无定形的基本碳，也叫做炭黑。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2353', 'resign', '[rɪzaɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resign', '{vt.}++放弃(要求等)；让出(工作任务等)：**++辞去(职务等)：**++把…委托给(常与to连用)：**++[resign oneself]使顺从；使听任(摆布)；使甘心(忍受)(常与to连用)：**{vi.}++辞职；退出(常与from连用)：**++听任；顺从(常与to连用)：**++投降**++【象棋】认输**', '++It is said he would resign.**++人们都传说他要辞职了。**++He@s going to resign. ——So I hear.**++他打算要辞职。——我也听说了。**++All the employees resign because the employer is too unreasonable.**++因为老板太不讲理，雇员全体辞职。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2354', 'resilience', '[rɪzɪliəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resilience', '{n.}++弹力；弹性**++回弹能力；(体力或精神等的)恢复能力；顺应力；应变力；复原力；适应力；乐观的性格，达观[亦作resiliency]**', '++How do you instill pride and resilience in her?**++你怎样逐步帮她树立自豪感和适应能力呢？**++They like being around other people more, they have more sex per month, and they have more resilience to adverse events.**++她们更喜欢有人陪伴，每月有更多的性生活，并且对不良事件的回复能力更强。**++Similarly, with happiness, I get an abundance of confidence in my skills and in my resilience towards temporary failures to achieve success.**++同样地，拥有幸福，我从我的技能和对暂时失败的恢复力中得到了许多自信来实现成功。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2355', 'resolute', '[rɛzəlut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resolute', '{adj.}', '++We express strong dissatisfaction and resolute opposition to that.**++中方对此表示强烈不满和坚决反对。**++This is why Chinese leaders have been so resolute in their drive to lock up supplies of raw materials and other key commodities.**++这就是为什么中国领导人一直如此坚决的推动把目标锁定在原材料和其他关键商品的供应上的原因。**++China expresses strong dissatisfaction and resolute opposition to it.**++中方对此表示强烈不满和坚决反对。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2356', 'resonant', '[rɛznənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resonant', '{adj.}++回响的；反响的**++引起回响的；产生共鸣的**++由共鸣加强的；洪亮的**++共振的，谐振的；共鸣的**', '++From this, they can determine the lowest resonant frequencies.**++据此，他们就可以确定最低的共振频率。**++Meditators will find their resonant frequency naturally through trial and error, so we know that there@s something in that.**++冥想者会通过考验和错误而自然地找到他们的共振频率，我们知道其中有些原因。**++Every piece of glass has a natural resonant frequency—the speed at which it will vibrate if bumped or otherwise disturbed by some stimulus, such as a sound wave—as does every other material on Earth.**++每片玻璃都有一个自然的共鸣频率——在此速度下，如果受到碰撞或者由某种刺激物打扰，它就会震动，如声波——地球上其他物质也是如此。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2357', 'resourceful', '[rɪsɔrsfl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resourceful', '{adj.}++资源丰富的；财力充裕的**++机智的；足智多谋的；善于随机应变的**', '++Our enemies are innovative and resourceful, and so are we.**++我们的敌人具有创新性，足智多谋，我们也是。**++As most of them are far more resourceful than me, I@m once again relying on the kindness of strangers to help me out.**++他们大多数人要比我足智多谋，我又一次依靠陌生人的善意帮助来走出困境。**++As a structure and engineering achievement, the aircraft encloses a lot of space using the least amount of materials in a very resourceful and efficient manner.**++作为一个建筑学和工程学的巨大成就，飞机使用一种机智而高效的方式消耗少量的原材料包含住了大量的空间。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2358', 'respire', '[rɪspaɪɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=respire', '{vi.}++呼吸**++松口气**{vt.}++呼吸**++呼(气)；呼出**', '++Like other fruit bananas remain alive after being picked and they actually continue to respire.**++和其它水果一样，采摘之后香蕉还是活的，它们还能继续呼吸。**++He also discovered that plants respire in the same way as animals, taking up oxygen and giving out carbon dioxide.**++另外，他还发现了植物拥有和动物相同的呼吸方式，即吸收氧气并释放出二氧化碳。**++Some products, such as asparagus, corn, and strawberries, respire at a higher rate than other products, such as apples, oranges, and potatoes.**++一些农产品，比如芦笋、玉米和草莓，与其它农产品（如苹果、桔子和马铃薯）相比，其呼吸速率较大。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2359', 'respite', '[rɛspɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=respite', '{n.}++暂缓；展延(尤指死刑的缓期执行)**++暂时的休息；喘息时间，缓解**{vt.}++使延期；使暂缓；缓期执行：**++使暂息；使缓解；暂停：**', '++But if the laws were repealed tomorrow, most of the nations of the world would make no move to take advantage of the respite, and any that did would be in danger of finding their credit vanishing.**++但如果明天法律被废止，大部分国家可能不会利用这一暂缓期采取任何行动。 如果有国家贸然行事，可能会将自己置身于丧失信贷的危机中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2360', 'resplendent', '[rɪsplɛndənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resplendent', '{adj.}', '++Dad was resplendent in dark blue pants and a white short-sleeved shirt, providing a quiet background for Mom’s flamboyance. We all piled into the car.**++爸爸穿的身份华丽，一条深蓝色的裤子和白色的短袖衬衫，很好的映衬了妈妈的艳丽。**++Dressed in a white suit over a wide-lapel shirt, his hand poised on his breast, he stands a head above his classmates, and not just because of his resplendent afro.**++他穿着一套白色西装和一件大翻领衬衫，手在胸前摆了个姿势，他站着要比其他同学高出一个头，不过当然并不只是因为他那个华丽的爆炸头。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2361', 'responsive', '[rɪspɑnsɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=responsive', '{adj.}++应答的；表示回答的**++易受感动的；易起反应的；敏感的**++(做礼拜时)用应答歌的**', '++IT teams seem to work harder and harder, but their responsive to business deteriorates day by day.**++IT 团队似乎工作得越来越努力，但它们对业务的响应能力却在一天天降低。**++How does the solution guarantee that it includes all new and back versions of a policy, and can it operate in distributed and responsive environments?**++解决方案如何保证它包括所有新的及以前的策略版本，并且它能在发布及响应环境中进行操作么？**++As you can imagine, these systems are not very responsive to change, whether you wrap them in a new services layer or not.**++正如你能想象的，无论你是否用一个新的服务层包装，这些系统对变化的响应能力比较差。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2362', 'restitution', '[rɛstətʊʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=restitution', '{n.}++归还；偿还**++补偿；赔偿**++恢复原状；回复原位**++【物理学】(弹性体的)复原**', '++He believed at that moment that he had a grave duty to perform: the restitution of the six hundred thousand francs to some one whom he sought with all possible discretion.**++他认为，此刻他有一件重要的任务要完成，这就是把这六十万法郎归还他在尽量审慎地寻找的原主。**++Those notices disturb Amy when they arrive, but Mr. Marsh, looking at the same pieces of paper, saw an opportunity: he could intervene in the federal prosecutions and demand restitution.**++这些通知打乱了艾米的正常生活，但是玛希先生却在这些通知中发现了机会。 他可以据此介入联邦起诉并要求赔偿。**++He was sentenced to time served, probation, community service, and ordered to make restitution and undergo counseling.**++凯文最终被判入狱，缓期执行，他需服务社区，归还窃款并接受心理辅导。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2363', 'restive', '[rɛstɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=restive', '{adj.}++烦躁的；不耐烦的；动乱不安的**++倔强的；难驾驭的；难控制的**++(马等)不肯前进的，逡巡不前的**', '++For this reason the restive youth of China and Oman are different from those of north Africa.**++基于这个理由，中国及阿曼那些躁动不安的年轻人与北非的年轻人截然不同。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2364', 'restless', '[rɛstləs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=restless', '{adj.}++烦躁不安的；焦虑的**++受骚扰的；得不到休息的**++不安静的；不安宁的；静不下来的**++好动的；多变的；永不满足的**', '++The mind of most people is very restless.**++大多数人的思想都是焦躁不安的。**++I stood in restless anticipation, wondering what sort of new game he was about to teach us.**++我焦虑不安地站在那儿，满怀期待，想知道他将要教我们什么样的新游戏。**++When he says to himself, this is the work of my countrymen, who, when convulsed by factions, afflicted by a variety of miseries and wants, restless and impatient, took refuge here.**++这时他对自己说这是我的同胞们干的，他们是在受派别骚扰，为各种不幸和贫困感到痛苦，并且烦躁不安时，来到这里避难的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2365', 'restrain', '[rɪstren]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=restrain', '{vt.}++抑制，遏制；克制；控制:**++约束；限制 ；阻止(常与of，from 连用)：**++监禁；拘留，扣押:**', '++They couldn@t restrain their excitement.**++他们无法抑制自己的激动。**++She was so angry that she could hardly restrain herself.**++她气得几乎控制不了自己。**++Individuals restrain themselves all the time; why can@t we do it collectively?**++每个人都在时时约束自己，为什么我们不能集体约束自己？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2366', 'resurgence', '[rɪsɝdʒəns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resurgence', '{n.}++复活；复苏**++再次的波动**++【地质学】复流；再现**', '++For decades countries around Asia have been wary of China’s resurgence — tracking how many ships and missiles it was acquiring, and how it was using its influence as an investor.**++几十年来，亚洲国家一直对中国的东山再起保持警惕：密切关注它有多少船只多少导弹，关注它如何像投资商一样运用自己的影响力。**++My Bostonian bug turned out to be one of many on the forefront of an unprecedented resurgence.**++我的这只来自波士顿的臭虫被证明是前所未有的复苏的众多臭虫中的一只。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2367', 'resurrect', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resurrect', '{vt.}++【神学】使复活；使复苏：**++使恢复应用；使重新流行；重新唤起对…的记忆：**++【地质学】使(断层等)复露**{vi.}++【神学】复活；复苏：**++【神学】复活；复苏：**', '++So God will resurrect the dead.**++那么上帝将复活死者。**++Can we ever hope to use avatars to resurrect the dead?**++我们到底希不希望用化身来从死亡中复活？**++Most of those embedded viruses are now extinct, but in 2005 French researchers applied for permission to resurrect one of them.**++嵌入病毒的大多数已经灭绝，但2005年法国的研究人员申请许可去复活其中的一种。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2368', 'resuscitate', '[rɪsʌsɪtet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=resuscitate', '{vt.}++使复活；使复苏：**++使恢复；使复兴：**{vi.}++复活；复苏**++恢复；复兴**', '++Encouraged by falling inflation, central banks are cutting interest rates, and policy makers are implementing big stimulus plans to resuscitate economic growth.**++受通胀回落激励,各大央行纷纷降息,决策者亦开始实施大型激励计划,以恢复经济增长.**++His personal physician who was with him at the time attempted to resuscitate my brother, as did the paramedics who transported him to Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Centre.**++当时在场的我弟弟的私人医生和将他送到加州大学洛杉矶分校罗纳德·里根医疗中心的医护人员都曾试图帮助他恢复知觉。**++Returning from making phone calls to find his patient not breathing, he told police he tried to resuscitate him and one of Jackon@s staff called for an ambulance.**++在他打完电话回去后，穆雷医生发现杰克逊已经没有了呼吸，他告诉警方当时他试图给他做心肺复苏，同时杰克逊的一个职员叫了救护车。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2369', 'retainer', '[rɪtenɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retainer', '{n.}++保持者；保留者；保留物**++家臣，侍从；仆人；雇员**++[亦作cage，separator]【机械学】制动装置(如护圈，挡板，滚动轴承的保持架等)**++【牙科学】固位器**{n.}++保留职务**++【法律】(律师、顾问等的)聘定；聘请定金**', '++And the company@s advertising agency, which receives shares in addition to a small monthly cash retainer, has a stake in finding the best way to deliver Purple@s message.**++公司的广告代理商也是一样，除每月拿到少量现金薪酬外都是用股票来答谢，却足以让代理商绞尽脑汁地为‘紫饮’做最好的广告。**++Hire a good business attorney: You don@t necessarily need to have an attorney on a retainer, but you@ll want to hire an attorney experienced with new businesses to help you get started.**++雇佣一个优秀的公司律师： 你没有必要付给律师聘用定金，但是你将需要雇佣一个有相关经验的律师来帮助你的公司起步。**++Suppose you’re negotiating an assignment with one of your clients, who typically pays a retainer for your services.**++假设你正在和一个客户谈判转让事宜，而按惯例她是先预付服务费的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2370', 'retaliate', '[rɪtælɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retaliate', '{vi.}++报复；回敬；以牙还牙：**++报复；回敬；以牙还牙：**{vt.}++回报；为…进行报复：**++回报；为…进行报复：**', '++If we raise our import duties on their goods,they may retaliate against us.**++如果我们提高他们的货物的进口税，他们可能要对我们进行报复。**++As in, “if you come after us (or our partners) Microsoft, just remember that we can now retaliate”.**++如，“如果你跟在我们（或我们的合伙人）微软后面，记得我们现在就可以进行报复”。**++Unbridled freedom of expression that ignites and insult sentiments of others incites people to fiercely retaliate in the name of protecting their faiths and ideologies.**++表达自由激烈的呼声点燃了不满的情感，并煽动人们以保护信仰和意识形态的名义进行猛烈的报复行动。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2371', 'retard', '[rɪtɑrd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retard', '{vt.}++使减速，使放慢；阻碍；阻止：**++延迟；推迟：**{vi.}++减速；受阻碍；延迟**{n.}++减速；阻碍；延迟；耽误**++／ri:tɑ:d／ [美国俚语]弱智者，智力迟钝者；呆子**', '++And I make a  solemn  oath to myself that nothing will retard my new life@s growth.**++我郑重地发誓，绝不让任何事情妨碍我新生命的成长。**++Will a bigger, longer, and presumably bloodier occupation advance or retard the ultimate aim of discouraging Islamist terrorism?**++一种更大规模、更持久，或许会产生更多流血事件的进军，对挫败伊斯兰恐怖主义的最终目标会起推进作用，还是造成妨碍呢？**++But that is the right question to ask, not whether we should retard its development with complex regulations, or still worse, relinquish it.**++其实这才是要解决的关键问题，而非我们是否应该通过复杂的规章来限制发展，或更糟糕地，干脆放弃。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2372', 'retentive', '[rɪtɛntɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retentive', '{adj.}++保持的；保留的**++有保持力的**++记忆力强的；能记住的**++【医学】用以固位的**++沉默的**', '++Pale ink is better than the most retentive memory.**++暗淡的墨水比最好的记忆好多了。**++I@m not going to miss upgrading software all the time. I@m not going to miss being anal retentive about backing up all my files.**++回想过去的20几年，我一点都不怀念带着笔记本上下班的日子，我不怀念在不同设备之间同步文件的日子，我不怀念一直升级软件的日子，我不怀念定期备份文件的日子，我不怀念windows，我不怀念outlook，exchange还有黑莓的exchange服务器。**++Although XML itself is whitespace retentive, most applications normalize whitespace before further processing.**++尽管 XML本身保留空白，但大多数应用程序会在做进一步处理之前将空白标准化。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2373', 'reticent', '[rɛtɪsnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=reticent', '{adj.}++沉默的；寡言的；言不尽意的；有保留的**++(艺术风格等)谨严的；含蓄的；有节制的**++犹豫的；勉强的**', '++Just how much can a polite and reticent people withstand? That is the test for modern China.**++现在的问题是，儒雅而沉默的中国人能对此容忍多少，这是对当代中国的一个考验。**++Although CNN may have been initially reticent to accept unpolished citizen reports, the network\\\@s editors and producers are now comfortable using the best of the online reports on the air.**++尽管CNN可能对这些未经润饰的报告使用保持沉默，但现在网络编辑和制片人却舒服的用这些最好的网上素材制作广播节目。**++Babel@s muted celebration of his marvellous goal may have been the expression of a naturally reticent temperament, or it may have been a comment on his manager@s lack of faith.**++巴贝尔在精彩进球后作出的无声庆祝或许是出于他自身沉默寡言的性格，但这也有可能是他对球队教练缺乏信心的不满。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2374', 'retinue', '[rɛtənu]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retinue', '{n.}', '++And both leaders have a history of, shall we say, recruiting young women from the palace retinue.**++而且，两位领导人都有从自己的随从团队里面“招募”年轻女性的历史。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2375', 'retort', '[rɪtɔrt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retort', '{vt.}++反驳，回嘴：**++反击；进行报复：**{vi.}++反驳；顶嘴：**++反击；报复**{n.}++反驳；顶嘴**++反击；报复行动**{n.}++曲颈瓶**++蒸馏罐**{vt.}++蒸馏；干馏**', '++The night before, he had imagined the reaction of the girl and her female allies to his message, and had composed an eloquent retort to throw at these petty-minded women.**++昨天晚上，他曾经想象女孩和她的支持者们对他的留言会有怎样的反映，还为反驳这些心地狭窄的女人构思出雄辩的腹稿。**++Tune in to your partner when they talk instead of thinking about your next retort.**++当你的另一半讲话的时候，要听进去，不要去想着你下一轮的反驳。**++Pakistanis retort by complaining their country is not getting enough credit for putting these men on trial, even as some of them recognize more could have been done.**++巴基斯坦方面反驳，他们抱怨将这些人送上了法庭却没能得到应有的赞扬，虽然他们中的一些人认识到他们能做的还有很多。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2376', 'retouch', '[,ritʌtʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retouch', '{vt.}++润色；修改：**++【摄影术】修描(底片等)：**++补染(新长出的头发)**++【考古学】修磨(石器毛坯等)**{vi.}++润色；修整**++补染**{n.}++润色；修饰**++润色时的增删部分**++【摄影术】修描过的照片(或底片等)；修版**++(头发的)补染**++【考古学】(石器毛坯的)修磨**', '++Tourism consumption has increased for the new middle class of China trying to retouch their roots.**++中国新一代的中产阶级想要寻根也使得旅游消费有所增长。**++All corrections that affect the whole image, such as color, saturation, level and contrast, should be made first, before starting to edit and retouch more in detail.**++所有影响整体形象的修改，如色彩、饱和度、色阶、对比度，都应首当其冲，再进行细节性的编辑和修整。**++Magazines that do retouch pictures run the risk of breaking their own code of conduct, which states they should not publish inaccurate, misleading or distorted information, she added.**++那些确实存在润饰照片行为的杂志，正冒着破坏行业准则的危险。 行业准则规定，他们不能发表错误的、有误导性或者失真的信息。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2377', 'retract', '[rɪtrækt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retract', '{vt.}++缩回；缩进(爪等)；缩卷(舌头等)；收起(飞机起落架等)：**++收回；撤消(声明、语言等)：**++【语音学】收舌(发音)**++【棋类】悔棋，撤回(刚走的一步棋)**{vi.}++缩回；缩进：**++变卦；食言：**{n.}', '++A ladybug can retract its head into its body.**++瓢虫可以将自己的头缩回到躯体中去。**++“We fully retract this paper from the published record,” Lancet editors said in a statement Tuesday.**++“我们从发表记录中完全撤消了该论文”，《柳叶刀》编辑周二在一份声明中说。**++As the infection worsens, the nail bed may retract, and nails may thicken and crumble.**++随着感染的加重，甲床会缩回，然后指甲变得越来越厚，最后碎裂。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2378', 'retrench', '[ritrɛntʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retrench', '{vt.}++减少；紧缩(开支)；节约(经费):**++删除；省略(书中部分内容)：**{vi.}++节省；紧缩开支：**++节省；紧缩开支：**', '++Growth in China, for instance, will undoubtedly slow, as its major western customers retrench.**++例如，中国的经济增长无疑会放缓，因为其主要的西方国家客户减少了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2379', 'retribution', '[,rɛtrɪbjuʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retribution', '{n.}++惩罚**++【神学】报应；果报**++报答；善报**', '++That war was an act of retribution and prevention.**++那是一场惩罚和阻止对方的战争。**++Happiness and courage, retribution or justice are secondary ends for them.**++幸福和勇气，报应或正义都是次要他们的目的。**++They want to exact retribution from those people or organizations that have wronged them.**++人们想要惩罚那些对自己不公的组织或者个人。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2380', 'retrieve', '[rɪtriv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retrieve', '{vt.}++重获；收回；找回：**++恢复：**++挽救；拯救：**++补偿；纠正；扭转：**++回忆；追溯**++[美国英语]【计算机】检索：**++【打猎】(猎犬)找回；衔回，叼回(被击中的猎物)：**++【网球】击回险球，救出险球**{vi.}++【打措】找回猎物：**++【打措】找回猎物：**{n.}++= retrieval**++[美国英语]击回险球**', '++She tried hard to retrieve her luxurious life.**++她极力设法恢复她的奢华生活。**++This statement needs no WHERE clause, because we want to retrieve all the rows.**++这个语句不需要任何 WHERE 子句，因为我们希望检索所有的行。**++As with the original form, however, there’s a performance issue if you have to perform nine lookups to retrieve each of the nine virtualized fields.**++然而与最初的表单一样，如果必须执行九个查找来检索那九个虚拟字段中的每一个字段，这样就会存在性能问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2381', 'retrograde', '[rɛtrəɡred]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retrograde', '{adj.}++后退的**++次序颠倒的；反常规的**++退步的；衰退的；恶化的**++【生物学】退化的**++【天文学】倒退的；逆行的；产生制动力的**++【音乐】逆行演奏的**++【地质学】逆向的**++[废语]相反的；对立的**{vi.}++后退；倒退：**++退步；衰退；恶化**++【生物学】退化**++【天文学】逆行**{vt.}++使向后移动**{adv.}++向后，后退**', '++You may be wondering whether you should  finalize any of this with Mercury retrograde.**++你也许会好奇你是否需要因为水星的逆行而作出定论。**++Alas, Mercury, as said, will be retrograde, so we have to factor this into the mix of the month.**++哎，可是如上所说的，水星要逆行了，所以这个月我们要把这个因素考虑在内。**++First, Mercury will be retrograde in Gemini and Taurus, and because Mercury is the planet of  communication and  commerce, you will find these areas  liable to have problems.**++首先，水星在双子座和金牛座逆行。 而且由于水星是掌管沟通和商业的行星，你可能会在这些领域遇到一些麻烦。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2382', 'retrospective', '[,rɛtrəspɛktɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=retrospective', '{adj.}++回忆的；回顾的**++在…后面的**++追溯的；有追溯效力的**{n.}++(艺术家)某个时期的作品展览，(对过去作品的)回顾展**++(音乐家等)作品回顾演出**', '++At the end of the first iteration of development, there will be a demonstration and a reflection (or retrospective).**++在开发的首次迭代结束时，将会有一个示范和反映（或者回顾）。**++Before setting any new actions, the team should review whether there are outstanding actions from their previous retrospective.**++在设置任何新的行动之前，团队应该检查在以前的回顾中是否有出色的行动。**++As for timing, when working on an iterative planning cycle, you need to hold the retrospective before planning the next efforts.**++至于时间，当工作在一个迭代计划周期内，你需要在下一个跌代计划之前举行回顾。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2383', 'revelry', '[rɛvlri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=revelry', '{n.}', '++The revelry was snubbed by my father.**++我父亲终止了那次狂欢宴会。**++But it was easy to get caught up in the revelry.**++不过在那狂欢的盛宴中却很容易被狂热所感染。**++But in a crowd of like-minded people, the most intense drives for justice become the norm: People who may have felt a mix of emotions in response to the news can be swept up in the general revelry.**++但是对于一群志同道合的人，对于正义的最强烈的渴望成为了团队标准：对于这个新闻有着复杂情绪反应的人，会被驱逐出这次有广泛参与者的狂欢。**');
