insert into GREWordBook values ('2422', 'rupture', '[rʌptʃɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rupture', '{n.}++裂，破裂**++(关系的)决裂；断交；失和**++【病理学】(血管、膀胱等的)破裂；疝(尤指腹股沟疝)**{vt.}++使破裂**++决裂；断交：**++使发疝气：**{vi.}++破裂；决裂：**++发疝气**', '++In the event of a large rupture, the system would vent directly to the atmosphere.**++万一发生了大的破裂，这个系统就直接把放射性、物质排向大气。**++The accusation led to a rupture of the company’s relationship with China and a decision by Google not to cooperate with China’s censorship demands.**++这种指责最终导致了谷歌公司与中国关系的破裂以及谷歌公司拒绝与中国网络审查要求合作的决定。**++It more or less goes perpendicular with the fault rupture of the earthquake.**++海啸的行进方向与地震断层破裂带通常会相互垂直。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2423', 'ruse', '[ruz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ruse', '{n.}', '++But that too, it seems, was just another ruse.**++然而这看来同样是他的另一个诡计。**++But it was a ruse and within hours he underwent the painful treatment.**++但这是一个诡计，接下来的几小时里他经历了痛苦的治疗。**++The request for exfiltration was a ruse, and the promised documentation and purported contact with a local dissident leader were merely bait.**++要求空中接人只不过是一个诡计，所谓的文件和与当地反对派领导人的联络都是诱饵。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2424', 'rustic', '[rʌstɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rustic', '{adj.}++乡村的；在乡村生活的**++简朴的，质朴的**++土气的；粗俗的；不精致的；笨拙的**++粗制的；(桌、椅等)用带皮树干做成的**++(石工)粗面的**{n.}++乡巴佬；庄稼汉；粗人**', '++Good idea. I like a rustic style.**++好主意，我喜欢乡村风格的。**++We hoped the fresh air and rustic atmosphere would help him adjust.**++我们希望新鲜的空气和乡村的氛围能帮他调整自己。**++The era privileged elegance and wit in its music above almost all other qualities, and Haydn, despite his rustic origins, was hardly lacking in either.**++这个时代所特有的高雅与智慧先于其他一切特质存在于音乐作品之中，尽管是出身乡村的海顿，也绝不缺少这些气质。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2425', 'rustle', '[rʌsl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=rustle', '{vi.}++发出沙沙声；窸窣作响：**++窸窣作响着移动：**++穿窸窣作响的衣服**{vt.}++使窸窣作响；把…弄得沙沙作响：**++使窸窣作响；把…弄得沙沙作响：**{n.}++沙沙声，窸窣声**{n.}++急忙**{vi.}++奋力工作；急速移动：**++寻找(食物)**++偷牲口**{vt.}++急速弄到：**++把(牲口)赶拢**++偷(牲口等)：**', '++Every rustle of wind in the trees catches their attention and can be used to judge distances.**++树丛刮风的沙沙声都能够引起他们的注意，用来判断距离。**++The rumble of cars and trucks, though, washed into a high distant sound that blended with the rustle of the wind through the leaves.**++汽车和卡车的轰轰声在风吹树叶沙沙声的洗刷下，化作了一种遥远的响动。**++Usually I go in the early evening, especially in the summer and fall, when the air in Washington is warm and still and the leaves on the trees barely rustle.**++通常，我在傍晚进去，特别是在夏天和秋天，那时华府的空气温暖，而且寂静，树上的树叶几乎不会发出瑟瑟声。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2426', 'ruthless', '[rʊθləs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ruthless', '{adj.}++无情的；残忍的；冷酷的**++下定决心的，坚决彻底的**', '++If you only want to work four hours a day, then be ruthless about it.**++如果你一天只想工作四个小时，那么就要对它无情。**++‘With her acid tongue, she was ­ruthless with him, ’ said one friend.**++“她用刻薄的语气无情的对待他，”一个朋友说。”**++His business rivals knew they could expect no quarter from such a ruthless adversary.**++他的业务对手都知道不可能指望他这样无情的人会手软。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2427', 'sabotage', '[,sæbətɑʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sabotage', '{n.}++(敌特、敌对分子等的)蓄意破坏；破坏活动**++(劳资纠纷中不满劳工的)毁坏行为(尤指毁坏机器、原材料等)**++(对事业、运行等的)暗中破坏**{vt.}++蓄意破坏：**++有意毁坏：**{vi.}++破坏；从事破坏活动：**++破坏；从事破坏活动：**', '++Their apparent eagerness to sabotage the talks reveals the dangers that progress poses for them.**++他们显然渴望破坏谈判，这显示了进程给他们造成的威胁。**++It’s relentless and, until you acknowledge it, it’s willing to sabotage all your attempts at peace.**++它静不下来直到你肯承认，它很愿意以一种平和的方式破坏你的所有企图。**++Life coaches are taught to be conscious of the power of negative self talk and how to get control over “the voices” so they won’t sabotage our lives.**++生活导师会意识到消极型自我对话所产生的力量，也知道如何去控制这些“声音”，这样它们就不会破坏我们的生活。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2428', 'saccharine', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=saccharine', '{adj.}++糖的，含糖的；产糖的**++[美国英语]太甜的；(表情等)甜蜜的**{n.}++[美国英语] = saccharin**', '++Make sure the products you buy do not contain aspartame, sucralose, saccharine, cyclamate, acesulfame-k and other sweeteners.**++请确保您购买的产品不包含阿斯巴甜，三氯蔗糖，糖精，甜蜜素，安赛蜜- K和其他甜味剂。**++The authors trained rats to avoid both saccharine and salty liquids over the course of three days, and then injected the virus a week after the last training.**++作者在三天的实验过程中，训练小鼠回避糖精和有咸味的液体，并且在最后的训练中注射了该种病毒。**++The saccharine, confectionary pink objects that fill my images of little girls and their accessories reveal a pervasive and culturally manipulated expression of femininity” and a desire to be seen.**++我相片中呈现的这些小女孩和她们如糖果般甜蜜的粉红色物品揭示了一种无所不在的女性柔性文化和她们急于展示自我的欲望。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2429', 'sacrilege', '[sækrəlɪdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sacrilege', '{n.}++亵渎神圣**++渎圣行为；偷盗圣品**', '++Although some would probably declare this sacrilege, the similarities between both bands, at least in terms of make-up and influences are blindingly obvious for all to see.**++虽然有些人会断言这是一种亵渎，因为两支乐队的相似性——至少在装扮上和受到的影响上——对所有人都是毋庸置疑的明显。**++An ogre isn’t definitely the coolest living thing and the entire appearance makes us hate the package but, when we think about Shrek, the whole hatred theme seems a sacrilege.**++恶魔们并非都是冷冰冰的生物，虽然其总体形象使人厌恶，但是当我们想到怪物史瑞克时，它的形象看起来亵渎了恶魔们的憎恶形象。**++You make the American flag in the eyes of a numerous people the emblem of sacrilege in Christian churches, and of the burning of human dwellings, and of the horror of the water torture.**++在众人眼里，美国的星条旗成为了对基督教堂的亵渎，代表着对人类家园的焚烧，牵连着人们对于水刑的恐惧，而这正是您造成的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2430', 'sacrosanct', '[sækrosæŋkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sacrosanct', '{...}++...**', '++He never saw the burning towers until this year, and I was relieved that I mostly managed to keep his life sacrosanct.**++他直到今年才看到了燃烧的双塔，而我也为竭尽全力保护了他神圣不可侵犯的生活而宽慰。**++Again and again it referred to the users as sacrosanct: "We believe that our user focus is the foundation of our success to date.**++它一而再的强调用户是神圣不可侵犯的：“我们相信，我们一直将用户看作重点是我们成功的基础。**++It has ready and free access to the processor, its memory is sacrosanct, and attached devices serve the application@s every whim.**++它随时可以访问处理器，它的内存是神圣不可侵犯的，连接它的设备只为它服务。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2431', 'saddle', '[sædl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=saddle', '{n.}++鞍；鞍具**++(套车的)挽具，(尤指)鞍部肚带**++(自行车、摩托车等的)车座，鞍座**++(类似)鞍作用的东西**++鞍状物**++【地理学】鞍状山；鞍状构造；山口**++(马等的)鞍部，(牛羊等的)脊背部；脊肉**++(家禽的)背脊**++【动物学】环带，生殖带**++书脊**++(悬索桥的)承梁；(电线杆的)托架**++(鞋帮的)镶皮脊**++(门槛上的)踏板**++(炮车的)炮耳架**++(火车车厢的)轴鞍；(垫船的)圆枕木**++【建筑学】托木，承枕**++【机械学】底座，座板，座架**++【制陶】(烧制时用的)支架**++【物理学】(谐振曲线的)凹谷(点)**{vt.}++给(马等)装鞍具**++使负重担；使承担(责任等)；接受(任务等)：**++强加，强加给…重担：**++驯(赛马)**++让(赛马等)参加比赛**{vi.}++备马，给马装鞍具 (up):**++骑(或跨)上马：**', '++It looks like a saddle.**++它看起来像一个马鞍。**++The saddle is secure.**++这鞍子安得很牢。**++In three-dimensions it could even be a saddle point.**++在三维空间的时候，这个甚至可以是鞍点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2432', 'safeguard', '[sefɡɑrd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=safeguard', '{n.}', '++Safeguard your passwords and change them frequently.**++经常保护和更改你的密码。**++If we have to, we are prepared to go further and be tougher than our international partners to safeguard our economy.**++如果有必要，我们准备更进一步，采取比我们的国际伙伴更严格的措施来保卫我们的经济。**++Every one of us has a "safeguard" within our system that will prevent us from bringing in more frequency than what our bio-systems can safely hold at any given time.**++在我们的系统中，每人都有一个“保护措施”以防止我们在任何给定时间内带入过多的频率，超过我们生物系统能够承受的安全额度。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2433', 'sage', '[sedʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sage', '{n.}++圣人，圣贤**++哲人**{adj.}++贤明的；远见卓识的**++聪慧的，精明的，明智的**{n.}++【植物】鼠尾草属(Salvia)植物**++【植物】鼠尾草(Salvia officinalis)**++鼠尾草叶(用作作料或入药)**++= sagebrush**{abbr.}{n.}', '++Remember when web sites were a new concept and the sage advice to print your web address everywhere you print your phone number?**++记住，如果网站的内容是新概念的，明智的建议就是只要印有你电话号码的地方，就印上你的网址。**++How could my sage advice be “put down” so quickly?**++我明智的建议怎么能这么快就被放到一边去？**++" Montaigne gives a similar example, saying that if you put a sage on the edge of a precipice, "he must shudder like a child.**++蒙田举了个类似的例子，说如果你把一个圣人放在悬崖边上，“他一定像个孩子一样发抖”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2434', 'salient', '[selɪənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=salient', '{adj.}++突起的，凸出的**++突出的，显著的**++跳跃的，跳动的**++喷射的**++【纹章学】(兽)后腿直立前腿前伸的**{n.}++凸角；凸出部分**++凸出物，突起物**++【军事】(战线、防线等的)突出部(队)**++【地球物理学】突出部分[参较 reentrant]**', '++One of the most salient features of our culture is that there is so much [bull].**++我们的文化最显著的特色之一就是有太多的扯淡。**++Both pain and pleasure are salient.**++其实痛苦与快乐都很突出。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2435', 'salubrious', '[səlubrɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=salubrious', '{adj.}', '++Go there for unique and salubrious air, to enjoy the primeval purity of tarns.**++去那儿呼吸独特的清爽空气，享受那里原始时代的纯静湖泊。**++It is may be called “the lungs” of Russia. Go there for unique and salubrious air, to enjoy the primeval purity of tarns.**++它可以叫做俄罗斯的“肺”。去那儿呼吸独特的清爽空气，享受那里原始时代的纯静湖泊。**++His features were pretty yet, and his eye and complexion brighter than I remembered them, though with merely temporary lustre borrowed from the salubrious air and genial sun.**++他的相貌挺好看，眼睛和气色也比我所记得的有精神些，虽然那仅仅是从有益健康的空气与和煦的阳光中借来的暂时的光辉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2436', 'salutary', '[sæljətɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=salutary', '{adj.}++有益健康的**++有利的，有益的**', '++One can only hope that the result will be an equally salutary debate.**++我们只能希望这本书引发是一场同样有益的争论。**++We also hope that our consultation and cooperation on issues of regional peace, security and stability will continue to make a salutary impact on the overall environment.**++我们还希望双方在地区和平、安全与稳定问题上的磋商和合作将继续对整体环境带来有益的影响。**++Mr Obama was not yet born in 1957, when the Soviet Union put the first satellite in orbit around the Earth, but the moment is remembered as a salutary shock to an America grown complacent.**++1957年奥巴马先生还未出生，前苏联就将第一颗人造卫星送上了地球轨道，那一刻使已变得自满的美国人突然受到了一个有益的教训，从此得到纪念。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2437', 'salutation', '[sæljʊteʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=salutation', '{n.}++招呼，致意**++(口头的或书面的)招呼语，致意语**++(书信等开头的)致意词，致敬语**', '++The letter bears the salutation “Dear Sir”。**++信上写有称呼语“亲爱的先生”。**++Leaning upon his rake, the Peasant returned the salutation with a nod, but said nothing.**++倚在他的草耙上，农夫点了一下头回了招呼，但不发一语。**++As they get older buy them their own stationery and teach them how we write a letter with a salutation and signature.**++当他们大一些的时候，你可以买给他们文具，然后让他们写一封有称呼语和署名的信。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2438', 'salvage', '[sælvɪdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=salvage', '{n.}++(对遇难船只、货物等的)抢救，救助；海上打捞**++打捞出的财产(价值)**++海上救助费用(或报酬)**++挽救；挽救物**++从灾难中抢救出的物资；(抢救物的)残值**++(生命等)拯救；(名誉等的)挽回**++抢救物资的拍卖(款项)**++废物的收集(或利用) **++可利用的废物**{vt.}++打捞(沉船等):**++救助(失事船只、飞机等)，抢救(遇难人员、物资等)：**++拯救(生命)；挽回(声誉等)：**++利用(废旧物等)：**++【医学】抢救(生命垂危者等)：**++[美国俚语]把…据为己有，窃取：**', '++We is unable to salvage anything when the factory burn down.**++当工厂烧毁时，我们没有能抢救出任何东西。**++One of the first steps in this process is to salvage (for reuse) the code from legacy applications.**++此流程的早期步骤之一是从遗留应用程序“打捞”代码（以便重用）。**++Friends from College Heights Christian Church and Ozark Christian College helped us most of the day to salvage what was worth saving, in the eyes of the beholders.**++一些来自学院高原基督教堂和奥扎克基督学院的朋友花了大半天的时间帮我们打捞在我们看来还有价值保留的东西。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2439', 'salve', '[sæv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=salve', '{n.}++【药物】软膏**++唇膏，口红**++安慰，慰藉；宽慰话**++缓解物，解救物；起缓冲作用的事物**++恭维话；赞颂语**++[古语]文过饰非的话**{vt.}++在…上敷药膏，给(某人)涂软膏；为…涂唇膏：**++缓解，平息：**++安慰、宽慰：**++[古语]为…文过饰非：**{vt., vi.}++= salvage**++[古语]【宗教】拯救**{interj.}', '++Earlier my husband came into the room with some salve and a cloth.**++早些时候我的丈夫拿了些药膏和布到房间来。**++Another way to open up nasal passages is to dab mentholated salve under the nose, according to WebMD.**++打开鼻腔的另一种方法是在鼻子上涂抹薄荷药膏，根据中央社报道。**++Don@t spend time running home and buy a TP, get the chicken to bring a Salve, while you hug the tower!**++别花时间跑回家然后买个回城卷轴，买只鸡然后运个治疗药膏过来，而此刻你正窝在塔下！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2440', 'sanctify', '[sæŋktɪfaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sanctify', '{vt.}++使神圣化；使圣洁；把…奉若神明：**++使圣洁化；使无罪：**++供奉，把…留作宗教供奉**++使…传导神恩；使…产生神恩**++使神圣不可侵犯，供奉**++证明…正当，使合法化：**++使获得批准(或认可)：**++[俚语]向…敲诈(或勒索)**', '++Sanctify them through thy truth: thy word is truth.**++求你用真理使他们成圣。 你的道就是真理。**++From that point of view, it is hard to quibble with Russia’s desire to protect and sanctify the memory of its millions of soldiers who fell in the fight against Nazism.**++从这个观点出发，很难为俄罗斯的这种观点进行诡辩，即想要保护和尊重那些承载着在抗击纳粹中牺牲的几百万士兵的记忆。**++And for their sakes I sanctify myself, that they also might be sanctified through the truth.**++我为他们的缘故，自己分别为圣，叫他们也因真理成圣。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2441', 'sanctimonious', '[,sæŋktɪmonɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sanctimonious', '{adj.}', '++Though most of the critical letters were sanctimonious in tone (and presumptuous about all the mistakes I@d made), not all of them were.**++大部分持批评态度的人都会（对我所犯下的所有过错）假装虔诚，，但我知道他们并非真的如此。**++Meanwhile, here@s Thomas Jefferson weighing in: "Some men look at constitutions with sanctimonious reverence, and deem them like the ark of the covenant, too sacred to be touched.**++此外，托马斯.杰斐逊也曾就此表态："一些人以虚伪的敬意来看待宪法，将其视为盟约之柜（约柜），因为它太过神圣，以至于不可触摸。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2442', 'sanction', '[sæŋkʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sanction', '{n.}++认可，批准；允许，准许**++支持，支援，赞助**++赞许，鼓励**++(誓言等的)约束力；(法律、规章等的)约束作用**++【法律】(对遵守法律情况等的)奖惩(条款)**++【国际法】[常用复数] 制裁**++【宗教】法令，法规**++[废义]誓约，誓言**{vt.}++批准；准许：**++认可；公认：**++惩处，对…实行惩罚；对…实行制裁：**++赞许，支持，鼓励：**++在…上附加奖惩条款**', '++The church would not sanction his second marriage.**++教会不会认可他的第二次婚姻。**++In the service of the empress, this inept chauffeur faced no legal sanction for the mishap.**++由于服侍太后，这位无能的司机在这场车祸中没有受到任何法律的制裁。**++The new restrictions “do not exhaust our opportunities to sanction Iran, ” she said.**++她说，新的限制措施“并未用尽我们制裁伊朗的机会”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2443', 'sanctuary', '[sæŋktʃuɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sanctuary', '{n.}++圣所；教堂，寺院**++【犹太教】(圣经)圣幕，圣堂；圣殿，至圣所**++基督教教堂；(教堂内的)高坛，祭坛**++避难所，庇护所；(教堂等的)庇护权**++(鸟兽)禁猎区，自然保护区**++避难，庇护**', '++In May, she escaped to Tunisia with the help of a defecting military officer and Libyan rebels, and found temporary sanctuary in Qatar before being deported back to Benghazi in Libya in early June.**++五月份，她在变节军事官员和利比亚反叛武装的帮助下逃到了突尼斯，在六月早些时候回到利比亚班加西之前，在卡塔尔找到了临时的避难所。**++Find a secret spot and make it your sanctuary, whether it’s in your backyard or the Reference section.**++找一个隐蔽点让它成为你的避难所，不论他是在后院还是参照区域。**++I have seen you in the sanctuary and beheld your power and your glory.**++我在圣所中曾如此瞻仰你，为要见你的能力，和你的荣耀。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2444', 'sand', '[sænd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sand', '{n.}++沙，砂**++沙漏用沙**++沙土；沙质土壤**++[常用复数] 沙地，沙滩**++= sandbank**++沙色，红黄色**++= sandbar**++[复数] 时间，光阴**++[复数] 生命，寿命**++[俚语]眼屎**++[口语]勇气，胆量；坚毅，坚定**++【冶金学】矿渣；尾渣**++【石油】含油沙层**++【医学】沙(状结石)**{vt.}++往…上撒沙子；给…填沙子：**++用砂纸磨，磨壳，抛光：**++给…掺沙子：**++用沙覆盖，用沙埋：**++使(尤指港湾)淤积沙子**++像撒沙子一样布满：**{vi.}++沙，被沙堵塞(up):**++沙，被沙堵塞(up):**{abbr.}', '++The blowing sand stung his cheeks.**++飞沙打得他的双颊生疼。**++Dry sand absorbs water.**++干沙吸收水分。**++Harry was coated in sand and cement,but we picked him up and dusted him down.**++哈里满身全是沙子和水泥，我们把他扶起来，给他掸掸干净。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2445', 'sanguine', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sanguine', '{adj.}++(脸色等)红润的，气色好的，有血色的**++【古生理学】多血质的**++血的，由血组成的**++血色的，红色的**++= sanguinary**++(情绪)乐观的；乐天派的**++嗜血的，残忍的**++【纹章学】(徽章)紫红色的**{n.}++血红色 **++【纹章学】紫红色**{vt.}++[诗歌用语]把…染红，血染成：**++[诗歌用语]把…染红，血染成：**', '++...**++...**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2446', 'sanitary', '[sænətɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sanitary', '{adj.}++关于健康的；卫生的，清洁的**++关于卫生的；公共卫生的**++提供健康的，提供卫生的**{n.}++公共厕所**', '++They have no access to toilets or sanitary facilities.**++他们不能上厕所，也没有其他卫生设备。**++We have discussed our safety and sanitary regulations.**++我们已经讨论了安全规则和卫生规则。**++We subcontracted  for sanitary-plumbing equipment in the project.**++在该项工程中我们分包了卫生设备的承建。**');
