insert into GREWordBook values ('2472', 'scour', '[skaʊr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scour', '{vt.}++擦净，擦亮：**++除去…的油污(污渍等)：**++冲刷(管道)；疏通(河道等)：**++冲成：**++洗刷，洗涤：**++清除…中的杂物：**++荡涤，肃清：**++打(虫)，泻(肚)：**++灌(肠)，洗(胃)：**++【冶金学】侵蚀，烧蚀：**{vi.}++擦，磨；拭光，擦亮：**++拭去,擦掉(away, off, out):**++洗净；能擦洗干净：**++清除；肃清：**++(家畜)腹泻，拉肚子：**++(犁等)翻地时不沾泥：**++恶化，变坏**{n.}++擦；洗；拭**++冲刷；冲刷处**++清除；肃清**++被擦洗掉的污垢**++擦拭用物；冲刷用物**++擦拭(或冲刷)干净的地方**++(流水等的)冲刷力，冲蚀力**++清洗剂，洗涤剂，除垢剂**++[复数，用作单数或复数](牛、马等的)腹泻，痢疾**{vi.}++急匆匆地走，奔跑：**++搜寻，搜索：**{vt.}++快跑，迅速跑过(某处)：**++来回搜索，四处搜寻:**', '++Mother made me scour the family silver.**++妈妈让我把家里的银器都擦亮。**++Then we scour them like this! VERY carefully!**++然后我们象这样冲洗肠子！要很小心哦！**++Scour your phone bill and see if one or two of those extras can be turned off.**++清洗你的账单，同时看一下是否一至两个额外事额能够被关闭。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2473', 'scourge', '[skɝdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scourge', '{vt.}++鞭笞，鞭打：**++严惩，重责；斥责，严厉批评：**++使痛苦；使苦恼，折磨：**++使遭受(苦难等)：**++(鞭打般地)驱赶**{n.}++鞭子**++灾难，灾害；天灾，天罚**++惩罚，惩罚的工具(或手段)**++被视为惩罚工具的人(或事物)**++苦难(或灾祸)的根源**', '++Smallpox was probably the single biggest scourge to hit North America.**++天花可能是袭击美洲的最大的一个灾祸。**++Thatcher has relentlessly flogged the book in Britain and the U.S., giving TV interviews that scourge what she sees as the collapse of her country’s leadership.**++撒切尔毫不客气地在英国和美国销售此书，同时接受电视台采访，起到了鞭笞在她看来摇摇欲坠的英国领导的作用。**++And your covenant with death shall be disannulled, and your agreement with hell shall not stand; when the overflowing scourge shall pass through, then ye shall be trodden down by it.**++你们与死亡所立的约，必然废掉，与阴间所结的盟，必立不住。 敌军（原文作鞭子）如水涨漫经过的时候，你们必被他践踏。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2474', 'scowl', '[skaʊl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scowl', '{n.}++皱着眉头的脸，愁容，不悦之色；怒容**++(人或天气的)阴沉**++阴沉的脸色；威胁的样子**{vi.}++皱眉头；沉下脸**++(天气、表情等)阴沉下来：**++威胁**{vt.}++对…皱眉(或绷脸)；以怒容表示(不快等)，皱着眉拒绝：**++对…皱眉(或绷脸)；以怒容表示(不快等)，皱着眉拒绝：**', '++The boss manifested his disgust with a scowl.**++老板皱皱眉表露出厌恶。**++Their inability to scowl seemed to impair their ability to see why pushy telemarketers or a lack of birthday wishes might make one’s face fall.**++无法生气地皱眉似乎让他们不能很好地理解为什么咄咄逼人的电话销售或是没得到生日祝愿会让人沉下脸来。**++The child may scowl, squint, or shield his or her eyes more than expected when in bright sunlight.**++患儿在强烈的阳光下时可能会出人意料地皱眉，眯眼，甚至遮住他/她的双眼。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2475', 'scrap', '[skræp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrap', '{n.}++小片，小块；碎片**++碎屑；(工业)废料**++(剪贴的)零星资料**++片断，残篇，残简**++[复数]残羹剩饭；油渣**++少量，一点儿**++(书报等的)剪切材料；剪报**++[口语]小个子**{adj.}++零星的；片断的**++由零碎(或废料)组成的**++废弃的，丢弃的**++剩余的**++胡乱拼凑的**{vt.}++使解体，拆毁**++废弃，废止：**{n.}++口角，争吵；打架(with)**++职业拳击赛**{vi.}++打架；吵嘴：**++打架；吵嘴：**', '++Once you do the calculations, you realise that the scrap in your hand is a very exciting discovery.**++一旦你进行计算，你就会发现手中的这个碎片是一个非常令人兴奋地发现。**++Then they ripped radiators and pipes from the walls and sold them to scrap dealers, who then sold the metal in China.**++然后又从墙上据开暖气片和管道并把它们卖给碎片商人，这些商人又把金属卖给中国。**++However, scrap and rework are not limited to code; they also result from design changes and can be monitored in the design model.**++然而，废弃和返工不仅限于代码；他们也会从设计的变更所导致，并且能够在设计模型中被监视。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2476', 'scrappy', '[skræpi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrappy', '{adj.}++碎料制成的；拼凑的**++不连贯的，杂乱的**{adj.}++[口语]**++好吵架的，爱打斗的**++斗志旺盛的**++勇于拼斗的；坚决的**', '++It may have something to do with the fact that Apple leaks have shifted from scrappy fan sites into the mainstream.**++这大概与泄密行动已经从小打小闹的粉丝网站逐渐向主流媒体转移这一事实有点关系。**++At the heart of this cautionary tale sits the cigar-chomping Mr Cayne, who revelled in his firm’s image as Wall Street’s scrappy outsider.**++大声嚼着雪茄的凯恩先生处于这个引人警戒的故事的中心，他酷爱其公司作为华尔街好斗的局外人形象。**++Daniel appears to have been a scrappy lad who loved hunting, the wilderness, and independence.**++那时的丹尼尔个性独立、出入荒野，热爱狩猎，是一个精力旺盛的男孩。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2477', 'scrawl', '[skrɔl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrawl', '{n.}++乱涂，乱画，涂鸦**++潦草的字迹；胡乱涂画的东西**++潦草**{vt.}++涂写，潦草地写(或画)：**++在…上涂画**++涂抹掉(out)：**{vi.}++涂写；乱写，乱画：**++涂写；乱写，乱画：**', '++He found a note on his kitchen table. It was a dinner invitation for that very night, in a childish scrawl.**++他在厨房的桌上看到了一张请柬，就是当晚的晚餐请柬，请柬上是孩子气的潦草笔迹。**++If you write, you must believe — in the truth and worth of the scrawl, in the ability of the reader to receive and decode the message.**++如果你写作的话，你必须相信真理，相信涂鸦的价值，相信读者接收、译解信息的能力。**++In 2004, Andre Geim at the University of Manchester made a pencil scrawl on a sheet of paper, then used a length of Sellotape to pull off the graphite deposits.**++2004年，曼彻斯特大学，科学界安德烈·海姆先用铅笔在一页纸上乱涂，然后使用透明胶带剥离出表面的石墨烯涂层。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2478', 'screen', '[skrin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=screen', '{n.}++屏，幕，幔，帘，帐**++围屏；屏风；屏幕**++(装饰性)隔墙，隔板，围板**++(教堂的)祭坛围屏，装饰性围屏**++(金属或塑料)纱网；纱门，纱窗**++遮掩物，遮蔽物**++掩护，庇护**++粗筛；滤网；过滤器**++筛选；筛选的方式**++(电视)屏幕；(电影等的)银幕**++(监视器的)荧光屏**++[the screen]电影；电影业；电影界；电影艺术**++(汽车等的)挡风玻璃**++布告板；展示板**++【计算机】**++屏面(= video screen)**++帧；画面**{vt.}++遮；遮蔽；隔开：**++掩护，庇护；隐藏：**++隔挡，遮住(out)：**++筛(煤、矿石等)；筛分：**++甄别；筛选；测试：**++把…放映到银幕上；播放…节目：**++(用摄影机)拍摄(分镜头等)**++把(小说、戏剧等)改编成电影**++给…装上窗帘；给…装纱门(或纱窗等)：**++【印刷】把…加网印刷**++【物理学】过滤(油、空气等)**++【电子学】屏蔽**{vi.}++拍电影；(演员)上镜头，(剧本)适于拍成电影：**++【体育】掩护：**', '++The mound can be used as our screen.**++这个土丘可做我们的掩蔽物。**++He looks much younger and handsomer than on the screen.**++他看上去比在银幕上要年轻漂亮得多。**++Her screen career, for all practical purposes, had guttered out.**++她的银幕生涯实际上默默无闻地结束了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2479', 'scribble', '[skrɪbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scribble', '{vt.}++潦草地书写；胡写，乱画：**++粗制滥造(文学作品等)：**{vi.}++潦草地书写；胡写；乱画：**++做文人，当作家**{n.}++潦草书写；胡写；乱画**++潦草地字迹**++拙劣的文章(或作品等)**{vt.}', '++Don@t scribble [scrawl] on the wall.**++别在墙上乱涂。**++With English selected as language, you can see the inflections for write and scribble, whereas wrte is out-of-vocabulary.**++如果选择 English 作为字典语言，那么会发现 write 和 scribble 等词形变化，而 wrte 属于词汇表以外的词汇。**++So the typically under-copyright law if you scribble something on a piece of paper, you automatically have a copyright to that.**++所以经典的版权保护法规定，即便你是在一张纸上乱涂乱画，你也自动拥有了对这张纸上信息的版权。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2480', 'scrimp', '[skrɪmp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrimp', '{vt.}++节省，节俭，节约：**++过度缩减；剋扣：**++对…吝啬：**{vi.}++节俭；吝啬(on)：**++节俭；吝啬(on)：**{adj.}++节俭的；缩减的**++不足的，短少的**{n.}++[口语]守财奴，吝啬鬼**', '++So don@t scrimp on smooching your girl different ways to ramp up the sensitive factor.**++因此不要吝啬亲吻你的女朋友，尝试用不同的方式来调动敏感的器官。**++Despite bitter complaints about soaring prices, workers say they can scrimp enough to save at least a chunk of their wages.**++尽管飞涨的物价让打工者叫苦不迭，但他们说如果精打细算一些，还是可以存下部分工资的。**++And yet the more they scrimp on investment, the more joblessness, especially among the young, will deepen Japan’s sense of malaise.**++但是他们越是在投资上节省资金，失业也就会更多，特别是在年轻人之中，这将会是日本萎靡不振的意识进一步恶化。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2481', 'scruple', '[skrupl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scruple', '{n.}++顾虑，顾忌；良心的责备，不安**{vt.}++对…有顾忌；对…感到不安：**++对…有顾忌；对…感到不安：**{vi.}++有顾虑，良心上感到不安：**++有顾虑，良心上感到不安：**{n.}++吩(英美药衡单位，等于 1.296克)**++微量**++[英国英语]两(液体容量单位，等于20量滴或 0.04166液量盎司)**++(古罗马)斯克鲁普尔(重量单位，等于1／24盎司)**++(古罗马)货币(由含金量确定其币值)**', '++Well, look at this footnote: And the history of words after a poem is written may contribute meanings which if relevant to the original pattern should not be ruled out by a scruple about intention.**++那么我们就来看一下这条脚注：,在诗产生后，语言的意思也就跟着产生了,这种意思如果和原始的形式不同,就不该有对作者意图的顾虑。**++He bowed. "I respect your scruple, sir; but in this case I believe true delicacy requires you to do as I ask.**++他点了点头，说：“我尊重你的顾虑，先生，不过对这件事，我以为真正的审慎还是要按我说的去做。**++and every speculative scruple will be solved by practical public blessing.**++并且每一个推测性的踌躇都将为符合实际的公共祝福所解决。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2482', 'scrupulous', '[skrupjələs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrupulous', '{adj.}++有顾虑的；小心谨慎的**++严谨的，认真负责的**', '++As producers of new journalism, they can be scrupulous with facts and transparent with their sources.**++对于新新闻的生产者，他们可以对事实一丝不苟，同时透明化新闻来源。**++A scrupulous writer, in every sentence that he writes, will ask himself at least four questions, thus: 1.  What am I trying to say?**++一位一丝不苟的作家在写每一个句子的时候会至少问自己这么四个问题：1.我要说什么？**++With type 2 diabetes, scrupulous attention to blood sugar levels and strict adherence to dietary rules can have payoffs in terms of reducing disease severity, the researchers suspect.**++研究者们推测说患有第2型糖尿病的人，他们小心谨慎关注血糖的含量，严格遵守饮食规定会有助于他们降低疾病的严重程度。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2483', 'scrutable', '[skrʊtəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrutable', '{adj.}++能辨认的，可辨认的**++可理解的**', '++Such tone framework expands scrutable of picture once and for all and releases connotation and inclusiveness of photography reading.**++这样的影调架构一下子扩大了画面内容的可解读空间，引导影像的阅读更具内涵与张力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2484', 'scrutinize', '[skrutənaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scrutinize', '{vt.}++细看，细读；详察，仔细观察(或检察)：**++细看，细读；详察，仔细观察(或检察)：**{vi.}++作仔细检查；细致观察：**++作仔细检查；细致观察：**', '++We must scrutinize and evaluate.**++我们必须细细察看并做出评价。**++Before you say, "I do," scrutinize your lover@s drinking habits. Or eating patterns.**++面对求婚，在你说“我愿意”之前，请仔细检查你爱人的饮食习惯。**++Since user and group account management is handled outside of DB2, DB2 does not scrutinize whether users should or should not be a member of a group.**++由于用户和组账户的管理是在 DB2 之外处理的，因此 DB2 不会仔细检查用户应不应该成为一个组的成员。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2485', 'scuff', '[skʌf]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scuff', '{vt.}++拖着(脚)走路：**++(因不安等)用脚擦(地)：**++把(鞋底)磨损，使磨损：**++[美国英语]用脚尖触碰：**++用手掌击打：**++[主苏格兰英语]掠过；擦过；擦掉：**{vi.}++拖着脚步：**++磨损，磨坏：**++[美国英语]用脚碰触：**{n.}++拖着脚行走**++拖着脚行走发出的声音，嚓嚓声**++家用平底拖鞋**++磨损；磨损处；伤疤**++[苏格兰英语]轻击，轻打**{n.}', '++The false alarm about Spanish cucumbers will further scuff Germany’s image in a neighbourhood where it has not been popular lately.**++近来德国在邻国中颇不受欢迎，这次对黄瓜的误报将进一步损害德国在邻国中的形象。**++For Ferguson to devise this team and his goalkeeper, Ben Amos, to go through the match without getting a scuff of mud on his kit demonstrates what a demoralising night it was for Leeds.**++在这样一个夜晚士气低落的利兹联队员们完全没有给弗格森设计的这个奇怪的阵型，以及曼联年轻的门将本·阿莫斯带来任何麻烦。**++If you scuff a shoe, he reveals, "A Sharpie the color of your shoe can save the day!"**++他说，如果你的鞋子磨坏了，一双和鞋子颜色一样的平底帆可能会让你转危为安。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2486', 'scurrilous', '[skɜrələs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scurrilous', '{adj.}++庸俗下流的；满口脏话的**++以污言秽语谩骂的，恶意诽谤的**++下流(或辱骂)性语言的**', '++It was written in response to attacks on mainstream science which the Royal Society considered scurrilous.**++它是为回应学会斥之为下流的关于主流科学的攻击而写就的。**++One such example involved a customer who asked the young printer to publish a piece in the Gazette that Franklin found "scurrilous and defamatory."**++这里有个例子，曾经有一名顾客要求这个年轻的出版商在报上刊登一则消息，而Franklin在其中发现了“下流和诽谤的字眼。”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2487', 'scurvy', '[skɝvi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scurvy', '{adj.}++卑鄙的，无耻的，下流的**++[废语]=scurfy**{n.}++【病理学】坏血病**', '++In humans, vitamin C deficiency causes scurvy, and can eventually cause death.**++人类缺乏维生素C会引起坏血病，最终导致死亡。**++Not eating enough of them can result in problems such as scurvy, dermatitis or dry, scaly skin.**++维生素摄入不足能导致坏血病、皮肤炎或干燥、鳞状皮肤之类的问题。**++Without the vitamin, scurvy would bring on rashes and gum disease, not to mention very bad breath.**++而坏血病就是由于缺乏维他命而导致的，会引起皮疹，牙周病的症状，口臭就更不在话下。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2488', 'seamy', '[simi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=seamy', '{adj.}++有线缝，露出线缝的**++有裂缝的；裂缝状的**++丑恶的；肮脏的，污秽的；卑鄙的**', '++What does your seamy side tell you?**++你的阴暗面告诉你什么？**++On a brighter note in this seamy investigation I came across clues to a most unusual dictionary.**++显然，本文涉及到了一个关于社会阴暗面和人性堕落的探究。 不过，在翻阅一部非同寻常的词典时，我却凑巧在一条基调较为明快的条目中找到了线索。**++They@re not necessarily about the seamy underbelly of life, but there is always the hint that we are eavesdropping.**++这样的照片不见得要揭露生活里丑陋的、脆弱的地方，但是却总暗示着——我们在偷听他人的生活。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2489', 'secede', '[sɪsid]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=secede', '{vt.}++从…中脱离；割让(土地等)：**++从…中脱离；割让(土地等)：**{vi.}++(由某宗教、团体、政党等中)退出，脱离：**++(由某宗教、团体、政党等中)退出，脱离：**', '++For several days, it seemed that all these states would secede and join the southern confederacy.**++几天来，似乎所有这些州都将脱离联邦加入到南方邦联中去。**++The first state to secede after the start of the Civil War was Virginia. It was an important state because of its location.**++内战暴发后第一个脱离联邦的是维吉尼亚州（弗吉尼亚州），该州在美国的地理位置上十分重要。**++Even if the south could secede without war, he said, it still would not get any of the things it demanded.**++即使南方脱离联邦而没有发生战争，他说，南方的脱离仍然无法得到它所需要的任何东西。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2490', 'secluded', '[sɪkludɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=secluded', '{vt.}++seclude的变形**{adj.}++隔离的；与世隔绝的；孤立的**++隐退的**++隐居的；僻静的，隐蔽的**{vt.}++使分离的；把…隔离开；使孤立：**++把…隐藏起来：**++[废语]把…排除在外；不让(某人)进入**', '++In her defense, though, the apartment they live in is off a long and somewhat secluded alley.**++但是，刘的妻子辩解说，他们居住的房子在一个长而隐蔽的巷子里。**++There were plenty of secluded places in the huge warehouse, behind piles of crates or in the freezer.**++在那间宽敞的库房中有很多隐蔽的地方，比如成堆的板条箱后面或者在冷冻库中。**++In the bar, snacks are served, and the visitor can relax with a drink or a cup of coffee, while the secluded VIP Lounge offers more private and undisturbed seating for meetings and conversations.**++在吧台区，有小吃提供，游客可以在这里放松的喝点小酒或者喝点咖啡，但是在隐蔽一点的贵宾区，则提供更多私人空间的座位，适合不被打扰的会面和交谈。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2491', 'secrete', '[sɪkrit]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=secrete', '{vt.}++藏，藏匿(东西等)：**++私下侵吞：**++／sikri:t／ 【生理学】分泌：**', '++Because the oil is used as a reserve nutrient—like fat—diatoms have evolved no mechanism to secrete it.**++由于油的作用是营养储备——就象脂肪似的——所以硅藻没有进化出分泌油份的机制。**++We know they smear a liquid on the tube, but we don’t know where they secrete it from or what its chemical composition is.**++我们知道它们在往玻璃管上抹一种液体，但我们不知道它们是从哪里分泌出来的，也不知道它的化学成分。**++The bacterium can also secrete chemicals that inhibit fungal growth, as well as hormones that stimulate the growth of its host plants.**++这种细菌也能够分泌抑制真菌生长的化学物质，同时，它还能产生促进宿主植物生长的激素。**');
