insert into GREWordBook values ('2493', 'secular', '[sɛkjəlɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=secular', '{adj.}++尘世的，世俗的**++修道院以外的；在俗的**++非宗教的，非教会的**++百年一次的，一世纪一次的**++长期的，永久的，不朽的；连续数个世纪的**++怀疑宗教教义的；反对宗教教育的**{n.}++院外僧侣(或修士)，俗僧；俗人**++平信徒**++[美国英语]黑人的俗歌**', '++Some will be relatively secular, but others will not separate religion and the state as the United States and France do.**++这些国家中，有些相对世俗，他们像美国和法国一样分州或分区治理，而另一些则不同。**++What would you say are some of the issues that Muslim students would face at a secular university like Princeton?**++你觉得在像普林斯顿这样的世俗学校,读书的穆斯林学生,都会遇到些什么样的问题呢？**++Its leap into modernity took the form of a secular revolution; that differs from places like Ireland or Poland， where church and modern nationhood go together.**++它通过长期变革完成到新式天主教的飞跃，这不同于像爱尔兰教会、波兰教会这些与其现代国家地位相符合的地区；**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2494', 'sedate', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sedate', '{adj.}{vt.}', '++Proponents of the Sleeping Beauty diet sedate themselves heavily for many days, so that when they wake up they’re much thinner.**++很多睡美人饮食的支持者通过多日沉重而安静的睡去,所以当他们醒来的时候,他们更瘦了。**++The party staged by Forbes, the swashbuckling celebrator of capitalism, American-style, was sedate, sparsely attended, devoid of young people.**++吹捧财富的福布斯举办的美式聚会非常安静，很少有人参加，根本看不到年轻的面孔。**++It can produce repulsive gravity to drive cosmic inflation in the big bang, while later on it could generate the more sedate acceleration that is ascribed to dark energy.**++它可以产生与万有引力相反的斥力，产生大爆炸中的暴涨，随后使宇宙产生更为平稳的加速度，这种加速度归因为暗能量。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2495', 'sedentary', '[sɛdntɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sedentary', '{adj.}++久坐不动的，不活动的；需要坐着(工作)的**++【鸟类学】不迁徙的，定居的**++【昆虫学】坐网的**++【贝类学】(贝壳)固定附着的，静止的**', '++I took up running and yoga after years of sedentary living.**++在多年久坐的生活后，我开始跑步和练瑜伽。**++They are not looking at how much they ate or that they smoke or that they are sedentary.**++他们从来不关注一下他们吃了多少或抽多少烟或者久坐不运动的时间。**++Moderate exercise, such as walking, can reduce the risk of diabetes in obese and sedentary people whose blood sugar is starting to rise.**++像步行之类的适度运动能够减少那些血糖正在升高的肥胖和久坐的人群患糖尿病的风险。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2496', 'seduce', '[sɪdʊs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=seduce', '{vt.}++使误入歧途；诱使…堕落：**++勾引，诱奸**++诱惑；使入迷：**', '++These things have I written unto you concerning them that seduce you.**++我将这些话写给你们，是指着那引诱你们的人说的。**++If the target is a wife or girlfriend, “We investigate her lover and send a female agent to seduce him.**++三岛说，如果目标对象是妻子或女朋友，“我们会调查她的爱人，然后派一名女代庸去引诱他。**++Nothing can beat striptease dancing if you want to effectively seduce your man.**++如果你想要引诱的你的男人，没有什么可以与脱衣舞相匹敌。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2497', 'sedulous', '[sɛdʒələs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sedulous', '{adj.}++勤奋的，刻苦的**++固执的，执著的**++坚持的，恒定不变的**', '++I promised myself I will never become the second sedulous example in this company.**++我对自己发誓，我决不能成为第二个她！**++She wondered what sort of herbs they were, which the old man was so sedulous to gather.**++她不晓得那老人如此勤快地采集的是哪种药草。**++Do I want to ask only have true feeling? Is everything misunderstanding or sedulous arrangement?**++我只想问有没有真情感?一切是误解还是刻意安排?。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2498', 'seemly', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=seemly', '{adj.}++适合的；合宜的，得体的**++[古语]好看的，美貌的**{adv.}++适合地；合宜地，得体地**', '++As snow in summer, and as rain in harvest, so honour is not seemly for a fool.**++夏天落雪，收割时下雨，都不相宜。 愚昧人得尊荣，也是如此。**++The ancient Roman poet Terrence declared that in every endeavor, the seemly course for wise men is to try persuasion first.**++古罗马诗人泰伦斯宣称，在每一次作出努力时，智者首先采用的适当途径是说服。**++Delight is not seemly for a fool; much less for a servant to have rule over princes.**++愚昧人宴乐度日，是不合宜的，何况仆人管辖王子呢。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2499', 'segment', '[sɛɡmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=segment', '{n.}++段，节；部分**++【计算机】(字符等的)分段；(程序)段；图块**++【动物学】节片，体节**++【数学】(线)段，节；球缺，弓形**++【机械学】扇形体**++【语音学】音节**{vt.}++把…分割(或切割)成段，使成节：**++把…分割(或切割)成段，使成节：**{vi.}++分割，分割成段(或节)：**++【生物学】细胞分裂**', '++Each segment contains rows from only one table defined in the table space.**++每个段只能包含该表空间中定义的一个表中的行。**++However, each of the following configurations takes one segment (256MB) away from the database shared memory.**++但是，下面的每种配置都会从数据库共享内存中拿出一个段（256MB）。**++Listing 2 shows a segment from one of these files.**++清单 2 展示了来自这样一个文件的片段。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2500', 'self-abasement', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=self-abasement', '{n.}', '++Europe@s self-abasement comes just weeks after the last round of Eurozone crisis mismanagement.**++就在欧洲妄自菲薄数周以前，欧元区刚刚出现了新一轮的危机管理欠妥问题。**++If they would serve their fellow-men, let them do it by making manifest the power and reality of conscience, in constraining them to penitential self-abasement!**++要是他们想为同伴们服务，那就先强制自己仟悔他们的卑下，以表明良心的力量和存在吧！**++She despised herself when she remembered the utter self - abasement of the past.**++当她回忆起过去的不折不扣的自卑时，她便瞧不起自己。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2501', 'self-absorbed', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=self-absorbed', '{adj.}', '++This self-absorbed perspective treats God as a genie who simply exists to serve you in your selfish pursuit of personal fulfillment.**++这种自私的看法就是把神当作一个精灵，神的存在只是为了服侍你，满足你的自私，实现你的个人追求。**++The Energy Vampire is self-absorbed and zaps our energy as they go on-and-on endlessly about themselves.**++精力吸血鬼。 他们是自私的，不断地为了他们自己吸取着我们的精力。**++Through Jesus Christ, He pleads with us to come out of our sinful, self-absorbed isolation and yield to the living God.**++这是藉着耶稣基督发生的，他恳求我们脱离我们罪恶的、以自我为中心的光景，真正来到永活的上帝面前。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2502', 'seminal', '[sɛmɪnl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=seminal', '{adj.}++精液的，含精液的；储存精液的；输精的**++【植物学】种子的**++繁殖的，生殖的**++有发展可能的；潜在的**++有创造力的，对未来有影响的；重大的**', '++Any seminal events that happened during your career to cause you to change direction and how that worked out for you.**++职业生涯中任何让你改变方向的重大事件；以及这些事件是如何影响你的。**++His actions touched people so deeply that they felt compelled to reach out and share their own seminal experiences with him.**++他的壮举如此感人，以致于人们觉得必须表达出来，和萨伦伯格分享他们自己的重要体验。**++Mandelbrot@s observations provided him with the material for his seminal book, The Fractal Geometry of Nature, published in 1982.**++曼德布洛特的观察为他于 1982 年发表的创造性的著作《自然的分形几何》提供了素材。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2503', 'sensation', '[sɛnseʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sensation', '{n.}++感觉，知觉**++兴奋，激动；感动**++感觉能力**++兴奋状态**++轰动 **++引起轰动的事(或事物等)**', '++The new book has created a great sensation.**++这本新书引起了巨大轰动。**++Working with one@s head causes a sensation of hunger quite as much as muscular work.**++脑力劳动与体力劳动引起的饥饿感觉是完全一样的。**++This responsiveness to reward thus works like the desire for new sensation: It gets you out of the house and into new turf.**++这种对奖励的反应就像对新感觉的渴望一样在起作用：它让你走出家门进入新的活动领域。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2504', 'sensitive', '[sɛnsətɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sensitive', '{adj.}++感觉的，感受的；有感觉的**++易受(外界)影响的**++(情绪等)易波动的；(思维等)敏锐的**++【生理学】敏感的，神经质的**++有关感觉的，与感官有关的**++(文件、工作等)机密的，绝密的**++【植物学】(叶等)有刺激反应的**++【摄影术】(相纸等)感光度高的，反应敏捷的**++【无线电】灵敏度高的**++【机械学】(仪器)高灵敏度的**{n.}++敏感的人**++具有超感觉的人；通灵者**', '++This instrument is highly sensitive.**++这架仪器很灵敏。**++We@d better keep off the sensitive topic.**++我们最好避开这个敏感的话题。**++Try your best to sidestep for sensitive issues like this.**++你应尽可能地回避像这类敏感的问题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2505', 'sentinel', '[sɛntɪnl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sentinel', '{n.}++看守者**++哨兵；步哨**++【计算机】标记(表示程序开始或结束的符号；亦作 tag)**++[S-]【军事】(美国五十个州)卫兵反弹道导弹系统**{vt.}++警卫，守卫；警戒：**++在…放哨；在…设岗哨**', '++The lack of poultry outbreaks spells trouble because the birds normally serve as a sentinel, sounding the alarm.**++禽类暴发的缺失让人们感到烦恼，因为禽类通常是发出警报的哨兵。**++In this sample, we implemented a similar JDBC results resolver that uses named statements and positional parameters with the XML parameter denoted a sentinel value of —XML—.**++在本例中，我们实现了一个类似的 JDBC 结果解析器，它通过以一个哨兵值 —XML— 标示的 XML 参数使用几个已命名语句和位置参数。**++A source familiar with the Heat@s chances told the Sun Sentinel that the team knows James "still has interest" but that management is not necessarily completely confident that it is the favorite.**++一名熟悉热火内幕的消息人士告诉太阳哨兵报，球队知道詹姆斯对其很感兴趣，但是管理层仍不敢完全相信热火就是詹姆斯最中意的球队。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2506', 'septic', '[sɛptɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=septic', '{adj.}++【医学】**++腐败性的，引起化脓的**++感染的，有脓血的；引起感染的**{n.}++引起感染的物质；败血症病原体**++[澳大利亚口语]化粪池**', '++Put some anti-septic cream on it.**++涂上一些防止败血症的药膏。**++At the Mahatma Gandhi Hospital intensive-care unit, Ms. Ruksana suffered kidney failure and septic shock.**++在圣雄甘地医院的加护病房里，卢卡莎娜遭受了肾衰竭和败血症的袭击。**++It’s fair to say that when an advertisement describes a septic tank as “the best invention since the wheel, ” we’ve begun to take our round, load-bearing companion for granted.**++当一个广告将一个奢侈的水箱描述为“自轮子以来最伟大的发明”时，公平地说，我们已经开始将我们圆形，负重的伙伴看得太习以为常了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2507', 'sepulchral', '[səpʌlkrəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sepulchral', '{adj.}++墓的，可用作坟墓的**++埋葬的**++像坟墓似的，阴森森的**++空洞的；低沉的；阴郁的**', '++Then a sort of sepulchral transformation straightened up this centenarian as erect as a young man.**++这时一种阴森森的变态使这个百岁老人象年轻人一样竖直了身子。**++This group of victim and executioner was illuminated by the sepulchral light which he bore in his own soul.**++他心里燃烧着的阴森火光，照亮了受刑人和刽子手这一对形象。**++During a sepulchral press conference to launch the Bank of England@s quarterly inflation report, the governor made it clear that he was losing no sleep over the rise in asset prices.**++在一次气氛阴沉的发布英国央行季度通胀报告的新闻发布会上，这位英国央行行长明确表示，他不会因资产价格上涨而夜不能眠。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2508', 'sequel', '[sikwəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sequel', '{n.}++(文学作品的)续篇，续集**++(事情或情况的)继续，后续；随之而来的事**++后果，结局；余波**++[废语]推论**', '++How do you see technology changing for the Avatar sequel?**++您怎么看待科技对《阿凡达》续集的影响呢？**++Once, when a movie was successful there used to be a "sequel", a follow-up film destined to build on the popularity of its predecessor and extend the life of the story at the box office.**++编者 一旦一部影片成功了，往往就会有一部“续集”出现，这部紧随其后的电影注定是建立在前一部影片的名气之上并在票房收入方面延续该故事生命的。**++Bates is best known for The Darling Buds of May, which was a TV hit; this sequel was also adapted for television in 1977.**++贝茨最有名的小说《五月的花朵》改编成电视剧风靡一时，这本书作为续集也于 1977 年被改编成电视剧。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2509', 'sequela', '[sɪkwilə]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sequela', '{n.}++结果，后果**++【病理学】后遗症，续发症，遗患**', '++I burned sequela me! ! ! ! !**++我烙后遗症了我！**++For transmuted diseases [such as diabetes], the sequela of treatment start to become as problematic as the underlying disease.**++对蜕变疾病而言（例如糖尿病），治疗的后遗症开始成为与疾病本身一样的问题。**++Grind bone how many money ah? What sequela to have?**++磨骨多少钱啊？有没有什么后遗症？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2510', 'sequester', '[sɪkwɛstɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sequester', '{vt.}++使隐退；使隔离：**++使移开，使分开：**++【法律】查封；扣押；没收(地产等)：**++【宗教】(为清偿债务或为新任教师积累基金)贡献(圣职收入等)**++【化学】使多价螯合**{n.}++[废语]隔离，分离**', '++Fitch and Moody’s, the other main ratings agencies, have refrained from doing so, in part because of the promised deficit reductions under the sequester.**++而另两家主要的信用评级机构惠誉和穆迪则并未这样做，某种程度上是因为美政府承诺将自动减少赤字。**++Officials at a natural gas project in Algeria are working on the In Salah Gas Project, which will strip carbon dioxide out of its emissions and sequester it a mile underground.**++阿尔及利亚官员正在一个天然气开采项目中实施“因萨拉温室气体计划”。 这一计划会把气田排放出的二氧化碳收集起来，将其封存在地下一英里处。**++Rooted in metres of thick peat, the rainforests of Central Kalimantan, Indonesia sequester vast quantities of the greenhouse gases carbon dioxide and methane.**++印度尼西亚加里曼丹地区中部的雨林植根于数米厚的泥炭之中，它们吸收了大量的温室气体二氧化碳和甲烷。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2511', 'sere', '[sɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sere', '{adj.}++枯萎的，干枯的[亦作 sear]**++[古语](衣服等)破旧的**{n.}{n.}', '++The trees begin to proclaim the change. Soon the leaves will be discarded, the grass will sere.**++渐黄的树木开始宣告季节的变更，很快叶落归根，小草即将枯萎。**++But when the researchers measured levels of the hormone in saliva samples taken during SERE training, they found exactly the opposite.**++但当研究人员测试在SERE训练过程中提取的受训者唾液样本中发现，结果与预期恰恰相反。**++Immediately after SERE training the researchers gave soldiers a drink containing either a low or high dose of a carbohydrate that is rapidly digested to glucose, or a similar-tasting inert drink.**++SERE训练一结束，研究人员让士兵们饮用一种饮料，其中或高或低含有能迅速转变为葡萄糖的碳水化合物，或者味道相似的惰性饮料。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2512', 'serendipity', '[,sɛrəndɪpəti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=serendipity', '{n.}++意外发现的东西；好运**++意外发现珍贵物品的天赋才能**', '++This is the kind of serendipity you want!**++这正是那种你心心期盼的命中注定！**++Serendipity and luck are by their very nature unpredictable, and therefore not part of any good plan.**++意外之得和幸运本质上都是不可预测的，因此不属于任何好计划的一部分。**++You will also discover the benefits of synchronicity, which is sometimes called coincidence or serendipity.**++与此同时，你将会发现同步性的好处。 它也被称为巧合或意外。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2513', 'serene', '[sərin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=serene', '{adj.}++平静的，宁静的**++明朗的，清澈的**++(天气)晴朗的，无云的**++(心境、态度等)安详的**++[常S-]尊贵的(对皇族、贵族等的尊称)**{n.}++平静；宁静；安详**++晴朗的天空；平静的海面**{vt.}++使平静(或安详等)**', '++Either way, they were serene and unwilling to inflict pain on others—exactly like those who were given word of social acceptance.**++在任一种情况下，他们都很平静，不愿对他人造成痛苦——完全像那些收到通知被社会接受的人。**++And in the meantime the serene autumn afternoon is filtering through the walls of this little Calcutta room filling it, as a cup, with golden intoxication.**++这时，晴朗的秋日下午，阳光透过加尔各答这间小屋的四壁，充满了整个屋子，仿佛往一只酒杯里斟满金色的醇酒。**++On the other hand, if we cultivate a serene attitude and thoughts that are free from covetousness and are frankly honest and helpful, we shall call out the best in other people.**++另一方面，如果我们培养出一种平静的态度和思想，这种思想是从贪婪中解放出来的，是很坦白地诚实和有用的，我们应该能够唤起其他人心里最好的思想。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2514', 'sermon', '[sɝmən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sermon', '{n.}++布道，讲道**++冗长的讲话**++说教，训诫**++启示**{vt.}++对…布道；对…说教：**++对…布道；对…说教：**{vi.}++讲道，布道**', '++A typical day will begin with morning prayers, followed by a sermon on the significance of jihad.**++一个典型的训练日将会以晨祈开始，随后便是关于圣战意义方面的布道。**++This could be anything ranging from a boring lecture or sermon, to a monotonous conversation with people.**++这可以是任何东西，一次枯燥的演讲或布道，或者是人们单调的一段对话。**++Such was the position which the minister occupied, as he bowed his head forward on the cushions of the pulpit, at the close of his Election Sermon.**++当我们的这位牧师结束了他在庆祝选举日的布道，在讲坛的靠垫上向前垂着头时，所处的正是这样一个高位。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2515', 'serpentine', '[sɝpəntin]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=serpentine', '{adj.}++蛇的**++似蛇的，蛇状的**++(道路等)弯弯曲曲的，蜿蜒的**++阴险的，狡猾的；奸诈的**{n.}++弯弯曲曲的东西；有如盘蛇状的东西**{vt., vi.}++(使)迂回曲折地前进**{n.}', '++This is a serpentine road going through the Urals.**++这是一条蜿蜒的路穿过乌拉尔山。**++For example, the marble hierarchy includes multiple peer-level types of marble, such as travertine, serpentine, and onyx.**++例如，大理石层次结构包括多种对等级别的大理石类型，例如石灰华、蛇纹石和缟玛瑙。**++Like those of China, Japan’s dragons are usually serpentine creatures with clawed feet and lack the wings of their European counterparts.**++像中国的龙一样，日本的龙通常是蜿蜒的动物，拥有可以爬行的腿，而没有欧洲龙的翅膀。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2516', 'serrate', '[səret]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=serrate', '{adj.}++有锯齿边的**++(器械)有锯齿的**++【生物学、解剖学】锯齿状的**{vt.}++使有锯齿；使成锯齿状：**++使有锯齿；使成锯齿状：**', '++European perennial whose serrate leaves yield a yellow dye.**++欧洲终年植物，其锯齿状叶子可制黄色染料。**++Trees or shrubs. Leaves petiolate , entire or serrate at margin.**++乔木或灌木叶具叶柄，全缘的或有锯齿在边缘。**++North American deciduous tree (Ulmus americana) having double serrate leaves and winged fruits. It is grown chiefly as an ornamental shade tree but often dies from Dutch elm disease.**++一种北美落叶树（美洲榆），有双齿叶和双翼果，主要作为观赏性浓荫树，但常患荷兰榆树病而坏死。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2517', 'serried', '[sɛrɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=serried', '{adj.}++锯齿状的**++紧排的，密集的；拥挤的**{vt.}++serry的变形**{vt.}++使(队伍行列)靠紧，使密集**{vi.}++排紧；密集；拥挤**', '++Walking through the serried stone pillars,tourists feast their eyes on changing spots, feeling they are in aparadise where the Gods live.**++在不同的石柱间走动，游客享受着不停改变的景观，会觉得自己好像生在上帝住的天堂一样。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2518', 'servile', '[sɝ​vl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=servile', '{adj.}++奴隶的；奴仆的**++处于奴役地位的，受压迫的**++奴性的；卑贱的；奴颜媚骨的**++屈从的；盲从的(to)**++奴隶特有的，像奴隶一样的**++(文学、艺术等)无独创性的，模仿的**++【语言学】附属性的；(单词)非词根的**{n.}++奴性十足的人，奴颜屈膝者**++【语法学】附属性成分(指除词根以外的前缀、后缀等构词成分等)**', '++From involuntary idleness, servile dependence, penury, and useless labour, he has passed to toils of a very different nature, rewarded by ample subsistence.--This is an American....**++他经历厂被迫失业、卑屈的依赖、赤贫和无用的劳动之后，现在正从事一个性质完全不同的劳动，这种劳动将得到充足的物质报酬。**++Men, she believed, had created a domestic, servile role for women in order that men could havethe career and the opportunity to participate in making the great decisions of society.**++她认为男人为妇女创制了一个持家操劳的奴隶角色，为的是男人可以获得事业和机遇参与决定重大的社会抉择。**++Listen to Virginia Woolf on page 600 of A Room of One@s Own where she says, top of the left-hand column: For genius like Shakespeare@s is not born among labouring, uneducated, servile people.**++看看伍尔夫在《一间自己的房间》第600页,都说了些什么，左边一栏最上面：,“劳动者，未受教育和卑躬屈膝的人们之中，不会有如莎士比亚似的天才诞生。**');
