insert into GREWordBook values ('2545', 'sinew', '[sɪnju]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sinew', '{n.}++筋；【解剖学】肌腱**++[复数]肌肉；体力；精力的来源**++力量；精力**++[常用复数]主要资源；主要手段；主要依靠**++[废语]神经**{vt.}++给…以力量，加强；支持：**++使连结；使牢固**', '++He’ll strain every sinew at this World Cup.**++在本届杯赛上，他就是要卓越超群。**++Therefore the children of Israel eat not of the sinew which shrank， which is upon the hollow of the thigh， unto this day： because he touched the hollow of Jacob@s thigh in the sinew that shrank.**++32：32 故此，以色列人不吃大腿窝的筋，直到今日，因为那人摸了雅各大腿窝的筋。**++BHP strained every sinew to make its bid attractive to Canada and the province of Saskatchewan, where the target mines its potash.**++为了让自己的报价能吸引加拿大和目标公司开采钾盐所在的萨斯喀彻温省，必和必拓可谓竭尽全力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2546', 'singe', '[sɪndʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=singe', '{vt.}++把…的表面烫焦，烧焦…的浅表：**++燎掉(屠宰后动物)的毛：**++烧焦(尤指头发)的尖端，烫(发)：**++轻度伤害，微损；给…造成意外的苦恼(或麻烦等)：**++【纺织业】把…作烧毛处理**{vi.}++烫焦；轻微烧焦：**++烫焦；轻微烧焦：**{n.}++烧焦；烫焦；燎**++轻微的焦痕**', '++In French, the same saying exists: Singe qui voit, singe qui fait.**++法语中也有这样的说法：Singe qui voit, singe qui fait.**++"They singe the fur off, then sell the animals naked but intact," U.K. photographer David Maitland explained.**++“他们将皮毛烤掉，然后剥干净，整只完好地出售。” 英国摄影师大卫·梅特兰解释道。**++There is no need for a singe European state. Nor for a single political-economic authority.**++但建立一个单独的欧洲国家是没有必要的，也没有必要形成单独的政治经济权力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2547', 'sinuous', '[sɪnjʊəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sinuous', '{adj.}++弯曲的；蜿蜒的**++动作柔软的**++错综复杂的，情节曲折的**++邪门歪道的，不正当的**++(叶子边缘)呈深波状的**', '++The great creator raised his sinuous, powerful, flexible arm, and we know where we stand.**++伟大的造物主抬起了他弯曲的，有力的，灵活的手臂，我们知道了我们的立场。**++Why It@s Innovative: The sinuous Pythonbrug is one of the most modern bridges in Amsterdam, a city famous for its traditional canal bridges.**++创新点：阿姆斯特丹以运河桥著称，而蜿蜒的巨蛇桥是阿姆斯特丹最具现代气息的桥梁之一。**++The narrow, uneven, sinuous streets, full of angles and turns, were admirably chosen; the neighborhood of the Halles, in particular, a network of streets more intricate than a forest.**++令人折服地选择了那些狭窄、不平整、弯曲、凸凹、转拐的街道，特别是菜市场那一带，有着象森林一样紊乱的街道网。**');
