insert into GREWordBook values ('2562', 'slippery', '[slɪpəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=slippery', '{adj.}++滑的；致使打滑的 **++(问题等)需小心对待的**', '++The forest is thick and the moss is slippery.**++林深苔滑。**++In that time Turner hopes to catch thousands of the slippery fish for his smokehouse business in the New York Catskills.**++那个时候，特纳希望为他在纽约卡茨基尔的熏制房生意捉到数千条狡猾的鳗鱼。**++So it must be slippery outside. Do be careful!**++所以外面一定滑。一定要当心。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2563', 'slipshod', '[slɪpʃɑd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=slipshod', '{adj.}++不整洁的；潦草的；邋遢的**++马虎的，不严谨的**++破烂的，衣衫褴褛的**', '++Selling assets does not solve the problem, except in a very short-term slipshod accounting sense.**++除非在极短期内使用粗疏的会计方法来考察，否则出售资产不会解决问题。**++In other words, if you have allowed no time at the end of your project before it’s due, you run the risk of turning in slipshod work or not being able to complete it at all.**++换句话说，如果你在安排工作时间的时候没有考虑到特殊情况的话，你最终可能会交个烂摊子或者压根没时间去完成工作。**++Small firms with slipshod standards are being replaced by bigger, better ones. Where people are creating companies, they are doing so out of choice, not economic necessity.**++在某些层面上看这是一个好消息，那些不认真奉行标准的小公司正在被更大，更好的公司取代，在哪里创办公司将基于个人的选择而不再是经济的需要。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2564', 'sloppy', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sloppy', '{adj.}++潮湿的，湿污的**++溅湿的，溅污的**++泥泞的；(天气)多雨的，多雪的**++(食物、饮料)无味的，不好吃的**++[口语]马虎的；凌乱的**++邋遢的；不整洁的**++(衣服)不合身的，肥大的**++(飞机跑道等)潮湿且有水坑的**++(海洋等)风浪大起的**++(感情)激动的；过于感伤的**++11[俚语]喝醉的**', '++They pulled away in the fourth quarter helped by Miami@s sloppy play and turnovers.**++他们利用迈阿密人的粗心大意和失误在第四节一举甩开了对手。**++Ultimately, sloppy programming -- even if you achieve the desired result -- is going to result in sloppy performance.**++最终，即使您可以得到预期的结果，但草率的编程还是会导致拙劣的性能。**++Embroidery calls for great care. There must not be even a single sloppy stitch.**++刺绣要求很高， 一针也不能马虎。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2565', 'sloth', '[sloθ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sloth', '{n.}++懒惰，怠惰**++【动物】树懒科(Bradypodidae)动物;树懒 (Bradypus didactylus)**++／sləuɵ／ 一群熊**++[古语] 缓慢；延误**', '++In an unusual display of sloth caution on my part, however, I held back out of prudence.**++在一个对我来说非同寻常的对懒惰谨慎的展示，但是，我出于谨慎忍住发表评论的欲望。**++You know how there are times when we are really inspired to work, where other times we’ll feel like a total sloth?**++你知道当我们真正受启发而工作的时候怎么会有时间，其他我们总会感觉很懒惰的时候在哪里？**++They then found the same virus lurking in the genome of the three-toed sloth.**++然后他们发现同样的病毒也潜伏在三趾树懒基因组里。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2566', 'slouch', '[slaʊtʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=slouch', '{vi.}++没精打采地坐着(或站立)：**++(帽子等)低垂，耷拉：**{vt.}++使低垂；使耷拉：**++使低垂；使耷拉：**{n.}++没精打采坐(或站立、行走)的姿势**++萎靡不振的人；笨手笨脚的人；邋遢的人**++[口语] 懒汉；不中用的人**++(帽边等的)低垂，耷拉**', '++If you slouch, cross your legs, or look weak, it works against you.**++如果你没精打采，交叉双腿，看上去很虚弱，那么结果就对你不利。**++The reverse is also true. If you slouch, cross your legs, or look weak, it works against you. Sitting powerfully for just two minutes can make a psychological difference.**++反之亦如此。如果你没精打采，交叉双腿，看上去很虚弱，那么结果就对你不利。笔直地坐两分钟就能产生心理差异。**++It’s easy to slouch if you’re not constantly thinking about your posture (in fact, you’re probably even doing it while you read this article), but there’s good news: Your slouch is reversible.**++如果你没有时常考虑你的姿势（事实上你在读这篇文章时仍可能是这样），你很容易没精打采，但这里有个好消息：你的没精打采是可以改变的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2567', 'slovenly', '[slʌvnli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=slovenly', '{adj.}++不修边幅的，邋遢的**++懒散的；马虎的**{adv.}++不修边幅地，邋遢地**++懒散地；马虎地**', '++Not only does slumping over your keyboard give you chronic backache and make you look slovenly, it also increases your risk of heart disease, says The Journal of Neuroscience.**++不仅在你的键盘 给你的滑坡慢性背痛 使你看起来邋遢 它也增加你患心脏病的风险 称神经科学杂志》上。**++Obese people were also significantly more likely to be pictured from the side or rear, unclothed or in slovenly attire, eating unhealthy food and being lazy.**++肥胖者也更有可能是从侧面或者后面进行拍照，没穿衣服或者穿着邋遢，吃着不健康的食物而且表现懒惰。**++Such slovenly work habits will never produce good products.**++这样马马虎虎的工作习惯决不能生产出优质产品来。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2568', 'sluggard', '[slʌɡɚd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sluggard', '{n.}++懒汉，偷懒的人**{adj.}++懒汉般的，懒怠的**', '++Go to the ant, you sluggard; consider its ways and be wise!**++懒惰人啊，你去察看蚂蚁的动作，就可得智慧！**++As a door turns on its hinges, so a sluggard turns on his bed.**++门在枢纽转动，懒惰人在床上也是如此。**++It is no wonder the Biblical Solomon rebuked the lazy man: "Go to the ant, you sluggard; consider its ways and be wise!**++难怪圣经中的索罗门职责那些懒汉们说：“到蚂蚁中去，你这个懒鬼；思考它们的方法，做一个智慧的人！”**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2569', 'sluggish', '[slʌɡɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sluggish', '{adj.}++懒怠的，不好动的**++无活力的；呆滞的**++功能不佳的；性能不好的**++慢的；缓慢的**', '++Rather than feeling healthy however, they often feel bloated and sluggish – symptoms of water retention which can be caused by the hidden salt in these salads.**++相比于感觉良好，人们更多的是感觉臃肿和懒洋洋的—这是水潴留的症状，而这些症状可由沙拉中隐藏的盐导致。**++For the few weeks prior, she had been feeling a little sluggish, but nothing else.**++在此前的几个星期里，她只是感觉有些浑身无力，没有其他症状。**');
