insert into GREWordBook values ('2700', 'subjugate', '[sʌbdʒuɡet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subjugate', '{vt.}++制服，征服，使屈从：**++使从属，使隶属：**++克制，抑制：**', '++With your new army, continue to subjugate the planet’s other inhabitants using science.**++你有新军队在手，可以继续用科学去征服这个星球上其他的居民。**++That the Japanese, in thrall to China from time immemorial, should try to subjugate their vast neighbor seemed an inversion of the cosmic order.**++对于自上古时代起便臣服于中国的日本人来说，试图征服自己庞大的邻国，这看上去有些悖逆常理。**++The engineering feat, called the South-North Water Diversion Project, is China’s most ambitious attempt to subjugate nature.**++这项工程被称为南水北调工程，是一项中国试图征服自然的雄心计划。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2701', 'sublime', '[səblaɪm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sublime', '{adj.}++(思想、语言等)高尚的，崇高的**++雄伟的，壮丽的；令人崇敬的，庄严的**++超群的，卓越的，出众的**++极度的**++[口语、常含贬义]极端的；十足的；惊人的**++[常作S-][用于称呼之前]至高无上的，至尊至贵的**++[诗歌用语]神采超群的**++[古语]喜气洋洋的，兴高采烈的**++[古语]突出的，高出的**++[废语]傲慢的，高傲的**{n.}++[the sublime]**++崇高，庄严，高尚，雄伟**++至高无上；顶点，极点，绝顶**{vt.}++使净化，使纯化：**++使变得高尚(或崇高)**++使变得雄伟壮丽(或庄严)**++使变得超群出众：**++【化学】使升华**{vi.}++【化学】升华**', '++The one is magnificent, the other sublime.**++一个是宏伟的，另一个是崇高的。**++Everything in Heaven should be utterly sublime.**++天堂里的一切都应当是绝对庄严的。**++"Good" is not the word for it.You ought to have said "sublime".**++“好”这字眼在这儿用得不恰当，你应该说“崇高”。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2702', 'subliminal', '[,sʌblɪmɪnl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subliminal', '{adj.}++微小得难以察觉的**++【心理学】下意识的，潜(在)意识的；(刺激)阈下的**{n.}++【心理学】潜意识，阈下意识**', '++Experts say picking up new skills in your sleep may not be possible, but subliminal learing is posible to enhance information that is already there.**++专家称，在睡梦过程中掌握一门新技能是不大可能的，但潜意识学习则有可能会巩固已学到的知识。**++But because we are so used to these effects they become subliminal, automatic - they\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\@re so embedded in our everyday lives that we\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\@re unaware of them.**++正是由于我们的司空见惯才让这些影响变成了我们的潜意识——他们深深植根于我们的日常生活而我们却毫无觉察。**++But it contained an almost subliminal suggestion that somehow the clock could be turned back—that the events of the Afghanistan war’s first months could be replayed, this time with a better outcome.**++但它也隐含了一个几乎是潜意识中的建议，那就是，时光可能会倒流——阿富汗战争的第一个月的光景可能会重演，这一次，可能结果会更理想。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2703', 'submerge', '[səbmɝdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=submerge', '{vt.}++淹没，沉浸；使沉没：**++把…放入(或浸入)水中(或其他液体中)：**++使沉浸，使集中精力于：**++湮没，湮灭：**++使沦落，使沉沦：**{vi.}++潜入水中，没于水中：**++湮没，湮灭：**', '++If sea levels rise, it means some parts of land will submerge under water.**++一旦海平面升高，意味着一部分陆地将淹没在水下。**++South Korea feared that a sudden release of water from the dam could submerge part of Seoul, and hurried to build a counter-dam downstream called Peace Dam.**++韩国担心，朝鲜突然开闸放水会将首尔部分地区淹没，于是赶紧建立了一个顺流区的抗洪坝，名为“和平大坝”。**++At the first sign of danger the submarine would submerge.**++一有危险迹象，潜艇就会潜入水中。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2704', 'submissive', '[səbmɪsɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=submissive', '{adj.}++顺从的，惟命是从的；卑躬屈膝的**++谦恭的，谦卑的**', '++I feel clear that I am submissive, yet this man left me feeling battered and belittled.**++我可以清楚地感觉到我是顺从的，但这个男人让我有受伤和被贬低的感觉。**++Yes, she was submissive and sweet at the store, but most of these girls are the opposite, privately, of what they are in public.**++不错，她在店里显得很顺从，很甜美。 可是这些女孩大多数在私下里都跟在外面是完全相反的。**++Another aspect is that middle-class and upper-class men were expected to be very controlled — to control their emotions, their servants and their women — and women were expected to be submissive.**++另一方面就是：中等阶层和上层的男人们都应该性格克制，他们能控制自己的感情，能掌控家里的仆人们和女人们——女人应该是柔顺的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2705', 'subordinate', '[səbɔːdɪnɪt (for n. &adj.) ; səbɔːdɪˌnet (for v.)]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subordinate', '{adj.}++下级的，级别低的；次级的**++次要的，第二位的**++顺从的；低下的**++顺从的，服从的**++附属的，隶属的**++【语法学】**++从属的**++从属连接词的**++从句的**{n.}++下级，下属，部下**++从属物，附属物**{vt.}++使成为下级，使位于较低级别：**++使列于次要地位，使成为次要(常与 to 连用)：**++使服从，使从属(常与 to 连用)：**++征服，控制：**', '++All the other issues were subordinate to this one.**++相对这个问题，其他问题都是次要的。**++In the army, lieutenants are subordinate to captains.**++在陆军中, 中尉是上尉的下级。**++The deparment manager devolved the work on a subordinate.**++部门经理把工作移交给下属。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2706', 'subservient', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subservient', '{adj.}++有利的，有益的，有用的**++从属的，附属的；辅助的**++屈从的，恭顺的，低声下气的，俯首帖耳的**', '++The Parliament which used to be a subservient arm of the Executive is now a vigorous forum for debate, and an important check on Executive power.**++议会过去是行政部门的一个唯唯诺诺的臂膊，现在成为了一个举行辩论的活跃论坛，成为了行政权力的一个重要制衡。**++They should see themselves as aliens,as exiles, and yet they should see themselves as properly subservient,honorable, well behaved exiles in a Roman context.**++他们应该把自己当做入境者，寄居者，并应该把自己看做是,适当屈从的和可敬的，行为良好的在罗马的寄居者。**++We tend to expect certain things from our wives but we cannot bring ourselves to show honor and respect to such that is subservient.**++我们期待妻子能给我们某些东西，可是我们不能表现出那些让人觉得屈从的荣誉与尊重。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2707', 'subside', '[səbsaɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subside', '{vi.}++下降，下沉，下陷；沉到底；沉淀：**++平静，平息：**++减弱，消退；消失，退落：**++[口语]坐下，跪下；躺下：**', '++The lees of wine gradually subside.**++酒渣慢慢地沉淀下来。**++After a few minutes,the amylum began to subside.**++几分钟之后，淀粉开始沉淀。**++Once the excitement, the motivation and the initial momentum subside (and they will), what will keep you doing what you need to do, to create the change you want to see in your world?**++人一旦兴奋，动机和最初的动力就会减弱（他们会这样），什么会让你保持做你要做的，去创造出这种在你的世界里你想看到的改变？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2708', 'subsidiary', '[səbsɪdɪɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subsidiary', '{adj.}++辅助的，补充的，附带的**++次要的**++附属的，附设的，隶属的**++补助的，补贴的；拿津贴的**{n.}++辅助者，副手**++辅助物，附属物；附件**++＝ subsidiary company**++【音乐】副主题**', '++The deals usually involve small firms with specialist technology, which sell a stake or a subsidiary rather than the whole company, typically for a few million dollars.**++参与交易的通常是有拥专门技术的小公司，且只卖部分股份或一个子公司而非整个公司，通常交易额在几百万美元。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2709', 'subsidy', '[sʌbsədi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subsidy', '{n.}++(政府、慈善机构等分发的)补助金；津贴，补贴**++捐款，资助；拨款**++(国家之间的)财政援助**++【历史】(英国国会拨给王室的)特别津贴**', '++The great advantage of a subsidy, indeed, from the standpoint of the public, is that it makes this fact so clear.**++站在公众角度而言，补贴的最大好就是它使得财富专业的这样一个事实变得如此清晰。**++If Copenhagen does not reach agreement on it we will do it next year, either via a subsidy, levy or tax.**++如果在哥本哈根没有达成协议，我们明年就会自己来，不管是用补贴还是征税的方法。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2710', 'substantial', '[səbstænʃəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=substantial', '{adj.}++多的，大量的；大的**++真实的，实在的，有实质的**++独立(存在)的**++坚固的，牢固的，结实的**++富裕的，殷实的**++(价值)重大的**++实质上的，物质的**++本质的**++重要的；实际价值(或效果)的**++【哲学】实体的**{n.}++[常用复数]**++实质性的东西**++内容充实的东西；有实际价值的东西**++重要的事物(或材料等)**++【解剖学】质，物质(指组成器官、组织、身体等的物质)**', '++The thesis may at first strike one as extreme, but substantial evidence exists to support it.**++这一论文起初给人以偏激的印象，但是存在大量的证据支持这一观点。**++To go there, however, he will have to prove that the expandable habitat does indeed work, and also generate substantial returns on his investment in LEO, to provide the necessary cash.**++然而为了达到那个目标，他将要证明可伸展太空屋确实能用，而且需要他在近地轨道飞行的投资产生大量的回报来提供必需资金。**++There is also substantial information on conventions and usage.**++此外，还有大量关于约定和用法的信息。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2711', 'substantiate', '[səbstænʃɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=substantiate', '{vt.}++证明，证实：**++使具体化，使实体化；实现：**++充实，加强；使有实质内容：**', '++Tracking reaching behavior or eye movements will be necessary to substantiate the findings, she adds.**++追踪到行为或者眼神移动将进一步证实这个结果，她补充说。**++The building will be used as a laboratory and educational facility to substantiate the Living Building Challenge.**++该建筑将被用作实验室和教育设施，以证实活建筑难题的可行性。**++A visit to a salon will substantiate these observations.**++一次在沙龙里的访问将证实这些观察资料。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2712', 'substantive', '[səbstæntɪv]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=substantive', '{adj.}++独立的，独立存在的**++真正的，实际的**++实在的，实质性的；本质的**++大量的，数量可观的；重大的**++(染料)直接的，无需媒染剂的**++【法律】实体的；规定权利和义务的**++【语法学】**++名词的**++名词作用的**++表示存在的**{n.}++独立的人，自立的人**++独立存在的事物，实际存在的事物**++【语法学】**++名词；名词性词组**++体词**++名词性实词**', '++Sweden also benefits from substantive industry research, which in turn relies on the quality of public institutions.**++瑞典也因为大量的工业研究而获益，后者又依赖于公共研究机构的质量。**++The US should insist on a substantive agenda as a precondition for any Obama visit.**++美国应该坚持将实质性的议事日程作为奥巴马访问的前提。**++This is a substantive, serious meeting and he looks forward to it, but I don@t have any policy change announcements to make for you from here.**++这将是一次实质性的，严肃的会谈，多尼隆期待这次会谈，不过我这次没有任何有关政策改变的消息要向你们宣布。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2713', 'substitute', '[sʌbstɪtut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=substitute', '{n.}++代替者，代理人**++替换者；替补运动员；代人应征入伍者**++替代物，代用品**++【语法学】代用词；代用语(如用 to 代替不定式短语，用 do代替句子等)**++[苏格兰英语]【法律】副职**++【航海学】代用旗，代用小信号旗**++【采矿】转接器**{adj.}++代替的；代用的；替补的**++用代用品的；由代用品构成的**{vt.}++用…代替，代以：**++由…接替，派…替换：**++【化学】使取代，置换**++[废语]接替，代替**{vi.}++做…的代理人，接替：**++代替，代用：**++【化学】取代**', '++Nothing could substitute for mother@s milk.**++什么也替代不了母乳。**++Emotion should never be a substitute for sound policy.**++感情不能代替政策。**++The problem of little fuel has been outworked by the substitute.**++燃料不足的问题已用替代品予以解决了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2714', 'subterfuge', '[sʌbtɚfjudʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subterfuge', '{n.}', '++Men and women were equally guilty of subterfuge.**++男人和女人都有一样的诡计.**++Their communication is natural and direct, without subterfuge or cunning, and every movement has meaning.**++它们的交流自然而直接，没有诡计没有欺骗，每一分每一秒都是那么的有意义。**++They may fight you openly in meetings, through the media, or with the subterfuge of palace intrigue. And you@ll need to make your case in all those venues.**++他们可能会在会议上公开地反对你，可能通过媒体或是一些阴谋诡计来反对你，你必须在上述所有场合都表明自己的观点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2715', 'subtle', '[sʌtl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subtle', '{adj.}++(流体、气味等)稀薄的，淡淡的；淡雅的，微微的**++隐约的，模模糊糊的**++纤细的，极细的**++难以理解的，难以捉摸的，微妙的**++细微的；神秘的**++细心的，精细的；敏感的，有洞察力的**++灵巧的，精妙的；精湛的**++狡猾的，狡诈的，诡计多端的**++在不知不觉中加剧的，暗中为害的；(作用)隐伏的**++灵巧的，有独创性的**', '++What I wanted did not belong to me by right and whilst it could not be refused tome in quite same way, we still have subtle punishments for anyone who insists on what they are and what they want.**++我所想要的，并不理当属于我，而虽然它也不能以完全同样的方式拒我于外，但是任何人若坚持要做某种人或是想要某些东西，我们仍然会给他很微妙的惩罚。**++The answer might be as subtle as how you made eye contact or where you were standing.**++或许是因为你们的眼神接触或者是你所站的位置，这些微妙的动作所影响的。**++They’re great for easily adding lots of interest and depth to a design, whether it be a huge background pattern or just some subtle textures here and there.**++它们实在太棒了，无论是一幅巨大的背景图案还是只有一些精细的纹理，都能轻易地为设计处处增添不少吸引力与深度。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2716', 'subvert', '[sʌbvɝt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subvert', '{vt.}++颠覆，推翻(政权等)：**++使覆灭，使毁灭；破坏：**++腐蚀，败坏(道德等)：**', '++The rebellious troops attempted to subvert the present government.**++叛军曾企图推翻现政府。**++There are other idioms that can similarly ignore or subvert object lifecycle management and can also lead to memory leaks.**++还有一些其他的情况可以类似地忽略或破坏对象生命周期管理，并导致内存泄漏。**++If you do not carefully control who has write access to the file system, a user can subvert the product security controls (such as auditing) by simply hand editing the configuration files.**++如果不谨慎地控制谁对文件系统有写访问权限，用户只需手工编辑配置文件，就可以破坏产品的安全性控制（比如审计）。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2717', 'succinct', '[səksɪŋkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=succinct', '{adj.}++简洁的，简明的，扼要的**++紧缩的，压缩在小范围内的**++[古语]束紧的；(衣服)紧身的**', '++EPF and RUP address this concern by separating a rich reference library of practices from a succinct description of how the team chooses to work in their specific project.**++EPF和RUP通过将一个实践丰富的引用库，与这个团队是如何选择到他们特殊项目中工作的简洁描述分离来解决这个问题。**++Manufacturing, logistics, supply chain management, energy management, recycling and waste management all break down into succinct business processes, with human tasks and interventions.**++制造、后勤、供应链管理、能源管理、回收和废物管理都可以分解为简洁的业务流程，其中包含人类任务和干预。**++I believe that longer templates in multiple languages will make the system unmaintainable in short order, so I recommend sticking with one language if you can -- and let that language be succinct.**++我认为以多种语言编写的更长的模板，将使系统不能得到及时维护，所以，我建议您，只要 可能，请坚持只使用一种语言 —— 并保持语言的简洁。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2718', 'succor', '[sʌkɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=succor', '{n., vt.}', '++These refugees are very grateful to the government@s succor.**++这些难民非常感激政府的救援。**++Because we do not rest,we lost our way.We lose the nourishment that gives us succor.**++因为我们从不休息，以致迷失了方向。 失去了为我们补充能量的营养。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2719', 'succumb', '[səkʌm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=succumb', '{vi.}++屈服，屈从；听任；弃置(常与to连用)：**++被压垮，死于过度劳累(常与to连用)：**', '++And yet I succumb to watching it.**++然而，我却需要看它，向它屈服。**++Whatever you do, don@t succumb to it.**++无论你做什么，都不要屈服于它。**++But why did a once-mighty civilisation succumb to the West?**++但为什么，一个一度强大的文明竟会屈服于西方呢？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2720', 'suffocate', '[sʌfəket]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=suffocate', '{vt.}++把…闷死，使窒息而死：**++使窒息，使呼吸困难：**++使感到气闷：**++闷熄：**++抑制，扼制；阻止…的发展：**{vi.}++被闷死：**++窒息，透不过气，呼吸困难：**++感到气闷**++受扼制，受压制：**', '++If you stayed seated, he said, you@d suffocate.**++如果你还留在座位上，他说，你就窒息了。**++You don’t “need” to be single, being single will only suffocate your personal growth.**++你没有必要恢复单身，单身的状态只能阻碍你的个人成长。**++There is very little air in that space. But not so little that we might suffocate, and thus create a story.**++那个空间只有那么一点空气，但也没有少到让我们可能窒息，免得产生一个故事。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2721', 'suffuse', '[səfjuz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=suffuse', '{vt.}', '++Better still pour your love out to suffuse any chance of negative energies turning nasty.**++更好的方式依旧是灌输你的爱充满任何的地方而不给任何负面下流的能量机会。**++This sensitivity to feel should suffuse the whole endeavor, from the foundational user experience work to the final UI.**++这种对感受的敏锐，涵盖了所有的努力，从基本的用户体验到最终的UI设计。**++This includes user interface design and the brand qualities that suffuse the site’s visual language, content, and user interactions.**++这包括用户界面设计和充溢网站的视觉语言，内容和用户交互之中的品牌特质。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2722', 'sulk', '[sʌlk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sulk', '{vi.}++愠怒，怒而不语：**++愠怒，怒而不语：**{n.}++愠怒的发作(或样子)**++[常用复数]生气，怒而不语，愠怒**++[亦作 sulker]愠怒者**', '++You must promise me that you won@t sulk if I tell you all about it.**++你得保证你不生气，我才肯把一切都告诉你。**++Just because your bias or your tendency or your experience tells you to sulk and stonewall, you don@t have to react that way.**++如果只因为您的偏见或者是您的意向或经验就让您生气或采取抵制行为，那么最好不要那样做。**++Ronaldo may sulk if things aren’t going his way, Deco is on the verge of retirement, Nani is more of an impact player and Simao usually bottles under pressure.**++罗纳尔多一旦事情进行得不顺利就爱生气，德科已经差不多在退役边缘了，纳尼更多的是个冲击型球员，西芒则常常会被压力给打垮。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2723', 'sullen', '[sʌlən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sullen', '{adj.}++愠怒的，不高兴的，闷闷不乐的**++愁眉不展的，苦闷的**++沮丧的**++(声音等)沉闷的**++(颜色、色彩等)不鲜明的，阴暗的**++阴沉的**++(流水等)缓慢的；停滞的**++[废语]邪恶的，不吉利的**{n.}++[用复数][古语]愠怒，生气，情绪消沉**', '++Heathcliff, dear! you should not be sullen now.**++希刺克厉夫，亲爱的！ 现在你不该沉着脸。**++And I felt just like a sullen new mom, not ready for her role.**++并且我就像一个闷闷不乐的新妈妈，来不及应付她的角色。**++Henry was a neat man, his lab coat clean, what remained of his hair combed and parted precisely; he was quiet, but said enough not to seem sullen.**++亨利是一个整洁的男士，他的实验工作服很干净，他的头发梳理过，而且整齐的分开；他很安静，话多的刚好让他不会显得阴沉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2724', 'summary', '[sʌməri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=summary', '{adj.}++总结性的，概括的，概述的**++简明的，扼要的**++即时的，即刻的**++简化了的；草率的**++【法律】简易的，即决的**++[废语]大体上的，不详细的**++[废语]最高的，顶点的**{n.}++总结，概略，摘要，一览**++[废语]结局；顶点**', '++His summary prosifies the poem.**++他的摘要把诗散文化了。**++Then, write a quick summary of the conversation and why youare perfect for the job.**++然后，写一个谈话的快速摘要以及为什么你非常适合这份工作。**++The Controller Summary provides a list of all the controller actions in an application in one report.**++控制器概要提供了一份报告，列出了应用程序中所有的控制器行为。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2725', 'summit', '[sʌmɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=summit', '{n.}++最高峰，极顶，最高点**++极度，极点**++(成就、抱负等的)顶峰，巅峰**++(政府、外交等的)最高官阶，首脑；最高级会谈**++【数学】锥顶，锥体顶点**{adj.}++最高级的，国家元首之间的**{vi.}++参加最高级会谈，参加峰会，参加首脑会晤：**++达到性欲高潮**{vt.}++使达到顶峰**', '++All their attempts at reaching the summit failed.**++他们攀登顶峰的一切尝试都失败了。**++But are these the summit of our values, of our aspirations of society?**++但这些是我们的价值观、我们对社会的抱负的顶点吗？**++Should you reach the summit you would have only one desire, and that to descend and be with those who dwell in the deepest valley.**++一旦你登上顶峰，你就只有一个愿望，那就是往下走入最深的峪谷里，和那里的人民一同生活。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2726', 'summon', '[sʌmən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=summon', '{vt.}++召唤;召来(常与 away, to 或 from连用)：**++【法律】传唤，传讯：**++号召；召集：**++鼓起，激起，使振作(常与 up 连用)：**++要求，请求；要…投降：**', '++Parliament has powers to introduce and pass legislation, summon and impeach ministers or the president.**++议会拥有提出和通过法律、召集弹劾内阁成员或总统的权力。**++Her magnanimity provoked his tears: he wept wildly, kissing her supporting hands, and yet could not summon courage to speak out.**++她的宽宏大量惹起他的眼泪；他发狂地哭着，吻她那扶着他的手，却还不能鼓起勇气说出来。**++Yet we are still heirs to a noble struggle for freedom. And now we must summon all of our might and moral suasion to meet the challenges of a new age.**++然而我们依然是为争取自由而战的崇高使命的继承者，我们必须召唤我们所有的力量和道义的呼声应对新时代的各种挑战。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2727', 'sumptuous', '[sʌmptʃuəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sumptuous', '{adj.}++奢侈的；昂贵的**++豪华的，华丽的**', '++The next two formulas are from the Cucumber Growers Association, and are simple yet sumptuous treats for your face.**++接下来的两种方法来自黄瓜种植者协会，仍是简单而又对你的脸是奢侈的款待。**++If you can@t have sumptuous play at a World Cup you at least need underdog valour and surprising outcomes to discuss in the pub.**++既然在世界杯上打不出华丽的足球，那么你至少要拥有哀兵之勇，以及足成酒吧谈资的冷门结果。**++But inside, it was fitted with electric windows - rare for the time - power steering, sumptuous leather seats and a decent sound system.**++但是从内部来说，他装备了电动窗（当时很稀少哦）助力转向，豪华皮革座椅，高级的音响系统。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2728', 'sunder', '[sʌndɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sunder', '{vt.}++隔离，分开；分裂；断开，切断，割裂：**++隔离，分开；分裂；断开，切断，割裂：**{vi.}++分离；断开；碎裂**', '++For now will I break his yoke from off thee, and will burst thy bonds in sunder.**++现在我必从你颈项上折断他的轭，扭开他的绳索。**++He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and brake their bands in sunder.**++他从黑暗中，和死荫里，领他们出来，折断他们的绑索。**++The lord of that servant will come in a day when he looketh not for him, and at an hour when he is not aware, and will cut him in sunder, and will appoint him his portion with the unbelievers.**++在他想不到的日子，不知道的时辰，那仆人的主人要来，重重的处治他，或作把他腰斩了定他和不忠心的人同罪。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2729', 'supercilious', '[,supɚsɪlɪəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supercilious', '{adj.}++高傲的，傲慢的；盛气凌人的，目空一切的**++[古语]=superciliary**', '++Her supercilious attitude enraged me.**++她的傲慢态度使我极为愤怒。**++This supercilious attitude relegates me to the level of the commonplace.**++这种目空一切的心态把我归入大路货的档次。**++Now he was a sturdystraw-haired man of thirty with a rather hard mouth and a supercilious manner.**++如今的他已是个三十岁的卷发男人，说话僵冷，举止高傲。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2730', 'superficial', '[,supɚfɪʃl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superficial', '{adj.}++表面的，外部的；外表的**++表皮的**++表面上的；表面性的**++肤浅的，浅薄的**++草率的，粗略的**++微不足道的**++面的，面积的，平方的**{n.}++[the superficial]浅薄的人;表面文章**++[用复数]表面，外表；外部**', '++Happily, there was no apparent discomfort to any of the animals, although therewere some changes in pigmentation and superficial damage to the skin.**++令人高兴的是，虽然有某些色素沉着的改变和皮肤表面的损伤，这些动物没有出现明显的不适。**++The only problem is that you have no system to what you do, you shadow them and copy the superficial parts of their life and get exhausted doing it.**++问题是你对自己所做的没有一个系统的整体概念。 你只是跟随模仿了他们生活中表面的一部分，最终只会感到疲惫。**++Filial piety should not be expressed via superficial “performance”, but via children’s genuine care and love for their parents.**++孝顺不应该通过表面的“表演”来表现，而是应该通过孩子们对父母真正的关爱来表达。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2731', 'superfluous', '[sʊpɝflʊəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superfluous', '{adj.}++多余的，过剩的，过多的**++不必要的；不相干的**++[废语]奢侈的；铺张的**', '++So she never said superfluous words to him.**++于是她从来都不对他说多余的话。**++Respond by letting them know how much, to the cent, they owe you for superfluous texts the next time you’re together.**++下次你们在一起时，让他们知道因为这多余的信息，他们欠你多少钱，精确到美分。**++Considerable sums of money passed through his hands, but nothing could induce him to make any change whatever in his mode of life, or add anything superfluous to his bare necessities.**++大笔大笔的款项都经过他的手，但没有任何东西能稍稍改变他的生活方式，或使他在他所必需的用品以外增添一点多余的东西。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2732', 'superimpose', '[,supərɪmpoz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=superimpose', '{vt.}++把…放在…之上(常与on或upon连用)：**++加上，添上；附加上(常与on或upon连用)：**++【电影、电视】叠印，叠加(画面)**{vi.}++(数字等)重叠**', '++Mentally superimpose the above graph on your desktop (or if you really want, draw it as your background).**++想象中 把上面的图形叠放 到你计算机的桌面上（或者，如果愿意，可以把它设成桌面背景）。**++It can superimpose data, maps, and graphics on-the-fly, upon any screen and from any video source, including DoD and public computer networks.**++它可以添加数据、地图和空中图形，在任何屏幕上和从任何视频来源，包括国防部和公共计算机网络。**++I can understand this limitation: it@s not usually easy to superimpose a regular lattice of information upon an XML document; such is the mismatch between extensible hierarchies and rigid tables.**++我完全理解这种局限性，要将规整的信息表格添加到 XML 文档通常并非易事，这就是可扩展层次结构和严整表格的不匹配。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2733', 'supersede', '[,supɚsid]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supersede', '{vt.}++代替，取代：**++接替，充任；使让位：**++废弃：**++占先于；紧接着…而来到：**++【法律】延期(或中止)…的审理**{vi.}++推迟行动；忍住，克制：**++推迟行动；忍住，克制：**', '++In the future, robots will supersede human beings for very heavy work.**++今后，机器人必将取代人类的繁重劳动。**++Will multiple versions of the same application run concurrently, or does a new version supersede an older version?**++同一应用程序的多个版本是否可以同时运行，或者新版本是否会取代旧版本？**++Confusingly, the annual tax return does not supersede an existing monthly requirement to report and pay tax on non-taxed income if total earnings exceed a certain threshold.**++复杂的是，这一新政策并不代替个人收入如果超过一定数额，那么就要每月报告并对非税收入缴税的已有政策。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2734', 'supine', '[supaɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supine', '{adj.}++仰卧的；面朝上的**++[诗歌用语]向后靠的，向后倾斜的**++怠惰的，懒散的，无精打采的**++(精神、道德等)因循守旧的，消极的**++掌心向上的 **++掌心朝外的**{n.}++【语法学】**++(拉丁语中宾格、与格、夺格中的)动名词(如mirābile dictū中的dictú)**++(英语的)带to的不定式**++非谓语动词**', '++Reading is a quiet activity and it will often induce sleep in the supine position. Especially if it@s a dreary textbook or work paper.**++阅读是一种很安静的活动，特别是在阅读工作文件或者阅读的内容很枯燥时，仰卧的姿势容易使人入睡。**++When supine, he had severely reduced blood flow through his brain returning to his heart.**++在仰卧的时候，由大脑流向心脏的血流会出现神经性减少。**++A referee traduced, a nation conned, a morally demented coach, an unrepentant perpetrator, supine governing bodies, a contagion of embarrassment across France: all in all, a grand night in Paris.**++毁誉的裁判，受骗的国家，疯狂的教练，不知悔改的罪人，懒散昏庸的监管，蔓延全国的尴尬：总而言之，巴黎上演了伟大之夜。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2735', 'supplant', '[səplænt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supplant', '{vt.}++(以暴力、阴谋等手段)排挤掉，撵走；篡夺…的位置：**++代替；取代：**++[古语]使垮台**++[废语]使跌倒**++[废语]根除，连根拔掉**', '++No man could supplant him.**++没有人能够代替他的工作。**++He was hanged for plotting to supplant the king.**++他因阴谋篡夺皇位而被绞死。**++Not all of these have asserted their dominance yet, and there’s no guarantee that they’ll ever totally supplant more traditional rules and ways of working.**++并非所有的这些都已经家喻户晓，而且也不能保证他们将会最终取代那些传统的规则和工作方式。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2736', 'supple', '[sʌpl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supple', '{adj.}++易弯曲的，柔韧的**++柔软的，富于弹性的**++适应性强的；(思想)易适应的**++随和的，易相处的，柔顺的**++逢迎的，巴结的，讨好的**++流畅的，顺畅的**++[苏格兰英语]狡猾的**{vt.}++使柔软**++使柔顺，使顺从**++[废语](擦涂药膏)减轻(痛苦等)**{vi.}++[古语]**++变柔软**++变顺从**', '++I often do yoga, so I@m quite supple.**++我常常做瑜伽，所以我的身体很柔软。**++Moisturizer is the key to soft, supple skin in winter.**++在冬季，润肤霜是保持皮肤柔软细滑的密钥。**++In 1823, he patented what was the first truly waterproof fabric, supple enough to be used in clothing.**++1823年，他获得了第一个真正的防水织物专利，这种布料相当柔软，可用来做服装。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2737', 'supplement', '[sʌplɪmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supplement', '{n.}++增补，补充；增补(或补充)物**++(书籍、文件等的)补遗，补编；附录**++(报刊的)增刊，副刊**++补品，营养补给物**++(高蛋白的)补养性饲料**++【几何学】**++补角**++补弧**{vt.}++增补；补编：**++补充…的不足：**', '++I use cloth napkins and cleaning cloths entirely, and I supplement with paper.**++我完全使用餐巾布和清洁布，有时候补充使用餐巾纸。**++I say "almost” because some women will find they need to supplement their newborn’s diet with formula.**++我说“几乎”是因为一些女性发现他们需要为新生儿购买配方食品来作补充。**++In addition, in the fourth article in this series, you will learn how to write your own analyzers to supplement those shipped with the tool itself.**++此外，在本系列的第四篇文章中，您将学习如何编写 您自己的分析程序以补充该工具本身所提供的那些分析程序。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2738', 'supplicate', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supplicate', '{vi.}++恳求，哀求；祈求：**++[英国英语](尤指向牛津大学等)提出学位申请：**{vt.}++哀求，乞求：**++祈祷，祈求：**', '++Therefore never supplicate. Appreciate.**++所以，绝不要祈求。要感激。**++Also , you could be a guy who supplicate in his behavior to women , especially good-looking women .**++另外，您也可能是一个对女人苦苦哀求的人，特别是漂亮的女人。**++We supplicate your majesty to grant him amnesty.**++我们恳求恳求陛下给予他特赦。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2739', 'supposition', '[,sʌpəzɪʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=supposition', '{n.}++假想，臆测**++假定(或推测)的行为**++冒充，假冒；篡改**++靠不住，有问题；有待探讨**++见解，看法**', '++I cannot even entertain the supposition that ...;**++我甚至不能想像...**++As for the spiral itself, current supposition is that this is the result of a star in a binary star system entering the planetary nebula phase, when its outer atmosphere is ejected.**++至于螺旋本身，最近的推测是这是双子星系统中的一个恒星进入行星星云阶段的结果，此时它的外层大气会被喷出。**++Were the similarities to Way of the Dragon brought up, leading to the supposition that this is a remake?**++《太极》在情节上与《猛龙过江》有点相似，但凭这点就能推测出它是一部翻拍之作？**');
