insert into GREWordBook values ('2939', 'variegated', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=variegated', '{vt.}++variegate的变形**{adj.}++杂色的；带斑点的**++多种多样的，多样化的**{vt.}++使呈杂色，使色彩斑驳**++使不同，使差异；使多样化**', '++@There is a variegated thread that goes purple to white then back to purple,@ he said.**++“有一种杂色线，它的颜色从紫色变成白色，然后又变回紫色”，他说。**++They exhibit a most conspicuous figure in this great and variegated picture; they too enter for a great share in the pleasing perspective displayed in these thirteen provinces.**++在这幅伟大的杂色图画里，他们展现出一幅最引人注目的图像。 在这十三个省展现出的令人喜悦的前景里，有一大部分是他们的。**++The rippling, variegated strips of green light and blue shade may be replaced with deep purples, pale pinks, a grey dark as pewter or a greenish beige, like sand.**++那绿色的光线还有那蓝色的阴影在荡漾着，形成斑驳的条纹，这些条纹也许有时候会变成深紫色，或浅桃红色，或像白蜡般的暗黑色，或带绿的米黄色，就像海边的沙滩一样。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2940', 'varnish', '[vɑrnɪʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=varnish', '{n.}++清漆，亮漆**++光泽面**++虚饰；外表**++[英国英语]指甲油**{vt.}++给…上清漆：**++文饰，粉饰，添油加醋：**', '++The floor is coated with varnish.**++地板上涂了一层清漆。**++In fact, the chrome yellow chemical reaction occurred between the layers of varnish and paint.**++实际上，铬黄的化学反应在光泽面和颜料面之间也会发生。**++Varnish is the glossy protective layer applied to wooden furniture and other surfaces.**++（清漆）是用于木质家具和其他表面的光滑的保护层。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2941', 'vault', '[vɔlt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vault', '{n.}++【建筑工程】拱顶；穹隆**++拱顶室；(尤指)地下拱顶室；地窖**++地下储藏室；酒窖**++墓穴**++[美国英语](银行等的)保险库；金库**++【解剖学】穹隆；腔拱**{vt.}++给…盖以拱顶**++作成穹形**{vi.}++成穹状弯曲**{vi.}++跳跃(尤指用手或竹竿支撑跳跃)；腾跃：**++一跃而及；一蹴而就：**{vt.}++(用手或竹竿撑着)跳过：**++(用手或竹竿撑着)跳过：**{n.}++跳跃；撑杆跳**++(马的)腾跃**', '++I hastened up the steps of the vault and out into the street.**++我匆忙走上地下室的台阶，出去到了街上。**++Extrapolating current trends, some forecasters predict that China’s economy will vault ahead of America’s in 15 years.**++一些预言家根据目前的趋势推断，中国经济将在未来的15年来跳跃到美国的前面去。**++They also offer an option that allows your hidden door to double as a vault door, so your valuables stay double protected.**++他们还提供了一个选择，可以使你的隐蔽门也充当地下室，所以你的贵重物品得到双倍保护。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2942', 'vaunt', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vaunt', '{vt.}++夸耀；吹嘘：**++夸耀；吹嘘：**{vi.}++自夸,吹牛(常与of, over, about 连用):**++自夸,吹牛(常与of, over, about 连用):**{n.}++自吹自擂；吹牛**', '++The problem is that to vaunt modernisation, which implies that technological successes will make Russia a great world power again, is to set the wrong priority.**++问题是吹嘘那种所谓技术进步可以让俄罗斯重新成为世界强国的所谓“现代化”，是在设定错误的优先目标。**++And the LORD said unto Gideon, The people that are with thee are too many for me to give the Midianites into their hands, lest Israel vaunt themselves against me, saying, Mine own hand hath saved me.**++耶和华对基甸说，跟随你的人过多，我不能将米甸人交在他们手中，免得以色列人向我夸大，说，是我们自己的手救了我们。**++No matter how people vaunt an own great activity, they are usually just the outcomes of opportunity, rather than a great intention of result.**++不管人们怎样夸耀自己的伟大行动，它们常常只是机遇的产物，而非一个伟大意向的结果。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2943', 'veer', '[vɪr]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=veer', '{vi.}++转变方向；转身；转变：**++改变观点；改变态度；转变话题：**++【气象学】(风向)顺时针转向**++【航海学】(船)顺风转向，掉转船尾向上风**{vt.}++改变方向**++【航海学】改变航向**{n.}++改变方向，转向；【橄榄球】转向进攻**{vt.}', '++The other driver would have to either brake, crash into the truck, or veer right into the open field.**++那个开车的要么踩刹车要么撞到卡车，或者转向路外面的泥地。**++And the majority of his Seventies work would veer toward a more insidious realization of America Via explorations in the realm of punk and blues.**++并且他大多数七十年代的作品将通过对朋克和布鲁斯领域的探索转向对美国更隐秘的认知当中。**++Respect their views and boundaries and do not veer off regardless of their final decision.**++尊重她们的观点和底线，不要做完最后决定后又临时改变决定。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2944', 'vehement', '[viəmənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vehement', '{adj.}++热烈的；热情的；激情的**++激烈的；猛烈的；强烈的；暴力的**', '++Haley was not at all in accord with the Nation@s theology or its vehement ideology of racial separatism.**++哈雷一点都不赞同“伊斯兰民族”组织的神学思想和其激烈的种族分离主义的意识形态。**++He lived and died not like most people but better, and even his most vehement critics will admit to that.**++他的人生与死亡不同于众人，而是更好，就算是批评他最猛烈的人,也会如此认同。**++Since emerging into the public consciousness, genetically modified foods have been at the center of vehement controversy.**++自从转基因食物逐渐出现在公众的意识中，它们就成为了激烈争论的焦点。**');
