insert into GREWordBook values ('2959', 'versatile', '[vɝsətl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=versatile', '{adj.}++有多种技能的，多才多艺的，多面的**++有多种用途的，多功能的，通用的，万能的**++易变的；反复无常的**++可四面转动的，万向的**++【植物学】(花粉)丁字形的**++【动物学】(鸟趾)能前后转动的；(昆虫触角)能上下转动的**', '++He is a nimble and versatile wit.**++他是一个机敏而又多才多艺的才子。**++The more versatile the tool, the less you can predict how people will use it.**++这个工具越多才多艺，你越难以预计人们可以用它来做些什么。**++They are more like versatile servants who can provide security advice as well as transportation and secretarial services.**++多才多艺的特卫员，他们更象谁可以提供安全咨询以及运输和秘书服务。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2960', 'verse', '[vɝs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=verse', '{n.}++诗行；诗句**++诗；韵文；诗体**++格律；韵律**++(基督教《圣经》中的)节，句；(圣歌的)独唱部分**++= light verse**++诗作**{adj.}++诗句的，诗行的**++诗的，韵文的**{vi.,vt.}++= versify**{vt.}', '++He is good at verse.**++他善于作诗。**++Please turn this piece of prose into verse.**++请把这段散文改写成诗歌。**++Peter gives two explicit answers in verse 38 to what they need—what we need.**++彼得给出了两个在38至诗他们需要什么，我们需要明确的答案。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2961', 'versed', '[vɝst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=versed', '{vi.,vt.}++verse<sup style="font-size: 60%">1</sup>的变形**{vt.}++verse<sup style="font-size: 60%">2</sup>的变形**{adj.}++熟练的；精通的；通晓的**{n.}++诗行；诗句**++诗；韵文；诗体**++格律；韵律**++(基督教《圣经》中的)节，句；(圣歌的)独唱部分**++= light verse**++诗作**{adj.}++诗句的，诗行的**++诗的，韵文的**{vi.,vt.}++= versify**{vt.}', '++For those of us not versed in higher mathematics, it is impossible.**++对于那些不精通高等数学的人来说，这是不可能的。**++He is well versed in different methodologies and knows how and when to apply them.**++他精通不同的方法学，并且知道怎样以及何时需要使用它们。**++Others may not be well-versed in your field of expertise but they may have other domains of knowledge that are valuable to you.**++其他人可能对于你精通的领域并不熟悉，但是他们或许已掌握其他对于你来说极为有用的知识。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2962', 'vertigo', '[vɝtɪɡo]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vertigo', '{n.}', '++If nothing else, the next time someone in your audience complains of hearing loss, ringing, or vertigo, you’ll know what caused the problem.**++如果没有别的什么情况，下次你的听众里有人抱怨失聪，耳鸣或眩晕，你就该知道出什么问题了。**++For occupational exposure, present limits are based on avoiding the sensations of vertigo and nausea induced by movement in a static magnetic field.**++对于职业暴露来说，目前暴露限值的根据是避免在一个静电磁场中运动时产生眩晕和恶心的感觉。**++The key to this photograph is the tilted horizon, which exaggerates the feeling of vertigo and adds to the sense of disorientation and suspension that the photo creates.**++这张照片的关键是倾斜的地平线，它夸大了人们晕头转向的感觉，并增加了迷失方向和由照片所创造的倒悬的意念。**');
