insert into GREWordBook values ('2977', 'vigorous', '[vɪɡərəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vigorous', '{adj.}++充满力量的；强有力的**++强健的，茁壮的；健全的**++精力充沛的；朝气蓬勃的**', '++In their need, they have registered a mandate that they want direct, vigorous action.**++他们在困难中表达了自己的委托，即要求采取直接而有力的行动。**++Though nearly 50, he is exceptionally vigorous in work.**++别看他快50岁了， 工作却是雷厉风行。**++She had a vigorous opponent.**++她遇到一个劲敌。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2978', 'vile', '[vaɪl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vile', '{adj.}++恶劣的，极坏的**++卑鄙的；堕落的；卑贱的**++肮脏的，污秽的**++低下的；耻辱的，不光彩的**++无价值的；微不足道的；无足轻重的**', '++Either way, his demise spells the end of a vile reign.**++不论怎样，他的死终结了一个邪恶统治时代。**++The rage I expressed on the phone, the nasty and vile things I said.**++我不停地打电话表达我的愤怒，我还说了一些肮脏和卑鄙的话。**++Always in sublime carelessness had he lived, till now, and now it seemed to him that they had always reached out and dragged at him with vile hands.**++迄今为止，他一向过着洒脱的无忧无虑的生活，现在他却似乎觉得她们总是向他伸出邪恶的手要把他往下拽。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2979', 'vilify', '[vɪlɪfaɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vilify', '{vt.}++诽谤，诋毁，中伤：**++贬低；毁损**', '++A clutch of Maoist websites frequently vilify intellectuals such as Mr Mao.**++一群毛主义网站经常恶毒诽谤茅先生这样的知识分子。**++Those wishing to vilify Ono as a scheming individual found that the term “dragon lady” served their purposes rather well, and they never seemed to shrink from applying it.**++那些试图诽谤小野，将小野丑化为一个诡计多端的人，发现 “龙女”一词正合他们的目的，并且他们似乎从来没有不愿意运用这一术语。**++He continued, “I think that the disclosure around one transaction being the justification to vilify Goldman Sachs or to pass regulatory reform is just incredible.”**++他继续评论道：“指望一起商业泄密事件来中伤高盛或借此通过金融改革是不能让人信服的。”**');
