insert into GREWordBook values ('2993', 'vivacious', '[vɪveʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vivacious', '{adj.}++活泼的，轻快的，有生气的**++[古语]长寿的；生命力强的**++【植物学】多年生的；耐冬的**', '++Clapping your hands when you dance may indicate that you@re an extroverted, outgoing, vivacious type who loves to be the center of the social scene.**++在跳舞的时候拍手，表示你可能是一个那种喜欢在社交场合成为中心的外向的，活泼的人。**++It’s easy enough for the reader to guess where the relationship between Alvo and Lula is headed, even if Ms. Prose’s vivacious prose initially makes the road there fairly scenic.**++读者不难猜到阿尔瓦诺和卢拉的情感道路将通向何方，即使普罗斯女士起初用活泼的散文风格将这条道路描绘的景色迷人。**++The story told by a vivacious 24-year-old reflects the new trend.**++以下来自于一位24岁的活泼年轻人的口述，反映了这个新趋势。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2994', 'vocation', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vocation', '{...}++...**', '++His vocation coincides with his avocation.**++他的职业同他的爱好完全一致。**++She was equipped with knowledge for the vocation.**++她具备从事这项职业的知识。**++The  vocation  advocate found the word " vocal" and " reciprocal" not in the  vocabulary.**++职业倡导者发现"嗓音的"和"交互的"两词不在词汇表中.**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2995', 'vociferous', '[vosɪfərəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vociferous', '{adj.}++叫喊的，吵闹的，喧哗的**++大事声张的，大叫大嚷的**', '++And one by one, encouraged by vociferous applause, speaking with fire and enthusiasm and excited gestures, they replied to the attack.**++他们一个个受到喧闹的欢呼鼓掌的鼓励，怀着火焰和激情，打着激动的手势，回答了对他们的攻击。**++From his earliest writings to his last works, he has drawn vociferous critics, but that is the mark of a scholar who has important and fundamental things to say.**++从他最早的作品到他最后的工作，人们对他的批评纷至沓来，但对于一个有着自己真知灼见的学者而言，此无异为一种标志。**++They became more vociferous, and some of them began calling out what they thought of Hanna.**++他们变得更加吵闹了，一些人开始叫嚷着对汉娜的看法。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2996', 'volatile', '[vɑlətl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=volatile', '{adj.}++迅速挥发的，易挥发的；易气化的**++易发作的；爆炸性的**++易变的，反复无常的；轻浮的**++短暂的；易逝的**++(价格等)波动的；不稳定的**++【计算机】易失的**++[古语](飞禽等)能飞的；惯于飞行的**', '++What is driving these oil price spikes when so little of the oil supply is affected? Why is the market so volatile?**++在这么少的原油供应影响下，是什么在导致油价的急剧飚升？市场为什么会如此不稳定？**++It can either work for you or against you, but most likely, due to its volatile nature, it’s most likely to work against you.**++它既可为你所用，也会跟你对着干，但由于它本身不稳定的这一天性，最有可能发生的便是后者。**++Although the researchers are not sure how bacteria detect airborne ammonia, they have some hypotheses about why bacteria produce slime in response to volatile ammonia.**++尽管研究人员并不确定细菌是如何识别出到空气中的氨，但他们已经有了某些假设关于细菌为何能产生粘液以回应挥发性的氨。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2997', 'volition', '[vəlɪʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=volition', '{n.}++意志，决意；下决心**++意志力**++决断；取舍；抉择**', '++All talk about consciousness, volition, and aiming at ends is empty.**++任何有关意识、意志和最终目的的讨论是没有意义的。**++All the men have is momentum and loaded weapons, which seem to fire of their own volition, since that@s what loaded weapons like to do.**++这些男人们拥有的只有狂野的冲劲和上膛的武器，就仿佛这些武器都以自己的意志在开火一般，因为这正是上膛的武器的诉求。**++We perceive something in the world that we want and we have the power of volition to get it; likewise, we have the power to avoid the things we don’t want.**++我们将世界中的事物认知为我们需要的，和我们有意志力能得到的；同样，我们有能力避免不想发生的事情。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2998', 'voluble', '[vɑljəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=voluble', '{adj.}++健谈的，有口才的，口若悬河的**++【植物学】缠绕的**++[罕用语]易旋转的**', '++Unlike the U.S., says Abbas, China is viewed positively by much of the Pakistani public, whose voluble media tends to blame the country@s travails on American, Israeli or Indian meddling.**++不像美国，阿巴斯说，多数巴基斯坦公众积极看待中国，它健谈的媒体常常指责该国对美国，以色列或印度干涉所做的艰苦努力。**++"I@m sure he did," said Sister Grace Voluble firmly.**++“当然，当然。” 格蕾丝•健谈修女坚定地说。**++The new comer in our company is voluble.**++我们公司新来的同事很健谈。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('2999', 'voluminous', '[vəlʊmənəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=voluminous', '{adj.}++大量的；丰富的；浩瀚的**++多卷的；长篇的，大部头的**++著作多的，多产的**++话多的；冗长的；啰嗦的**++宽大的；宽松的**', '++As far as I can see, there isn@t a hint of this kind of thinking in his voluminous correspondence.**++据我所知，在他大量的信件中，这种思考的暗示一点都没有。**++Voluminous hair On the one hand, you will spend half the day unloading a can of hairspray on your scalp.**++波浪发卷 一方面，你需要花费半天的时间来清理大量的发胶；另一方面。**++In a series of online opinion-surveys and in voluminous press commentary, debate has been surprisingly intense.**++在一系列的在线调查和大量的新闻报道，公众辩论异常激烈。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3000', 'voluptuous', '[vəlʌptʃuəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=voluptuous', '{adj.}++骄奢淫逸的，贪恋酒色的；纵欲的**++满足于感官享受的**++以感官享受为目的的；与淫乐有关的**++性感的，妖娆的；色情的；激起情欲的**', '++The good news is you’ll feel quite voluptuous.**++好消息是你感觉自己十分有情欲。**++Her flamboyant image was attractive and inviting. She had a distinctive soft voice and a voluptuous figure.**++她艳丽的形象非常诱人，还有着独特的温柔嗓音和撩人的身段。**++At Mass the next morning, as the priest prepares to deliver his sermon, a tall, voluptuous, drop dead gorgeous woman enters the sanctuary.**++在第二天的弥撒上，神父准备布道时，一个高高的，艳丽的，简直要迷死人的女人走进了神殿。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3001', 'voracious', '[vəreʃəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=voracious', '{adj.}++贪吃的；狼吞虎咽的；饮食过度的**++非常渴望的；难满足的；贪婪的**', '++Life is voracious, it swallows all the dead.**++生命是贪婪的，它吞噬所有死亡。**++Death is voracious, it swallows all the living.**++死亡是贪婪的，它吞噬所有生命。**++Local media are covering every aspect of the scare with a voracious appetite.**++当地媒体正在用贪婪的胃口报道这一恐慌的每一方面。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3002', 'votary', '[votəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=votary', '{n.}++出家人；和尚；尼姑；修士**++上帝的信徒；基督教徒；信奉者**++爱好者；崇拜者；追求者；献身者**{adj.}++立誓任圣职的**++誓言的；与誓言有关的**', '++...**++...**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3003', 'vouch', '[vaʊtʃ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vouch', '{vi.}++担保，为…作保(常与 for 连用)：**++保证；证实；证明(常与 for 连用)：**{vt.}++保证；证实：**++引证，引典证实**++【法律】传(某人)出庭作证**{n.}++[废语]断言；保证**', '++It is that learning that a certification should vouch for.**++因此，这个学习的过程才是认证所要保证的。**++Actually Lucille is right about the eating slowly but I can@t vouch for the lying of one@s age.**++实际上露茜丽关于要慢慢地吃的观点是对的，不过我不敢担保谎报年龄也是。**++Among the various ways of doing this, the most widely used is to have one or more trusted third parties vouch for the public key.**++实现此目的的方法有许多种，其中最常用的是对公开密匙使用一个或多个可靠的第三方证明。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3004', 'vouchsafe', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vouchsafe', '{vt.}++赐予，惠予，给予：**++许可，允诺；恩准；准予：**{vi.}++屈尊；俯就**', '++Vouchsafe me a spirit of faith and knowledge.**++赐予我信心和一颗有知识的心灵。**++Perhaps R@hllor will vouchsafe me a glimpse of His Grace.**++希望拉赫洛赐予恩惠，让我一瞥国王陛下。**++I vouchsafe it to each girl but somebody let her cover with the dust.**++我把它赐给每一个女子，可有人让她蒙上了灰。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3005', 'voyeur', '[vɔɪjɝ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=voyeur', '{n.}', '++The court papers allege she may be a voyeur.**++法庭文件宣称她可能是一个偷窥狂。**++I like to think that these essays edify me in some way, but at the very least they appeal to the voyeur in me.**++我觉得他们的文章总在某些方面对我有所启发，起码，我知道了自己心底也是对别人的种种非常之有兴趣的。**++As in other albums, the listener is promoted to voyeur of miserablism: each track has a feel of a torn out diary entry, left to wilt on adeserted marital bed for our perusal.**++像其他专辑一样，听众被推动着窥探歌者的愁苦：听每一首歌都好像是在读一本日记，在久婚之后被遗弃的床边凋谢，又被不断翻开乃至破烂不堪。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3006', 'vulgar', '[vʌlɡɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vulgar', '{adj.}++粗俗的，粗鄙的，庸俗的**++下流的，猥亵的，淫荡的**++平民的；普通的，一般的**++流行的；受欢迎的**++(语言)通俗的；乡土的，方言的**{n.}++[古语]平民，百姓**++[废语]土语，方言**', '++The speaker played to the gallery by indulging in vulgar jokes.**++为了哗众取宠， 那位演讲者大讲特讲粗俗的笑话。**++Nevertheless, she was soon confronted with a wave of criticism, some of it vulgar, saying she had no appreciation for the arts.**++然而，她很快就遭到一波又一波的批评，一些评论还比较粗俗，说她根本不懂欣赏艺术。**++Nobody ever suggested that he was corrupt, or ambitious in any vulgar way, or that anything he did was actuated by fear or malice.**++没有任何人用任何粗俗的方式提到过他腐败或者有野心，或者他做的任何事是由恐惧或者敌意促成的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3007', 'vulnerable', '[vʌlnərəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vulnerable', '{adj.}++易受伤害的；脆弱的**++易受批评的；易受诱惑的**++(地方)易受攻击的，难防守的**++【桥牌】已成局的；打不到合约数时罚分要增加的**', '++Not only network is vulnerable, any piece of software is.**++不仅网络是脆弱的，任何一个软件都是脆弱的。**++And what was it about these people that made them seem vulnerable?**++但是对于这些人，是什么使他们看起来好象易受到攻击？**++If you take care of something, you begin to love it — which makes us very vulnerable.**++如果你照顾某些事情，你已经开始爱上它了--这让我们非常的投入.**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3008', 'waddle', '[wɑdl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=waddle', '{vi.}++蹒跚而行，摇摆而行**++摇摇摆摆地移动；踉跄地走**{n.}++蹒跚；摇摆的步伐**', '++I go for a waddle and do stretches and exercises every day.**++我每天都会出去散散步，做做伸展运动。**++Pre-pregnancy it seemed strange to me that pregnant women waddle while nonpregnant women who weigh the same walk normally.**++在怀孕之前看到怀孕的女性走跟蹒跚而一样体重的没有怀孕的女性去能正常走路，我感到很奇怪。**++To waddle a given distance, penguins use twice as much energy as other creatures of the same size use to walk equally far.**++同样一段距离，企鹅以其摇摆的方式来行走，所消耗掉的体能是其他同体型动物的两倍之多。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3009', 'waffle', '[wɑfl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=waffle', '{n.}++华夫饼干，蛋奶烘饼，奶油夹心饼干**{adj.}++有(威化饼干表面)格栅印的[亦作 waffled]**{vi.}++[主英国口语]**++闲聊，说无聊话；胡扯，唠叨：**++支吾，含糊其辞；(写作、说话)态度暧昧：**{n.}++[英国口语]无聊话；无意义的话；空话；装腔作势的言词**{adj.}++不明确的，含糊的**', '++Keeping things short and sweet not only shows people that you are concise and don@t waffle, but that you also know what you want.**++亲切简洁的语言彰显了你简明的个性，不仅不会被误认为是在胡扯，还让对方知道你是一个了解自己想要什么的人。**++Barry McRoy, a South Carolina fire and rescue director, was leaving a Waffle House restaurant when two men came in fighting over a gun.**++巴里·麦克罗伊是一位南加利福尼亚州的火灾和营救主管，当他离开“闲聊屋”旅店的时候正好碰上两个人在枪战。**++He needs to be a lot clearer and firmer about how he will deal with America’s foes and rivals: his first instinct when Russia invaded Georgia was to waffle.**++他需要更加清楚以及坚定他将如何处理美国的敌人和竞争对手。 当俄罗斯入侵格鲁吉亚的时候，他的第一反应竟认为这是胡扯。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3010', 'waft', '[wɑft]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=waft', '{vt.}++使漂浮；使飘荡： **++吹送，漂送：**{vi.}++飘荡，漂浮：**++(微风等)吹拂，掠过：**{n.}++吹送，飘送**++(气味、声音等的)一阵**++一阵风**++波浪，波动**++(宁静、喜悦等的)片刻感觉**++[苏格兰英语]=weft<sup style="font-size: 60%">1</sup>**', '++In the evenings, all manner of food smells waft down the corridors — stir-fried pork and tofu and greens.**++到晚上，各种饭菜的气味飘荡在走廊——有炒肉、豆腐和绿叶菜。**++I opened the plastic boxes that I@d carried, sealed, all the way from London, and the stench of farmhouse cheeses began to waft across the room.**++我打开了一个从伦敦带来的密封塑料盒，一时间，农场自制奶酪特有的臭味开始在房间里飘荡。**++Bustling, small streets are crammed with shops that sell everything from jade ashtrays to Mao watches, while enticing smells waft out from restaurants and side-street barbecues.**++熙熙攘攘的狭窄街道挤满了商店，这些商店从碧玉烟灰缸到毛氏手表无所不卖，诱人的香味从饭店和街边的烧烤摊飘出。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3011', 'wag', '[wæɡ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wag', '{vt.}++摇摆，摇动： **++(责备时)以手指指(人)；点头(召唤某人)：**{vi.}++摇摆，摇动：**++饶舌：**++蹒跚而行，摇摇摆摆地走：**++[英国口语]离开，动身：**++[古语](时势等)推移，变迁**{n.}++摇摆，摇动**{n.}++诙谐的人，好说笑打趣的人，小丑**++[废语]小伙子，年轻人**', '++I didn@t wag my finger at him.**++我没有对他摇摆手指。(指没有表示责备或不同意等)**++She writes “Seema Says ..., ” a column for The Wag, a giveaway fashion and party magazine in Westchester County.**++她为温彻斯特郡的一家免费时尚、社交杂志《摇摆》写专栏——西玛说。**++The first version of the WAG generator is used to provide a quick and dirty estimate for small "enhancement" requests made to a "business as usual" team.**++WAG生成器的第一个版本用于为来自“一如往常”的团队的小的“增强”请求提供快速粗糙的估算。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3012', 'wan', '[wɑn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wan', '{adj.}++苍白的，无血色的**++软弱的；无力的；病态的；有愁容的**++[废语]微弱的；暗淡的**++忧郁的，悲哀的**{vi., vt.}++[罕用语](使)变苍白；(使)呈病态：**{abbr.}', '++This approach overcomes the security problems of deploying two-tier systems over the WAN by replicating a native client to a remote user.**++通过将一个原生客户端复制给一个远程用户，这种途径克服了通过 WAN 部署两层系统的安全性问题。**++Moreover, n-tier architecture allows for applications to be securely deployed over the WAN while the database can remain securely behind the corporate firewall.**++而且，n 层架构允许将应用程序安全地部署在 WAN 上，同时数据库能够在公司防火墙之后得到保护。**++Kasab, a thin, wan figure, has sat through the trial largely indifferent to the testimony, although he has complained recently that his food might be laced with poison.**++体形瘦弱、苍白憔悴的卡萨伯在审判过程中对证人的证词表现出无比的冷漠，尽管他最近抱怨他的血液中可能被注入了毒素。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3013', 'wanderlust', '[wɑndɚlʌst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wanderlust', '{n.}', '++When we met, you warned me of your wanderlust.**++但我们相遇之时，你就警告我说你有漫游癖。**++Today, the route is greatly feted — a poll in Wanderlust Magazine, based in Britain, calls it the most scenic railway journey in the world.**++如今，该旅行线路的名气如日中天 --- 英国《沃德拉斯特》（Wanderlust）杂志所做的一项调查显示，它被人们推选为世界上风景最优美的线路。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3014', 'wane', '[wen]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wane', '{vi.}++(月)亏，缺**++变暗淡；变弱；减少**++衰落；衰退；没落**++消失，即将结束：**++退潮**{n.}++月亏 **++月亏期**', '++Protection in vaccinated individuals will wane after a year or two, so protection against Lyme disease in previously vaccinated people will be nonexistent.**++接种疫苗的个体在一到两年后预防效果就会衰退，所以之前接种过疫苗的人群并不能抵御莱姆病。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3015', 'want', '[wɔ:nt; wɔnt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=want', '{vt.}++不足，不够；没有：**++欠缺；缺少：**++要，想要：**++渴望，热望(后接不定式)：**++希望见到(某人)；希望与(某人)谈话： **++通缉：**{vi.}++需要；缺少(通常与 for 连用)：**++贫困；生活困难：**++[罕用语]欠缺；只差：**{n.}++缺乏，缺少，短缺**++贫困；匮乏**++希望；渴望；需求**++缺少的东西；必需品**++愿望；志向**', '++Tell me which ones you want.**++告诉我哪些是你需要的。**++I want a distinct answer to my question.**++我要求对我的问题作出明确的答复。**++I want you to undertake all the arrangements.**++我希望你来负责全面安排工作。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3016', 'wanting', '[wɔntɪŋ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wanting', '{adj.}++缺少的；没有的**++不合标准的，不合格的**++[英国方言]愚笨的，低能的**{prep.}++没有：**++差，缺少：**', '++But whether it was a failure to inherit this capacity, or that the unfavourable environment of which I have told proved the stronger, my appetite for milk was grievously wanting.**++也不知是我没有从他那里继承到这种能力，还是由于我之前提到的家庭的不利环境，我对于牛奶的食欲却是可悲地缺乏。**++It’s impossible to satisfy that hunger for more, because our culture is not satisfied with what we have, but is geared to wanting more.**++我们不可能满足对于要得更多的渴望，因为我们的文化并不满足于我们所拥有的，而是倾向于要得更多。**++But I think we all have our reasons for wanting life to be easier.**++但是我想，我们每个人都有我们自己为什么追求简约生活的理由。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3017', 'warmonger', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=warmonger', '{n.}', '++He added: "Behind this he has made a lot of enemies, the principal one being the warmonger, the United States."**++他补充说：“是的，他面对很多敌人，最主要的敌人是美国，那个战争贩子”**++The president now finds himself accused of being both a warmonger for entering the war and a wimp for his lame prosecution of it.**++总统发现他一方面因为参与战争被指责为战争贩子，另一方面因为战争执行不力被称作窝囊废。**++He was a warmonger, he was addicted to wars, he would ask the British people to make a sacrificefor the great good.**++他是个战争狂，他对战争上了瘾，他一定会要求不列颠人为着崇高而做出牺牲。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3018', 'warp', '[wɔrp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=warp', '{vt.}++使弯曲；使扭曲；弄歪：**++使离开自然正确的方向 **++使(性格等)不正常；使乖戾；使有偏见：**++歪曲：**{vi.}++变弯；弯歪；变成翘曲：**++离开自然正确的方向；变得反常；曲解：**++【航海学】被绞船索曳动；用绞船索曳船**++(科幻小说中)作空间翘曲飞行**++[古语]偏离**{n.}++(木材或木器的)弯曲，扭曲 **++(金属的)翘曲；歪斜**++翘曲状，弯曲状**', '++Years of living alone may warp one@s personality.**++长期的孤身生活会使人的性格变得乖戾。**++In his theory of general relativity, Einstein realized that space and time can stretch and warp in ways that change the trajectory of light.**++爱因斯坦在他的广义相对论中认识到，可以以改变光轨迹的方式对时间和空间进行拉伸和弯曲。**++My point is that so many people don’t follow the path from the beginning or time warp through the journey to a point in the future.**++很多人并没有遵循从旅行的一开始或者通过时间隧道这样的道路到达目的地，这就是我的观点。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3019', 'warrant', '[wɔrənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=warrant', '{n.}++授权；批准；认可 **++权利；正当的理由；根据**{vt.}++授权；批准：**++使有正当理由；成为…的根据：**++保证，具体指**++(向买主)保证所售货物如所介绍：**++(向买主)保证货物的质量等：**++(向买主)保证对所购货物的所有权，担保赔偿损失**++【法律】(向被授人)保证(财产)所有权**', '++Endowments of nature no one can give titles to with the warrant deeds are all waving us, smiling at us, opening her extensive warm arms to us and embracing us long and long.**++没有人能够用正当的理由和行为命名大自然的馈赠，他们都在向我们挥手，对我们微笑，向我们张开她广阔温暖的双臂久久得拥抱着我们。**++At Dean Miller@s suggestion, I have allowed her to give the current student organizers the opportunity to propose a program for next semester that might warrant continuation of this event on campus.**++根据米勒学监的建议，我允许她给学生机会，让他们给下学期的活动提出一个方案，保证这个活动得以在校园内继续开展。**++Their findings support restrictions on lighting up within a few feet of other people. But they don@t warrant more than that.**++他们的观测结果支持了对在他人几尺之外吸烟的限制，但是除此之外，它们并不能证明更多。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3020', 'wary', '[wɛri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wary', '{adj.}++谨慎的，小心的；警惕的**++慎重的，考虑周到的**++谨防的，惟恐的**', '++"Why are you so wary of thought"? said the philosopher.**++哲学家问：“为什么你对思想这样谨慎提防？**++Your frailty makes them wary of buying anything from you.**++你的虚弱使他们从你那里购买任何东西都很谨慎。**++Have we forgotten their warning to be especially wary of the demagogues who promise us something for nothing?**++我们是否忘记了他们警告：一定要特别小心那些吹嘘不劳而获的蛊惑民心的政客。？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3021', 'wastrel', '[westrəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wastrel', '{n.}++浪费者，挥霍者，败家子**++=good for nothing**++无用的人，饭桶**++流浪汉，流浪儿，浪荡子**++(路边的)荒地**++弱小的动物**', '++The government of Luxembourg, however, has recently grown fed up with wastrel youths applying for unemployment benefits while still living with their parents.**++然而在卢森堡，政府对那些与父母同住又来领救济金无所事事的年轻人越来越忍无可忍。**++The troubles that destroyed Tang—the loss of his job, the collapse of his marriage, heartbreak over his wastrel only child—are all too common across China.**++失业、离异、唯一的孩子又是个败家子，这些摧毁唐永明的麻烦事在全中国太常见了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3022', 'watershed', '[wɔtɚʃɛd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=watershed', '{n.}++分水岭；分界线**++[美国英语]流域**++转折点；重要关头**++(森林地带的)集水区**{adj.}++标志转折点的**', '++Was that something of a watershed for Spanish football?**++可以认为那是西班牙足球的转折点吗？**++Well, now today is obviously a kind of watershed or transition in our syllabus.**++好的，今天的课程很明显,在整个教学大纲中是一个转折点。**++Is this a watershed in the history of public health medicine – a @put it in the water’ moment?**++‘在水中添加阿司匹林’的这一时刻 - 会是公共健康医学史的分水岭吗？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3023', 'wax', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wax', '{...}++...**', '++Wax polish preserves wood and leather.**++上光蜡可以保护木材和皮革。**++A candle gutters when the melted wax runs down its sides.**++融化的蜡从蜡烛的边上淌下时，蜡烛产生融流。**++The candle guttered out when the melted wax ran down its sides.**++熔化的蜡沿着蜡烛四周淌下，蜡烛就渐渐熄灭了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3024', 'waylay', '[wele]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=waylay', '{vt.}++伏击，埋伏**++阻拦，拦住…询问**', '++One day his uncle asks Fish to deliver a package to a man at the docks, but pirates waylay him before he can pass it off.**++有一天，他的叔叔要求鱼商在码头一包到人，但海盗伏击才可以将它传递了他。**++How stupid of me that after the failed surprise on the ride to Scwetzingen, I had been afraid to waylay Hanna and see what she was like as a conductor.**++在乘车去往青格的途中，我感到多么愚蠢，我竟一直担心会碰到汉娜，看到她检票的情形。**++He would often waylay me as I was going to class and produce a piece of paper from his pocket, often with a puzzle already on it. The puzzles were usually mathematical or logical.**++他经常在我进教室的路上拦住我，然后从口袋里掏出一张纸条给我，上面通常写着有关数学或逻辑的难题。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3025', 'wayward', '[wewɚd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wayward', '{adj.}++固执的，倔强的，刚愎自用的，任性的**++反复无常的**++[古语]不如意的，与愿望相违的**', '++And behind the veil of secrecy there appears to be more hustle to crack down on wayward, smaller exporters.**++而且在神秘面纱背后，似乎有更急速的活动打击任性的、规模较小的出口商。**++While Paul is describing this behavior as the result of wayward passions, the chief sin is idolatry and separation from the one true God.**++虽然保罗描述这种行为为任性激情的结果，主要的罪来自偶像崇拜，将一个人与独一的真神分开。**++The “start of work means an end to freedom, but also to doubt, intensity and wayward desires...**++工作的开始意味着自由的结束，也同时是疑惑、不安和任性的欲望的终结……**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3026', 'weather', '[wɛðɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=weather', '{n.}++天气，气象条件，大气条件**++恶劣天气**++天气预报**++潮湿冷空气**++[常用复数]处境，境况**++【航海学】上风面，向风侧**{vt.}++暴露于空气之中，使经受风吹雨打太阳晒；风干，晒干，吹干：**++使退色；使分解；侵蚀：**++渡过(暴风雨，困难等)；经受住：**++使(建筑物、挑担等)倾斜(以便使雨水流泻)**++【航海学】航行…的上风；安全绕过：**{vi.}++(因风吹雨打太阳晒等而)退色，受侵蚀，风化：**++经受风雨；对风雨等能耐久：**{adj.}++【航海学】上风的；顶风的，迎风的**++经受风雨的；露天的**', '++Cold weather disagrees with her.**++寒冷天气对她不适宜。**++The close weather will last for some time.**++这种闷热的天气将持续一段时间。**++The dough would sour quickly in such weather.**++在这种天气生面团会很快发酵。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3027', 'welter', '[wɛltɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=welter', '{vi.}++滚动，翻滚；打滚 **++深陷**{n.}++(海浪等的)起落，颠簸，澎湃**++杂乱无章，混乱**++滚动，翻滚，打滚**{adj.}++重量级骑手的**{n.}++[口语]**++= welterweight**++= welter race**++大人物，大亨；大家伙**++沉重的打击**', '++Mother told her son not to welter in pleasure and idleness.**++妈妈对他的儿子说不要沉溺于享乐和闲逸之中。**++It should be very interesting to watch the political sparks fly as the W3C tries to extract something coherent from this welter.**++观赏这样的政治争斗非常有趣，因为 W3C 可以尝试着从这种混乱中获取相关的利益。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3028', 'wheedle', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wheedle', '{...}++...**', '++If North Korea does agree, economic distress and the opportunity to wheedle more aid out of China and the U.S. may explain this change of heart.**++如果朝鲜真的同意重返六方会谈，那么经济上的不景气和从中美两国骗取更多援助的机会可能就是它改变主意的原因。**++By the @80s, many Western Europeans came in too, some succumbing to the charms of @sex 007s@ - spies of both sexes who used seduction to wheedle out @secrets@ from unsuspecting tourists.**++到了八十年代，许多西欧游客也来到这里，他们中有些人跌入了“桃色陷阱”，异性间谍用色相引诱游客而获取情报。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3029', 'whet', '[wɛt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=whet', '{vt.}++磨；磨快；磨利(刀、斧等)：**++刺激；促进：**{n.}++磨**++增进(食欲等)的东西；刺激物**', '++Companions, the creator seeketh, and such as know how to whet their sickles.**++开创者找寻的是伙伴，是那些懂得如何磨快镰刀的人。**++The sight of Mercedes on the roads also whet the town@s appetite for more luxury cars.**++奔驰车在马路上形成的风景线还刺激了这个城镇购买更多豪华车的欲望。**++A little book on the human shadow, by the poet and author Robert Bly, is a wonderful introduction to the topic and will whet your appetite for a shadow buffet.**++一本由诗人兼作家罗伯特-布莱写的关于人类的隐性人格的小书是对于这一话题的精彩介绍并能促进你对隐性人格的冲击欲望。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3030', 'whiff', '[wɪf]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=whiff', '{n.}++[象声词]**++微风；空气轻微流动**++一阵(微弱的)气味**++一喷，一吹(烟、蒸汽等)**++(香烟的)一口；一吸**++[美国口语](高尔夫球或棒球)不成功的一击**++一点点，些许**++小发作**++[口语]小雪茄烟**++(霰弹等)少量发射**++[英国英语]轻型艇**{vt.}++吹送，吹起**++喷出(烟雾等)**++吸、抽(烟等)**++[美国口语]【棒球】使三击不中而出局**{vi.}++喷；吸**++吸(或喷)一口烟**++[美国口语]**++【高尔夫球】空棒；空挥**++【棒球】三击不中而出局**{n.}{n.}{vi.}', '++If that idea has the whiff of failure about it, well, sniff again.**++如果说这个主意有一点点失败之处的话，是呀，再闻一闻吧。**++Or tried take a whiff of any of the vegetation that surrounds us everyday?**++或者试着去吸一口我们周围植物的清新的气息吗？**++This I could see faintly shining as I raised or lowered the cigarette; and at each whiff the inside of my hand was illuminated, and became for a second the highest light in the landscape.**++当我拿起或者放下我的烟卷时，都可以看到它微弱的反光；我每吸一口，我的手掌都会被照亮，我的戒指便是此情此境里除了星星以外最亮的光了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3031', 'whimsical', '[wɪmzɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=whimsical', '{adj.}++异想天开的，想入非非的**++古怪的；怪异的**++反复无常的；难以预料的**', '++If we simply give in to every whimsical desire we have, virtually no one would spend less than they earn.**++如果我们轻易地向我们异想天开的欲望屈服，事实上没有人会花得比自己挣的少。**++They mainly show the way of life in Egypt, but others are whimsical, while still others are not even titled, very abstract, and allow the viewer to come to their own conclusions.**++他们大都反映了埃及的生活方式，但也有一部分是异想天开的创作，也有一些十分抽象，甚至都没被定名，给参观者留下了很大的想像空间。**++At the heart of my whimsical journey was an experiment that would test out a more philosophical idea: that what we experience in life is more important than what we bring with us.**++我做这么一次异想天开的旅行，其核心是要测试一下一种哲学理念：人生体验比随身携带的东西更加重要。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3032', 'wholesome', '[holsəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wholesome', '{adj.}++促进健康的；符合卫生的**++(道德上)有教益的；健康的**++健壮的；身心健康的；朝气蓬勃的**++表明身体健康的**++审慎的 **++安全的**', '++Water is a wholesome drink.**++水是有益健康的饮料。**++Start every day with a wholesome breakfast.**++以有益健康的早餐开始每一天。**++In order to maintain physical well being, a person should eat wholesome food and get sufficient exercise.**++为了维持身体健康，一个人应该吃有益健康的食品，并经常锻炼身体。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3033', 'wicked', '[wɪkɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wicked', '{adj.}++邪恶的；坏的**++讨厌的；令人讨厌的；刻毒的；有恶意的**++顽皮的，淘气的；恶作剧的**++[美国俚语、口语]技艺高超的；精彩的，顶呱呱的，极好的，了不起的**++(动物)性情凶恶的**++有害的**++超常的；极端的；过度的**{adv.}++非常**{n.}++[总称]恶人；道德败坏者**', '++Rich as Croesus and wicked as the black man below.**++像克罗伊斯一样富有， 可又像地狱里的撒旦一样邪恶。**++So most people at that time assume that if you were an atheist you were bound to be a wicked.**++这么一来当时的人们便开始假设,如果你是无神论者那么你一定是邪恶的化身。**++Remember, too, that he would eat no salt with you; and what would you have more to persuade you of his wicked design?**++同时记住，他不会和你一起吃盐；并且怎么样让你知道更多向你证明他邪恶的计划？**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3034', 'willful', '[wɪlfəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=willful', '{adj.}++故意的**++任性的；固执的；执拗的 [亦作 wilful]**', '++Even the best ones can be foiled, though, by a sufficiently willful programmer committed to ignoring basic principles of memory management.**++但是，即使最优秀的编程人员也可能会被忽略内存管理基本原则的非常任性的编程人员搅乱。**++It’s hard to see the end in sight, and there are sleepless nights peppered in our work weeks because of sick kiddos, nursing infants, or willful toddlers.**++看到尽头是困难的，因为要生病的家人、需要照顾得婴儿或者任性的孩子，无眠的夜晚布满我们的工作周。**++If you are under control when the child is misbehaving, you will be able to distinguish between willful misbehavior and reaction to stress.**++当孩子胡闹时，如果你能克制，你就可以分辨出是任性的胡闹还是对压力的反应。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3035', 'wilt', '[wɪlt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wilt', '{vi.}++(植物等)枯萎；凋萎：**++衰弱；萎缩；憔悴：**++丧失勇气；颓丧；退缩：**++(衣服等)变得软垂而不挺括**{vt.}++使枯萎；使憔悴；使萎缩：**++使(衣服等)变得软垂而不挺括**{n.}++枯萎；憔悴；衰弱**++某些毛虫的传染病[亦作 wilt dicease] **++【植物】萎蔫病**{v.}', '++Wilt thou not love him?**++难道你不肯爱他吗？**++Thou knowest that thou wilt do this thing for me.**++你最清楚不过了，你会为我做这件事的。**++@Alas! my son, @ she cried, @wilt thou not kiss me before I go?**++“唉！ 我的孩子啊，”她抽泣着说，“在我离开前你难道不亲吻一下妈妈吗？**');
