insert into GREWordBook values ('3037', 'wince', '[wɪns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wince', '{vi.}++(因疼痛，窘迫等)畏缩；退缩；面部肌肉抽搐：**++(因疼痛，窘迫等)畏缩；退缩；面部肌肉抽搐：**{n.}++畏缩；退缩；面部肌肉抽搐**{n.}', '++Who smile and frown, wince and hiss.**++他们微笑和皱眉，畏缩与嘶嘘。**++Who now remembers talk of American hyperpuissance without a wince?**++到现在还有谁记得 美国超级强权毫不畏缩的言论？**++We all wince at the thought of how Xerox utterly failed to innovate on PARC@s inventions, allowing Apple and Microsoft to run away with most of them.**++我们都退避在想到施乐如何完全的失败再帕洛阿尔托研究中心的发明，允许苹果和微软从他们这儿逃走。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3038', 'windbag', '[wɪndbæg]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=windbag', '{n.}++[口语]好发空议论者；夸夸其谈的人**++[戏谑语]胸**++(吹奏乐器等的)风囊，风袋**++[废语](风琴的)风箱**', '++John is such a windbag.**++约翰是一个饶舌大王。**++You poor guy! Everyone knows he@s a real windbag.**++你这个可怜的家伙!大家都知道他是个很罗哩巴嗦的人.**++John is such a windbag. He can talk for hours at a time without saying anything.**++约翰是一个饶舌大王。他能够一连好几个小时滔滔不绝的讲毫无内容的话。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3039', 'windy', '[wɪndi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=windy', '{adj.}++刮风的，起风的**++多风的；风大的；当风的；受风的；暴露在风中的**++狂风似的；猛烈的；狂暴的**++空洞的；虚无的 **++空谈的；夸夸其谈的；吹牛的**', '++And I like windy weather, too.**++我也喜欢有风的天气。**++I always think of Michelle on warm, windy days. I imagine her running through the clouds with a kite dancing above her!**++在暖和、多风的日子里，我总是会想起米歇尔，想象着她跑着穿过云层，一只风筝在她头顶上飘荡。**++To enjoy a good vantage point, the photographer hiked to a windy spot about 400 meters above a lake, Lago Argentino, climbing into the picture after setting up his camera on a tripod.**++为了享受一个好的观景地点，摄影师长途步行至拉戈阿根廷一个湖泊上方400米处一个多风地点，在三角架上架好相机后攀登进入画面。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3040', 'winsome', '[wɪnsəm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=winsome', '{adj.}++迷人的；有吸引力的；引人注目的**++高兴的；快乐的**', '++But winsome didn@t win the day, and neither did hard luck stories.**++但是可爱并没有获胜，而不幸的故事也没有获胜。**++After Mark Twain first glimpsed the girl of his dreams, he never forgot Laura Wright@s "frank and simple and winsome" charms.**++从看到她的第一眼起， 他就永远无法将她忘记。 劳拉·莱特，“那么真诚、那么单纯、那么美丽”，让他深深地着迷...**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3041', 'wiretap', '[waɪrˌtæp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wiretap', '{vt.}++窃听(电话等)；(用窃听器)监听：**++安装窃听器于…；搭线窃听…的电话：**{vi.}++搭线窃听**{n.}++(在线路上)窃听**++窃听器；窃听装置**{adj.}++(从电话线上)窃听来的**', '++A telephone company cut off an FBI international wiretap after the agency failed to pay its bill on time, according to a US government audit released on Thursday.**++据上周四公布的一份美国政府审计报告，美国联邦调查局由于未及时缴纳电话费，其国际窃听线路被电信公司切断。**++A telephone company cut off an FBI international wiretap after the agency failed to pay its bill on time，according to a US government audit released last Thursday.**++据上周四公布的一份美国政府审计报告，美国联邦调查局由于未及时缴纳电话费，其国际窃听线路被电信公司切断。**++Today, it bears a plaque testifying to its checkered past, and also noting the curious fact that the Finns pulled 40 kilometers of wiretap cable out of the walls after the KGB left.**++如今，只有酒店的牌匾昭示其盛衰无常的历史，而一个令人惊奇的事件也被发现，克格勃撤离后，芬兰人从墙里拉出来长达40公里的窃听电缆。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3042', 'wistful', '[wɪstfl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wistful', '{adj.}++渴望的；向往的**++深思的；忧思的**++留恋的；依依不舍的**', '++Brown can also be sad and wistful.**++褐色也象征着悲伤与渴望。**++Whereas wild animals like wolves will avert their eyes when spotted, dogs and cats readily return our gaze, and with an apparent emotiveness that stimulates the wistful narrative in our head.**++然而像狼这样的野生动物通常会躲避人类的直视，而猫狗则乐于回应我们的注目，而且还带有明显的情感表露，刺激了人脑中的叙事渴望。**++We could see them 3 kilometers off in the distance, and it was kind of a wistful feeling.**++我们能在3公里外看到那些山丘，当时有一种可望而不可及的感觉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3043', 'wit', '[wɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wit', '{n.}++意识；心智**++[复数]**++智力；智能；理解力**++(清醒的)头脑**', '++Ladies and gentlemen paraded their fine manners, wit, and charm.**++女士们和绅士们卖弄他们的美妙姿态、才智和魅力。**++The era privileged elegance and wit in its music above almost all other qualities, and Haydn, despite his rustic origins, was hardly lacking in either.**++这个时代所特有的高雅与智慧先于其他一切特质存在于音乐作品之中，尽管是出身乡村的海顿，也绝不缺少这些气质。**++Bond accomplishes these feats by the power of his wit and more importantly through violence.**++邦德能够实现这些壮举得益于他智慧的力量，更重要地，得益于暴力。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3044', 'withdraw', '[wɪðdrɔ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=withdraw', '{vt.}++缩回；拿回；使离去： **++收回(货币等)；使退出：**{vi.}++离开；引退，撤退：**++退出(某组织、活动或社交界等)：**++【精神病学】(精神分裂症的)逃避现实；离群：**++(在会议程序中)撤销动议(或声明等)：**++戒毒：**', '++The leader promised to support the plan;you can@t withdraw now.**++领导已答应支持这项计划，你们不能收回承诺。**++Sometimes this will make us withdraw, but it can also motivate us to shift our attention or change our learning strategy, he says.**++有时困惑会使我们撤退，但它也能激励我们转移注意力或者改变我们的学习策略，他如是说道。**++When workers retire, they can withdraw money from the plan.**++当工人们退休了，他们能从计划中收回金钱。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3045', 'wither', '[wɪðɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wither', '{vi.}++干枯，枯萎：**++凋谢；失去生气：**++(感情等)减弱；消失：**++感到羞愧(或惶惑)：**{vt.}++使凋谢；使枯萎；使干枯：**++使羞愧(或畏惧，沮丧)：**++(用炮火等)摧毁，歼灭**', '++If we follow the path of returning to sanity, they will wither.**++如果我们遵循回归理智的道路，基地组织就会枯萎。**++But, if you start to neglect her, stop thinking about her, and not keeping her in your heart, your relationship will soon wither and evaporate.**++但是，如果你开始忽略她，不再思念她，不再把她留在心里，你们的关系很快就会枯萎和破裂。**++If you are yourself at work, you will either thrive or wither, and if you wither chances are that you are in the wrong place to begin with.**++如果你在工作中坚持做自己，你要么茁壮成长，要么逐渐枯萎，当你枯萎的时候，还会有机会在你枯萎的错误地方重新开始。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3046', 'withhold', '[wɪðhold]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=withhold', '{vt.}++阻止；阻挡；制止： **++[美国英语]扣除，代扣(所得税等)；扣留：**{vi.}++克制；抑制；忍住：**++克制；抑制；忍住：**', '++Only in the administration@s second year did it withhold some aid.**++奥巴马政府执政第二年才保留了一部分的支援。**++What I am saying is that we should not withhold the fulfillment of our most basic human needs until we feel like we have earned them.**++我的意思是，我们不应该总是延迟满足自己这些最基本的情感需求，直到觉得自己靠努力“挣到”了它们为止。**++I had caved in after a short struggle when she threatened to send me away and withhold herself.**++经过短暂的斗争后，当她威胁要我走开并拒绝跟我在一起时，我就已经屈服了。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3047', 'wizen', '[wizən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wizen', '{vi., vt.}++(使)枯萎；(使)凋谢；(使)皱缩；(使)干瘪**{adj.}++= wizened**', '++Hard wind and wizen his face.**++强风与酷寒使他的脸孔皱缩了。**++Hard wind and bitter cold wizen his face.**++强风兴酷寒使他的脸孔皱缩了。**++You Have to admit that it is a garden, Even if walking on the wizen ones, Perhaps you lost all flowers once again, but you still didn@t lost whole garden !**++即使在凋零的花园中散步，也得学著承认她还是一座花园，你也许一次有一次的失去了朵朵鲜花，但你并没有失去整个花园！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3048', 'wobble', '[wɑbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wobble', '{vi.}++蹒跚：**++摇摆；摆动；晃动：**++颤动，颤抖：**++犹豫不决；踌躇：**{vt.}++使摇摆；使颤抖；使摆动**{n.}++摇摆，晃动，摆动；颤抖，犹豫**', '++As it slows down, its axis starts to wobble—unstable, " Nimmo said.**++当它慢下来时，它的轴就开始摇晃，不稳定。” 尼姆说。**++But in reality, the wobble of the Earth on its axis -- which we call "precession" -- has led to them being all out of sync.**++而事实情况是，地球在其轴线上的摇动——我们称为“岁差”——让这些星座都偏离了原来的时刻。**++HARPS can detect the slight gravitational wobble caused by planets as small as Earth, if they have incredibly close-in orbits.**++HARPS能检测到到由像地球一样小的行星引起的轻微的引力摇摆，只要它们无限接近运行轨道。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3049', 'worldly', '[wɝldli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=worldly', '{adj.}++人世的；世间的；尘世的**++世俗的；市侩气的；追求名利的[亦作 worldly-minded]**++老于世故的；善于处世的**++[古语]地球(上)的**++[废语]非宗教的，俗人的**{adv.}++老于世故地；善于处世地，世故地**++俗不可耐地**', '++He is fond of worldly enjoyments.**++他喜爱世俗的享乐。**++Secondly, some traditions do preach the value of giving up worldly possessions –but the teachers I was investigating do not.**++第二，传统大肆宣扬放弃世俗财产的重要性，但是我所研究的老师们没有。**++However, in real life, to be able to be a monastic who can shake off all worldly concerns requires a lot of merits and wisdom!**++然而，在现实生活中，有资格成为一名能够摆脱一切尘世困扰的和尚是需要大量的功德和智慧的！**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3050', 'worship', '[wɝʃɪp]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=worship', '{n.}++对神的崇拜(或崇敬) **++礼拜；礼拜仪式**{vt.}++崇拜，崇敬，敬仰：**++爱戴；爱慕**{vi.}++做礼拜，敬神，拜神：**++做礼拜，敬神，拜神：**', '++What day did they worship on?**++他们在什么日子做礼拜？**++Whatever is at the center of your life is what you worship.**++你的生活中心无论是什么都是你所崇拜的那个。**++You pretend that this black hole which you worship exists.**++你假装你崇拜的这个黑乎乎的洞是存在的。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3051', 'wrangle', '[ræŋɡəl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wrangle', '{vi.}++口角，争吵：**++争论；辩论：**{vt.}++争论，争辩，为…与…争吵：**++与…辩论结果使其做…(或停止…)(常与 into， out of， away 连用)**{n.}++口角，争吵；争论，辩论**{vt.}', '++Don@t wrangle with others over trifles.**++别为一些琐事与别人争吵。**++And China keeps giving reminders of its unresolved wrangle with India over what is now the Indian state of Arunachal Pradesh, which it briefly overran in 1962.**++中国反复提出与印度的边界纠纷，该争论尚未解决，1962年中国曾短暂占领过阿鲁纳恰邦，现在该地区属于印度。**++China@s Premier Wen Jiabao has warned against interference by "external forces" in the maritime wrangle, over a strategic and resource-rich area where several regional nations have overlapping claims.**++中国总理温家宝警告那些参与海上争论的“国外势力”不要介入南中国海问题，南海作为一块战略要地和资源丰富地区使得很多国家宣布对其有领土权。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3052', 'wrest', '[rɛst]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wrest', '{vt.}++扭；拧：**++夺取，扭夺：**++歪曲，曲解，牵强附会；滥用：**++费力取得，辛苦谋求：**{n.}++扭；拧**++[罕用语]【乐器】(校准弦音的)扭钥；校音钥**', '++Every day they wrest my words: all their thoughts are against me for evil.**++他们终日颠倒我的话。 他们一切的心思，都是要害我。**++Other smaller businesses create their own challenges in their quest to wrest market share from their competitors.**++其他较小的公司也会提出自己的挑战性要求以从竞争对手手中夺取市场份额。**++Fortunately, new lab facilities dedicated to the study of clouds will soon wrest that field from poets, the geophysicists argue.**++地球物理学家说：幸运的是，新建的云科学实验室设施，即将从诗人手中夺回这一领域。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3053', 'wretched', '[rɛtʃɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wretched', '{adj.}++可怜的，不幸的；悲惨的**++令人讨厌的；肮脏的；恶劣的；使人难受的**++质量很差的；很坏的；劣等的；拙劣的；破旧的**++卑鄙的，不齿的，可鄙的，无耻的**++[用作定语，表示责备]过度的，无法容忍的**', '++Wretched flocks of maids labour so that the adulteress may be visible through her thin dress, so that her husband has no more acquaintance than any outsider or foreigner with his wife@s body.**++可怜的成群女佣在一块儿劳作，那么奸妇可能穿过她那薄薄的裙子看到，因此她的丈夫再也不比任何外人或陌生人更熟悉他妻子的身体。**++The wretched man have lose all his money.**++这个不幸的男人丢了所有的钱。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3054', 'wrongheaded', '[rɔŋhɛdɪd]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wrongheaded', '{adj.}++顽固的；刚愎自用的；固执的**++判断错误的，坚持错误的**', '++Still, the prescription is wrongheaded.**++但是，这个处方是错误的。**++But it is similarly wrongheaded to seek to reverse the coup through violence, as Mr Zelaya, egged on by Mr Chávez, seems to wish.**++但是，任何想要通过暴力来颠覆政变的企图也是错误的，在查韦斯的怂恿下，塞拉亚似乎想要这么做。**++But the results have led Mr Simonsohn to rethink the earlier tests of seemingly wrongheaded consumers.**++但是，上述结果使西蒙松重新思考较早测试中似乎被误导的消费者。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3055', 'wry', '[raɪ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=wry', '{adj.}++扭歪的；歪斜的**++皱眉头的；(表示不满时)面部肌肉扭曲的；做出怪相的**++坚持错误的，固执己见的**++歪曲了的，曲解了的**++讽刺的，挖苦的，辛辣的；作弄(人)的**{vt.,vi.}++歪曲，扭曲；扭转**', '++Whether you like heart- stopping action or wry, witty dialogue, you should go out and see it.**++不管你喜欢令人停止心跳的动作还是讽刺而又幽默的对话你都应该去看看。**++Gives you a little sense of Hobbes@ spirit, his humor, the wry wit that becomes apparent on almost every page of this book, but you have to be a careful reader.**++这体现了一部分霍布斯的精神，他的幽默感，他的诙谐风趣,而这些也明显体现在他的每一页书里，你们必须非常仔细地读。**++Studies that link a sense of humor to good health are probably measuring this phenomenon; when you have a wry perspective, it@s hard to remain anxious or hostile for long.**++许多研究把幽默感与健康的身体联系起来，可能是在调查这一现象；当你有了一个扭曲的观点时，就很难长时间保持不安或敌对心态。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3056', 'xenophobe', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=xenophobe', '{n.}', '++There was no hiding it -- I was a clueless literary xenophobe.**++没有隐藏，我是一个无能的文学排外。**++Mr Bhalla is no xenophobe—he spontaneously professes a weakness for Marks & Spencer underwear—but says the reform is too controversial to be enacted.**++Bhalla先生不仇视外国人-在内衣和针织衣商标等他坦然承认其弱势-但他说改革仅是争议而已，却没有采取行动。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3057', 'yoke', '[jok]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=yoke', '{n.}++轭，牛轭，双牛梭[参较 harness]**++[复数] yoke共轭，一套两牛；两牛并挽**++象征轭的器具，如轭门(架矛而成的门，古时候被征服者被迫在其下通过)，奴役(或奴隶状态)的标志和象征 **++受支配，屈从；奴役，束缚**{vt.}++给…上轭；用轭连起来：**++把(牲口)套到(犁等)之上：**++连接；结合，接合；联系： **++使成配偶，结婚，使匹配：**{vi.}++联合，连接；结合，紧密联合；配合**{n.}', '++For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.**++因为我的轭是容易的，我的担子是轻省的。**++As a farmer, you should learn how to yoke the oxen together.**++作为农民，你应该学会怎样把一对牛用轭连起来。**++For thou hast broken the yoke of his burden, and the staff of his shoulder, the rod of his oppressor, as in the day of Midian.**++因为他们所负的重轭，和肩头上的仗，并欺压他们人的棍，你都已经折断，好像在米甸的日子一样。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3058', 'yokel', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=yokel', '{n.}', '++Local yokel:Nothing---I was born here.**++乡下佬：没什么--我就出生在这个地方。**++The clothes makes him look like a slack - jaw yokel .**++这件衣服让他看起来像个土包子。**++Before that, a "butter-and-egg man" was slang for a visitor with a lot of money, a yokel ready to be separated from his funds.**++在那之前，一个“黄油和鸡蛋人”是对有钱拜访者的俚语，一个将要和他的资金分离的庄稼汉。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3059', 'zeal', '[zil]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=zeal', '{n.}', '++They were animated by religious zeal.**++他们被宗教热情所驱使。**++He worked for the cause with great zeal.**++他怀着极大的热诚为理想而努力。**++They plunged into their work with immense zeal.**++他们以极大的热情投入工作。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3060', 'zealot', '[zɛlət]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=zealot', '{n.}++热心者，狂热者，狂热分子**++[Ｚ-]【历史】(公元69～81年间反抗罗马帝国统治的犹太教中的)狂热分子，吉拉德人**', '++Three hours later, the police arrested Scott Roeder, an anti-abortion zealot.**++三小时后，警方逮捕了斯考特-罗德，一名反堕胎的狂热者。**++My happiness project has turned me into a sleep zealot. If I want to feel happy, calm, energetic, and mentally sharp, I must get enough sleep.**++我的快乐方案让我变成一个睡眠狂热者，如果我想感觉快乐，平静，有活力，思维灵敏，我必须有充足的睡眠。**++He@s part of a plan to get more men on the diet and has become a zealot.**++他是打算让更多的男人减肥的计划中的一部分，同时他也成为一个狂热拥趸。**');
insert into GREWordBook values ('3061', 'zenith', '[zɛnɪθ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=zenith', '{n.}++【天文学】天顶[参较 nadir]**++顶点，顶峰，最高点；全盛时期**', '++He has crawled in the huge bureaucratic machinery for several decades, till to zenith, where he kicked this machinery aside though, and the falling down of this machinery also means his falling.**++他在这个庞大的官僚机器里爬行了几十年，爬到顶峰，却一脚踹开了这个机器，而这个机器的倒塌也意味着他自己的坠落。**++What’s possible in this field reaches its zenith in ATMs – and here, too, label printers provide the security printing, including among other things special security inks for banknotes and bank cards.**++这个领域可能会在ATM柜员机的应用方面发展到顶点。 而且，标签印刷商提供的安全印刷也包括以专用的安全油墨印刷钞票和银行卡。**++Obama will be the zenith of black America for as long as he lives.**++奥巴马毕其一生都将成为美国黑人运动成就的顶点。**');
